d.medium","second.visibility","third.communicating"],"pairs":["first.enter"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',216,'sha256:598630091cf0e01b473f9bc3a384a14b287b60d413c3a97ebac99bb952fd4166','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.apparent','Apparent','apparent','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Apparent.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/apparent.html','# Apparent

Apparent names what is presented as available distinction. It does not need trace, holding, or recognition before it can appear; it names what becomes available to enter them. Apparent may become visible or known, but first it is distinction present enough to be noticed.

## Places

Apparent places distinction as presented enough to become available to notice.

## Holds

Apparent is held by [[Boundary]], because distinction must be located enough to present.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Apparent is a singular carrier primitive — the condition through which something becomes presented at a boundary. There is no lateral contrast required at the apparent level. The asymmetry is expressed in what apparent makes possible: [[Visible]] and [[Invisible]], [[Notice]] and [[Trace]], [[Apparent Bearing]], and the later source-role read of [[Apparent Source]].

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Apparent nests before trace, holding, or recognition. It can open visibility, invisibility, notice, and trace without yet becoming any of them.

## Reads

Apparent becomes recognisable where distinction is present enough to be noticed — where something is available to enter notice, attention, and trace without yet being followed, held, or read.

## Carries

- [[Visible]]
- [[Invisible]]
- [[Notice]]
- [[Apparent Bearing]]
- [[Apparent Source]]','Apparent Apparent names what is presented as available distinction. It does not need trace, holding, or recognition before it can appear; it names what becomes available to enter them. Apparent may become visible or known, but first it is distinction present enough to be noticed. Places Apparent places distinction as presented enough to become available to notice. Holds Apparent is held by Boundary, because distinction must be located enough to present. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Apparent is a singular carrier primitive — the condition through which something becomes presented at a boundary. There is no lateral contrast required at the apparent level. The asymmetry is expressed in what apparent makes possible: Visible and Invisible, Notice and Trace, Apparent Bearing, and the later source role read of Apparent Source. Traces Boundary Nests Apparent nests before trace, holding, or recognition. It can open visibility, invisibility, notice, and trace without yet becoming any of them. Reads Apparent becomes recognisable where distinction is present enough to be noticed — where something is available to enter notice, attention, and trace without yet being followed, held, or read. Carries Visible Invisible Notice Apparent Bearing Apparent Source','Apparent Apparent names what is presented as available distinction. It does not need trace, holding, or recognition before it can appear; it names what becomes available to enter them.','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.invisible","first.notice","first.trace","first.visible","second.apparent-bearing","second.apparent-source"]','{"holds":["first.boundary"],"traces":["first.boundary"],"carries":["first.visible","first.invisible","first.notice","second.apparent-bearing","second.apparent-source"],"pairs":["first.visible","first.invisible","first.notice","first.trace","second.apparent-bearing","second.apparent-source"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',190,'sha256:7481deb4e46efd9fbfb998e93f8a59035d7fcfe006e1e3704c4c53f2fedede4a','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.asymmetry','Asymmetry','asymmetry','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Asymmetry.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/asymmetry.html','# Asymmetry

Asymmetry names uneven relation. It is the first readable condition that makes distinction possible, and it is not produced by a prior term beyond relation itself. Before boundary, locality, or order can be read, relation must be uneven enough for distinction to begin.

## Places

Asymmetry places the first readable unevenness within [[Relation]].

## Holds

Asymmetry is held by [[Relation]]. Relation must hold before unevenness within relation can become readable.

## Pairs

Asymmetry pairs with [[Clearance]]: asymmetry gives unevenness, while clearance keeps the relation from collapsing or becoming unrelated.

## Traces

- [[Relation]]

## Nests

Asymmetry nests before boundary and locality. It opens the possibility of distinction without yet locating that distinction.

## Reads

Asymmetry becomes recognisable where relation can no longer be read as uniform spread — where unevenness is present enough for distinction to begin.

## Carries

- [[Bounded Asymmetry]]
- [[Emergent Condition]]','Asymmetry Asymmetry names uneven relation. It is the first readable condition that makes distinction possible, and it is not produced by a prior term beyond relation itself. Before boundary, locality, or order can be read, relation must be uneven enough for distinction to begin. Places Asymmetry places the first readable unevenness within Relation. Holds Asymmetry is held by Relation. Relation must hold before unevenness within relation can become readable. Pairs Asymmetry pairs with Clearance: asymmetry gives unevenness, while clearance keeps the relation from collapsing or becoming unrelated. Traces Relation Nests Asymmetry nests before boundary and locality. It opens the possibility of distinction without yet locating that distinction. Reads Asymmetry becomes recognisable where relation can no longer be read as uniform spread — where unevenness is present enough for distinction to begin. Carries Bounded Asymmetry Emergent Condition','Asymmetry Asymmetry names uneven relation. It is the first readable condition that makes distinction possible, and it is not produced by a prior term beyond relation itself.','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bounded-asymmetry","first.clearance","first.emergent-condition","first.relation"]','{"holds":["first.relation"],"traces":["first.relation"],"carries":["first.bounded-asymmetry","first.emergent-condition"],"pairs":["first.clearance"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',136,'sha256:1bb40f06c7eaec740db527246ccccfae9d20845cbd9c45eb3e27cce807f427f5','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.attend','Attend','attend','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Attend.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/attend.html','# Attend

Attend names sustained presence with what has been noticed. Where [[Notice]] names first contact with what has become apparent, and [[Enter]] names passage into the relation opened by that contact, Attend names the chosen staying-with through which relation remains available long enough to become followable, readable, or cared for.

Attend comes before judgment, closure, or explanation. It keeps contact open without forcing the condition to resolve before its difference can be read.

## Places

Attend places sustained presence with what has been noticed and entered.

## Holds

Attend is held by [[Notice]], [[Enter]], and [[Availability]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Attend is a singular carrier primitive — the condition through which notice becomes directed. There is no lateral contrast required at the attend level. The asymmetry is expressed in what attend makes possible: [[Trace]], [[Read]], and [[Readability]].

## Traces

- [[Notice]]
- [[Enter]]
- [[Availability]]

## Nests

Attend nests between first contact and trace. It keeps relation open before judgment, closure, or explanation.

## Reads

Attend becomes recognisable where a noticed distinction is held in contact long enough for its relation, difference, or path to begin disclosing itself.

## Carries

- [[Read]]
- [[Readability]]
- [[Discipline]]
- [[Observation]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]
- [[Practice]]
- [[Tend]]','Attend Attend names sustained presence with what has been noticed. Where Notice names first contact with what has become apparent, and Enter names passage into the relation opened by that contact, Attend names the chosen staying with through which relation remains available long enough to become followable, readable, or cared for. Attend comes before judgment, closure, or explanation. It keeps contact open without forcing the condition to resolve before its difference can be read. Places Attend places sustained presence with what has been noticed and entered. Holds Attend is held by Notice, Enter, and Availability. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Attend is a singular carrier primitive — the condition through which notice becomes directed. There is no lateral contrast required at the attend level. The asymmetry is expressed in what attend makes possible: Trace, Read, and Readability. Traces Notice Enter Availability Nests Attend nests between first contact and trace. It keeps relation open before judgment, closure, or explanation. Reads Attend becomes recognisable where a noticed distinction is held in contact long enough for its relation, difference, or path to begin disclosing itself. Carries Read Readability Discipline Observation Atlas Practice Practice Tend','Attend Attend names sustained presence with what has been noticed. Where Notice names first contact with what has become apparent, and Enter names passage into the relation opened by that contact,…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.availability","first.enter","first.notice","first.read","first.trace","practice.atlas-practice","practice.discipline","practice.practice","practice.tend","second.observation","second.readability"]','{"holds":["first.notice","first.enter","first.availability"],"traces":["first.notice","first.enter","first.availability"],"carries":["first.read","second.readability","practice.discipline","second.observation","practice.atlas-practice","practice.practice","practice.tend"],"pairs":["first.trace","first.read","second.readability"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',190,'sha256:45bd6090e9d84e1e0738866a58ea7cb202152f9b1904401db0d716f38ec98e21','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.availability','Availability','availability','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Availability.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/availability.html','# Availability

Availability names the condition through which a located distinction can present. Where boundary names the locating act, availability names what that act makes possible — the condition under which distinction can enter participation. Availability does not yet require trace, holding, recognition, resolution, or allowance; it names the condition under which distinction can become present enough to enter them.

## Places

Availability places the condition through which located distinction can present.

## Holds

Availability is held by [[Boundary]]. A distinction must be located before its availability can be read.

## Pairs

Availability pairs with [[Boundary]]: boundary locates distinction; availability names the condition through which that located distinction can present. Each is only locatable against the other — boundary without availability is mere limit; availability without boundary is undirected openness.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Availability nests as both a first-order root condition and a passage condition. It names entry into possible participation before carrying, allowance, or resolution are decided.

## Reads

Availability becomes recognisable where a located distinction is present enough to participate in evaluation — where something can enter strain, holding, allowance, or resolution.

**Passage Role.**

Availability is a passage condition as well as a first-order root condition: it names whether a located distinction can enter later carrying without yet naming the carrying itself.

