INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.bearing','Bearing','bearing','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Bearing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/bearing.html','# Bearing

Bearing names strain held as a readable condition. Where strain names available distinction under contrast, bearing names that same contrast held — sustained without collapsing or dissipating. Bearing does not yet name carrying, coupling, or outcome. It names the held strain through which resolution becomes available.

## Places

Bearing places strain held as a readable condition.

## Holds

Bearing is held by [[Strain]]. Strain must press before it can be held.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Bearing is a singular condition at its juncture — the holding of strained distinction. There is no lateral contrast required to locate bearing. The structural asymmetry is fully expressed by what bearing becomes: [[Resolution]].

## Traces

- [[Strain]]

## Nests

Bearing nests between strain and resolution. It also nests under later carrying, closure, repair, and load-bearing reads without becoming those reads itself.

## Reads

Bearing becomes recognisable where strain can be read as held — where contrast is sustained within the bounded condition rather than dissipating or resolving.

**Structural Role.**

Bearing is a first-order root condition. Its high connectivity comes from load-bearing dependency: many later reads require strain to be held before it can resolve as hold, failure, yield, release, transfer, absorption, carrying, closure, or repair.

