- [[Contend]]','Boundary Boundary names the located distinction through which relation becomes locally distinguishable. Where Distinction names bounded unevenness becoming distinguishable, boundary names the locating act itself — the operation through which that distinction becomes a local condition. Boundary does not separate relation absolutely; it locates distinction within relation. Places Boundary places located distinction within relation. Holds Boundary is held by Distinction. Unevenness must be distinguishable before a boundary can locate it. Pairs Boundary pairs with Availability: boundary locates distinction; availability names the condition through which that located distinction can present. Traces Distinction Nests Boundary nests as both a first order root condition and a passage condition. It can hold local distinction while later reads test what can pass, fail, close, or remain outside scope. Reads Boundary becomes recognisable where distinguishability can be read as a local condition — where something is here rather than there, this rather than that. Passage Role. Boundary is a passage condition as well as a first order root condition: it locates the edge through which later carrying can pass, fail, close, or remain outside scope. Carries Availability Apparent In Out Divisible Indivisible Not Closure Enter Threshold Primitive Carrier Coupled Boundary Contact Competence Boundary Return Face Musical Rhythm Allow Transfer Within Terminal Interposed Carrier Throughput Guard Pressure Splinter Extend Extent Relative Dominion Translation Boundary Locating Space Based Solar Power Check Contend','Boundary Boundary names the located distinction through which relation becomes locally distinguishable. Where Distinction names bounded unevenness becoming distinguishable, boundary names the…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.allow","first.apparent","first.availability","first.contact","first.distinction","first.divisible","first.enter","fir