INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.bounded-asymmetry','Bounded Asymmetry','bounded-asymmetry','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Asymmetry Conditions/Bounded Asymmetry.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/bounded-asymmetry.html','# Bounded Asymmetry

Bounded asymmetry names asymmetry localised enough to become distinguishable. Where [[Asymmetry]] names unevenness within relation before it is located, bounded asymmetry names that unevenness held locally enough that a boundary can form.

## Places

Bounded Asymmetry places the hinge where uneven relation becomes local enough to be distinguished.

## Holds

Bounded Asymmetry is held by [[Asymmetry]]. Unevenness must already be readable before it can be locally held.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Bounded Asymmetry is the singular condition through which asymmetry becomes local enough to open [[Distinction]] and [[Strained Asymmetry]]. Distinction carries the located and readable branch; Strained Asymmetry carries the bearing branch.

## Traces

- [[Asymmetry]]
- [[Invariant]]

## Nests

Bounded Asymmetry nests between unlocated unevenness and located distinction. It is the hinge where difference becomes held enough to become locally readable.

## Reads

Bounded asymmetry becomes recognisable where unevenness can be read as local — where asymmetry is present enough for one distinguishable condition to be located against another.

Bounded asymmetry localises asymmetry enough that distinction can form. [[Distinction]] then carries [[Boundary]], through which primitive carriers emerge as the ways located distinction can be carried.

It also makes adaptation possible downstream. Adaptation does not erase asymmetry; it allows local resolutions and shifts to occur while the wider asymmetry remains available for further relation.

## Carries

- [[Distinction]]
- [[Strained Asymmetry]]
- [[Operational Condition]]
- [[Adaptation]]','Bounded Asymmetry Bounded asymmetry names asymmetry localised enough to become distinguishable. Where Asymmetry names unevenness within relation before it is located, bounded asymmetry names that unevenness held locally enough that a boundary can form. Places Bounded Asymmetry places the hinge where uneven relation becomes local enough to be distinguished. Holds Bounded Asymmetry is held by Asymmetry. Unevenness must already be readable before it can be locally held. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Bounded Asymmetry is the singular condition through which asymmetry becomes local enough to open Distinction and Strained Asymmetry. Distinction carries the located and readable branch; Strained Asymmetry carries the bearing branch. Traces Asymmetry Invariant Nests Bounded Asymmetry nests between unlocated unevenness and located distinction. It is the hinge where difference becomes held enough to become locally readable. Reads Bounded asymmetry becomes recognisable where unevenness can be read as local — where asymmetry is present enough for one distinguishable condition to be located against another. Bounded asymmetry localises asymmetry enough that distinction can form. Distinction then carries Boundary, through which primitive carriers emerge as the ways located distinction can be carried. It also makes adaptation possible downstream. Adaptation does not erase asymmetry; it allows local resolutions and shifts to occur while the wider asymmetry remains available for further relation. Carries Distinction Strained Asymmetry Operational Condition Adaptation','Bounded Asymmetry Bounded asymmetry names asymmetry localised enough to become distinguishable. Where Asymmetry names unevenness within relation before it is located, bounded asymmetry names that…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.asymmetry","first.distinction","first.operational-condition","first.strained-asymmetry","ground.invariant","second.adaptation"]','{"holds":["first.asymmetry"],"traces":["first.asymmetry","ground.invariant"],"carries":["first.distinction","first.strained-asymmetry","first.operational-condition","second.adaptation"],"pairs":["first.distinction","first.strained-asymmetry"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',216,'sha256:2d915dc0c7c69e03b6af5cc4f58462564f1a04258ebe0ed17a3367fd6bcd20ea','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.carry','Carry','carry','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Carry.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/carry.html','# Carry

Carry names the forward availability of held [[Connection]].

Carry is not yet [[Carrying]]. Carry names the passage connection offers where relation is held enough for forward availability to remain traceable. Carrying names movement through that passage. A connection may offer carry whether or not a participant, process, or condition is presently carrying through it.

Carry does not require the connected condition to remain unchanged. It only names forward availability through the connection.

## Places

Carry places the forward availability of held connection.

## Holds

Carry is held by [[Hold]] and [[Connection]]. Connection must hold before forward passage through it can be available.

## Pairs

Carry pairs with [[Trace]]. Carry is the forward availability of held connection; Trace is the backward availability of the same connection.

## Traces

- [[Connection]]
- [[Hold]]

## Nests

Carry nests within connection as its forward availability, before that availability is enacted as carrying.

## Reads

Carry becomes recognisable where held connection offers passage from a prior condition into a further condition without requiring that passage already to have been enacted.

## Carries

- [[First Order Crossing|Threshold (First → Second)]]
- [[Carrying]]','Carry Carry names the forward availability of held Connection. Carry is not yet Carrying. Carry names the passage connection offers where relation is held enough for forward availability to remain traceable. Carrying names movement through that passage. A connection may offer carry whether or not a participant, process, or condition is presently carrying through it. Carry does not require the connected condition to remain unchanged. It only names forward availability through the connection. Places Carry places the forward availability of held connection. Holds Carry is held by Hold and Connection. Connection must hold before forward passage through it can be available. Pairs Carry pairs with Trace. Carry is the forward availability of held connection; Trace is the backward availability of the same connection. Traces Connection Hold Nests Carry nests within connection as its forward availability, before that availability is enacted as carrying. Reads Carry becomes recognisable where held connection offers passage from a prior condition into a further condition without requiring that passage already to have been enacted. Carries First Order Crossing Carrying','Carry Carry names the forward availability of held Connection. Carry is not yet Carrying.','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.connection","first.first-order-crossing","first.hold","first.trace","second.carrying"]','{"holds":["first.hold","first.connection"],"traces":["first.hold","first.connection"],"carries":["first.first-order-crossing","second.carrying"],"pairs":["first.trace"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',173,'sha256:d5e9e2bc57a42b53da8893f62798a153b53fc4eca613c8aae5423c4f557f3a1c','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.clean','Clean','clean','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Clean.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/clean.html','# Clean

Clean names the invariant carrier by which relation remains free from residue, drift, or false mixture before readable difference is carried onward. It is the condition in which relation does not carry what prevents its own readability, handling, separation, or meeting.

Clean is hidden in many successful reads because it is not always the visible operation. Clear reading and tactful contact both depend on it.

## Places

Clean places the invariant carrier of undrifted relation before the clear/tact split.

## Holds

Clean is held by [[Relation]]. Relation must hold before anything can be cleanly read, handled, separated, or met.

## Pairs

Relation carries downward into Clean. Clean is an invariant carrier: it holds whether or not the split into readability or handling is visible.

## Traces

- [[Relation]]
- [[Invariant]]

## Nests

Clean nests before the clear/tact split. It is not a category above them; it is the hidden carrier that lets reading and contact remain undistorted.

## Reads

Clean becomes recognisable where relation is not carrying unnecessary residue, mixture, or drift into the next condition.

## Carries

- [[Clear]]
- [[Tact]]
