fference"],"pairs":["first.boundary","second.difference"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',213,'sha256:e0ce4fb4efd372ef4057203f5491757ccd6869e370775d16db5c2b21eab44300','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.divisible','Divisible','divisible','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Divisible.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/divisible.html','# Divisible

Divisible carries readable separation: distinction that can be separated while relation remains available. Destruction or disappearance can involve division, but divisible itself carries separability. What is divisible may remain related; separation is not non-relation.

## Places

Divisible places readable separation.

## Holds

Divisible is held by [[Boundary]]. Distinction must be located before separability can be read.

## Pairs

Divisible pairs with [[Indivisible]]. Divisible carries separability; Indivisible carries non-separability without sameness.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Divisible nests as a structural carrier. It can support later divisible bearing without turning separation into non-relation.

## Reads

Divisible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as separable within relation.

## Carries

- [[Divisible Bearing]]','Divisible Divisible carries readable separation: distinction that can be separated while relation remains available. Destruction or disappearance can involve division, but divisible itself carries separability. What is divisible may remain related; separation is not non relation. Places Divisible places readable separation. Holds Divisible is held by Boundary. Distinction must be located before separability can be read. Pairs Divisible pairs with Indivisible. Divisible carries separability; Indivisible carries non separability without sameness. Traces Boundary Nests Divisible nests as a structural carrier. It can support later divisible bearing without turning separation into non relation. Reads Divisible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as separable within relation. Carries Divisible Bearing','Divisible Divisible carries readable separation: distinction that can be separated while relation remains available. Destruction or disappearance can involve division, but divisible itself carries…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.indivisible","second.divisible-bearing"]','{"holds":["first.boundary"],"traces":["first.boundary"],"carries":["second.divisible-bearing"],"pairs":["first.indivisible"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',106,'sha256:948578ba2bab952f9ec82d8eb56fa63cfa2171f6245d925b827701b7b8852269','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.emergent-condition','Emergent Condition','emergent-condition','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Asymmetry Conditions/Emergent Condition.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/emergent-condition.html','# Emergent Condition

Emergent condition names the class of first-order conditions that arise from within relation through asymmetry rather than being imposed from outside it or established by operations. Where operations act on distinction, emergent conditions name what becomes available prior to those acts — the conditions that make operations possible, arising without external cause. Asymmetry, bounded asymmetry, strained asymmetry, and resolved asymmetry are emergent conditions.

## Places

Emergent Condition places the class of first-order conditions that arise from within relation through asymmetry.

## Holds

Emergent Condition is held by [[Asymmetry]]. Uneven relation must be readable before emergence through asymmetry can be named.

## Pairs

Emergent Condition pairs with [[Operational Condition]]. Emergent conditions arise through asymmetry; operational conditions act on located distinction.

## Traces

- [[Emergent]]
- [[Asymmetry]]

## Nests

Emergent Condition nests asymmetry, bounded asymmetry, strained asymmetry, and resolved asymmetry as conditions that become available before imposed operation.

## Reads

Emergent condition becomes recognisable where a term names something that arises from relation through asymmetry rather than something that acts upon or localises distinction.

## Carries','Emergent Condition Emergent condition names the class of first order conditions that arise from within relation through asymmetry rather than being imposed from outside it or established by operations. Where operations act on distinction, emergent conditions name what becomes available prior to those acts — the conditions that make operations possible, arising without external cause. Asymmetry, bounded asymmetry, strained asymmetry, and resolved asymmetry are emergent conditions. Places Emergent Condition places the class of first order conditions that arise from within relation through asymmetry. Holds Emergent Condition is held by Asymmetry. Uneven relation must be readable before emergence through asymmetry can be named. Pairs Emergent Condition pairs with Operational Condition. Emergent conditions arise through asymmetry; operational conditions act on located distinction. Traces Emergent Asymmetry Nests Emergent Condition nests asymmetry, bounded asymmetry, strained asymmetry, and resolved asymmetry as conditions that become available before imposed operation. Reads Emergent condition becomes recognisable where a term names something that arises from relation through asymmetry rather than something that acts upon or localises distinction. Carries','Emergent Condition Emergent condition names the class of first order conditions that arise from within relation through asymmetry rather than being imposed from outside it or established by…','stable','rooted',0,'first','class',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.asymmetry","first.operational-condition","ground.emergent"]','{"holds":["first.asymmetry"],"traces":["ground.emergent","first.asymmetry"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.operational-condition"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',169,'sha256:45e1f570bad9ebbe4b71dc9fa82ad053e3da417f410af199b12360768e973f71','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.enter','Enter','enter','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Enter.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/enter.html','# Enter

Enter names the passage by which a noticed distinction opens into a field of relation. Where [[Notice]] names first contact, Enter names crossing from contact with a boundary or threshold into the relation-space where what has been noticed can widen, disclose, and become available to attend.

Enter is not the same as [[Allow]]. Allow names permitted passage from the condition side; Enter names taken passage from the participating side.

## Places

Enter places the crossing from first contact into the relation-space opened by that contact.

## Holds

Enter is held by [[Notice]], [[Boundary]], [[Threshold]], [[Allow]], and [[Space]].

## Pairs

Enter pairs with [[Allow]]. Allow names permitted passage from the condition side; Enter names taken passage from the participating side.

## Traces

- [[Notice]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Threshold]]
- [[Allow]]
- [[Space]]

## Nests

Enter nests between notice and participation. It widens the field after contact without yet naming sustained attention or full participation.

## Reads

Enter becomes recognisable where first contact passes into participatory relation — where what was noticed is no longer only met from outside, but becomes available from within a widened field.

## Carries

- [[Attend]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]
