"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',182,'sha256:bcbd52c369d5fd3c7b735ba08befec00eb54396931805afa4b59431ac10d116d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.failure','Failure','failure','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Resolution Conditions/Failure.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/failure.html','# Failure

Failure names resolution where bearing cannot remain supportable at the current scope. Absence can follow failure, but failure first names the determined condition in which what bears strain no longer holds as the same supportable condition.

## Places

Failure places resolution where bearing cannot remain supportable at the current scope.

## Holds

Failure is held by [[Resolution]] and [[Bearing]]. Bearing must be present and determined before its loss of support can be read as failure.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Failure names [[Resolution]] where bearing cannot remain supportable: a specific mode of Resolution, not a juncture requiring co-presence. Its structural place is held by Resolution and Bearing.

## Traces

- [[Resolution]]
- [[Bearing]]

## Nests

Failure nests under first-order resolution. Absence, repair, harm, or disorder may follow, but failure itself names the loss of supportable bearing.

## Reads

Failure becomes recognisable where bearing resolves as loss of support, collapse, break, or inability to continue under the strain it bears.

## Carries','Failure Failure names resolution where bearing cannot remain supportable at the current scope. Absence can follow failure, but failure first names the determined condition in which what bears strain no longer holds as the same supportable condition. Places Failure places resolution where bearing cannot remain supportable at the current scope. Holds Failure is held by Resolution and Bearing. Bearing must be present and determined before its loss of support can be read as failure. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Failure names Resolution where bearing cannot remain supportable: a specific mode of Resolution, not a juncture requiring co presence. Its structural place is held by Resolution and Bearing. Traces Resolution Bearing Nests Failure nests under first order resolution. Absence, repair, harm, or disorder may follow, but failure itself names the loss of supportable bearing. Reads Failure becomes recognisable where bearing resolves as loss of support, collapse, break, or inability to continue under the strain it bears. Carries','Failure Failure names resolution where bearing cannot remain supportable at the current scope. Absence can follow failure, but failure first names the determined condition in which what bears…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.resolution"]','{"holds":["first.resolution","first.bearing"],"traces":["first.resolution","first.bearing"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.resolution"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',155,'sha256:7ae6d5f37f2202e289c8288ed7cd7bdb45dedfc1fa7f56679fa9b91f06a28ad8','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.first-order-crossing','Threshold (First → Second)','threshold-first-second','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/First Order Crossing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/threshold-first-second.html','# Threshold (First → Second)

This threshold names the crossing from First Order into Second Order.

## Places

Threshold (First → Second) places the crossing where held first-order carry is entered and enacted as second-order carrying.

## Holds

Threshold (First → Second) is held by [[First Order]], [[Hold]], [[Connection]], [[Carry]], and [[Place]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — marks the transition into [[Carrying]] and [[Second Order]]

## Traces

- [[First Order]]
- [[Hold]]
- [[Connection]]
- [[Carry]]
- [[Place]]

## Nests

Threshold (First → Second) nests between orders. It is not a general threshold; it marks the specific passage from first-order determination into second-order carrying.

## Reads

Threshold (First → Second) becomes recognisable where held forward availability is entered or continued as carrying.

**What First Order makes available.**

Relation becomes held and directionally available as carry and trace. Place makes that availability enterable, readable, and checkable. Boundary, availability, strain, bearing, and resolution can locate and shape the conditions that pass through connection.

**The crossing.**

Where [[Carry]] is enacted, [[Carrying]] becomes available as the first second-order movement. Resolution may shape a particular crossing, but it is not required to define every instance of carrying.

## Carries

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Second Order]]','Threshold (First → Second) This threshold names the crossing from First Order into Second Order. Places Threshold (First → Second) places the crossing where held first order carry is entered and enacted as second order carrying. Holds Threshold (First → Second) is held by First Order, Hold, Connection, Carry, and Place. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward — marks the transition into Carrying and Second Order Traces First Order Hold Connection Carry Place Nests Threshold (First → Second) nests between orders. It is not a general threshold; it marks the specific passage from first order determination into second order carrying. Reads Threshold (First → Second) becomes recognisable where held forward availability is entered or continued as carrying. What First Order makes available. Relation becomes held and directionally available as carry and trace. Place makes that availability enterable, readable, and checkable. Boundary, availability, strain, bearing, and resolution can locate and shape the conditions that pass through connection. The crossing. Where Carry is enacted, Carrying becomes available as the first second order movement. Resolution may shape a particular crossing, but it is not required to define every instance of carrying. Carries Carrying Second Order','Threshold (First → Second) This threshold names the crossing from First Order into Second Order. Places Threshold (First → Second) places the crossing where held first order carry is entered and…','working','planted',0,'first','crossing',NULL,'["First Order Crossing"]','[]','["first.carry","first.connection","first.first-order","first.hold","first.place","second.carrying","second.second-order"]','{"holds":["first.first-order","first.hold","first.connection","first.carry","first.place"],"traces":["first.first-order","first.hold","first.connection","first.carry","first.place"],"carries":["second.carrying","second.second-order"],"pairs":["second.carrying","second.second-order"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',190,'sha256:1b7852277f3815d42329c277651de197543f6aa27da66c6a1be2c0c7ed695d75','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.first-order','First Order','first-order','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/First Order.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/first-order.html','# First Order

First Order names the register where relation becomes connectable, orientable as [[Posture]], and placeable enough for carry and trace to become available. It establishes [[Connection]] before the forward direction is enacted as [[Carrying]] or the backward direction is followed through [[Retracing]].

In the tree read, First Order is root structure becoming readable. It is rooted in [[Ground]] and grows toward the trunk; its work is to make later carrying possible.

## Places

First Order places relation becoming connectable and placeable enough to offer forward carry and backward trace. Boundary, availability, strain, bearing, and resolution locate or shape what may pass without defining the working root itself.

## Holds

First Order is held by [[Root Order]]. Its terms follow dependency arrangement rather than topic sequence.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. First Order is a structural level marker, not a term with a lateral sibling. The asymmetry it names is fully expressed by the level it carries into: [[Second Order]].

## Traces

- [[Root Order]]

## Nests

First Order nests relation, hold, carry, place, connection, trace, and the conditions that distinguish, locate, strain, bear, or resolve what may pass through connection.

[[Emergent Condition]]
[[Operational Condition]]
[[Primitive Carrier]]
[[Operation Carrier]]
[[Structural Carrier]]
[[Hold]]
[[Connection]]
[[Posture]]
[[Carry]]
[[Place]]
[[Trace]]
[[Contact]]
[[First Order Crossing|Threshold (First → Second)]]
[[Second Order]]

## Reads

First Order becomes recognisable where relation becomes held and placeable enough to offer forward carry and backward trace before those directions are enacted in later orders.

It is read as root rather than branch: first-order conditions are repaired by retracing what must hold, not by replacing them with a later field or domain read.

## Carries

- [[Second Order]]
