INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.hold','Hold','hold','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Resolution Conditions/Hold.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/hold.html','# Hold

Hold names resolution remaining supportable as the same condition. Where bearing names strain sustained as readable and resolution names bearing determined at the current scope, hold names that determination settling as continued support rather than collapse, discharge, deformation, or transfer.

## Places

Hold places resolution remaining supportable as the same condition.

## Holds

Hold is held by [[Resolution]]. Bearing must be determined at the current scope before it can remain supportable.

## Pairs

Hold pairs with [[Release]]: hold names the maintaining of a resolved condition in place — continuing to carry what resolution has determined; release names the letting go of that same condition. Each requires the other to be locatable: you can only name something as held because it could be released; you can only name something as released because it was held.

## Traces

- [[Resolution]]

## Nests

Hold nests under first-order resolution. It may support later carrying, but it is not carrying by itself.

## Reads

Hold becomes recognisable where resolved bearing stays together enough to remain available for reading, support, or later carrying.
## Carries

- [[Carry]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[First Order Crossing|Threshold (First → Second)]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Read]]
- [[Retain]]','Hold Hold names resolution remaining supportable as the same condition. Where bearing names strain sustained as readable and resolution names bearing determined at the current scope, hold names that determination settling as continued support rather than collapse, discharge, deformation, or transfer. Places Hold places resolution remaining supportable as the same condition. Holds Hold is held by Resolution. Bearing must be determined at the current scope before it can remain supportable. Pairs Hold pairs with Release: hold names the maintaining of a resolved condition in place — continuing to carry what resolution has determined; release names the letting go of that same condition. Each requires the other to be locatable: you can only name something as held because it could be released; you can only name something as released because it was held. Traces Resolution Nests Hold nests under first order resolution. It may support later carrying, but it is not carrying by itself. Reads Hold becomes recognisable where resolved bearing stays together enough to remain available for reading, support, or later carrying. Carries Carry Trace First Order Crossing Carrying Read Retain','Hold Hold names resolution remaining supportable as the same condition. Where bearing names strain sustained as readable and resolution names bearing determined at the current scope, hold names…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.carry","first.first-order-crossing","first.read","first.release","first.resolution","first.trace","second.carrying","second.retain"]','{"holds":["first.resolution"],"traces":["first.resolution"],"carries":["first.carry","first.trace","first.first-order-crossing","second.carrying","first.read","second.retain"],"pairs":["first.release"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',181,'sha256:6d8c43d88096bae8f333720a42fe731eac11f3154f5e809902754d73f41f8884','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.in','In','in','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/In.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/in.html','# In

In carries interior placement: relation readable as within a bounded condition. Possession or enclosure can involve in, but in itself carries inward placement into later compounds such as within, inside, input, inhabit, and in-relation.

## Places

In places interior relation within a bounded condition.

## Holds

In is held by [[Boundary]]. A boundary must locate distinction before interior placement can be read.

## Pairs

In pairs with [[Out]]. In carries interior placement; Out carries exterior placement.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

In nests as a structural carrier that can enter later compounds such as within, inside, input, inhabit, and in-relation.

## Reads

In becomes recognisable where relation is read as within a located condition.

## Carries

- [[Within]]
- [[Intake]]','In In carries interior placement: relation readable as within a bounded condition. Possession or enclosure can involve in, but in itself carries inward placement into later compounds such as within, inside, input, inhabit, and in relation. Places In places interior relation within a bounded condition. Holds In is held by Boundary. A boundary must locate distinction before interior placement can be read. Pairs In pairs with Out. In carries interior placement; Out carries exterior placement. Traces Boundary Nests In nests as a structural carrier that can enter later compounds such as within, inside, input, inhabit, and in relation. Reads In becomes recognisable where relation is read as within a located condition. Carries Within Intake','In In carries interior placement: relation readable as within a bounded condition. Possession or enclosure can involve in, but in itself carries inward placement into later compounds such as…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.out","second.intake","second.within"]','{"holds":["first.boundary"],"traces":["first.boundary"],"carries":["second.within","second.intake"],"pairs":["first.out"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',114,'sha256:16e269ff2da7559bbddd3f18cd9da0ce011de6321215d829b340a5f848710430','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.indivisible','Indivisible','indivisible','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Indivisible.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/indivisible.html','# Indivisible

Indivisible carries non-separable distinction: distinction that cannot be separated without changing the condition being read. Fusion or sameness can involve indivisibility, but indivisible itself carries non-separability. What is indivisible may still contain relation; non-separability is not sameness.

## Places

Indivisible places non-separable distinction.

## Holds

Indivisible is held by [[Boundary]]. Distinction must be located before non-separability can be read.

## Pairs

Indivisible pairs with [[Divisible]]. Divisible carries separability; Indivisible carries non-separability without sameness.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Indivisible nests as a structural carrier. It can support later indivisible bearing without making non-separability into sameness.

## Reads

Indivisible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as unable to separate without changing the condition under evaluation.

## Carries

- [[Indivisible Bearing]]','Indivisible Indivisible carries non separable distinction: distinction that cannot be separated without changing the condition being read. Fusion or sameness can involve indivisibility, but indivisible itself carries non separability. What is indivisible may still contain relation; non separability is not sameness. Places Indivisible places non separable distinction. Holds Indivisible is held by Boundary. Distinction must be located before non separability can be read. Pairs Indivisible pairs with Divisible. Divisible carries separability; Indivisible carries non separability without sameness. Traces Boundary Nests Indivisible nests as a structural carrier. It can support later indivisible bearing without making non separability into sameness. Reads Indivisible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as unable to separate without changing the condition under evaluation. Carries Indivisible Bearing','Indivisible Indivisible carries non separable distinction: distinction that cannot be separated without changing the condition being read. Fusion or sameness can involve indivisibility, but…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.divisible","second.indivisible-bearing"]','{"holds":["first.boundary"],"traces":["first.boundary"],"carries":["second.indivisible-bearing"],"pairs":["first.divisible"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',119,'sha256:c1b6e2d616378c6b470125ea3e8ea30aae598cada28a3696302b68a416b42884','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.invisible','Invisible','invisible','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Invisible.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/invisible.html','# Invisible

Invisible carries non-presented readability: distinction that can hold without being presented to read. Absence, hiding, or destruction can involve invisibility, but invisible itself carries non-presentation. What is invisible may remain structurally active; non-presentation is not non-relation.

## Places

Invisible places non-presented readability.

## Holds

Invisible is held by [[Apparent]]. A distinction can be apparent to structure without being presented to read.

## Pairs

Invisible pairs with [[Visible]] and differs from Hidden. Invisible can be background-carrying; hidden implies concealment or blocked read.

## Traces

- [[Apparent]]

## Nests

Invisible nests under apparent presentation as its non-presented counterpart. It can remain structurally active without becoming absent from relation.

## Reads

Invisible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as not presented rather than absent from relation.

## Carries

- [[Invisible Bearing Read]]','Invisible Invisible carries non presented readability: distinction that can hold without being presented to read. Absence, hiding, or destruction can involve invisibility, but invisible itself carries non presentation. What is invisible may remain structurally active; non presentation is not non relation. Places Invisible places non presented readability. Holds Invisible is held by Apparent. A distinction can be apparent to structure without being presented to read. Pairs Invisible pairs with Visible and differs from Hidden. Invisible can be background carrying; hidden implies concealment or blocked read. Traces Apparent Nests Invisible nests under apparent presentation as its non presented counterpart. It can remain structurally active without becoming absent from relation. Reads Invisible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as not presented rather than absent from relation. Carries Invisible Bearing Read','Invisible Invisible carries non presented readability: distinction that can hold without being presented to read. Absence, hiding, or destruction can involve invisibility, but invisible itself…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.apparent","first.visible","second.invisible-bearing-read"]','{"holds":["first.apparent"],"traces":["first.apparent"],"carries":["second.invisible-bearing-read"],"pairs":["first.visible"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',128,'sha256:a274682b0df5964482cb47a1b8e7bd7fbd6a2007c75ed48bd238f9563c3376bf','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.not','Not','not','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Not.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/not.html','# Not

Not carries non-availability: relation marked as unavailable, interrupted, absent, excluded, or outside the current scope. Refusal or destruction can involve not, but not first marks non-availability rather than active barring. What is marked by not may remain related.

Not marks that what cannot be reached, traced, or carried within the current structure is not available here.

## Places

Not places non-availability within the current scope.

## Holds

Not is held by [[Boundary]] and [[Availability]]. Scope must be bounded, and availability must be readable, before non-availability can be marked.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Not marks non-availability as a structural carrier: it applies the [[Boundary]]/[[Availability]] pair to specific conditions. [[Availability]] already names the positive condition upstream.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]
- [[Availability]]

## Nests

Not nests as a structural carrier of absence, interruption, exclusion, and outside-scope relation without turning them into conclusions.

## Reads

Not becomes recognisable where a condition is read through what it excludes — where the boundary of a scope is readable as much as its interior.

Not allows absence, interruption, exclusion, and outside-scope relation to be carried without turning them into objects or conclusions.

## Carries','Not Not carries non availability: relation marked as unavailable, interrupted, absent, excluded, or outside the current scope. Refusal or destruction can involve not, but not first marks non availability rather than active barring. What is marked by not may remain related. Not marks that what cannot be reached, traced, or carried within the current structure is not available here. Places Not places non availability within the current scope. Holds Not is held by Boundary and Availability. Scope must be bounded, and availability must be readable, before non availability can be marked. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Not marks non availability as a structural carrier: it applies the Boundary/Availability pair to specific conditions. Availability already names the positive condition upstream. Traces Boundary Availability Nests Not nests as a structural carrier of absence, interruption, exclusion, and outside scope relation without turning them into conclusions. Reads Not becomes recognisable where a condition is read through what it excludes — where the boundary of a scope is readable as much as its interior. Not allows absence, interruption, exclusion, and outside scope relation to be carried without turning them into objects or conclusions. Carries','Not Not carries non availability: relation marked as unavailable, interrupted, absent, excluded, or outside the current scope. Refusal or destruction can involve not, but not first marks non…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.availability","first.boundary"]','{"holds":["first.boundary","first.availability"],"traces":["first.boundary","first.availability"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.boundary","first.availability"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',188,'sha256:61b6b82598b0186377e79e549a2643c905f920dbf71f3cc2e0fb83d69b6d3192','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.notice','Notice','notice','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Notice.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/notice.html','# Notice

Notice names first contact with what has become apparent. Where [[Apparent]] names distinction present enough to be available, Notice names the move through which that availability is met before it is entered, attended, followed, held, explained, or placed.

Notice comes before enter, attend, or trace. It is the first contact that makes passage, attention, and trace possible.

## Places

Notice places first contact with what has become apparent.

## Holds

Notice is held by [[Apparent]] and [[Availability]]. Something must be available enough to appear before it can be noticed.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — into [[Attend]]. Notice names first contact; what first contact opens is sustained holding. The structure flows sequentially rather than requiring a lateral co-condition.

## Traces

- [[Apparent]]
- [[Availability]]

## Nests

Notice nests before enter, attend, trace, and read. It is the smallest contact opening through which later reading can begin.

## Reads

Notice becomes recognisable where something available is met as worth following — where a distinction has entered contact enough that passage or attention may begin.

## Carries

- [[Attend]]
- [[Enter]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]','Notice Notice names first contact with what has become apparent. Where Apparent names distinction present enough to be available, Notice names the move through which that availability is met before it is entered, attended, followed, held, explained, or placed. Notice comes before enter, attend, or trace. It is the first contact that makes passage, attention, and trace possible. Places Notice places first contact with what has become apparent. Holds Notice is held by Apparent and Availability. Something must be available enough to appear before it can be noticed. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward — into Attend. Notice names first contact; what first contact opens is sustained holding. The structure flows sequentially rather than requiring a lateral co condition. Traces Apparent Availability Nests Notice nests before enter, attend, trace, and read. It is the smallest contact opening through which later reading can begin. Reads Notice becomes recognisable where something available is met as worth following — where a distinction has entered contact enough that passage or attention may begin. Carries Attend Enter Atlas Practice','Notice Notice names first contact with what has become apparent. Where Apparent names distinction present enough to be available, Notice names the move through which that availability is met…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.apparent","first.attend","first.availability","first.enter","practice.atlas-practice"]','{"holds":["first.apparent","first.availability"],"traces":["first.apparent","first.availability"],"carries":["first.attend","first.enter","practice.atlas-practice"],"pairs":["first.attend"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',172,'sha256:1cadd1f152fbcaabc8ec4c5a6516715964fd3d08a78d3709a5cf256d6a2e6697','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.operation-carrier','Operation Carrier','operation-carrier','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Operation Carrier.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/operation-carrier.html','# Operation Carrier

Operation carrier names the class of primitive carriers that carry the reading operation across the system. Where operational conditions act on distinction at specific points in the dependency spine, operation carriers run through the whole system — making distinction apparent, followable, held, and recognisable at any point. Apparent, trace, read, and orientation are operation carriers; hold is now placed as a resolution condition rather than an operation carrier.

## Places

Operation Carrier places the class of primitive carriers that make conditions readable across the system.

## Holds

Operation Carrier is held by [[Primitive Carrier]].

## Pairs

Operation Carrier pairs with [[Structural Carrier]]. Operation carriers make any condition readable; structural carriers transmit specific relational roles into later compounds.

## Traces

- [[Primitive Carrier]]

## Nests

Operation Carrier nests Apparent, Trace, Read, and Orientation as cross-system reading operations.

[[Apparent]]
[[Trace]]
[[Read]]
[[Orientation]]

## Reads

Operation carrier becomes recognisable where a term names something that makes any condition readable rather than acting on distinction at one point in the sequence.

## Carries

Nothing at class grain. Nested terms are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.','Operation Carrier Operation carrier names the class of primitive carriers that carry the reading operation across the system. Where operational conditions act on distinction at specific points in the dependency spine, operation carriers run through the whole system — making distinction apparent, followable, held, and recognisable at any point. Apparent, trace, read, and orientation are operation carriers; hold is now placed as a resolution condition rather than an operation carrier. Places Operation Carrier places the class of primitive carriers that make conditions readable across the system. Holds Operation Carrier is held by Primitive Carrier. Pairs Operation Carrier pairs with Structural Carrier. Operation carriers make any condition readable; structural carriers transmit specific relational roles into later compounds. Traces Primitive Carrier Nests Operation Carrier nests Apparent, Trace, Read, and Orientation as cross system reading operations. Apparent Trace Read Orientation Reads Operation carrier becomes recognisable where a term names something that makes any condition readable rather than acting on distinction at one point in the sequence. Carries Nothing at class grain. Nested terms are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.','Operation Carrier Operation carrier names the class of primitive carriers that carry the reading operation across the system. Where operational conditions act on distinction at specific points in…','stable','rooted',0,'first','class',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.primitive-carrier","first.structural-carrier"]','{"holds":["first.primitive-carrier"],"traces":["first.primitive-carrier"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.structural-carrier"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',180,'sha256:6940ccefdcacfc00d44cdb4df21c4bd5c11f6a93e65d641cdde90fdfe40256a9','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.operational-condition','Operational Condition','operational-condition','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Boundary Conditions/Operational Condition.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/operational-condition.html','# Operational Condition

Operational condition names the class of first-order conditions through which located distinction becomes available, contrasted, held, and determined. Where emergent conditions arise from within relation through asymmetry, operational conditions act on distinction — locating it, making it available, straining it, bearing it, and resolving it. Boundary, availability, strain, bearing, resolution, and threshold are all operational conditions.

## Places

Operational Condition places the class of first-order conditions that act on located distinction.

## Holds

Operational Condition is held by [[Bounded Asymmetry]]. Distinction must be local enough before operations can locate, make available, strain, bear, or resolve it.

## Pairs

Operational Condition pairs with [[Emergent Condition]]. Emergent conditions arise through asymmetry; operational conditions act on located distinction.

## Traces

- [[Bounded Asymmetry]]

## Nests

Operational Condition nests boundary, availability, strain, threshold, bearing, and resolution as first-order operations on located distinction.

[[Boundary]]
[[Availability]]
[[Strain]]
[[Threshold]]
[[Bearing]]
[[Resolution]]

## Reads

Operational condition becomes recognisable where a term names something that acts on located distinction rather than arising from within relation through asymmetry.

## Carries

Nothing at class grain. Nested terms are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.','Operational Condition Operational condition names the class of first order conditions through which located distinction becomes available, contrasted, held, and determined. Where emergent conditions arise from within relation through asymmetry, operational conditions act on distinction — locating it, making it available, straining it, bearing it, and resolving it. Boundary, availability, strain, bearing, resolution, and threshold are all operational conditions. Places Operational Condition places the class of first order conditions that act on located distinction. Holds Operational Condition is held by Bounded Asymmetry. Distinction must be local enough before operations can locate, make available, strain, bear, or resolve it. Pairs Operational Condition pairs with Emergent Condition. Emergent conditions arise through asymmetry; operational conditions act on located distinction. Traces Bounded Asymmetry Nests Operational Condition nests boundary, availability, strain, threshold, bearing, and resolution as first order operations on located distinction. Boundary Availability Strain Threshold Bearing Resolution Reads Operational condition becomes recognisable where a term names something that acts on located distinction rather than arising from within relation through asymmetry. Carries Nothing at class grain. Nested terms are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.','Operational Condition Operational condition names the class of first order conditions through which located distinction becomes available, contrasted, held, and determined. Where emergent…','stable','rooted',0,'first','class',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bounded-asymmetry","first.emergent-condition"]','{"holds":["first.bounded-asymmetry"],"traces":["first.bounded-asymmetry"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.emergent-condition"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',183,'sha256:cd942f9a65f94ffad872db36e7186c8f125dc4f72ac331bba226775ad4f98b4e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.orientation','Orientation','orientation','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Orientation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/orientation.html','# Orientation

Orientation names the bearing-direction of a located distinction. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, orientation names the direction in which that condition bears: this way rather than that way within relation. Preference, aim, intention, or outcome can involve orientation, but orientation itself names directionality before determination.

## Places

Orientation places the bearing-direction of a located distinction.

## Holds

Orientation is held by [[Bearing]]. Strain must be held before its direction can be read.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — into [[Polarity]]. Orientation names directionality before determination; Polarity is what that direction differentiates into. No lateral pair: direction of bearing does not require a co-present condition to be locatable.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]

## Nests

Orientation nests before preference, aim, intention, or outcome. It names directionality before determination.

## Reads

Orientation becomes recognisable where a located distinction can be read as bearing in one direction rather than another — where the held condition has a readable directionality.

## Carries

- [[Polarity]]
- [[Shift]]
- [[Current]]
- [[Velocity]]','Orientation Orientation names the bearing direction of a located distinction. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, orientation names the direction in which that condition bears: this way rather than that way within relation. Preference, aim, intention, or outcome can involve orientation, but orientation itself names directionality before determination. Places Orientation places the bearing direction of a located distinction. Holds Orientation is held by Bearing. Strain must be held before its direction can be read. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward — into Polarity. Orientation names directionality before determination; Polarity is what that direction differentiates into. No lateral pair: direction of bearing does not require a co present condition to be locatable. Traces Bearing Nests Orientation nests before preference, aim, intention, or outcome. It names directionality before determination. Reads Orientation becomes recognisable where a located distinction can be read as bearing in one direction rather than another — where the held condition has a readable directionality. Carries Polarity Shift Current Velocity','Orientation Orientation names the bearing direction of a located distinction. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, orientation names the direction in which that condition…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.polarity","first.shift","second.current","second.velocity"]','{"holds":["first.bearing"],"traces":["first.bearing"],"carries":["first.polarity","first.shift","second.current","second.velocity"],"pairs":["first.polarity"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',161,'sha256:99ba52558046f7b0b4e7ad2fd1dd98534ede87c56aaeea33c2e8a1493b74f5ec','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.out','Out','out','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Out.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/out.html','# Out

Out carries exterior placement: relation readable as beyond a bounded condition. Absence, rejection, or destruction can involve out, but out itself carries outward placement into later compounds such as outside, output, outward, and out-of-relation. What is out may remain related; exteriority is not non-relation.

## Places

Out places exterior relation beyond a bounded condition.

## Holds

Out is held by [[Boundary]]. A boundary must locate distinction before exterior placement can be read.

## Pairs

Out pairs with [[In]]. In carries interior placement; Out carries exterior placement.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Out nests as a structural carrier that can enter later compounds such as outside, output, outward, and out-of-relation.

## Reads

Out becomes recognisable where relation is read as beyond a located condition.

## Carries','Out Out carries exterior placement: relation readable as beyond a bounded condition. Absence, rejection, or destruction can involve out, but out itself carries outward placement into later compounds such as outside, output, outward, and out of relation. What is out may remain related; exteriority is not non relation. Places Out places exterior relation beyond a bounded condition. Holds Out is held by Boundary. A boundary must locate distinction before exterior placement can be read. Pairs Out pairs with In. In carries interior placement; Out carries exterior placement. Traces Boundary Nests Out nests as a structural carrier that can enter later compounds such as outside, output, outward, and out of relation. Reads Out becomes recognisable where relation is read as beyond a located condition. Carries','Out Out carries exterior placement: relation readable as beyond a bounded condition. Absence, rejection, or destruction can involve out, but out itself carries outward placement into later…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.in"]','{"holds":["first.boundary"],"traces":["first.boundary"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.in"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',124,'sha256:207d9a9440eb3415ce0d141e842fc5988c1b2bebbbcd5047913c868ef53814bc','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.place','Place','place','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Place.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/place.html','# Place

Place names locatable entry into relation: the first-order operation by which something becomes enterable, readable, checkable, correctable, or carryable within relation.

Place is not location alone. A location can be named without the operation being placed in Atlas order. Place names the availability of a locatable position through which relation, holding, carrying, and trace can become answerable, entered, and checked.

## Places

Place places locatable entry into relation, so an operation can be read, checked, corrected, or carried forward.

## Holds

Place is held by [[Relation]]. Relation must be available before any operation can become locatable within it. This is the first-order Place operation identified by `first.place`, not the downstream field note of the same title.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Place is a first-order operation in the Atlas, locatable through relation, carry, and trace rather than constituted by a lateral pairing.

## Traces

- [[Relation]]

## Nests

Place nests within first order as the operation that makes carrying enterable, readable, and correctable.

It is not identical to [[Placed Participation]], [[Place Field]], or any domain-specific place term. Those are downstream reads that can use first-order Place without becoming the root operation. Links to [[Place]] from first-order carrier mechanics should resolve to this `first.place` operation.

## Reads

Place becomes recognisable where an operation is locatable enough to be entered, read, checked, corrected, or carried forward without being confused with a later field of place.

Without Place, a carry may be available but not enterable; a hold may persist but not be checkable; a trace may exist but not be recoverable to a participant.

## Carries

- [[First Order Crossing|Threshold (First → Second)]]
