[]','["first.first-order-crossing","first.relation","practice.atlas-practice"]','{"holds":["first.relation"],"traces":["first.relation"],"carries":["first.first-order-crossing","practice.atlas-practice"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',269,'sha256:56ff3887a19317bcde06a7e787cf18ba99e2f1a688d9fc5fb2255e44e850d75e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.polarity','Polarity','polarity','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Polarity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/polarity.html','# Polarity

Polarity carries opposed direction: distinction presented as bearing in opposing directions within relation. Conflict or hierarchy can show polarity, but polarity names directional opposition before it names conflict. What is polar may remain related; opposition is not separation.

## Places

Polarity places opposed direction within relation.

## Holds

Polarity is held by [[Orientation]]. Direction must be readable before opposition of direction can be read.

## Pairs

Polarity pairs with [[Resolution Polarity]]. Polarity is first-order directional opposition; Resolution Polarity carries that opposition into resolution reads.

## Traces

- [[Orientation]]

## Nests

Polarity nests before conflict or hierarchy. It names directional opposition without making opposition into separation.

## Reads

Polarity becomes recognisable where distinction is read as bearing in opposed directions — where two orientations face away from each other within relation.

## Carries

- [[Resolution Polarity]]','Polarity Polarity carries opposed direction: distinction presented as bearing in opposing directions within relation. Conflict or hierarchy can show polarity, but polarity names directional opposition before it names conflict. What is polar may remain related; opposition is not separation. Places Polarity places opposed direction within relation. Holds Polarity is held by Orientation. Direction must be readable before opposition of direction can be read. Pairs Polarity pairs with Resolution Polarity. Polarity is first order directional opposition; Resolution Polarity carries that opposition into resolution reads. Traces Orientation Nests Polarity nests before conflict or hierarchy. It names directional opposition without making opposition into separation. Reads Polarity becomes recognisable where distinction is read as bearing in opposed directions — where two orientations face away from each other within relation. Carries Resolution Polarity','Polarity Polarity carries opposed direction: distinction presented as bearing in opposing directions within relation. Conflict or hierarchy can show polarity, but polarity names directional…','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.orientation","third.resolution-polarity"]','{"holds":["first.orientation"],"traces":["first.orientation"],"carries":["third.resolution-polarity"],"pairs":["third.resolution-polarity"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',128,'sha256:bde901285605064bebd1bead603f865e241115247b66b8a5841dfc41fbbca943','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.posture','Posture','posture','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Posture.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/posture.html','# Posture

Posture names connection held with orientation: how relation is held toward relation so that order can become constructible.

[[Connection]] gives a held and placeable passage. Posture names what happens when that passage is not merely present but directed — when the holding has a toward-ness that lets order begin to emerge. Without posture, connection remains available but not yet constructible. With posture, the held passage can carry as [[Structure]].

A posture is not a proof and not a doctrine. It is not a position that is occupied. It is the orientation through which carrying becomes ordered enough to bear.

The Euclid read is an exemplar of this: Euclid''s postulates are not claims that things exist. They are orientations from which construction proceeds. That structural pattern is what Posture names — not a belief to defend, but a held relation from which order can be built, tested, and corrected.

## Places

Posture places connection held with orientation: how relation is held toward relation so that order can become constructible.

## Holds

Posture is held by [[Connection]] and [[Asymmetry]]. Connection must hold as a passage, and asymmetry must give that passage direction, before the holding can become oriented enough for order to begin.

## Pairs

No lateral pair placed yet.

## Traces

- [[Connection]]
- [[Asymmetry]]

## Nests

Posture nests within first order, after connection. It is the orientation through which a held passage becomes constructible rather than merely available — between connection and the carrying that generates structure.

## Reads

Posture becomes recognisable where a connection is not just held but directed — where the holding has a toward-ness that makes order begin to emerge rather than remain merely available.

The toward-ness must be directed enough that the carry it opens is determinable at some scope. That scope may be wider than the scope at which the posture is currently read. What appears as indefinite holding from within one scope is posture resolving at a scope not yet entered — the orbit that looks permanent from inside a human lifetime, the held potential that has not yet met its condition. Posture is not indeterminate; it is resolution deferred to a scope not yet in view.

## Carries

