"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',160,'sha256:4334acfb704b720df419fad806ff8b4569555bd2c6f7911744df3a39a47fa570','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.space','Space','space','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Relation Conditions/Space.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/space.html','# Space

Space names clearance becoming locatable: relation readable as separation, extent, position, distance, inside/outside, here/there, and co-presence. Where time names held clearance as interval and continuation, space names the same clearance as separation and placement. Empty container or absolute extension can be later reads of space, but here space names clearance oriented enough for relation to be read as placed rather than only persisting.

## Places

Space places held clearance as separation and extent.

## Holds

Space is held by [[Clearance]]. Relation must remain held apart enough to become locatable.

## Pairs

Space pairs with [[Time]]. Space reads clearance as separation and extent; Time reads clearance as interval and continuation.

## Traces

- [[Clearance]]

## Nests

Space nests before boundary and before later reads of empty container or absolute extension. It names relation as placed rather than only persisting.

## Reads

Space becomes recognisable where clearance can be read as separated, extended, or located relation — where differences are not just held apart but placed in relation to each other. In later structure, space can carry as the unoccupied or uncarried interval that lets relations align and become readable.

## Carries

- [[Physical Space]]
- [[Placed Participation]]
- [[Enter]]
- [[Locating]]','Space Space names clearance becoming locatable: relation readable as separation, extent, position, distance, inside/outside, here/there, and co presence. Where time names held clearance as interval and continuation, space names the same clearance as separation and placement. Empty container or absolute extension can be later reads of space, but here space names clearance oriented enough for relation to be read as placed rather than only persisting. Places Space places held clearance as separation and extent. Holds Space is held by Clearance. Relation must remain held apart enough to become locatable. Pairs Space pairs with Time. Space reads clearance as separation and extent; Time reads clearance as interval and continuation. Traces Clearance Nests Space nests before boundary and before later reads of empty container or absolute extension. It names relation as placed rather than only persisting. Reads Space becomes recognisable where clearance can be read as separated, extended, or located relation — where differences are not just held apart but placed in relation to each other. In later structure, space can carry as the unoccupied or uncarried interval that lets relations align and become readable. Carries Physical Space Placed Participation Enter Locating','Space Space names clearance becoming locatable: relation readable as separation, extent, position, distance, inside/outside, here/there, and co presence. Where time names held clearance as…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.clearance","first.enter","first.time","third.locating","third.physical-space","third.placed-participation"]','{"holds":["first.clearance"],"traces":["first.clearance"],"carries":["third.physical-space","third.placed-participation","first.enter","third.locating"],"pairs":["first.time"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',190,'sha256:213d28fa56d2883dc2204b472196167fca4a081cfd7c2f3106e9070acb4917ba','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.strain','Strain','strain','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Strain.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/strain.html','# Strain

Strain names available distinction under contrast. Where availability names the condition under which distinction can present, strain names the same distinction pressing under contrast — present and pressured without yet being held or resolved. Strain does not yet name bearing, carrying, or outcome. It names the contrasted condition that can become held, resolved, remembered, or checked.

## Places

Strain places available distinction under contrast.

## Holds

Strain is held by [[Availability]]. Distinction must be present enough to enter contrast before strain can be read.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Strain is a singular condition at its juncture — the press that makes bearing necessary. There is no other mode of strain required to locate strain. The structural asymmetry is fully expressed by what strain becomes: [[Bearing]].

## Traces

- [[Availability]]

## Nests

Strain nests between available distinction and bearing. It names why a distinction becomes worth holding, resolving, remembering, or checking.

## Reads

Strain becomes recognisable where available distinction can be read as under contrast — where something is present and pressing rather than merely available.

**Structural Role.**

Strain is a first-order root condition. It does not gate passage by itself; it names the pressure through which available distinction can become held as bearing.

## Carries

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Threshold]]
- [[Absorb]]
- [[Release]]
- [[Disorder]]
- [[Degeneration Read]]
- [[Contend]]','Strain Strain names available distinction under contrast. Where availability names the condition under which distinction can present, strain names the same distinction pressing under contrast — present and pressured without yet being held or resolved. Strain does not yet name bearing, carrying, or outcome. It names the contrasted condition that can become held, resolved, remembered, or checked. Places Strain places available distinction under contrast. Holds Strain is held by Availability. Distinction must be present enough to enter contrast before strain can be read. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Strain is a singular condition at its juncture — the press that makes bearing necessary. There is no other mode of strain required to locate strain. The structural asymmetry is fully expressed by what strain becomes: Bearing. Traces Availability Nests Strain nests between available distinction and bearing. It names why a distinction becomes worth holding, resolving, remembering, or checking. Reads Strain becomes recognisable where available distinction can be read as under contrast — where something is present and pressing rather than merely available. Structural Role. Strain is a first order root condition. It does not gate passage by itself; it names the pressure through which available distinction can become held as bearing. Carries Bearing Threshold Absorb Release Disorder Degeneration Read Contend','Strain Strain names available distinction under contrast. Where availability names the condition under which distinction can present, strain names the same distinction pressing under contrast —…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.absorb","first.availability","first.bearing","first.release","first.threshold","practice.contend","second.disorder","third.degeneration-read"]','{"holds":["first.availability"],"traces":["first.availability"],"carries":["first.bearing","first.threshold","first.absorb","first.release","second.disorder","third.degeneration-read","practice.contend"],"pairs":["first.bearing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',208,'sha256:e4c7083b39335ac98c093d93a40aefe8e045b6b08951f49e501cef8d09a778be','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.strained-asymmetry','Strained Asymmetry','strained-asymmetry','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Asymmetry Conditions/Strained Asymmetry.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/strained-asymmetry.html','# Strained Asymmetry

Strained asymmetry names bounded asymmetry under contrast. Where bounded asymmetry names localised unevenness available for distinction, strained asymmetry names that same condition pressing at a boundary where contrast is present but not yet resolved. It does not yet name bearing, carrying, or outcome. It names the condition through which bounded asymmetry becomes consequential.

## Places

Strained Asymmetry places bounded asymmetry under contrast.

## Holds

Strained Asymmetry is held by [[Bounded Asymmetry]]. Local unevenness must be distinguishable before it can be strained.

## Pairs

Strained Asymmetry pairs with [[Resolved Asymmetry]]. Strained asymmetry names the contrast; resolved asymmetry names the same contrast determined at scope.

## Traces

- [[Bounded Asymmetry]]

## Nests

Strained Asymmetry nests between bounded asymmetry and resolved asymmetry. It echoes [[Strain]] without becoming the whole operational condition.

## Reads

Strained asymmetry becomes recognisable where bounded asymmetry can be read as under contrast — where the localised unevenness is present enough that something must either hold or resolve.

## Carries

- [[Resolved Asymmetry]]','Strained Asymmetry Strained asymmetry names bounded asymmetry under contrast. Where bounded asymmetry names localised unevenness available for distinction, strained asymmetry names that same condition pressing at a boundary where contrast is present but not yet resolved. It does not yet name bearing, carrying, or outcome. It names the condition through which bounded asymmetry becomes consequential. Places Strained Asymmetry places bounded asymmetry under contrast. Holds Strained Asymmetry is held by Bounded Asymmetry. Local unevenness must be distinguishable before it can be strained. Pairs Strained Asymmetry pairs with Resolved Asymmetry. Strained asymmetry names the contrast; resolved asymmetry names the same contrast determined at scope. Traces Bounded Asymmetry Nests Strained Asymmetry nests between bounded asymmetry and resolved asymmetry. It echoes Strain without becoming the whole operational condition. Reads Strained asymmetry becomes recognisable where bounded asymmetry can be read as under contrast — where the localised unevenness is present enough that something must either hold or resolve. Carries Resolved Asymmetry','Strained Asymmetry Strained asymmetry names bounded asymmetry under contrast. Where bounded asymmetry names localised unevenness available for distinction, strained asymmetry names that same…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bounded-asymmetry","first.resolved-asymmetry"]','{"holds":["first.bounded-asymmetry"],"traces":["first.bounded-asymmetry"],"carries":["first.resolved-asymmetry"],"pairs":["first.resolved-asymmetry"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',156,'sha256:5f780e73efeb41cec884d0b0369c3e5326e2620afd28fac03922404d48c2fe8a','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.structural-carrier','Structural Carrier','structural-carrier','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Structural Carrier.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/structural-carrier.html','# Structural Carrier

Structural carrier names the class of primitive carriers that carry relation into later structural compounds through small relation-words. Where operation carriers make any condition readable across the system, structural carriers transmit specific relational roles — placement, direction, and polarity — into language and downstream compounds. A structural carrier does not make structure; it preserves and transmits relations already available to read.

## Places

Structural Carrier places the class of primitive carriers that transmit specific relational roles into later compounds.

## Holds

Structural Carrier is held by [[Primitive Carrier]] and [[Read]].

## Pairs

Structural Carrier pairs with [[Operation Carrier]]. Operation carriers make any condition readable; structural carriers preserve and transmit specific relational roles.

## Traces

- [[Primitive Carrier]]
- [[Read]]

## Nests

Structural Carrier nests the small relation-words that carry placement, direction, and polarity.

[[In]]
[[Out]]
[[Not]]
[[Divisible]]
[[Indivisible]]
[[Visible]]
[[Invisible]]
[[Polarity]]

## Reads

Structural carrier becomes recognisable where a small relation-word can be shown to carry a specific relational role into a later compound without becoming an order root itself.

## Carries

Nothing at class grain. Nested terms are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.','Structural Carrier Structural carrier names the class of primitive carriers that carry relation into later structural compounds through small relation words. Where operation carriers make any condition readable across the system, structural carriers transmit specific relational roles — placement, direction, and polarity — into language and downstream compounds. A structural carrier does not make structure; it preserves and transmits relations already available to read. Places Structural Carrier places the class of primitive carriers that transmit specific relational roles into later compounds. Holds Structural Carrier is held by Primitive Carrier and Read. Pairs Structural Carrier pairs with Operation Carrier. Operation carriers make any condition readable; structural carriers preserve and transmit specific relational roles. Traces Primitive Carrier Read Nests Structural Carrier nests the small relation words that carry placement, direction, and polarity. In Out Not Divisible Indivisible Visible Invisible Polarity Reads Structural carrier becomes recognisable where a small relation word can be shown to carry a specific relational role into a later compound without becoming an order root itself. Carries Nothing at class grain. Nested terms are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.','Structural Carrier Structural carrier names the class of primitive carriers that carry relation into later structural compounds through small relation words. Where operation carriers make any…','stable','rooted',0,'first','class',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.operation-carrier","first.primitive-carrier","first.read"]','{"holds":["first.primitive-carrier","first.read"],"traces":["first.primitive-carrier","first.read"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.operation-carrier"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',184,'sha256:348d0468bab1ce0f45e98fc5f81ba27452c7f3c31f9a1556024e4366049c496f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.tact','Tact','tact','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Boundary Conditions/Tact.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/tact.html','# Tact

Tact names the handling side of clean relation. Tact is not politeness in the shallow sense; it is the condition by which relation can meet, touch, or be handled without collapsing into interference, pressure, collision, or harm.

Tact opens [[Contact]]. Contact is not yet coupling; it is the meeting condition itself. Tact is the prior handling condition that lets contact remain clean enough to be carried further.

## Places

Tact places the handling side of clean relation: where relation can meet or be touched without collapsing into interference, pressure, or harm.

## Holds

Tact is held by [[Clean]] and [[Relation]]. Relation must remain free from residue or drift before contact can be handled without distortion.

## Pairs

Tact pairs with [[Clear]]. Tact governs handling at contact; clear governs readability.

## Traces

- [[Relation]]
- [[Clean]]

## Nests

Tact nests before [[Contact]]. It is the handling condition by which meeting can occur without requiring coupling or becoming interference.

## Reads

Tact becomes recognisable where contact is approached with enough restraint, placement, and handling that relation is not damaged by the touch.

## Carries

