INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.transfer','Transfer','transfer','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Resolution Conditions/Transfer.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/transfer.html','# Transfer

Transfer names resolution where bearing passes strain, load, or support into another condition. Transfer is not carrying in the second-order sense; it is the first-order determination that what was borne is now borne elsewhere.

## Places

Transfer places resolution where bearing passes strain, load, or support into another condition.

## Holds

Transfer is held by [[Resolution]], [[Bearing]], and [[Boundary]]. What was borne must be determined enough to pass across a boundary.

## Pairs

Transfer pairs with [[Absorb]]: transfer names the moving of a resolved condition across a boundary to another carrier; absorb names the taking in of a condition under strain and bearing. Each requires the other to be locatable: transfer is only readable against the possibility of something absorbing what is moved; absorb is only readable against the possibility of what is received having been transferred or generated elsewhere.

## Traces

- [[Resolution]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Transfer nests under first-order resolution. It can open carrying, but it is not carrying in the second-order sense.

## Reads

Transfer becomes recognisable where bearing resolves by passing strain or support across a boundary into another condition.

## Carries','Transfer Transfer names resolution where bearing passes strain, load, or support into another condition. Transfer is not carrying in the second order sense; it is the first order determination that what was borne is now borne elsewhere. Places Transfer places resolution where bearing passes strain, load, or support into another condition. Holds Transfer is held by Resolution, Bearing, and Boundary. What was borne must be determined enough to pass across a boundary. Pairs Transfer pairs with Absorb: transfer names the moving of a resolved condition across a boundary to another carrier; absorb names the taking in of a condition under strain and bearing. Each requires the other to be locatable: transfer is only readable against the possibility of something absorbing what is moved; absorb is only readable against the possibility of what is received having been transferred or generated elsewhere. Traces Resolution Bearing Boundary Nests Transfer nests under first order resolution. It can open carrying, but it is not carrying in the second order sense. Reads Transfer becomes recognisable where bearing resolves by passing strain or support across a boundary into another condition. Carries','Transfer Transfer names resolution where bearing passes strain, load, or support into another condition. Transfer is not carrying in the second order sense; it is the first order determination…','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.absorb","first.bearing","first.boundary","first.resolution"]','{"holds":["first.resolution","first.bearing","first.boundary"],"traces":["first.resolution","first.bearing","first.boundary"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.absorb"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',184,'sha256:5ed2152280ec6b096c463dec6315b00c9c16705d5ef0714ba9e112f1f87393e5','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.visible','Visible','visible','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Carrier Mechanics/Visible.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/visible.html','# Visible

Visible carries presented readability: distinction presented to read. Truth, explanation, or understanding can involve visibility, but visible itself carries presentation. What is visible may remain unresolved; presentation is not interpretation.

## Places

Visible places presented readability.

## Holds

Visible is held by [[Apparent]]. A distinction must be apparent before it can be presented to read.

## Pairs

Visible pairs with [[Invisible]]. Visible presents readability; Invisible can carry non-presented readability without becoming absent or hidden.

## Traces

- [[Apparent]]

## Nests

Visible nests under apparent presentation. It can support truth, explanation, and understanding without being identical with them.

## Reads

Visible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as presented rather than hidden, absent, or unavailable.

## Carries

- [[Visibility]]
- [[Surface]]','Visible Visible carries presented readability: distinction presented to read. Truth, explanation, or understanding can involve visibility, but visible itself carries presentation. What is visible may remain unresolved; presentation is not interpretation. Places Visible places presented readability. Holds Visible is held by Apparent. A distinction must be apparent before it can be presented to read. Pairs Visible pairs with Invisible. Visible presents readability; Invisible can carry non presented readability without becoming absent or hidden. Traces Apparent Nests Visible nests under apparent presentation. It can support truth, explanation, and understanding without being identical with them. Reads Visible becomes recognisable where distinction is read as presented rather than hidden, absent, or unavailable. Carries Visibility Surface','Visible Visible carries presented readability: distinction presented to read. Truth, explanation, or understanding can involve visibility, but visible itself carries presentation.','stable','rooted',0,'first','carrier',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.apparent","first.invisible","second.surface","second.visibility"]','{"holds":["first.apparent"],"traces":["first.apparent"],"carries":["second.visibility","second.surface"],"pairs":["first.invisible"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',112,'sha256:54bee3ae8db147bf7542458a148ee9ca955683651fc7b9378be5a62e5221e18f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('first.yield','Yield','yield','Reality_Mechanics/1_First/Resolution Conditions/Yield.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/yield.html','# Yield

Yield names resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing. Yield is not stable hold and not total collapse; it is a determined give in the condition that bears.

## Places

Yield places resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing.

## Holds

Yield is held by [[Resolution]] and [[Bearing]]. Bearing must be determined under strain before give can be read.

## Pairs

Yield pairs with [[Shift]]: yield names resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing; shift names resolution where bearing relocates orientation without yielding. Each requires the other to be locatable — yield is only readable against the possibility of shifting; shift is only readable against the possibility of yielding.

## Traces

- [[Resolution]]
- [[Bearing]]

## Nests

Yield nests under first-order resolution as partial give rather than stable hold or total failure.

## Reads

Yield becomes recognisable where bearing resolves as deformation, concession, or give while some support or continuity remains.

## Carries','Yield Yield names resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing. Yield is not stable hold and not total collapse; it is a determined give in the condition that bears. Places Yield places resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing. Holds Yield is held by Resolution and Bearing. Bearing must be determined under strain before give can be read. Pairs Yield pairs with Shift: yield names resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing; shift names resolution where bearing relocates orientation without yielding. Each requires the other to be locatable — yield is only readable against the possibility of shifting; shift is only readable against the possibility of yielding. Traces Resolution Bearing Nests Yield nests under first order resolution as partial give rather than stable hold or total failure. Reads Yield becomes recognisable where bearing resolves as deformation, concession, or give while some support or continuity remains. Carries','Yield Yield names resolution where bearing gives under strain without fully failing. Yield is not stable hold and not total collapse; it is a determined give in the condition that bears.','stable','rooted',0,'first','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.resolution","first.shift"]','{"holds":["first.resolution","first.bearing"],"traces":["first.resolution","first.bearing"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.shift"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',152,'sha256:2e72db8f7f6b6c441fb37468ceea4f513e3b8687d4699f343fc1ce9396a56790','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.degenerate','Degenerate','degenerate','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Degenerate.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/degenerate.html','# Degenerate

Degenerate names the structural condition where carrying continues while the generative trace is lost. What was generated from a prior source carries on — its form persists, its downstream effects continue — but the dependency trace back to what generated it has been dropped. The generated instance has become a local primitive: treated as if it had no generative origin, as if it were the source.

Degenerate is a specific form of [[Structural Disorder]]: the structure may still function, but it carries as if its source no longer matters. What was generated begins behaving as generator.

This is why [[Practice]] cannot be once-only. Every carried term, pattern, or procedure risks letting its trace become formal rather than live.

## Places

Degenerate places the structural condition where carrying continues while the generative trace is lost — where a term, pattern, or practice carries forward without remaining answerable to the source that generated it.

## Holds

Degenerate is held by [[Generic]] and [[Structural Disorder]]. A generative source must be operative before it can be lost, and loss of dependency readability must be nameable before its specific form as generative trace loss can be placed.

## Pairs

Degenerate pairs with [[Regenerate]]. Degenerate names carrying that has lost its generative trace; Regenerate names the return to generative conditions from within that loss. Each requires the other: Degenerate is only nameable against the possibility of returning from it; Regenerate is only nameable against the condition it addresses.

## Traces

- [[Generic]]
- [[Structural Disorder]]

## Nests

Degenerate nests within Structural Disorder as the mode where carrying continues while the generative trace drops.

## Reads

Degenerate becomes recognisable where a term, pattern, or practice carries forward while the trace to its generative origin has been lost — where what was an instance has become a local primitive, and where the form of the source persists without the source itself being held.

The response is [[Regenerate]]: retrace through the carrying, recover the generative source, and carry forward with the origin held rather than dropped.

## Carries

- [[Source Drift]]
- [[Thin Carrying]]
- [[Destination-Led Carrying]]
