INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.generic','Generic','generic','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Generic.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/generic.html','# Generic

Generic names the structural condition through which a pattern generates instances of itself. It is the originating source from which instances arise, operative before any instance appears.

[[Kind]] names recurrent form recognisable across instances. Generic names the prior condition: the pattern already operative before those instances appear.

Generic operates throughout the spine: each order generates instances without becoming identical with them. The danger specific to Generic is [[Degenerate]]: what was generated begins to carry as if it were the source.

## Places

Generic places the structural condition through which a pattern generates instances of itself — the originating source from which instances arise, operative before any instance appears.

## Holds

Generic is held by [[Natural Order]] and [[Root Order]]. The dependency order must hold and natural order must be operative before a structural pattern can generate instances from a prior source.

## Pairs

Generic pairs with [[Emergent]]. Generic names what generates instances from a prior structural source; Emergent names what arises from conditions without a prior generative source. Each requires the other to be locatable: a generative source is only nameable against what arises without one; emergence is only nameable against what comes from a prior source.

## Traces

- [[Natural Order]]
- [[Root Order]]

## Nests

Generic nests at Ground as the originating condition through which structural patterns generate their instances — including the dependency patterns that each order instantiates from the prior order.

## Reads

Generic becomes recognisable where what appears can be traced to an originating structural source rather than arising from the interaction of conditions.

## Carries

- [[Kind]]
- [[Degenerate]]
- [[Regenerate]]','Generic Generic names the structural condition through which a pattern generates instances of itself. It is the originating source from which instances arise, operative before any instance appears. Kind names recurrent form recognisable across instances. Generic names the prior condition: the pattern already operative before those instances appear. Generic operates throughout the spine: each order generates instances without becoming identical with them. The danger specific to Generic is Degenerate: what was generated begins to carry as if it were the source. Places Generic places the structural condition through which a pattern generates instances of itself — the originating source from which instances arise, operative before any instance appears. Holds Generic is held by Natural Order and Root Order. The dependency order must hold and natural order must be operative before a structural pattern can generate instances from a prior source. Pairs Generic pairs with Emergent. Generic names what generates instances from a prior structural source; Emergent names what arises from conditions without a prior generative source. Each requires the other to be locatable: a generative source is only nameable against what arises without one; emergence is only nameable against what comes from a prior source. Traces Natural Order Root Order Nests Generic nests at Ground as the originating condition through which structural patterns generate their instances — including the dependency patterns that each order instantiates from the prior order. Reads Generic becomes recognisable where what appears can be traced to an originating structural source rather than arising from the interaction of conditions. Carries Kind Degenerate Regenerate','Generic Generic names the structural condition through which a pattern generates instances of itself. It is the originating source from which instances arise, operative before any instance appears.','stable','rooted',0,'ground','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.degenerate","ground.emergent","ground.natural-order","ground.regenerate","ground.root-order","second.kind"]','{"holds":["ground.natural-order","ground.root-order"],"traces":["ground.natural-order","ground.root-order"],"carries":["second.kind","ground.degenerate","ground.regenerate"],"pairs":["ground.emergent"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',256,'sha256:48e4a53ed23bdcd4b44861d0cab5b69dd4c805e5eac41c8d4afa28779acddbbe','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.ground','Ground','ground','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Ground.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/ground.html','# Ground

Ground names what Reality Mechanics acknowledges but does not derive. It is the source-limit the Atlas remains answerable to.

[[Relation]] is the primitive where the dependency spine begins. Ground names what holds prior to that beginning without being traced to. Ground holds [[Seed]], and Seed holds Relation before the dependency spine begins, without making Relation produced by a prior term. Ground is not a term inside the dependency spine. It is the source-limit the first-order boundary protects: the acknowledged-prior that keeps Relation primitive within the system without claiming to be the origin of everything. Ground is the [[Terminal]] below — the read-stop where digging downward ends while what is acknowledged continues underived.

Ground prevents the system from becoming self-sealing. It gives Reality Mechanics a place to remain answerable without claiming to produce what answers it.

## Places

Ground places the acknowledged-prior of [[Reality Mechanics]]. It sits before the dependency spine and marks the lower source-limit and read-stop of the system.

## Holds

Ground is held by nothing within the system — acknowledged but not derived. From that position it holds the first distinction between what is acknowledged and what is derived, and holds [[Seed]] as the Ground-level relation-to-Ground through which [[Relation]] is held before traceable order begins.

## Pairs

Ground pairs with [[Relation]]: Ground is acknowledged but not derived; Relation is the primitive condition from which the Atlas begins tracing. Ground also pairs with [[Seed]]: Seed names Ground as relation-to-Ground becomes carryable within the loop — what the highest formation traces back to is the same source condition that held the first relation.

## Traces

Ground is prior to the system''s first-order boundary. It is acknowledged but not defined within the system.

## Nests

Ground nests below [[Root Order]] and [[Natural Order]] as the source-limit that lets the Atlas participate in what it does not claim to originate.

## Reads

Ground becomes recognisable where the system participates in something prior rather than engineering itself from nothing — where its terms can be checked against what they did not generate.

## Carries

- [[Seed]]
- [[Natural Order]]
- [[Root Order]]
- [[Opacity]]
- [[Reality Mechanics]]
