INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.groundedness','Groundedness','groundedness','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Groundedness.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/groundedness.html','# Groundedness

Groundedness names the condition of remaining answerable to what holds. A term, read, path, or practice is grounded where it can be traced back through its conditions without losing contact with the dependency that makes it readable.

In the Atlas, Groundedness is also the root-contact check on a note: grounded where the note remains answerable to what holds it; ungrounded where its traces still require checking. This is not the same as permission to enter the Atlas. A placed growth may be working, planted, or tending while its groundedness is still being checked.

## Places

Groundedness places the condition of remaining answerable to what holds. It names where dependency contact is maintained — where a term or read has not drifted from what makes it readable.

## Holds

Groundedness is held by [[Root Order]]. Dependency arrangement must hold before remaining answerable to it can be named.

## Pairs

Groundedness pairs with [[Structural Disorder]]. Groundedness names maintained dependency contact; Structural Disorder names its loss.

## Traces

- [[Root Order]]

## Nests

Groundedness nests wherever a read remains answerable to what holds it, from root terms through later fields and practices.

## Reads

Groundedness becomes recognisable where a term, read, path, or practice remains answerable to the conditions that hold it.

## Carries

- [[Root Resilience]]
- [[Terms and Conditions]]
- [[Recarry]]','Groundedness Groundedness names the condition of remaining answerable to what holds. A term, read, path, or practice is grounded where it can be traced back through its conditions without losing contact with the dependency that makes it readable. In the Atlas, Groundedness is also the root contact check on a note: grounded where the note remains answerable to what holds it; ungrounded where its traces still require checking. This is not the same as permission to enter the Atlas. A placed growth may be working, planted, or tending while its groundedness is still being checked. Places Groundedness places the condition of remaining answerable to what holds. It names where dependency contact is maintained — where a term or read has not drifted from what makes it readable. Holds Groundedness is held by Root Order. Dependency arrangement must hold before remaining answerable to it can be named. Pairs Groundedness pairs with Structural Disorder. Groundedness names maintained dependency contact; Structural Disorder names its loss. Traces Root Order Nests Groundedness nests wherever a read remains answerable to what holds it, from root terms through later fields and practices. Reads Groundedness becomes recognisable where a term, read, path, or practice remains answerable to the conditions that hold it. Carries Root Resilience Terms and Conditions Recarry','Groundedness Groundedness names the condition of remaining answerable to what holds. A term, read, path, or practice is grounded where it can be traced back through its conditions without losing…','stable','rooted',0,'ground','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.root-order","ground.structural-disorder","practice.root-resilience","practice.terms-and-conditions","second.recarry"]','{"holds":["ground.root-order"],"traces":["ground.root-order"],"carries":["practice.root-resilience","practice.terms-and-conditions","second.recarry"],"pairs":["ground.structural-disorder"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',211,'sha256:b8380f003f8586d17fb867191e632ebb13d9c8a57fb78c3dcc5903e3925e1fb3','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.invariant','Invariant','invariant','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Invariant.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/invariant.html','# Invariant

Invariant names what remains stable across traversal, revision, application, or scale. Where dependency order names structural precedence, an invariant names what that precedence preserves — the condition that continues to hold despite changes in how the system is read, applied, or extended. An invariant is not permanent or immobile; it names preserved structure.

[[Bounded Asymmetry]] is the structural invariant of Reality Mechanics: it holds across domain, scale, and application.

[[Clean]], [[Union]], [[Communion]], and [[Legion]] are invisible invariants at their orders. They name what must already hold before the lateral pair at that order can split.

## Places

Invariant places what remains stable across traversal, revision, application, or scale.

## Holds

Invariant is held by [[Root Order]].

## Pairs

Invariant pairs with [[Primitive]]. Primitive names what cannot be reduced without losing the read; Invariant names what remains unchanged across variation.

## Traces

- [[Root Order]]

## Nests

Invariant nests across variation: it holds where change occurs without altering the condition being tested.

## Reads

Invariant becomes recognisable where variation occurs while a condition remains unchanged enough to keep the read stable. It lets change be tested without losing what must still hold.

## Carries

- [[Bounded Asymmetry]]
- [[Root System]]
- [[Translation Invariance]]','Invariant Invariant names what remains stable across traversal, revision, application, or scale. Where dependency order names structural precedence, an invariant names what that precedence preserves — the condition that continues to hold despite changes in how the system is read, applied, or extended. An invariant is not permanent or immobile; it names preserved structure. Bounded Asymmetry is the structural invariant of Reality Mechanics: it holds across domain, scale, and application. Clean, Union, Communion, and Legion are invisible invariants at their orders. They name what must already hold before the lateral pair at that order can split. Places Invariant places what remains stable across traversal, revision, application, or scale. Holds Invariant is held by Root Order. Pairs Invariant pairs with Primitive. Primitive names what cannot be reduced without losing the read; Invariant names what remains unchanged across variation. Traces Root Order Nests Invariant nests across variation: it holds where change occurs without altering the condition being tested. Reads Invariant becomes recognisable where variation occurs while a condition remains unchanged enough to keep the read stable. It lets change be tested without losing what must still hold. Carries Bounded Asymmetry Root System Translation Invariance','Invariant Invariant names what remains stable across traversal, revision, application, or scale. Where dependency order names structural precedence, an invariant names what that precedence…','stable','rooted',0,'ground','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bounded-asymmetry","ground.primitive","ground.root-order","practice.root-system","practice.translation-invariance"]','{"holds":["ground.root-order"],"traces":["ground.root-order"],"carries":["first.bounded-asymmetry","practice.root-system","practice.translation-invariance"],"pairs":["ground.primitive"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',192,'sha256:01b799aef1f019f06971ae0fe76aea18df41ebfc9b51cbd227f87f5cb3ccdf94','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.label','Label','label','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Label.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/label.html','# Label

Label names a name that marks without carrying traceable conditions. Where a [[Term]] gives relation a placed opening that can be entered, traced, read, and carried forward, a Label marks without that dependency structure: it names something without carrying what it depends on, what it opens, or what becomes readable through it.

A label is not a failed term. Proper names, placeholders, tags, and identifiers operate legitimately as labels — marking a point without needing to carry conditions. The distinction is structural: a label marks; a term carries.

## Places

Label places a name that marks without carrying traceable conditions.

## Holds

Label is held by [[Root Order]]. Dependency arrangement must hold before naming of any kind can occur, including marking without conditions.

## Pairs

[[Term]] — Label marks without carrying traceable conditions; Term names with dependency, opening, and carried relation travelling together. Each requires the other to be locatable: the distinction between marking and carrying can only hold where both conditions are present as possibilities.

## Traces

- [[Root Order]]

## Nests

Label nests wherever a name functions as a marker rather than as a carryable length of relation.

## Reads

Label becomes recognisable where a name marks something without the conditions through which it could be traced, entered, or carried forward. A word operating as a label may later become a term if conditions are placed under it — or may remain a label where marking without carrying is sufficient.

A label can also mark a current [[Member|member-read]] for communication, coordination, or action. In that use, the label points to the placed read; it does not become the member''s source.

## Carries

Label carries no conditions forward: it marks without opening what it names.','Label Label names a name that marks without carrying traceable conditions. Where a Term gives relation a placed opening that can be entered, traced, read, and carried forward, a Label marks without that dependency structure: it names something without carrying what it depends on, what it opens, or what becomes readable through it. A label is not a failed term. Proper names, placeholders, tags, and identifiers operate legitimately as labels — marking a point without needing to carry conditions. The distinction is structural: a label marks; a term carries. Places Label places a name that marks without carrying traceable conditions. Holds Label is held by Root Order. Dependency arrangement must hold before naming of any kind can occur, including marking without conditions. Pairs Term — Label marks without carrying traceable conditions; Term names with dependency, opening, and carried relation travelling together. Each requires the other to be locatable: the distinction between marking and carrying can only hold where both conditions are present as possibilities. Traces Root Order Nests Label nests wherever a name functions as a marker rather than as a carryable length of relation. Reads Label becomes recognisable where a name marks something without the conditions through which it could be traced, entered, or carried forward. A word operating as a label may later become a term if conditions are placed under it — or may remain a label where marking without carrying is sufficient. A label can also mark a current Member for communication, coordination, or action. In that use, the label points to the placed read; it does not become the member''s source. Carries Label carries no conditions forward: it marks without opening what it names.','Label Label names a name that marks without carrying traceable conditions. Where a Term gives relation a placed opening that can be entered, traced, read, and carried forward, a Label marks…','stable','rooted',0,'ground','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.root-order","ground.term"]','{"holds":["ground.root-order"],"traces":["ground.root-order"],"carries":[],"pairs":["ground.term"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',279,'sha256:b9bd9bfd10fdca8c4fa4ff2a8fcabf6a6460778c54d271f3a6539310d2ad6f2c','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.natural-order','Natural Order','natural-order','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Natural Order.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/natural-order.html','# Natural Order

Natural Order names the order already available within the governing arrangement: dependency readability that holds without being imposed by the read that enters it. Moral, cultural, preferred, or enforced order may participate in Natural Order, but they do not define it. Organic and Engineered are both modes of participation within Natural Order; neither is its opposite.

Natural Order does not require entry by read in order to hold. A read may enter Natural Order, trace it, name it, measure it, act within it, or alter the relation it joins, but the read does not create the order it enters.

## Places

Natural Order places the order already available within the governing arrangement — dependency readability that holds without being imposed by the read that enters it. It names availability rather than imposition.

## Holds

Natural Order is held by [[Root Order]].

## Pairs

Natural Order pairs with [[Dependency Order]]. Natural Order names the order available within the governing arrangement without imposition; Dependency Order names the structural precedence within that same arrangement. Each requires the other: available order is only readable against what must structurally precede it; structural precedence is only nameable against the order it orders.

## Traces

- [[Root Order]]
- [[Ground]]

## Nests

Natural Order nests wherever order holds through available relation rather than continual external correction.

## Reads

Natural Order becomes recognisable where recurring conditions continue to preserve the same dependency structure without requiring continual external correction. It is order holding because it is available, not because it is imposed.

Entering the order as a read is required for the Atlas to trace it, not for the order to exist. Once entered, a read becomes participation and must be checked for whether it remains traceable and compatible with the relation it affects.

## Carries

- [[Participation]]
- [[Organic]]
- [[Generic]]
- [[Emergent]]
- [[Natural World]]
- [[Field of Participation]]
