ield','Natural Order Natural Order names the order already available within the governing arrangement: dependency readability that holds without being imposed by the read that enters it. Moral, cultural,…','stable','rooted',0,'ground','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.dependency-order","ground.emergent","ground.generic","ground.ground","ground.root-order","second.participation","third.field-of-participation","third.natural-world","third.organic","third.organic-field"]','{"holds":["ground.root-order"],"traces":["ground.root-order","ground.ground"],"carries":["second.participation","third.organic","ground.generic","ground.emergent","third.natural-world","third.field-of-participation","third.organic-field"],"pairs":["ground.dependency-order"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',301,'sha256:d56920b389abb090d1c1750969c440203a005d1b578abafaf0ce94c1aa378c47','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('ground.passage-condition','Passage Condition','passage-condition','Reality_Mechanics/0_Ground/Passage Condition.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/passage-condition.html','# Passage Condition

Passage Condition names a structural role: a term whose function is to regulate whether order can pass, hold, close, or remain available across a boundary or scope. A passage condition is not an order root — it does not make an order emerge by itself. It may be highly connected because many later terms must pass through it, but its role is regulative rather than root-emergent. High linkage alone does not make a term a root.

[[Boundary]] and [[Availability]] are the primary passage conditions of the first order. [[Allow]], [[Compatibility]], [[Scope]], and [[Closure Scope]] extend this role into later orders.

## Places

Passage Condition places a structural role within Root Order — the regulative function that determines whether carrying can continue, close locally, be allowed through, or remain available across a boundary or scope.

## Holds

Passage Condition is held by [[Root Order]]. The governing arrangement must hold before regulative roles within it can be named.

## Pairs

Passage Condition pairs with root conditions. Where a root condition lets order emerge upward, a passage condition regulates whether that order can pass or remain available across a scope.

## Traces

- [[Root Order]]
## Nests

Passage Condition nests across orders wherever a boundary or scope must regulate continuation, closure, allowance, or availability.

## Reads

Passage Condition becomes recognisable where a term does not make the next order emerge, but determines whether existing carrying can continue, remain supportable, close locally, be allowed through, or become available inside a given scope.

## Carries
