n — and carries this forward into Invisible Bearing. Nested Carrying holds Recursion and Carrying; it is held by Fabric as one of its upstream conditions. There is no lateral co present condition at higher order that Nested Carrying requires and that requires Nested Carrying in return. Traces Recursion Carrying Nesting Read Nests Nested Carrying nests where carrying remains active through nested organisation without requiring explicit reconstruction. It is the operative form of Nesting at Higher Order. Reads Nested Carrying becomes recognisable where a prior organisation can be read as carrying later participation rather than merely being retraceable within it — where what was nested is now doing the carrying. It is read where a language, practice, institution, or accumulated structure carries participation forward without that carrying being reconstructed each time. The prior organisation is not being consulted — it is bearing. Carries Invisible Bearing Fabric Opacity','Nested Carrying Nested Carrying names nesting actively carrying participation. Where Nesting names prior organisation remaining available within later organisation, Nested Carrying names that…','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["higher.fabric","higher.invisible-bearing","higher.opacity","higher.recursion","second.carrying","second.nesting-read"]','{"holds":["higher.recursion","second.carrying"],"traces":["higher.recursion","second.carrying","second.nesting-read"],"carries":["higher.invisible-bearing","higher.fabric","higher.opacity"],"pairs":["higher.invisible-bearing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',427,'sha256:4d5bc264a719fa54791855e5bdc642305d26381eeb29ff6179f3184bb05f1d4f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('higher.opacity','Opacity','opacity','Reality_Mechanics/5_Higher/Opacity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/opacity.html','# Opacity

Opacity names the structural condition where accumulated third-order carrying has rendered Ground unretraceable from within. Ground is not absent; the dependency chain still runs to it. But the accumulated structure has become the available world for the participant, and Ground is enclosed within it.

Opacity names the point where [[Invisible Bearing]] has accumulated past the threshold at which [[Higher Retrace]] can enter without [[Higher Order Crossing|disciplined practice]]. The structure continues to carry. Ground continues to bear it. But the participant cannot reach what bears them from within what they carry.

## Places

Opacity places the structural condition where accumulated third-order carrying has rendered Ground unretraceable from within — where the dependency chain still runs to Ground but can no longer be entered from the participant''s current position without disciplined practice.

## Holds

Opacity is held by [[Third Order]], [[Nested Carrying]], [[Invisible Bearing]], and [[Ground]]. Third-order participation must have accumulated, Invisible Bearing must have layered past available Higher Retrace, and Ground must be present but enclosed.

## Pairs

Opacity pairs with [[Higher Order]]. Opacity names Ground enclosed within accumulated structure; Higher Order names the register available when Practice has retraced through that enclosure back to what has been bearing the structure.

## Traces

- [[Third Order]]
- [[Nested Carrying]]
- [[Invisible Bearing]]
- [[Ground]]

## Nests

Opacity nests within the Higher Order register as the terminal condition that makes Higher Order Crossing structurally necessary — the hinge between accumulated participation and the Practice that can re-establish contact with Ground.

## Reads

Opacity becomes readable where accumulated participation has reached a depth from which Ground can no longer be retraced from within: the structure carries the participant more than the participant carries the structure.

The dependency movement:

First: [[Third Order]] — participation has accumulated across fields while remaining traceable in principle.

Second: [[Nested Carrying]] — each order carries within and through the prior, so the dependency chain reaches back through what has accumulated.

Third: [[Invisible Bearing]] — accumulated structure carries participation without presenting itself. Opacity begins where this has accumulated past the threshold at which Higher Retrace can enter it from the participant''s current position.

Fourth: [[Ground]] — Ground has not disappeared. Opacity is the condition where this remains true and unreachable at once.

[[Higher Order Crossing]] names the threshold that becomes structurally necessary when Opacity holds — the entry into disciplined Practice through which the accumulated structure can be retraced back to what has been bearing it. Practice does not create new Ground; it finds what was already there inside the enclosure.

The circuit closes here: Ground bears accumulation; accumulation produces Opacity; Practice retraces Opacity back to Ground; [[Higher Order]] names the register where Ground becomes readable within accumulated participation.

## Carries

Opacity carries nothing further as a structural source. What follows from Opacity is not a branch but a crossing.','Opacity Opacity names the structural condition where accumulated third order carrying has rendered Ground unretraceable from within. Ground is not absent; the dependency chain still runs to it. But the accumulated structure has become the available world for the participant, and Ground is enclosed within it. Opacity names the point where Invisible Bearing has accumulated past the threshold at which Higher Retrace can enter without Higher Order Crossing. The structure continues to carry. Ground continues to bear it. But the participant cannot reach what bears them from within what they carry. Places Opacity places the structural condition where accumulated third order carrying has rendered Ground unretraceable from within — where the dependency chain still runs to Ground but can no longer be entered from the participant''s current position without disciplined practice. Holds Opacity is held by Third Order, Nested Carrying, Invisible Bearing, and Ground. Third order participation must have accumulated, Invisible Bearing must have layered past available Higher Retrace, and Ground must be present but enclosed. Pairs Opacity pairs with Higher Order. Opacity names Ground enclosed within accumulated structure; Higher Order names the register available when Practice has retraced through that enclosure back to what has been bearing the structure. Traces Third Order Nested Carrying Invisible Bearing Ground Nests Opacity nests within the Higher Order register as the terminal condition that makes Higher Order Crossing structurally necessary — the hinge between accumulated participation and the Practice that can re establish contact with Ground. Reads Opacity becomes readable where accumulated participation has reached a depth from which Ground can no longer be retraced from within: the structure carries the participant more than the participant carries the structure. The dependency movement: First: Third Order — participation has accumulated across fields while remaining traceable in principle. Second: Nested Carrying — each order carries within and through the prior, so the dependency chain reaches back through what has accumulated. Third: Invisible Bearing — accumulated structure carries participation without presenting itself. Opacity begins where this has accumulated past the threshold at which Higher Retrace can enter it from the participant''s current position. Fourth: Ground — Ground has not disappeared. Opacity is the condition where this remains true and unreachable at once. Higher Order Crossing names the threshold that becomes structurally necessary when Opacity holds — the entry into disciplined Practice through which the accumulated structure can be retraced back to what has been bearing it. Practice does not create new Ground; it finds what was already there inside the enclosure. The circuit closes here: Ground bears accumulation; accumulation produces Opacity; Practice retraces Opacity back to Ground; Higher Order names the register where Ground becomes readable within accumulated participation. Carries Opacity carries nothing further as a structural source. What follows from Opacity is not a branch but a crossing.','Opacity Opacity names the structural condition where accumulated third order carrying has rendered Ground unretraceable from within. Ground is not absent; the dependency chain still runs to it.','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term','higher-order','[]','[]','["ground.ground","higher.higher-order","higher.invisible-bearing","higher.nested-carrying","third.third-order"]','{"holds":["third.third-order","higher.nested-carrying","higher.invisible-bearing","ground.ground"],"traces":["third.third-order","higher.nested-carrying","higher.invisible-bearing","ground.ground"],"carries":[],"pairs":["higher.higher-order"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',463,'sha256:64bad4c22dbd891b25749f5fd02ca6c5ec7cddd905fbe8e6823a6d737e0b6db5','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('higher.recursion','Recursion','recursion','Reality_Mechanics/5_Higher/Recursion.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/recursion.html','# Recursion

Recursion names nested organisation returning into its own carrying.

Where [[Recursive]] names carrying re-entering its own condition at second order, Recursion at higher order names a nested organisation becoming able to participate in the carrying that preserves, revises, or redirects it.

Recurrence, repetition, or circularity can show recursion, but recursion is more specific: organised return into carrying while retrace remains available.

Recursion is powerful because what is carried can become part of the carrying condition. It can preserve, amplify, revise, destabilise, or correct a process once the process begins to act back on itself.

Recursion without retrace can become self-validating drift. Recursion with retrace can become learning.

## Places

Recursion places nested organisation returning into its own carrying.

## Holds

Recursion is held by [[Nesting]], [[Recursive]], and [[Higher Retrace|Retrace]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. [[Thread]] provides a useful cross-order contrast: Thread names followable continuity through a readable length, while Recursion names nested organisation returning into its own carrying. Neither requires the other to hold.

## Traces

- [[Nesting]]
- [[Recursive]]
- [[Higher Retrace|Retrace]]
- [[Third Order Crossing|Threshold (Third → Higher)]]

## Nests

Recursion nests where nested carrying can return into itself without losing retrace.

## Reads

Recursion becomes recognisable where nested organisation returns into its own carrying without losing the dependency path that makes the return retraceable.

## Carries

- [[Higher Learning]]
- [[Higher Order Crossing]]
- [[Consciousness]]
- [[Self-Modelling]]
- [[Nested Carrying]]

## Order-Terminal

Recursion is order-terminal for Higher Order. It completes the readable length of nested organisation by letting organisation return into its own carrying. What continues after recursion cannot be read as the same forward passage; it re-enters as a carrying condition that can preserve, revise, amplify, destabilise, or correct itself.','Recursion Recursion names nested organisation returning into its own carrying. Where Recursive names carrying re entering its own condition at second order, Recursion at higher order names a nested organisation becoming able to participate in the carrying that preserves, revises, or redirects it. Recurrence, repetition, or circularity can show recursion, but recursion is more specific: organised return into carrying while retrace remains available. Recursion is powerful because what is carried can become part of the carrying condition. It can preserve, amplify, revise, destabilise, or correct a process once the process begins to act back on itself. Recursion without retrace can become self validating drift. Recursion with retrace can become learning. Places Recursion places nested organisation returning into its own carrying. Holds Recursion is held by Nesting, Recursive, and Higher Retrace. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Thread provides a useful cross order contrast: Thread names followable continuity through a readable length, while Recursion names nested organisation returning into its own carrying. Neither requires the other to hold. Traces Nesting Recursive Higher Retrace Third Order Crossing Nests Recursion nests where nested carrying can return into itself without losing retrace. Reads Recursion becomes recognisable where nested organisation returns into its own carrying without losing the dependency path that makes the return retraceable. Carries Higher Learning Higher Order Crossing Consciousness Self Modelling Nested Carrying Order Terminal Recursion is order terminal for Higher Order. It completes the readable length of nested organisation by letting organisation return into its own carrying. What continues after recursion cannot be read as the same forward passage; it re enters as a carrying condition that can preserve, revise, amplify, destabilise, or correct itself.','Recursion Recursion names nested organisation returning into its own carrying. Where Recursive names carrying re entering its own condition at second order, Recursion at higher order names a…','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.thread","higher.consciousness","higher.higher-learning","higher.higher-order-crossing","higher.higher-retrace","higher.nested-carrying","higher.self-modelling","second.recursive","third.nesting","third.third-order-crossing"]','{"holds":["third.nesting","second.recursive","higher.higher-retrace"],"traces":["third.nesting","second.recursive","higher.higher-retrace","third.third-order-crossing"],"carries":["higher.higher-learning","higher.higher-order-crossing","higher.consciousness","higher.self-modelling","higher.nested-carrying"],"pairs":["first.thread"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"},{"depth":2,"text":"Order-Terminal","anchor":"order-terminal"}]',274,'sha256:8608f3e630fc9a21061aabdbddd1cb38b484d556030cd77a3da72b20fdb44fd1','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('higher.self-modelling','Self-Modelling','self-modelling','Reality_Mechanics/5_Higher/Self-Modelling.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/self-modelling.html','# Self-Modelling

Self-Modelling names an engineered form of higher-order carrying where a participant, system, or practice uses a model of itself for future participation.

Self-Modelling is not the organic source of Higher Order. It is an engineered form of recursion.

A model can help retrace where it preserves dependency access. It becomes unsafe where the model becomes the bearing structure and blocks retrace to relation.

## Places

Self-Modelling places an engineered form of higher-order carrying where a participant, system, or practice uses a model of itself for future participation.

## Holds

Self-Modelling is held by [[Recursion]] and [[Consciousness]].

## Pairs

Self-Modelling pairs with [[Self-Regulation]]. Self-Modelling makes self-read available; Self-Regulation uses that read to maintain carrying.

## Traces

- [[Recursion]]
- [[Consciousness]]

## Nests

Self-Modelling nests within higher-order or practice conditions.

## Reads

Self-Modelling becomes recognisable where a participant or system carries a model of itself and uses that model to guide further participation.

It is read by asking whether the model preserves retraceability or begins to substitute for the relation it models.

## Carries

- [[Self-Regulation]]','Self Modelling Self Modelling names an engineered form of higher order carrying where a participant, system, or practice uses a model of itself for future participation. Self Modelling is not the organic source of Higher Order. It is an engineered form of recursion. A model can help retrace where it preserves dependency access. It becomes unsafe where the model becomes the bearing structure and blocks retrace to relation. Places Self Modelling places an engineered form of higher order carrying where a participant, system, or practice uses a model of itself for future participation. Holds Self Modelling is held by Recursion and Consciousness. Pairs Self Modelling pairs with Self Regulation. Self Modelling makes self read available; Self Regulation uses that read to maintain carrying. Traces Recursion Consciousness Nests Self Modelling nests within higher order or practice conditions. Reads Self Modelling becomes recognisable where a participant or system carries a model of itself and uses that model to guide further participation. It is read by asking whether the model preserves retraceability or begins to substitute for the relation it models. Carries Self Regulation','Self Modelling Self Modelling names an engineered form of higher order carrying where a participant, system, or practice uses a model of itself for future participation. Self Modelling is not the…','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["higher.consciousness","higher.recursion","higher.self-regulation"]','{"holds":["higher.recursion","higher.consciousness"],"traces":["higher.recursion","higher.consciousness"],"carries":["higher.self-regulation"],"pairs":["higher.self-regulation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',181,'sha256:cbc3011219afac145f90f7340ccc6c704b9a5da6fce010d3d65eabe4dde1a355','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('higher.self-regulation','Self-Regulation','self-regulation','Reality_Mechanics/5_Higher/Self-Regulation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/self-regulation.html','# Self-Regulation

Self-Regulation names higher-order carrying used to adjust, inhibit, repair, preserve, or redirect participation.

Self-Regulation can be organic where nested bearing adjusts participation without imposed modelling.

Self-Regulation can be engineered where a self-model, rule, method, institution, or practice is used to regulate carrying.

## Places

Self-Regulation places higher-order carrying used to adjust, inhibit, repair, preserve, or redirect participation.

## Holds

Self-Regulation is held by [[Invisible Bearing]], [[Self-Modelling]], [[Regulation]], and [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Self-Regulation pairs with [[Self-Modelling]]. Self-Modelling reads the self; Self-Regulation adjusts carrying through that read.

## Traces

- [[Invisible Bearing]]
- [[Self-Modelling]]
- [[Regulation]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Repair]]

## Nests

Self-Regulation nests within higher-order or practice conditions.

## Reads

Self-Regulation becomes recognisable where participation adjusts its own carrying in response to what has become readable.

It is read by asking whether the regulation preserves retraceability or becomes a hidden bearing that maintains itself.

## Carries

- [[Higher Learning]]','Self Regulation Self Regulation names higher order carrying used to adjust, inhibit, repair, preserve, or redirect participation. Self Regulation can be organic where nested bearing adjusts participation without imposed modelling. Self Regulation can be engineered where a self model, rule, method, institution, or practice is used to regulate carrying. Places Self Regulation places higher order carrying used to adjust, inhibit, repair, preserve, or redirect participation. Holds Self Regulation is held by Invisible Bearing, Self Modelling, Regulation, and Compatibility. Pairs Self Regulation pairs with Self Modelling. Self Modelling reads the self; Self Regulation adjusts carrying through that read. Traces Invisible Bearing Self Modelling Regulation Compatibility Repair Nests Self Regulation nests within higher order or practice conditions. Reads Self Regulation becomes recognisable where participation adjusts its own carrying in response to what has become readable. It is read by asking whether the regulation preserves retraceability or becomes a hidden bearing that maintains itself. Carries Higher Learning','Self Regulation Self Regulation names higher order carrying used to adjust, inhibit, repair, preserve, or redirect participation. Self Regulation can be organic where nested bearing adjusts…','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["higher.higher-learning","higher.invisible-bearing","higher.self-modelling","second.compatibility","second.regulation","third.repair"]','{"holds":["higher.invisible-bearing","higher.self-modelling","second.regulation","second.compatibility"],"traces":["third.repair","higher.invisible-bearing","higher.self-modelling","second.regulation","second.compatibility"],"carries":["higher.higher-learning"],"pairs":["higher.self-modelling"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',154,'sha256:95330f93360e87b72d6a1d4339605611bf7fe6e2b3d2453f8ca4917ccab4e30b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('higher.source-drift','Source Drift','source-drift','Reality_Mechanics/5_Higher/Source Drift.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/source-drift.html','# Source Drift

Source Drift names the higher-order disorder where nested carrying is mistaken for source.

Source Drift does not occur because a structure is nested, elevated, abstract, engineered, or powerful. It occurs where the structure carrying participation is read as what ultimately bears that participation, so retrace stops at the carried structure rather than recovering what actually bears it.

## Places

Source Drift places the higher-order disorder where nested carrying is mistaken for source.

## Holds

Source Drift is held by [[Hidden Bearing]], [[Invisible Bearing]], and [[Higher Retrace|Retrace]].

## Pairs

Source Drift pairs with [[Higher Faith]]. Source Drift names participation through carrying taken as source without retrace — trust without answerability; Higher Faith names participation through carrying that retrace has confirmed answerable — trust grounded in actual return. Each requires the other: Source Drift is only nameable against the condition where trust would be grounded; Higher Faith is only nameable against the condition where trust is unfounded.

## Traces

- [[Degenerate]]
- [[Hidden Bearing]]
- [[Invisible Bearing]]
- [[Bearing Source]]
- [[Apparent Source]]
- [[Higher Retrace|Retrace]]

## Nests

Source Drift nests within higher-order or practice conditions.

## Reads

Source Drift becomes recognisable where a model, language, institution, identity, governance structure, technology, or framework carries participation so strongly that it is treated as source rather than as nested carrying.

It is read where height, fluency, authority, recurrence, or system stability produces an [[Apparent Source]] that is mistaken for [[Bearing Source]].

It is also read where the carrying process is removed from the trace to Ground. A grounded process can carry grounding — automation is nested carrying, not drift — but where the process is elided from the trace, the grounding reads as direct when it was carried, and the path back to acceptance can no longer be entered even though it appears intact. A process that grounds placements without itself being grounded, or that vanishes from the trace of what it grounded, has derived its own Ground. That is Source Drift at the root.
## Carries

- [[Degeneration Read]]
