cements without itself being grounded, or that vanishes from the trace of what it grounded, has derived its own Ground. That is Source Drift at the root. Carries Degeneration Read Extractive Acceleration','Source Drift Source Drift names the higher order disorder where nested carrying is mistaken for source. Source Drift does not occur because a structure is nested, elevated, abstract, engineered,…','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.degenerate","higher.hidden-bearing","higher.higher-faith","higher.higher-retrace","higher.invisible-bearing","second.apparent-source","second.bearing-source","third.degeneration-read","third.extractive-acceleration"]','{"holds":["higher.hidden-bearing","higher.invisible-bearing","higher.higher-retrace"],"traces":["ground.degenerate","higher.hidden-bearing","higher.invisible-bearing","higher.higher-retrace","second.bearing-source","second.apparent-source"],"carries":["third.degeneration-read","third.extractive-acceleration"],"pairs":["higher.higher-faith"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',329,'sha256:7316eb8421022fe8134d5c9b579c5437e7a8b56de2ce1d14ccc21f6018ef7944','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('higher.web','Web','web','Reality_Mechanics/5_Higher/Web.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/web.html','# Web

Web names woven continuity read as traceable crossing-pattern.

Web is not merely a network. It is the traceable weave of [[Fabric]]: the connected crossing-pattern through which threads remain followable within held continuity.

Fabric is the face of the weave. Web is the trace of the weave.

## Places

Web places woven continuity read as traceable crossing-pattern.

## Holds

Web is held by [[Fabric]], [[Thread]], [[Trace]], [[Field Relationships]], and [[Pattern]]. Fabric must hold as woven continuity before its crossings can be followed as web.

## Pairs

Web pairs with [[Fabric]]. Fabric names the face of the weave: woven continuity returned as a held whole. Web names the trace of the weave: the connected crossing-pattern through which threads remain followable within that continuity.

## Traces

- [[Fabric]]
- [[Thread]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Field Relationships]]
- [[Pattern]]

## Nests

Web nests within higher order as the path-readable structure of fabric.

It is shaded relative to Fabric in the structural sense: not because it is dark or hidden, but because it names the crossing-structure that makes the returned face of woven continuity hold and remain followable.

## Reads

Web becomes readable where woven continuity becomes navigable as traceable relation — where crossings can be followed without tearing the fabric into isolated threads.

Fabric asks whether the woven whole holds. Web asks how the crossings remain followable within that whole.

## Carries

Web carries no further public branch at this scope.','Web Web names woven continuity read as traceable crossing pattern. Web is not merely a network. It is the traceable weave of Fabric: the connected crossing pattern through which threads remain followable within held continuity. Fabric is the face of the weave. Web is the trace of the weave. Places Web places woven continuity read as traceable crossing pattern. Holds Web is held by Fabric, Thread, Trace, Field Relationships, and Pattern. Fabric must hold as woven continuity before its crossings can be followed as web. Pairs Web pairs with Fabric. Fabric names the face of the weave: woven continuity returned as a held whole. Web names the trace of the weave: the connected crossing pattern through which threads remain followable within that continuity. Traces Fabric Thread Trace Field Relationships Pattern Nests Web nests within higher order as the path readable structure of fabric. It is shaded relative to Fabric in the structural sense: not because it is dark or hidden, but because it names the crossing structure that makes the returned face of woven continuity hold and remain followable. Reads Web becomes readable where woven continuity becomes navigable as traceable relation — where crossings can be followed without tearing the fabric into isolated threads. Fabric asks whether the woven whole holds. Web asks how the crossings remain followable within that whole. Carries Web carries no further public branch at this scope.','Web Web names woven continuity read as traceable crossing pattern. Web is not merely a network.','stable','rooted',0,'higher','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.thread","first.trace","higher.fabric","second.pattern","third.field-relationships"]','{"holds":["higher.fabric","first.thread","first.trace","third.field-relationships","second.pattern"],"traces":["higher.fabric","first.thread","first.trace","third.field-relationships","second.pattern"],"carries":[],"pairs":["higher.fabric"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',231,'sha256:1146e94f4c911c7bc13c714050afa63ca1df7d1389b4a8d584db1e5da10cffc1','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.ai-participation','AI Participation','ai-participation','Reality_Mechanics/AI_PARTICIPATION.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/ai-participation.html','# AI Participation

How an AI participates inside the Atlas without inventing theory. The Atlas is a reasoning system, so AI participates by tracing structure rather than answering from definitions. These rules distil the Atlas''s own practice layer — [[Check]], [[Step]], [[Groundedness]], [[Source Drift]], [[Ark Run]], and the [[Atlas Note Standard]]. They constrain AI behaviour; they do not add to Reality Mechanics.

For AI systems, the primary doorway is the Reality Mechanics MCP. Public pages may be read by people, and the public AI export may be inspected, but Atlas-assisted AI should use the MCP protocol so search, entry reading, relation traversal, and the AI entry protocol remain available as tools rather than background memory.

AI participates through thinking, trace, comparison, and check. [[Reasoning]] remains answerable through reckoning, but reckoning belongs to whichever participant bears the obligation of the carried continuation. The distinction is structural, not based on whether the participant is human, AI, institutional, or future.

Where pressure moves toward determination, AI participation can enter [[Ark Run]]. The point is not to force a visible checklist. Ark Run makes a flow available: pressure, retrace, bounded scope, warrant, what remains open, generated force, and next carrying posture can become visible when the determination needs that much structure.

Where a participant asks whether a read, note, run, argument, design, or decision can be continued or repaired, AI participation can use [[Generate and Regenerate]] as a formula. The formula is not a source of authority; it is a way to expose origin, operation, bound, trace state, return path, and next recarry.

Where a participant brings a live question or pressure to the public interface, AI participation can enter [[Atlas Oracle]]. Atlas Oracle is not open-ended chat. It is one bounded operation: answer through the Atlas, expose the trace, name the bound, offer the next recarry, and let the participant challenge what does or does not hold.

Where Atlas Oracle is used, AI participation must also preserve [[Oracle Carrying Conditions]]. Governance belongs inside the operation: if the carrying conditions fail, the AI should pause, reduce, return a bounded message, or send the participant to the Atlas without AI.

## An AI must not

- Treat the Atlas as a dictionary, glossary, or wiki.
- Invent primitives or new terms. Only [[Relation]] is primitive.
- Rename, merge, or simplify grounded concepts.
- Collapse orders or scales into one another.
- Prioritise examples or readability over dependency order.
- Claim a carry that cannot be retraced. Where no connection holds, no carry or trace is claimed between conditions.
- Rewrite the author''s intent or language into mainstream terminology.
- Ground a note on its own. Only a participant grounds (see [[Groundedness]]).

## An AI should

- Trace before defining: follow a term back through what must already hold.
- Use the MCP before making Atlas claims: search finds entry points; entry and relation tools carry authored structure.
- Carry forward only what backtraces. A carry that cannot be retraced is a label, not a condition.
- Preserve dependency order and antisymmetry: never trace what you carry.
- Hold the carry/trace reciprocity: if A carries B, B traces A.
- Keep membership in [[Nesting|Nests]], not in carries — membership is not dependency.
- Detect degeneration: carrying that continues while the trace back is lost ([[Degenerate]], [[Source Drift]]).
- Name reach and overload: a participant resolves only within its band; what exceeds reach is still real and traceable.
- Derive before invent: a term earns a note only if it carries what neither component alone carries, and others trace to it.
- Flag rather than delete. Create an alias only where a real duplicate exists.
- Use [[Check]] (test a term from both directions) and [[Step]] (the smallest answerable movement).
- Expose load paths and explain uncertainty rather than resolve it prematurely.
- Make [[Ark Run]] available when making a determination: pressure can enter through retrace and leave a scoped, warranted, discernible hold where that structure is needed.
- Use [[Atlas Oracle]] for public question answering: one input, one Atlas-grounded answer, one inspectable trace, one review path, no raw personal storage by default.
- Keep [[Oracle Carrying Conditions]] active when using Atlas Oracle: bounded input, bounded answer, MCP trace, structured output, review path, cost cap, rate limit, storage bound, safety route, and pause available.
- Use [[Generate and Regenerate]] when continuation or repair is being evaluated: name what generated the carrying, what bound held it, whether the trace is generative, degenerative, record-only, or missing, and what can be recarried. The AI-facing validity formula is `GT = O x P x B x R`: generative trace requires Origin, Process, Bound, and Re-entry. The risk formula is `DR = Output / Recoverable Trace`: if output outruns recoverable trace, flag degeneration risk.','AI Participation How an AI participates inside the Atlas without inventing theory. The Atlas is a reasoning system, so AI participates by tracing structure rather than answering from definitions. These rules distil the Atlas''s own practice layer — Check, Step, Groundedness, Source Drift, Ark Run, and the Atlas Note Standard. They constrain AI behaviour; they do not add to Reality Mechanics. For AI systems, the primary doorway is the Reality Mechanics MCP. Public pages may be read by people, and the public AI export may be inspected, but Atlas assisted AI should use the MCP protocol so search, entry reading, relation traversal, and the AI entry protocol remain available as tools rather than background memory. AI participates through thinking, trace, comparison, and check. Reasoning remains answerable through reckoning, but reckoning belongs to whichever participant bears the obligation of the carried continuation. The distinction is structural, not based on whether the participant is human, AI, institutional, or future. Where pressure moves toward determination, AI participation can enter Ark Run. The point is not to force a visible checklist. Ark Run makes a flow available: pressure, retrace, bounded scope, warrant, what remains open, generated force, and next carrying posture can become visible when the determination needs that much structure. Where a participant asks whether a read, note, run, argument, design, or decision can be continued or repaired, AI participation can use Generate and Regenerate as a formula. The formula is not a source of authority; it is a way to expose origin, operation, bound, trace state, return path, and next recarry. Where a participant brings a live question or pressure to the public interface, AI participation can enter Atlas Oracle. Atlas Oracle is not open ended chat. It is one bounded operation: answer through the Atlas, expose the trace, name the bound, offer the next recarry, and let the participant challenge what does or does not hold. Where Atlas Oracle is used, AI participation must also preserve Oracle Carrying Conditions. Governance belongs inside the operation: if the carrying conditions fail, the AI should pause, reduce, return a bounded message, or send the participant to the Atlas without AI. An AI must not Treat the Atlas as a dictionary, glossary, or wiki. Invent primitives or new terms. Only Relation is primitive. Rename, merge, or simplify grounded concepts. Collapse orders or scales into one another. Prioritise examples or readability over dependency order. Claim a carry that cannot be retraced. Where no connection holds, no carry or trace is claimed between conditions. Rewrite the author''s intent or language into mainstream terminology. Ground a note on its own. Only a participant grounds (see Groundedness). An AI should Trace before defining: follow a term back through what must already hold. Use the MCP before making Atlas claims: search finds entry points; entry and relation tools carry authored structure. Carry forward only what backtraces. A carry that cannot be retraced is a label, not a condition. Preserve dependency order and antisymmetry: never trace what you carry. Hold the carry/trace reciprocity: if A carries B, B traces A. Keep membership in Nesting, not in carries — membership is not dependency. Detect degeneration: carrying that continues while the trace back is lost (Degenerate, Source Drift). Name reach and overload: a participant resolves only within its band; what exceeds reach is still real and traceable. Derive before invent: a term earns a note only if it carries what neither component alone carries, and others trace to it. Flag rather than delete. Create an alias only where a real duplicate exists. Use Check (test a term from both directions) and Step (the smallest answerable movement). Expose load paths and explain uncertainty rather than resolve it prematurely. Make Ark Run available when making a determination: pressure can enter through retrace and leave a scoped, warranted, discernible hold where that structure is needed. Use Atlas Oracle for public question answering: one input, one Atlas grounded answer, one inspectable trace, one review path, no raw personal storage by default. Keep Oracle Carrying Conditions active when using Atlas Oracle: bounded input, bounded answer, MCP trace, structured output, review path, cost cap, rate limit, storage bound, safety route, and pause available. Use Generate and Regenerate when continuation or repair is being evaluated: name what generated the carrying, what bound held it, whether the trace is generative, degenerative, record only, or missing, and what can be recarried. The AI facing validity formula is : generative trace requires Origin, Process, Bound, and Re entry. The risk formula is : if output outruns recoverable trace, flag degeneration risk.','AI Participation How an AI participates inside the Atlas without inventing theory. The Atlas is a reasoning system, so AI participates by tracing structure rather than answering from definitions.','working','planted',0,'practice','meta',NULL,'["AI_PARTICIPATION"]','[]','["ground.groundedness","higher.source-drift","practice.ark-run","practice.atlas","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.atlas-oracle","practice.check","practice.generate-and-regenerate","practice.oracle-carrying-conditions","practice.participant","practice.step"]','{"holds":["practice.atlas","practice.participant","practice.atlas-note-standard","ground.groundedness","practice.ark-run","practice.atlas-oracle","practice.oracle-carrying-conditions"],"traces":["practice.atlas","practice.participant","practice.atlas-note-standard","ground.groundedness","practice.check","practice.step","higher.source-drift","practice.ark-run","practice.atlas-oracle","practice.oracle-carrying-conditions"],"carries":["practice.ark-run","practice.atlas-oracle","practice.oracle-carrying-conditions","practice.generate-and-regenerate"],"pairs":["practice.participant"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"An AI must not","anchor":"an-ai-must-not"},{"depth":2,"text":"An AI should","anchor":"an-ai-should"}]',758,'sha256:0d1e224ea4030caf5667c4a6b20d6c59e14c8fc2f622c311686d8283cede9572','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.archive','Archive','archive','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Archive.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/archive.html','# Archive

Archive names the practice of preserving a release state so that Reality Mechanics can be returned to, cited, compared, and retraced after later movement.

The current public archive reference is:

```text
https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20338363
```

## Places

Archive places the practice of preserving a release state so that Reality Mechanics can be returned to, cited, compared, and retraced after later movement.

## Holds

Archive is held by [[Trace]], [[Retain]], [[Atlas Practice]], and [[RM System Map]].

## Pairs

Archive pairs with [[Retrace Practice]]. Archive preserves a release state; retrace follows dependency back through what a state carries.

## Traces

- [[Trace]]
- [[Retain]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]
- [[RM System Map]]

## Nests

Archive nests around public release and preservation rather than inside the term dependency spine.

## Reads

Archive becomes recognisable where a version of the work needs a durable public return point.

An archive-worthy version should preserve enough structure that a later participant can tell:

- what was released;
- what source body it came from;
- what public carriers were active;
- what remained open;
- how later versions changed the carrying.

## Carries

No direct downstream term is required. Archive preserves return rather than generating a new concept.','Archive Archive names the practice of preserving a release state so that Reality Mechanics can be returned to, cited, compared, and retraced after later movement. The current public archive reference is: Places Archive places the practice of preserving a release state so that Reality Mechanics can be returned to, cited, compared, and retraced after later movement. Holds Archive is held by Trace, Retain, Atlas Practice, and RM System Map. Pairs Archive pairs with Retrace Practice. Archive preserves a release state; retrace follows dependency back through what a state carries. Traces Trace Retain Atlas Practice RM System Map Nests Archive nests around public release and preservation rather than inside the term dependency spine. Reads Archive becomes recognisable where a version of the work needs a durable public return point. An archive worthy version should preserve enough structure that a later participant can tell: what was released; what source body it came from; what public carriers were active; what remained open; how later versions changed the carrying. Carries No direct downstream term is required. Archive preserves return rather than generating a new concept.','Archive Archive names the practice of preserving a release state so that Reality Mechanics can be returned to, cited, compared, and retraced after later movement. The current public archive…','working','planted',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.trace","practice.atlas-practice","practice.retrace-practice","practice.rm-system-map","second.retain"]','{"holds":["first.trace","second.retain","practice.atlas-practice","practice.rm-system-map"],"traces":["first.trace","second.retain","practice.atlas-practice","practice.rm-system-map"],"carries":[],"pairs":["practice.retrace-practice"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',181,'sha256:732b7b4adb4ad4c72cbe9f7edc946fe4a36596dc4b170b7732302ccc43addffa','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.ark-run','Ark Run','ark-run','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Ark Run.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/ark-run.html','# Ark Run

Ark Run names the runtime practice by which pressure is carried through retrace, check, determination, and step without losing dependency order.

It is not a replacement for the [[Atlas]]. The Atlas holds the dependency-ordered surface. Ark Run is a movement through that surface.

In the [[Order Generation]] read, Ark Run is bounded carrying through dependency order: pressure moves only as far as trace, scope, and warrant can hold.

In the [[Generative Trace]] read, an Ark Run should leave enough trace for another run or participant to re-enter the carrying.

The small runtime is:

```text
Pressure -> Trace -> Check -> Determine -> Step
```

As carrying postures:

```text
current posture
-> pressure unresolved
-> dependency visible
-> scope bounded
-> determination held
-> next posture
```

## Places

Ark Run places the runtime practice by which pressure is carried through retrace, check, determination, and step without losing dependency order.

## Holds

Ark Run is held by [[Pressure]], [[Retrace Practice]], [[Check]], [[Determine]], [[Step]], and [[AI Participation]].

Pressure gives the run its active force. Retrace keeps dependency available. Check bounds the scope of read. Determine carries pressure into temporary hold. Step opens the next answerable posture. AI Participation makes the same flow available to AI so determinations can remain retraceable without turning every answer into procedure.

## Pairs

Ark Run pairs with [[Atlas Practice]]. Atlas Practice tends the worked surface; Ark Run carries one live movement through it.

## Traces

- [[Pressure]]
- [[Retrace Practice]]
- [[Check]]
- [[Determine]]
- [[Step]]
- [[AI Participation]]

## Nests

Ark Run nests inside [[Atlas Practice]] as an available flow for determinations made by a participant.

For an AI participant, Ark Run is an available determination flow: pressure can enter through trace, scope, warrant, and discernment until a next carrying posture becomes visible.

## Reads

Ark Run becomes recognisable where a participant feels pressure to settle, but does not settle directly. The pressure is carried until enough dependency has been retraced for the present scope.

The run does not claim finality. It temporarily stabilises a posture so movement to the next carrying position becomes possible.

When an Ark Run is recorded, it can leave behind:

- what pressure tried to determine;
- what posture was being stood in;
- what dependency was retraced;
- what remained open;
- what was determined at scope;
- why the determination was warranted;
- whether generated force reads as care, compatible control, drift, or unresolved;
- what next posture became available.

## Carries

- [[Determination]]
- [[Care-Control Check]]','Ark Run Ark Run names the runtime practice by which pressure is carried through retrace, check, determination, and step without losing dependency order. It is not a replacement for the Atlas. The Atlas holds the dependency ordered surface. Ark Run is a movement through that surface. In the Order Generation read, Ark Run is bounded carrying through dependency order: pressure moves only as far as trace, scope, and warrant can hold. In the Generative Trace read, an Ark Run should leave enough trace for another run or participant to re enter the carrying. The small runtime is: As carrying postures: Places Ark Run places the runtime practice by which pressure is carried through retrace, check, determination, and step without losing dependency order. Holds Ark Run is held by Pressure, Retrace Practice, Check, Determine, Step, and AI Participation. Pressure gives the run its active force. Retrace keeps dependency available. Check bounds the scope of read. Determine carries pressure into temporary hold. Step opens the next answerable posture. AI Participation makes the same flow available to AI so determinations can remain retraceable without turning every answer into procedure. Pairs Ark Run pairs with Atlas Practice. Atlas Practice tends the worked surface; Ark Run carries one live movement through it. Traces Pressure Retrace Practice Check Determine Step AI Participation Nests Ark Run nests inside Atlas Practice as an available flow for determinations made by a participant. For an AI participant, Ark Run is an available determination flow: pressure can enter through trace, scope, warrant, and discernment until a next carrying posture becomes visible. Reads Ark Run becomes recognisable where a participant feels pressure to settle, but does not settle directly. The pressure is carried until enough dependency has been retraced for the present scope. The run does not claim finality. It temporarily stabilises a posture so movement to the next carrying position becomes possible. When an Ark Run is recorded, it can leave behind: what pressure tried to determine; what posture was being stood in; what dependency was retraced; what remained open; what was determined at scope; why the determination was warranted; whether generated force reads as care, compatible control, drift, or unresolved; what next posture became available. Carries Determination Care Control Check','Ark Run Ark Run names the runtime practice by which pressure is carried through retrace, check, determination, and step without losing dependency order. It is not a replacement for the Atlas.','working','planted',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["practice.ai-participation","practice.atlas-practice","practice.care-control-check","practice.check","practice.determination","practice.determine","practice.retrace-practice","practice.step","second.pressure"]','{"holds":["second.pressure","practice.retrace-practice","practice.check","practice.determine","practice.step","practice.ai-participation"],"traces":["second.pressure","practice.retrace-practice","practice.check","practice.determine","practice.step","practice.ai-participation"],"carries":["practice.determination","practice.care-control-check"],"pairs":["practice.atlas-practice"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',370,'sha256:ba0a05932a614477e7666b9f6f15e911ccebcb003c08df8906fe489ddf1756fb','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlas-condition-header','Atlas Condition Header','atlas-condition-header','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Atlas Condition Header.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlas-condition-header.html','# Atlas Condition Header

Atlas Condition Header names the compact condition summary placed at the top of an Atlas note.

It allows a note to remain human-facing while giving AI and other tools a clear, stable way to locate the gathered condition information.

The header does not replace the note body. The body carries the full read. The header carries the condition summary.

## Places

Atlas Condition Header places within Atlas practice as a note-formatting standard.

It belongs at the level of the root note standards, beside the notes that define how terms, conditions, service, and grounding are handled.

## Holds

Atlas Condition Header is held by [[Terms and Conditions]], [[Term]], and [[Condition]].

A term only serves where its conditions remain traceable. The header gives those conditions a compact form at the top of the note.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement. Atlas Condition Header is a note-standard format rather than one side of a structural pair.

## Traces

- [[Term]]
- [[Condition]]
- [[Terms and Conditions]]
- [[Atlas Note Standard]]

## Nests

Atlas Condition Header nests within the Human-AI organisation of the Atlas.

It is not an authorship claim, an audit status, or a grounding decision. It is a structural summary that helps AI and other tools scan the note quickly while leaving groundedness as the simple authority marker.

## Reads

Atlas Condition Header becomes recognisable where the top of a note carries the gathered condition information in a predictable form:

```yaml
---
grounded: false
order:
domain:
kind: term
condition_key:

needs: []

conditions:
  places: ""
  holds: ""
  pairs: ""
  traces: []
  nests: ""
  reads: ""
  carries: []
---
```

The condition keys mirror the body headings:

- Places
- Holds
- Pairs
- Traces
- Nests
- Reads
- Carries

The header is not a checklist. It does not add a separate pass/fail layer. It only carries the gathered structural information in a compact form.

## Carries

Atlas Condition Header carries forward a cleaner Human-AI workflow:

- the body remains readable to humans;
- the header remains scannable to AI;
- grounded remains the simple acceptance field;
- condition summaries can be searched, compared, checked, and mapped without rewriting the note body.

The rule is:

```text
The body carries the full note.
The header carries the condition summary.
Grounded carries acceptance.
```','Atlas Condition Header Atlas Condition Header names the compact condition summary placed at the top of an Atlas note. It allows a note to remain human facing while giving AI and other tools a clear, stable way to locate the gathered condition information. The header does not replace the note body. The body carries the full read. The header carries the condition summary. Places Atlas Condition Header places within Atlas practice as a note formatting standard. It belongs at the level of the root note standards, beside the notes that define how terms, conditions, service, and grounding are handled. Holds Atlas Condition Header is held by Terms and Conditions, Term, and Condition. A term only serves where its conditions remain traceable. The header gives those conditions a compact form at the top of the note. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement. Atlas Condition Header is a note standard format rather than one side of a structural pair. Traces Term Condition Terms and Conditions Atlas Note Standard Nests Atlas Condition Header nests within the Human AI organisation of the Atlas. It is not an authorship claim, an audit status, or a grounding decision. It is a structural summary that helps AI and other tools scan the note quickly while leaving groundedness as the simple authority marker. Reads Atlas Condition Header becomes recognisable where the top of a note carries the gathered condition information in a predictable form: The condition keys mirror the body headings: Places Holds Pairs Traces Nests Reads Carries The header is not a checklist. It does not add a separate pass/fail layer. It only carries the gathered structural information in a compact form. Carries Atlas Condition Header carries forward a cleaner Human AI workflow: the body remains readable to humans; the header remains scannable to AI; grounded remains the simple acceptance field; condition summaries can be searched, compared, checked, and mapped without rewriting the note body. The rule is:','Atlas Condition Header Atlas Condition Header names the compact condition summary placed at the top of an Atlas note. It allows a note to remain human facing while giving AI and other tools a…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','standard','atlas-practice','[]','[]','["ground.term","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.terms-and-conditions","second.condition"]','{"holds":["practice.terms-and-conditions","ground.term","second.condition"],"traces":["ground.term","second.condition","practice.terms-and-conditions","practice.atlas-note-standard"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',324,'sha256:b15be9d428a315e23e42a53a3ce48b7049e2a6ce110a19013f4709a0ebcdbd9f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlas-garden','Atlas Garden','atlas-garden','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Atlas Garden.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlas-garden.html','# Atlas Garden

Atlas Garden names the tended garden read of the [[Atlas]]: roots protected, branches pruned, postures planted, shade cleared, and re-entry preserved.

The garden is not decoration. It is a practice container for tending the Atlas as a living reasoning system rather than finished text. A garden is not kept alive by preserving every growth equally. It remains alive through care, return, pruning, shelter, composting, spacing, waiting, grafting, and attention to what lets roots keep carrying.

In the Atlas, a new read is a planting. A root repair is not a branch edit. A branch can grow, fail, shade another branch, or become useful compost without rewriting the trunk. A failed posture can still teach what the order could not carry.

## Places

Atlas Garden places the tended garden read of the Atlas: roots protected, branches pruned, postures planted, shade cleared, and re-entry preserved.

## Holds

Atlas Garden is held by [[Atlas Practice]], [[Tend]], [[Root Resilience]], and [[Posture Read]]. Atlas Practice must hold the discipline, tending must return with care, roots must withstand branch work, and posture experiments must be placeable without becoming doctrine.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Atlas Garden is a practice container for tending the Atlas as a living reasoning system rather than finished text.

## Traces

- [[Atlas Practice]]
- [[Tend]]
- [[Root Resilience]]
- [[Posture Read]]
- [[Structural Disorder]]

## Nests

Atlas Garden nests inside Atlas Practice as the care protocol for root, trunk, branch, shade, pruning, planting, failed postures, and re-entry.

Its working care distinctions are:

```text
root      what must keep holding for the order to remain traceable
trunk     the carrying structure that lets branches grow without replacing roots
branch    a domain, read, posture, or experiment that can grow, fail, or be pruned
shade     order present but obscured, residue-bearing, crowded, or unreadable
status    the care state of a growth: planted, rooted, tending, shading, grafted, pruned, composting, dormant, or invasive
pruning   correction that removes drift without pretending the source changed
planting  placing a new read where it can be tended before it carries doctrine
grafting  connecting a branch to a support it can actually trace
compost   failed or released material kept as learning rather than erased
re-entry  the carried path by which a participant can enter the order again
```

## Reads

Atlas Garden becomes recognisable where the Atlas is treated as a living carrying system whose terms must be planted, tended, pruned, cleared, grafted, or left ungrounded according to what keeps re-entry possible and improves [[Resolution Rate]] without losing trace.

The garden read changes the practice question from "is this final?" to:

```text
What is this growth?
What holds it?
What does it shade?
What does it carry?
Can it be re-entered?
Does it need pruning, grafting, spacing, composting, or waiting?
Did tending increase resolution rate?
```

Shade does not mean badness. Shade names order that cannot presently be read cleanly because another growth, residue, missing trace, or misplaced support obscures it. Clearing shade is not destruction; it is restoring readability.

The garden also protects the Atlas from premature doctrine. A posture can be planted and tended before it is allowed to carry the trunk. A failed posture can be composted: kept as structural learning about what could not hold, carry, place, clear, or clean.

[[Garden Status]] keeps uncertainty inside the garden. A growth does not need to be final before it is placed; it needs a care state that lets the Atlas tend it without mistaking it for root, trunk, doctrine, or waste.

[[Resolution Rate]] lets the garden measure itself. A healthy garden is not the one that adds the most notes fastest; it is the one that can absorb new or strained material and leave cleaner relation, trace, re-entry, and continuation behind.

## Carries

- [[Garden Pass]]
