ently be read cleanly because another growth, residue, missing trace, or misplaced support obscures it. Clearing shade is not destruction; it is restoring readability. The garden also protects the Atlas from premature doctrine. A posture can be planted and tended before it is allowed to carry the trunk. A failed posture can be composted: kept as structural learning about what could not hold, carry, place, clear, or clean. Garden Status keeps uncertainty inside the garden. A growth does not need to be final before it is placed; it needs a care state that lets the Atlas tend it without mistaking it for root, trunk, doctrine, or waste. Resolution Rate lets the garden measure itself. A healthy garden is not the one that adds the most notes fastest; it is the one that can absorb new or strained material and leave cleaner relation, trace, re entry, and continuation behind. Carries Garden Pass Garden Status','Atlas Garden Atlas Garden names the tended garden read of the Atlas: roots protected, branches pruned, postures planted, shade cleared, and re entry preserved. The garden is not decoration.','working','planted',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.structural-disorder","practice.atlas-practice","practice.garden-pass","practice.garden-status","practice.posture-read","practice.root-resilience","practice.tend","second.resolution-rate"]','{"holds":["practice.atlas-practice","practice.tend","practice.root-resilience","practice.posture-read"],"traces":["practice.atlas-practice","practice.tend","practice.root-resilience","practice.posture-read","ground.structural-disorder"],"carries":["practice.garden-pass","practice.garden-status"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":["second.resolution-rate"]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',464,'sha256:d980b58dbcbe4d5ac0a2989a89c0eec8b54d52b6e880b7a8077edb1fb1b7c637','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlas-note-standard','Atlas Note Standard','atlas-note-standard','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Atlas Note Standard.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlas-note-standard.html','# Atlas Note Standard

Atlas Note Standard names the placement standard by which an interpretation becomes a term inside the [[Atlas]].

An Atlas note is a mapped reasoning position, not a glossary entry. Its form exists to make order explicit: what the term places, what holds it, what it pairs with, where it traces, where it nests, how it reads, and what it carries.

In the garden read, an Atlas note is also a planted growth. Its note form places it; its [[Garden Status]] names how it is being tended. A working note is not outside the Atlas. It is inside the Atlas as living structure whose care state remains visible.

The `garden_status` field may name that care state in metadata. It is not a permission field; it is a tending signal.

## Places

Atlas Note Standard places the note spine:

```text
Places
Holds
Pairs
Traces
Nests
Reads
Carries
```

These are term conditions. They let a note be mapped, compared, corrected, grounded, and retraced.

## Holds

Atlas Note Standard is held by the term conditions. Holds names the nearest condition doing the bearing.

## Pairs

Pairs names what the term must be read with, against, or beside in order to remain locatable. A pair is the minimum carrying relation, not only an opposite.

Not every term requires a lateral pair. Root, order, invariant, class-forming, vertical, or terminal terms may carry downward instead.

## Traces

- [[Reality Mechanics]]
- [[Atlas]]
- [[Retrace Read|Retrace]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Groundedness]]
- [[Garden Status]]

Traces names the dependency path backward through the order.

## Nests

Nests names the closure level where the term holds and the larger or smaller reads it can sit within without losing trace.

## Reads

Atlas Note Standard becomes recognisable where a note can be placed, compared, revised, grounded, and retraced because its term conditions remain explicit.

The note should state the term directly, show its immediate support, name how it becomes recognisable, and show what it carries forward. Explanation serves placement.

Garden status does not replace the note spine. It protects the note spine from becoming a permission system. If a term can be placed and tended, it can enter as a planted growth while its holds, traces, shade, and future care remain answerable.

The two dependency directions are not interchangeable:

```text
generative direction: prior term ──carries──▶ downstream term
evidential direction: prior term ◀──traces── downstream term
```

Reality may carry a condition before that carrying is read. The Atlas, however, grounds a `Carries` claim only where a downstream term has become available and its `Traces` can recover the dependency. What a term may make possible remains an opening until a return trace confirms the continuation. Prediction does not by itself establish carrying.

A downstream term may trace several prior conditions and the passage through which they participate. The test does not force a single source where the dependency is multiple. Failure of an anticipated downstream term also does not by itself disprove bearing from an upstream condition; allowance, compatibility, boundary, interruption, or other passage conditions may have prevented continuation.

## Carries

- [[Check]]
- [[Atlasing]]
- [[Terms and Conditions]]
- [[Carry-Trace Test]]
- [[Discipline]]

Carries names confirmed continuation from the term into downstream terms. Possible continuation belongs to available openings until it becomes recoverable through a downstream trace.

Carries and Traces record dependency. If a note carries a term, that term traces back to it. Nested placement belongs in Nests; dependency belongs in Traces and Carries.','Atlas Note Standard Atlas Note Standard names the placement standard by which an interpretation becomes a term inside the Atlas. An Atlas note is a mapped reasoning position, not a glossary entry. Its form exists to make order explicit: what the term places, what holds it, what it pairs with, where it traces, where it nests, how it reads, and what it carries. In the garden read, an Atlas note is also a planted growth. Its note form places it; its Garden Status names how it is being tended. A working note is not outside the Atlas. It is inside the Atlas as living structure whose care state remains visible. The field may name that care state in metadata. It is not a permission field; it is a tending signal. Places Atlas Note Standard places the note spine: These are term conditions. They let a note be mapped, compared, corrected, grounded, and retraced. Holds Atlas Note Standard is held by the term conditions. Holds names the nearest condition doing the bearing. Pairs Pairs names what the term must be read with, against, or beside in order to remain locatable. A pair is the minimum carrying relation, not only an opposite. Not every term requires a lateral pair. Root, order, invariant, class forming, vertical, or terminal terms may carry downward instead. Traces Reality Mechanics Atlas Retrace Read Boundary Groundedness Garden Status Traces names the dependency path backward through the order. Nests Nests names the closure level where the term holds and the larger or smaller reads it can sit within without losing trace. Reads Atlas Note Standard becomes recognisable where a note can be placed, compared, revised, grounded, and retraced because its term conditions remain explicit. The note should state the term directly, show its immediate support, name how it becomes recognisable, and show what it carries forward. Explanation serves placement. Garden status does not replace the note spine. It protects the note spine from becoming a permission system. If a term can be placed and tended, it can enter as a planted growth while its holds, traces, shade, and future care remain answerable. The two dependency directions are not interchangeable: Reality may carry a condition before that carrying is read. The Atlas, however, grounds a claim only where a downstream term has become available and its can recover the dependency. What a term may make possible remains an opening until a return trace confirms the continuation. Prediction does not by itself establish carrying. A downstream term may trace several prior conditions and the passage through which they participate. The test does not force a single source where the dependency is multiple. Failure of an anticipated downstream term also does not by itself disprove bearing from an upstream condition; allowance, compatibility, boundary, interruption, or other passage conditions may have prevented continuation. Carries Check Atlasing Terms and Conditions Carry Trace Test Discipline Carries names confirmed continuation from the term into downstream terms. Possible continuation belongs to available openings until it becomes recoverable through a downstream trace. Carries and Traces record dependency. If a note carries a term, that term traces back to it. Nested placement belongs in Nests; dependency belongs in Traces and Carries.','Atlas Note Standard Atlas Note Standard names the placement standard by which an interpretation becomes a term inside the Atlas. An Atlas note is a mapped reasoning position, not a glossary entry.','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","ground.groundedness","practice.atlas","practice.atlasing","practice.carry-trace-test","practice.check","practice.discipline","practice.garden-status","practice.reality-mechanics","practice.terms-and-conditions","second.retrace-read"]','{"holds":[],"traces":["practice.reality-mechanics","ground.groundedness","practice.garden-status","practice.atlas","second.retrace-read","first.boundary"],"carries":["practice.check","practice.atlasing","practice.terms-and-conditions","practice.carry-trace-test","practice.discipline"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',532,'sha256:6c73789cee25c5ed02d9c82d349fc5e86b96daaba8c51b1eb1ec95564fa6cf74','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlas-oracle','Atlas Oracle','atlas-oracle','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Atlas Oracle.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlas-oracle.html','# Atlas Oracle

Atlas Oracle names the bounded instrument by which a participant brings pressure to the [[Atlas]], receives an Atlas-grounded answer, inspects the trace, and can challenge what does or does not hold.

It is not a claim that AI knows the truth. It is a way for AI to answer through the Atlas while leaving enough trace for the answer to be accepted, rejected, corrected, or tended.

The simple human surface is:

```text
Ask the Atlas.
Receive an answer.
Inspect the trace.
If it does not hold, trace why.
```

The answer is provisional. The trace is inspectable. Disagreement is participation.

The Oracle is available only while its [[Oracle Carrying Conditions]] hold. If those conditions fail, the Oracle pauses rather than drifting into unbounded AI use.

## Places

Atlas Oracle places a bounded interface where pressure can enter as a question, confusion, challenge, absence, or need for orientation, and leave as an answer that remains answerable to its Atlas trace.

## Holds

Atlas Oracle is held by [[Atlas]], [[Reasoning]], [[AI Participation]], [[Ark Run]], [[Check]], [[Generate and Regenerate]], [[Carried Condition]], and [[Oracle Carrying Conditions]].

The Atlas provides the dependency-ordered surface. Reasoning keeps the answer answerable as traceable support. AI Participation constrains the artificial participant. Ark Run carries pressure through trace, bound, determination, and next posture. Check lets the answer be challenged. Generate and Regenerate tests whether the trace can be continued. Carried Condition holds the return point where load exceeds solitary carrying and meaning can wait. Oracle Carrying Conditions keep governance inside the operation.

## Pairs

Atlas Oracle pairs with open-ended chat.

Open-ended chat may continue fluently without preserving the carrying path. Atlas Oracle carries one pressure through a bounded answer and exposes enough trace for the participant to test whether it holds.

## Traces

- [[Atlas]]
- [[Reasoning]]
- [[AI Participation]]
- [[Ark Run]]
- [[Check]]
- [[Generate and Regenerate]]
- [[Carried Condition]]
- [[Oracle Carrying Conditions]]

## Nests

Atlas Oracle nests inside [[Atlas Practice]] as a human-facing instrument and AI-facing bounded operation.

For a human participant, it is a doorway: bring a pressure, receive an answer, inspect the trace, and challenge the movement.

For an AI participant, it is an operation:

```text
input pressure
-> carrying conditions check
-> MCP entry and traversal
-> Atlas-grounded answer
-> trace path
-> bound and uncertainty
-> next recarry
-> review event
```

## Reads

Atlas Oracle becomes recognisable where the value is not that AI is always right, but that its move can be traced.

If the answer holds, the participant can continue from it.

If the answer does not hold, the challenge becomes tending:

```text
wrong handle
missing trace
too much interpretation
bound crossed
answer did not carry
```

The review is not only feedback on AI quality. It is a trace event that can show where the Atlas needs tending, where a route is missing, where a handle is overloaded, or where the answer tried to carry more than the trace could hold.

Atlas Oracle stores trace events by default, not private stories:

```text
pressure category
selected handles
trace path
answer bound
review action
raw personal text stored: false
```

The Oracle does not answer merely because a question arrived. It answers only where the carrying conditions hold:

```text
bounded input
bounded answer
MCP trace
structured output
review path
cost cap
rate limit
storage bound
safety route
pause available
```

The Oracle may be embedded in other places only where the Atlas trace remains attached:

```text
source visible
trace visible
review visible
bound visible
no diagnosis claim
no final authority claim
raw storage off by default
```

An embed is not a separate Oracle. It is the same Oracle carried in another place.

Where koha is offered, it should come after value has been carried:

```text
If this carried value for you, koha helps carry it forward.
```

Koha is not a paywall. It is a return path for shared carrying.

Where load is too concentrated for interpretation, Atlas Oracle should return through [[Carried Condition]] before meaning:

```text
You are carried.
Meaning can wait.
```

## Carries

- [[Garden Pass]]
- [[Generative Trace]]
