INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlas-root','Atlas Root','atlas-root','Reality_Mechanics/00_ROOT.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlas-root.html','# Atlas Root

Reality Mechanics is the discipline of keeping relation traceable as order. It begins from a working postulate:

```text
Relation holds.
Order carries.
Trace places.
```

The Atlas is the dependency-ordered reasoning system produced through that discipline. It is the worked surface through which the relation-order-trace practice becomes inspectable.

It is not a glossary.
It is not a wiki.
It is not a philosophy.
It is not a taxonomy.

It is a tended surface for reasoning. Terms are handles; order is what they handle. Its purpose is to preserve dependency order so that humans and AI can participate within relation rather than only describe it.

The Atlas is not the authority-object. The relation-order-trace practice is what must remain repeatable: place the term, trace what holds it, test what it carries, prune where it drifts, and correct what no longer remains answerable.

## Root Dependency Order

[[Relation]] grounds. Two conditions arise from it: [[Connection]] (relation holding between distinguishable conditions) and [[Asymmetry]] (relation uneven enough for distinction to begin). [[Posture]] is connection held with orientation, depending on both.

**Dependency spine:**

```text
Relation
├── Connection ─── Posture
└── Asymmetry → Bounded Asymmetry → Strained Asymmetry → Resolved Asymmetry
                                     ↓
                    Boundary → Availability → Strain → Bearing → Resolution
                                                                      ↓
                                                         Hold   Carry   Place
```

**Posture read** (a reading of the spine, not a separate dependency chain or root postulate):

```text
Connection → Posture → Structure → Clear → Clean
```

The posture read names how order can become workable when followed through the dependency spine. It does not replace the spine or the working postulate; it shows one way to enter and test them.

Everything in the Atlas must ultimately remain answerable to this working root. [[Resolution]] closes a condition at its scope without ending wider relation; it is not a universal prerequisite for carrying.

## Orders as Modes of Carrying

```text
First      order becomes locatable through hold / carry / place
Second     carried order is enacted as carrying, through coupling and participation
Third      participating carrying becomes organised and nested
Higher     organised carrying enters its own carrying
Practice   a participant follows trace through retracing
```

An order changes where carrying takes on a new structural role. A crossing is the passage through which that change occurs.

## Entering the Atlas

- Trace backward: follow a term through the prior conditions that must already hold.
- Carry forward: move only what can be retraced.
- Preserve dependency order: never make a downstream term primitive in place of what holds it.

See [[Reality Mechanics]] (the discipline), [[Theory]] (the working postulate), [[Atlas Note Standard]] (the note grammar), [[AI Participation]] (how AI participates), and [[Invariants]] (what does not change).','Atlas Root Reality Mechanics is the discipline of keeping relation traceable as order. It begins from a working postulate: The Atlas is the dependency ordered reasoning system produced through that discipline. It is the worked surface through which the relation order trace practice becomes inspectable. It is not a glossary. It is not a wiki. It is not a philosophy. It is not a taxonomy. It is a tended surface for reasoning. Terms are handles; order is what they handle. Its purpose is to preserve dependency order so that humans and AI can participate within relation rather than only describe it. The Atlas is not the authority object. The relation order trace practice is what must remain repeatable: place the term, trace what holds it, test what it carries, prune where it drifts, and correct what no longer remains answerable. Root Dependency Order Relation grounds. Two conditions arise from it: Connection (relation holding between distinguishable conditions) and Asymmetry (relation uneven enough for distinction to begin). Posture is connection held with orientation, depending on both. Dependency spine: Posture read (a reading of the spine, not a separate dependency chain or root postulate): The posture read names how order can become workable when followed through the dependency spine. It does not replace the spine or the working postulate; it shows one way to enter and test them. Everything in the Atlas must ultimately remain answerable to this working root. Resolution closes a condition at its scope without ending wider relation; it is not a universal prerequisite for carrying. Orders as Modes of Carrying An order changes where carrying takes on a new structural role. A crossing is the passage through which that change occurs. Entering the Atlas Trace backward: follow a term through the prior conditions that must already hold. Carry forward: move only what can be retraced. Preserve dependency order: never make a downstream term primitive in place of what holds it. See Reality Mechanics (the discipline), Theory (the working postulate), Atlas Note Standard (the note grammar), AI Participation (how AI participates), and Invariants (what does not change).','Atlas Root Reality Mechanics is the discipline of keeping relation traceable as order. It begins from a working postulate: The Atlas is the dependency ordered reasoning system produced through…','working','planted',0,'practice','meta',NULL,'["00_ROOT"]','[]','["ground.root-order","practice.atlas","practice.reality-mechanics","practice.reality-mechanics-theory"]','{"holds":["practice.reality-mechanics","practice.atlas","ground.root-order","practice.reality-mechanics-theory"],"traces":["practice.reality-mechanics","practice.atlas","ground.root-order","practice.reality-mechanics-theory"],"carries":[],"pairs":["practice.atlas"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Root Dependency Order","anchor":"root-dependency-order"},{"depth":2,"text":"Orders as Modes of Carrying","anchor":"orders-as-modes-of-carrying"},{"depth":2,"text":"Entering the Atlas","anchor":"entering-the-atlas"}]',347,'sha256:b24f29d903dea32a623fadf7dbfd1163153d790bf69955f5c37c679c8fa63d03','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlas','Atlas','atlas','Reality_Mechanics/Atlas.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlas.html','# Atlas

Atlas names the dependency-ordered reasoning system produced through [[Reality Mechanics]]: the worked and tended surface where terms, traces, reads, openings, and corrections are held in retraceable order.

An Operating System for Reasoning may become a future-facing evolution of the Atlas as its human and AI participation surfaces mature. It is not the current claim. The current claim is simpler: the Atlas is a dependency-ordered reasoning system.

The Atlas is not identical to its written notes. Writing is its present durable medium. Its reasoning may be carried through words, signs, diagrams, arrangements, actions, or thought; the Atlas remains the same mapped body only where dependency placement remains recoverable across those changes of carrier.

The Atlas is not the authority-object. The relation-order-trace practice is what must remain repeatable: place the term, trace what holds it, test what it carries, prune where it drifts, and correct what no longer remains answerable.

The working postulate — relation holds, order carries, trace places — bounds what counts as a valid Atlas operation. The posture sequence — [[Connection]], [[Posture]], [[Structure]], [[Clear]], [[Clean]] — remains a planted read for testing how that operation becomes workable.

Its value is in [[Reality-Bearing Connection]]: terms, supports, reads, openings, and retraces connected in a way that can carry reality rather than merely link information.

The Atlas couples reads and nests them by dependency, so pattern recognition stays traceable to what carries it. Coupling lets terms, supports, and reads participate in one another; nesting keeps that participation ordered enough to retrace.

The Atlas does not make order. It traces reads that enter order, checks whether they remain answerable to what carries them, and shows what they carry forward.

## Places

Atlas places the dependency-ordered reasoning system produced by [[Reality Mechanics]] — the worked and tended surface where terms, traces, reads, and corrections are held in retraceable order.

## Holds

Atlas is held by the discipline of [[Reality Mechanics]], the governing dependency arrangement of [[Root Order]], and the working postulate named by [[Theory]].

## Pairs

Atlas pairs with [[Reality Mechanics]]: one is the worked surface, the other is the practice that keeps the surface traceable.

Atlas also pairs with [[Theory]]. Atlas preserves dependency-ordered interpretations; Theory gives selected Atlas operations a working postulate through which they can be composed, tested, compared with existing mathematics, and rejected where they fail.

## Traces

- [[Reality Mechanics]]
- [[Root Order]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]
- [[Order Trace]]

## Nests

Atlas nests term notes, root notes, applied reads, practice notes, and higher-order retraces without making them identical.

[[Atlas Note Standard]]
[[Reality-Bearing Connection]]
[[Order Trace]]
[[Translation Boundary]]
[[Translation Invariance]]
[[Atlasing]]

## Reads

Atlas becomes recognisable where terms, traces, reads, and corrections are held together by structural role, immediate support, available openings, and retraceable placement.

It places and holds reality-bearing connections rather than merely linking information.

The Atlas is a return path for participation that would otherwise dissipate. Placed into the Atlas, a read returns to a checkable order that outlasts the occasion and answers back.

It couples human and AI reads, then nests those reads by dependency so recognition remains answerable to ordered relation.

The Atlas tests its structure through [[Translation Invariance]]: vary the carrier, preserve the interpretation, and check which dependency relations remain recoverable. If the wording survives but the dependency order does not, the inscription has remained while the Atlas structure has been lost.

The Atlas keeps [[Regenerate|regeneration]] available: each term keeps a trace back to what generates it, so accumulated carrying does not have to become [[Source Drift]].

In the tree read, Atlas keeps roots, trunk, branches, translation boundaries, path reads, applied reads, and tending practices distinct enough to be cared for. A branch can be pruned or translated without pretending the trunk has changed. The trunk is not replaced unless the carrying structure itself proves wrongly read. Ground and root conditions are not casually edited; they are retraced.

## Carries

- [[Atlas Note Standard]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]
- [[Reality-Bearing Connection]]
- [[Theory|The Working Postulate]]
- [[Atlasing]]
- [[Translation Invariance]]
- [[Atlas Root]]
- [[AI Participation]]
- [[Invariants]]','Atlas Atlas names the dependency ordered reasoning system produced through Reality Mechanics: the worked and tended surface where terms, traces, reads, openings, and corrections are held in retraceable order. An Operating System for Reasoning may become a future facing evolution of the Atlas as its human and AI participation surfaces mature. It is not the current claim. The current claim is simpler: the Atlas is a dependency ordered reasoning system. The Atlas is not identical to its written notes. Writing is its present durable medium. Its reasoning may be carried through words, signs, diagrams, arrangements, actions, or thought; the Atlas remains the same mapped body only where dependency placement remains recoverable across those changes of carrier. The Atlas is not the authority object. The relation order trace practice is what must remain repeatable: place the term, trace what holds it, test what it carries, prune where it drifts, and correct what no longer remains answerable. The working postulate — relation holds, order carries, trace places — bounds what counts as a valid Atlas operation. The posture sequence — Connection, Posture, Structure, Clear, Clean — remains a planted read for testing how that operation becomes workable. Its value is in Reality Bearing Connection: terms, supports, reads, openings, and retraces connected in a way that can carry reality rather than merely link information. The Atlas couples reads and nests them by dependency, so pattern recognition stays traceable to what carries it. Coupling lets terms, supports, and reads participate in one another; nesting keeps that participation ordered enough to retrace. The Atlas does not make order. It traces reads that enter order, checks whether they remain answerable to what carries them, and shows what they carry forward. Places Atlas places the dependency ordered reasoning system produced by Reality Mechanics — the worked and tended surface where terms, traces, reads, and corrections are held in retraceable order. Holds Atlas is held by the discipline of Reality Mechanics, the governing dependency arrangement of Root Order, and the working postulate named by Theory. Pairs Atlas pairs with Reality Mechanics: one is the worked surface, the other is the practice that keeps the surface traceable. Atlas also pairs with Theory. Atlas preserves dependency ordered interpretations; Theory gives selected Atlas operations a working postulate through which they can be composed, tested, compared with existing mathematics, and rejected where they fail. Traces Reality Mechanics Root Order Translation Boundary Order Trace Nests Atlas nests term notes, root notes, applied reads, practice notes, and higher order retraces without making them identical. Atlas Note Standard Reality Bearing Connection Order Trace Translation Boundary Translation Invariance Atlasing Reads Atlas becomes recognisable where terms, traces, reads, and corrections are held together by structural role, immediate support, available openings, and retraceable placement. It places and holds reality bearing connections rather than merely linking information. The Atlas is a return path for participation that would otherwise dissipate. Placed into the Atlas, a read returns to a checkable order that outlasts the occasion and answers back. It couples human and AI reads, then nests those reads by dependency so recognition remains answerable to ordered relation. The Atlas tests its structure through Translation Invariance: vary the carrier, preserve the interpretation, and check which dependency relations remain recoverable. If the wording survives but the dependency order does not, the inscription has remained while the Atlas structure has been lost. The Atlas keeps Regenerate available: each term keeps a trace back to what generates it, so accumulated carrying does not have to become Source Drift. In the tree read, Atlas keeps roots, trunk, branches, translation boundaries, path reads, applied reads, and tending practices distinct enough to be cared for. A branch can be pruned or translated without pretending the trunk has changed. The trunk is not replaced unless the carrying structure itself proves wrongly read. Ground and root conditions are not casually edited; they are retraced. Carries Atlas Note Standard Atlas Practice Reality Bearing Connection Theory Atlasing Translation Invariance Atlas Root AI Participation Invariants','Atlas Atlas names the dependency ordered reasoning system produced through Reality Mechanics: the worked and tended surface where terms, traces, reads, openings, and corrections are held in…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.root-order","practice.ai-participation","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.atlas-practice","practice.atlas-root","practice.atlasing","practice.invariants","practice.order-trace","practice.reality-bearing-connection","practice.reality-mechanics","practice.reality-mechanics-theory","practice.translation-invariance","third.translation-boundary"]','{"holds":["practice.reality-mechanics","ground.root-order","practice.reality-mechanics-theory"],"traces":["third.translation-boundary","practice.order-trace","practice.reality-mechanics","ground.root-order"],"carries":["practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.atlas-practice","practice.reality-bearing-connection","practice.reality-mechanics-theory","practice.atlasing","practice.translation-invariance","practice.atlas-root","practice.ai-participation","practice.invariants"],"pairs":["practice.reality-mechanics","practice.reality-mechanics-theory"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',663,'sha256:8f08f774307dcad1dc5aa2029625e8ea0307070bb838229f183cff8dc16b2e5e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.atlasing','Atlasing','atlasing','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Atlasing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/atlasing.html','# Atlasing

Atlasing names the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace. It is more than collecting notes: it is the disciplined placement act through which a possible connection is tested for reality-bearing fit.

Atlasing treats a term as a participation handle rather than a static definition: a placed way to enter relation without losing dependency, bearing, or return path.

## Places

Atlasing places the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace.

## Holds

Atlasing is held by [[Atlas]], [[Atlas Note Standard]], and [[Reality-Bearing Connection]].

## Pairs

Atlasing is vertical. It names the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace. Atlasing holds [[Atlas]], [[Atlas Note Standard]], and [[Reality-Bearing Connection]] — it is the downstream practice that those conditions make available. It carries no further term. There is no lateral co-present condition that Atlasing requires and that requires Atlasing in return at this order.

## Traces

- [[Atlas]]
- [[Atlas Note Standard]]
- [[Reality-Bearing Connection]]
- [[Check]]

## Nests

Atlasing nests as the ongoing practice of keeping the Atlas placed, grounded, and retraceable.

[[Tracing]]
[[Retracing]]

## Reads

Atlasing becomes recognisable where a term, experience, correction, or contribution is placed so its support, readable condition, and available openings remain retraceable.

## Carries

No downstream term placed yet — Atlasing is the terminal practice act.','Atlasing Atlasing names the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace. It is more than collecting notes: it is the disciplined placement act through which a possible connection is tested for reality bearing fit. Atlasing treats a term as a participation handle rather than a static definition: a placed way to enter relation without losing dependency, bearing, or return path. Places Atlasing places the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace. Holds Atlasing is held by Atlas, Atlas Note Standard, and Reality Bearing Connection. Pairs Atlasing is vertical. It names the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace. Atlasing holds Atlas, Atlas Note Standard, and Reality Bearing Connection — it is the downstream practice that those conditions make available. It carries no further term. There is no lateral co present condition that Atlasing requires and that requires Atlasing in return at this order. Traces Atlas Atlas Note Standard Reality Bearing Connection Check Nests Atlasing nests as the ongoing practice of keeping the Atlas placed, grounded, and retraceable. Tracing Retracing Reads Atlasing becomes recognisable where a term, experience, correction, or contribution is placed so its support, readable condition, and available openings remain retraceable. Carries No downstream term placed yet — Atlasing is the terminal practice act.','Atlasing Atlasing names the act of placing, revising, or connecting terms inside the Atlas according to trace, read, opens, and retrace. It is more than collecting notes: it is the disciplined…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["practice.atlas","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.check","practice.reality-bearing-connection"]','{"holds":["practice.atlas","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.reality-bearing-connection"],"traces":["practice.atlas","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.reality-bearing-connection","practice.check"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',235,'sha256:99ba15977ca2de577b453be8e9cedf719d79fc2df0c4ce825d2b2411f119fe5f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.care-control-check','Care-Control Check','care-control-check','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Care-Control Check.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/care-control-check.html','# Care-Control Check

Care-Control Check names the practice check that reads what kind of force a [[Determination]] generates: care, compatible control, control drift, or unresolved force.

It is not a moral label placed on a person. It is a runtime read of generated force.

## Places

Care-Control Check places the practice check that reads what kind of force a determination generates.

## Holds

Care-Control Check is held by [[Ark Run]], [[Determination]], [[Care]], [[Control]], [[Control Drift]], and [[Check]].

Determination generates force because something has been temporarily fixed. Care-Control Check asks what that force now does.

## Pairs

Care-Control Check pairs with [[Care Without Bearing]]. Care-Control Check asks whether care or control remains borne; Care Without Bearing names a failure where care is claimed without bearing.

## Traces

- [[Determination]]
- [[Ark Run]]
- [[Care]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Control Drift]]
- [[Check]]

## Nests

Care-Control Check nests inside [[Ark Run]] as the force-read after determination and before movement to the next posture.

## Reads

Care-Control Check becomes recognisable through questions:

- What force does this determination generate?
- Does the force preserve availability?
- Does it direct while remaining correctable by what it directs?
- Has it begun to proceed after correction is no longer being received?
- Must the run remain unresolved, retrace, or rescope?

In the Ark runtime, care preserves availability. Compatible control directs while remaining answerable to correction from the directed condition. Control drift blocks movement until correction or rescope occurs.

## Carries

No direct downstream term is required. Care-Control Check constrains movement by checking generated force.','Care Control Check Care Control Check names the practice check that reads what kind of force a Determination generates: care, compatible control, control drift, or unresolved force. It is not a moral label placed on a person. It is a runtime read of generated force. Places Care Control Check places the practice check that reads what kind of force a determination generates. Holds Care Control Check is held by Ark Run, Determination, Care, Control, Control Drift, and Check. Determination generates force because something has been temporarily fixed. Care Control Check asks what that force now does. Pairs Care Control Check pairs with Care Without Bearing. Care Control Check asks whether care or control remains borne; Care Without Bearing names a failure where care is claimed without bearing. Traces Determination Ark Run Care Control Control Drift Check Nests Care Control Check nests inside Ark Run as the force read after determination and before movement to the next posture. Reads Care Control Check becomes recognisable through questions: What force does this determination generate? Does the force preserve availability? Does it direct while remaining correctable by what it directs? Has it begun to proceed after correction is no longer being received? Must the run remain unresolved, retrace, or rescope? In the Ark runtime, care preserves availability. Compatible control directs while remaining answerable to correction from the directed condition. Control drift blocks movement until correction or rescope occurs. Carries No direct downstream term is required. Care Control Check constrains movement by checking generated force.','Care Control Check Care Control Check names the practice check that reads what kind of force a Determination generates: care, compatible control, control drift, or unresolved force. It is not a…','working','planted',0,'practice','check',NULL,'[]','[]','["practice.ark-run","practice.check","practice.determination","third.care","third.care-without-bearing","third.control","third.control-drift"]','{"holds":["practice.ark-run","practice.determination","third.care","third.control","third.control-drift","practice.check"],"traces":["practice.determination","practice.ark-run","third.care","third.control","third.control-drift","practice.check"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.care-without-bearing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',250,'sha256:9e0937dcc702040d8be935950780b19d118096184f841e95006b7e0d9ca14c68','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.carry-trace-test','Carry-Trace Test','carry-trace-test','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Carry-Trace Test.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/carry-trace-test.html','# Carry-Trace Test

Carry-Trace Test names the Atlas practice test that distinguishes confirmed downstream carrying from projected openings by requiring a recoverable return trace.

It separates the order operating from the order known. Reality may carry a condition before any participant reads it. The Atlas does not create that carrying through recognition, but it grounds its own claim only where the downstream condition can be followed back through what made it available.

## Places

Carry-Trace Test places the Atlas practice test that distinguishes confirmed downstream carrying from projected openings by requiring a recoverable return trace.

## Holds

Carry-Trace Test is held by [[Atlas Note Standard]], [[Dependency Order]], [[Trace]], and [[Retracing]]. Term placement, structural precedence, a followable path, and the checking act must be available before a carry claim can be grounded.

## Pairs

Carry-Trace Test is vertical. Carry and trace are two reading directions through one dependency relation, not a lateral pair:

```text
generative direction: A ──carries──▶ B
evidential direction:  A ◀──traces── B
```

## Traces

- [[Atlas Note Standard]]
- [[Dependency Order]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Retracing]]

## Nests

Carry-Trace Test nests wherever an Atlas note claims that one term carries another, including paths with multiple prior conditions or interrupted passage.

## Reads

Carry-Trace Test becomes recognisable where a proposed forward carry is accepted only after a downstream term can recover the prior condition and relevant passage through its trace.

Reckoning belongs at this point in the test. A forward carry must not be accepted simply because it is plausible, elegant, or useful. The carry becomes answerable only where the return trace can account for what the forward claim asks later terms or participants to bear.

The test asks:

1. Is the downstream term already available, or is it only anticipated?
2. Does the downstream term trace this prior term as a condition that had to hold?
3. What passage conditions allowed, shaped, delayed, blocked, or transformed the carrying?
4. Does the downstream term require several prior conditions rather than a single source?
5. If the anticipated condition did not appear, did carrying fail, or was passage interrupted?

The placement rule is:

```text
possible downstream continuation → opening
projected continuation from prior traces → prediction
downstream continuation with recoverable return trace → carry
retained returnable trace → memory
```

Prediction may direct a later check, but it does not establish a `Carries` link. Absence of an anticipated outcome does not alone establish absence of bearing; the passage must also be checked. A confirmed carry may remain unread for a time, but once claimed inside the Atlas it must be answerable to retrace.

The deeper warrant for the test is nesting location. A carry claimed without a recoverable trace leaves the nesting position of the carried term unresolved — it may be a genuine downstream term or a projection from outside the order. Running carry and trace simultaneously through the same passage is how a participant locates a pattern''s nesting position within the dependency order. The test is structural and not merely procedural: without it, the order cannot determine where a term sits.

## Carries

- [[Garden Pass]]

The test usually returns its result to the dependency links being checked. It carries Garden Pass where the Atlas is being tended as a garden, because a tending pass requires the carry-trace distinction before deciding whether to plant, prune, graft, clear, compost, wait, or release.','Carry Trace Test Carry Trace Test names the Atlas practice test that distinguishes confirmed downstream carrying from projected openings by requiring a recoverable return trace. It separates the order operating from the order known. Reality may carry a condition before any participant reads it. The Atlas does not create that carrying through recognition, but it grounds its own claim only where the downstream condition can be followed back through what made it available. Places Carry Trace Test places the Atlas practice test that distinguishes confirmed downstream carrying from projected openings by requiring a recoverable return trace. Holds Carry Trace Test is held by Atlas Note Standard, Dependency Order, Trace, and Retracing. Term placement, structural precedence, a followable path, and the checking act must be available before a carry claim can be grounded. Pairs Carry Trace Test is vertical. Carry and trace are two reading directions through one dependency relation, not a lateral pair: Traces Atlas Note Standard Dependency Order Trace Retracing Nests Carry Trace Test nests wherever an Atlas note claims that one term carries another, including paths with multiple prior conditions or interrupted passage. Reads Carry Trace Test becomes recognisable where a proposed forward carry is accepted only after a downstream term can recover the prior condition and relevant passage through its trace. Reckoning belongs at this point in the test. A forward carry must not be accepted simply because it is plausible, elegant, or useful. The carry becomes answerable only where the return trace can account for what the forward claim asks later terms or participants to bear. The test asks: 1. Is the downstream term already available, or is it only anticipated? 2. Does the downstream term trace this prior term as a condition that had to hold? 3. What passage conditions allowed, shaped, delayed, blocked, or transformed the carrying? 4. Does the downstream term require several prior conditions rather than a single source? 5. If the anticipated condition did not appear, did carrying fail, or was passage interrupted? The placement rule is: Prediction may direct a later check, but it does not establish a link. Absence of an anticipated outcome does not alone establish absence of bearing; the passage must also be checked. A confirmed carry may remain unread for a time, but once claimed inside the Atlas it must be answerable to retrace. The deeper warrant for the test is nesting location. A carry claimed without a recoverable trace leaves the nesting position of the carried term unresolved — it may be a genuine downstream term or a projection from outside the order. Running carry and trace simultaneously through the same passage is how a participant locates a pattern''s nesting position within the dependency order. The test is structural and not merely procedural: without it, the order cannot determine where a term sits. Carries Garden Pass The test usually returns its result to the dependency links being checked. It carries Garden Pass where the Atlas is being tended as a garden, because a tending pass requires the carry trace distinction before deciding whether to plant, prune, graft, clear, compost, wait, or release.','Carry Trace Test Carry Trace Test names the Atlas practice test that distinguishes confirmed downstream carrying from projected openings by requiring a recoverable return trace. It separates the…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.trace","ground.dependency-order","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.garden-pass","practice.retracing"]','{"holds":["practice.atlas-note-standard","ground.dependency-order","first.trace","practice.retracing"],"traces":["practice.atlas-note-standard","ground.dependency-order","first.trace","practice.retracing"],"carries":["practice.garden-pass"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',517,'sha256:72f2f7a2e585bf624474d3003ab5f437060e4333116e5084263a0e5ed36fe164','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.check','Check','check','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Check.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/check.html','# Check

Check names the Atlas practice of testing a term from both directions to locate its boundary. It does not prove a term as an object; it asks where the relation begins to hold, where it stops holding, and whether the term carries the strain that makes it worth preserving.

## Places

Check places the Atlas practice of testing a term from both directions to locate its boundary.

## Holds

Check is held by [[Practice]], [[Boundary]], [[Tracing]], and [[Retracing]].

## Pairs

Check pairs with [[Step]]. Check tests the boundary of a read; Step names the smallest answerable movement from it.

## Traces

- [[Terms and Conditions]]
- [[Atlas Note Standard]]
- [[Groundedness]]
- [[Practice]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Tracing]]
- [[Retracing]]
## Nests

Check nests where a read is tested from both directions until its boundary becomes clear.

## Reads

Check becomes recognisable where a term, note, or contribution is tested backward from the present read through trace, and projected forward only as openings until downstream retrace confirms carrying, so that its boundary becomes readable rather than assumed as a thing.

Reckoning is the structural obligation behind check: can this term bear what it is being asked to carry? Where a read may affect later terms, participants, or consequences, check keeps reasoning answerable rather than merely coherent.

The forward and backward movements have different evidential weight. A backward trace can test what had to hold for an available condition. A forward opening can guide attention or prediction, but it becomes a grounded carry only where a downstream condition can retrace the passage. [[Carry-Trace Test]] applies this distinction to note links.
## Carries

- [[Atlasing]]
- [[Discipline]]
- [[Garden Pass]]
- [[Reasoning]]','Check Check names the Atlas practice of testing a term from both directions to locate its boundary. It does not prove a term as an object; it asks where the relation begins to hold, where it stops holding, and whether the term carries the strain that makes it worth preserving. Places Check places the Atlas practice of testing a term from both directions to locate its boundary. Holds Check is held by Practice, Boundary, Tracing, and Retracing. Pairs Check pairs with Step. Check tests the boundary of a read; Step names the smallest answerable movement from it. Traces Terms and Conditions Atlas Note Standard Groundedness Practice Boundary Tracing Retracing Nests Check nests where a read is tested from both directions until its boundary becomes clear. Reads Check becomes recognisable where a term, note, or contribution is tested backward from the present read through trace, and projected forward only as openings until downstream retrace confirms carrying, so that its boundary becomes readable rather than assumed as a thing. Reckoning is the structural obligation behind check: can this term bear what it is being asked to carry? Where a read may affect later terms, participants, or consequences, check keeps reasoning answerable rather than merely coherent. The forward and backward movements have different evidential weight. A backward trace can test what had to hold for an available condition. A forward opening can guide attention or prediction, but it becomes a grounded carry only where a downstream condition can retrace the passage. Carry Trace Test applies this distinction to note links. Carries Atlasing Discipline Garden Pass Reasoning','Check Check names the Atlas practice of testing a term from both directions to locate its boundary. It does not prove a term as an object; it asks where the relation begins to hold, where it stops…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","ground.groundedness","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.atlasing","practice.discipline","practice.garden-pass","practice.practice","practice.reasoning","practice.retracing","practice.step","practice.terms-and-conditions","practice.tracing"]','{"holds":["practice.practice","first.boundary","practice.tracing","practice.retracing"],"traces":["practice.terms-and-conditions","practice.atlas-note-standard","ground.groundedness","practice.practice","first.boundary","practice.tracing","practice.retracing"],"carries":["practice.atlasing","practice.discipline","practice.garden-pass","practice.reasoning"],"pairs":["practice.step"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',263,'sha256:fcf2e2bd6df310357e502bd4c890ddae9c0916381db6fe848c7d5c7aec8a5752','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.composting','Composting','composting','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Composting.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/composting.html','# Composting

Composting names the garden practice of releasing failed or pruned material as doctrine while keeping what it taught available to the order.

Composting is not deletion. It is the practice of letting a claim stop carrying authority without erasing the trace of its failure. A failed posture can show what the order could not hold, what became shaded, where re-entry collapsed, or which dependency was missing.

## Places

Composting places the garden practice of releasing failed or pruned material as doctrine while keeping what it taught available to the order.

## Holds

Composting is held by [[Garden Pass]], [[Release]], and [[Root Resilience]]. A tending pass must identify the material, release must let the claim go, and root resilience must keep the failure from corrupting the dependency order.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Composting is a care action inside Garden Pass.

## Traces

- [[Garden Pass]]
- [[Release]]
- [[Root Resilience]]

## Nests

Composting nests inside Atlas Garden wherever failed postures, released claims, or pruned branch material can become learning without remaining doctrine.

## Reads

Composting becomes recognisable where failed material is released from carrying authority but retained as traceable learning about what could not hold, carry, place, clear, or clean.

The composting question is:

```text
What claim must stop carrying?
What did the failure reveal?
What trace should remain so the failure can teach?
What needs to be released so the root can stay clean?
```

## Carries

No downstream carries are claimed yet.','Composting Composting names the garden practice of releasing failed or pruned material as doctrine while keeping what it taught available to the order. Composting is not deletion. It is the practice of letting a claim stop carrying authority without erasing the trace of its failure. A failed posture can show what the order could not hold, what became shaded, where re entry collapsed, or which dependency was missing. Places Composting places the garden practice of releasing failed or pruned material as doctrine while keeping what it taught available to the order. Holds Composting is held by Garden Pass, Release, and Root Resilience. A tending pass must identify the material, release must let the claim go, and root resilience must keep the failure from corrupting the dependency order. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Composting is a care action inside Garden Pass. Traces Garden Pass Release Root Resilience Nests Composting nests inside Atlas Garden wherever failed postures, released claims, or pruned branch material can become learning without remaining doctrine. Reads Composting becomes recognisable where failed material is released from carrying authority but retained as traceable learning about what could not hold, carry, place, clear, or clean. The composting question is: Carries No downstream carries are claimed yet.','Composting Composting names the garden practice of releasing failed or pruned material as doctrine while keeping what it taught available to the order. Composting is not deletion.','working','tending',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.release","practice.garden-pass","practice.root-resilience"]','{"holds":["practice.garden-pass","first.release","practice.root-resilience"],"traces":["practice.garden-pass","first.release","practice.root-resilience"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',206,'sha256:88217038b1700b1a1fd04bec0cec3c6136cbcee7bd88a0627a0ec7004d4a4f22','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.contend','Contend','contend','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Contend.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/contend.html','# Contend

Contend names tending under strain, pressure, resistance, or competing claim.

Contending is not simply fighting. It is tending where care has to meet opposition without dropping the relation. A participant may contend with a limit, a pressure, an argument, a wound, a competing claim, or a condition that resists simple maintenance.

## Places

Contend places tending under strain, pressure, resistance, or competing claim.

## Holds

Contend is held by [[Tend]], [[Strain]], [[Pressure]], [[Resistance]], and [[Boundary]]. A relation must be tended, and that tending must meet pressure or opposition at a boundary, before contending can be named.

## Pairs

Contend pairs with [[Tend]]. Tend names care applied through attended practice; Contend names the same care where resistance must be met without losing relation.

## Traces

- [[Tend]]
- [[Strain]]
- [[Pressure]]
- [[Resistance]]
- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Contend nests within practice where care has to hold through opposition, pressure, or competing claim.

## Reads

Contend becomes readable where tending cannot continue by simple maintenance, because pressure, resistance, or competing claim must be met and carried at a boundary.

Contend becomes unsafe where the relation is dropped and only force remains. It remains answerable where resistance is met in a way that preserves or clarifies the relation being tended.

## Carries

Contend carries no further public branch at this scope.','Contend Contend names tending under strain, pressure, resistance, or competing claim. Contending is not simply fighting. It is tending where care has to meet opposition without dropping the relation. A participant may contend with a limit, a pressure, an argument, a wound, a competing claim, or a condition that resists simple maintenance. Places Contend places tending under strain, pressure, resistance, or competing claim. Holds Contend is held by Tend, Strain, Pressure, Resistance, and Boundary. A relation must be tended, and that tending must meet pressure or opposition at a boundary, before contending can be named. Pairs Contend pairs with Tend. Tend names care applied through attended practice; Contend names the same care where resistance must be met without losing relation. Traces Tend Strain Pressure Resistance Boundary Nests Contend nests within practice where care has to hold through opposition, pressure, or competing claim. Reads Contend becomes readable where tending cannot continue by simple maintenance, because pressure, resistance, or competing claim must be met and carried at a boundary. Contend becomes unsafe where the relation is dropped and only force remains. It remains answerable where resistance is met in a way that preserves or clarifies the relation being tended. Carries Contend carries no further public branch at this scope.','Contend Contend names tending under strain, pressure, resistance, or competing claim. Contending is not simply fighting.','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.strain","practice.tend","second.pressure","second.resistance"]','{"holds":["practice.tend","first.strain","second.pressure","second.resistance","first.boundary"],"traces":["practice.tend","first.strain","second.pressure","second.resistance","first.boundary"],"carries":[],"pairs":["practice.tend"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"}