INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.discipline','Discipline','discipline','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Discipline.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/discipline.html','# Discipline

Discipline names practice constrained by a standard, scope, and retraceable correction. In Reality Mechanics, discipline is what keeps practice from becoming mere preference, fluency, or accumulation.

## Places

Discipline places practice constrained by a standard, scope, and retraceable correction.

## Holds

Discipline is held by [[Practice]], [[Closure Scope]], [[Atlas Note Standard]], and [[Check]].

## Pairs

Discipline pairs with [[Practice]]. Discipline gives the ordered constraint through which practice remains answerable.

## Traces

- [[Practice]]
- [[Restraint]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Atlas Note Standard]]
- [[Check]]
- [[Attend]]

## Nests

Discipline nests within higher-order or practice conditions.

## Reads

Discipline becomes recognisable where practice remains answerable to a standard and can be checked, corrected, and retraced within a scope.

## Carries

- [[Reality Mechanics]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]','Discipline Discipline names practice constrained by a standard, scope, and retraceable correction. In Reality Mechanics, discipline is what keeps practice from becoming mere preference, fluency, or accumulation. Places Discipline places practice constrained by a standard, scope, and retraceable correction. Holds Discipline is held by Practice, Closure Scope, Atlas Note Standard, and Check. Pairs Discipline pairs with Practice. Discipline gives the ordered constraint through which practice remains answerable. Traces Practice Restraint Closure Scope Atlas Note Standard Check Attend Nests Discipline nests within higher order or practice conditions. Reads Discipline becomes recognisable where practice remains answerable to a standard and can be checked, corrected, and retraced within a scope. Carries Reality Mechanics Atlas Practice','Discipline Discipline names practice constrained by a standard, scope, and retraceable correction. In Reality Mechanics, discipline is what keeps practice from becoming mere preference, fluency,…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.attend","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.atlas-practice","practice.check","practice.practice","practice.reality-mechanics","second.closure-scope","third.restraint"]','{"holds":["practice.practice","second.closure-scope","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.check"],"traces":["practice.practice","third.restraint","second.closure-scope","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.check","first.attend"],"carries":["practice.reality-mechanics","practice.atlas-practice"],"pairs":["practice.practice"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',112,'sha256:892951fe9b2092519863c4722249a283f361fa6caec36a30fec4ce90caf276e9','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.garden-pass','Garden Pass','garden-pass','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Garden Pass.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/garden-pass.html','# Garden Pass

Garden Pass names a repeatable tending pass through an Atlas growth: identify it, trace what holds it, test what it carries, name shade, test whether resolution rate improved, and choose the next care action.

The pass is deliberately ordinary. It keeps the garden read from becoming a metaphor without practice.

```text
1. Identify the growth.
2. Trace what holds it.
3. Test what it claims to carry.
4. Name what it shades or what shades it.
5. Ask whether the growth preserves generative trace or shows degenerative trace.
6. Ask whether the pass improved resolution rate.
7. Name the garden status and choose the next care action.
```

The possible care actions are:

```text
plant     place as a working read
tend      return and adjust conditions
prune     remove drift or overgrowth
graft     connect to the support it actually traces
clear     remove shade so order can be read
compost   keep failed material as learning
wait      leave ungrounded or working until a trace appears
release   remove the claim without erasing what it taught
```

## Places

Garden Pass places a repeatable tending pass through an Atlas growth: identify it, trace what holds it, test what it carries, name shade, and choose the next care action.

## Holds

Garden Pass is held by [[Atlas Garden]], [[Check]], [[Carry-Trace Test]], and [[Resolution Rate]]. The garden must provide the care frame, Check must locate the boundary of the growth, Carry-Trace Test must distinguish confirmed carries from openings, and Resolution Rate must keep tending answerable to cleaner continuation rather than mere speed.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Garden Pass is a repeated care movement inside Atlas Garden.

## Traces

- [[Atlas Garden]]
- [[Check]]
- [[Carry-Trace Test]]
- [[Resolution Rate]]

## Nests

Garden Pass nests inside Atlas Garden as the ordinary pass for tending a term, branch, posture, domain, applied read, or failed growth.

## Reads

Garden Pass becomes recognisable where a participant can return to one growth and ask:

```text
What is this growth?
What holds it?
What does it claim to carry?
What does it shade?
What shades it?
Can it be re-entered?
Does it preserve generative trace?
Does it show degenerative trace?
Did this pass increase resolution rate?
What garden status names its current care state?
What care action keeps the Atlas alive?
```

The pass does not force every growth to become stable. Some growths remain working. Some are left ungrounded. Some are composted as failed postures. The test is not whether the growth is impressive or whether the edit was fast; the test is whether the Atlas can keep its relation, trace, re-entry, and next continuation clean enough to tend.

Where continuation or repair is specifically at issue, [[Generate and Regenerate]] can be used inside a Garden Pass to test whether the growth preserves generative trace, shows degenerative trace, or only records what happened.

## Carries

- [[Garden Status]]
- [[Shade Clearing]]
- [[Pruning]]
- [[Grafting]]
- [[Composting]]','Garden Pass Garden Pass names a repeatable tending pass through an Atlas growth: identify it, trace what holds it, test what it carries, name shade, test whether resolution rate improved, and choose the next care action. The pass is deliberately ordinary. It keeps the garden read from becoming a metaphor without practice. The possible care actions are: Places Garden Pass places a repeatable tending pass through an Atlas growth: identify it, trace what holds it, test what it carries, name shade, and choose the next care action. Holds Garden Pass is held by Atlas Garden, Check, Carry Trace Test, and Resolution Rate. The garden must provide the care frame, Check must locate the boundary of the growth, Carry Trace Test must distinguish confirmed carries from openings, and Resolution Rate must keep tending answerable to cleaner continuation rather than mere speed. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Garden Pass is a repeated care movement inside Atlas Garden. Traces Atlas Garden Check Carry Trace Test Resolution Rate Nests Garden Pass nests inside Atlas Garden as the ordinary pass for tending a term, branch, posture, domain, applied read, or failed growth. Reads Garden Pass becomes recognisable where a participant can return to one growth and ask: The pass does not force every growth to become stable. Some growths remain working. Some are left ungrounded. Some are composted as failed postures. The test is not whether the growth is impressive or whether the edit was fast; the test is whether the Atlas can keep its relation, trace, re entry, and next continuation clean enough to tend. Where continuation or repair is specifically at issue, Generate and Regenerate can be used inside a Garden Pass to test whether the growth preserves generative trace, shows degenerative trace, or only records what happened. Carries Garden Status Shade Clearing Pruning Grafting Composting','Garden Pass Garden Pass names a repeatable tending pass through an Atlas growth: identify it, trace what holds it, test what it carries, name shade, test whether resolution rate improved, and…','working','tending',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["practice.atlas-garden","practice.carry-trace-test","practice.check","practice.composting","practice.garden-status","practice.grafting","practice.pruning","practice.shade-clearing","second.resolution-rate"]','{"holds":["practice.atlas-garden","practice.check","practice.carry-trace-test","second.resolution-rate"],"traces":["practice.atlas-garden","practice.check","practice.carry-trace-test","second.resolution-rate"],"carries":["practice.garden-status","practice.shade-clearing","practice.pruning","practice.grafting","practice.composting"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',304,'sha256:75026bba19ddfc1addea2dc3931bc9501206a17fc76b876c0c0eacb98474f740','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.garden-status','Garden Status','garden-status','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Garden Status.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/garden-status.html','# Garden Status

Garden Status names the garden-care state of an Atlas growth: how a placed term, branch, posture, or read is being tended without treating uncertainty as outside the Atlas.

Garden Status does not decide whether a growth is allowed to exist. If a term can be placed and tended, it belongs in the Atlas as living structure. Garden Status names how that living structure is being cared for.

[[Groundedness]] remains the root-contact check: whether the growth remains answerable to what holds it. Garden Status is the visible care state around that check.

In note metadata, `garden_status` may name this care state directly. It should not replace `status`, `grounded`, or the note''s declared structure; it tells a participant how to tend the growth next.

When no individual garden pass has yet been made, a conservative default may be used: stable notes can be marked `rooted`, working notes can be marked `planted`, and active care practices can be marked `tending`. Later passes may revise these care states without changing whether the note belongs to the Atlas.

## Places

Garden Status places the garden-care state of an Atlas growth: how a placed term, branch, posture, or read is being tended without treating uncertainty as outside the Atlas.

## Holds

Garden Status is held by [[Atlas Garden]], [[Garden Pass]], and [[Groundedness]]. The garden must provide the care frame, a tending pass must locate the growth, and groundedness must remain the root-contact check rather than a public permission badge.

## Pairs

Garden Status pairs with approval status. Garden Status names care state; approval status treats placement as permission.

## Traces

- [[Atlas Garden]]
- [[Garden Pass]]
- [[Groundedness]]
- [[Root Resilience]]

## Nests

Garden Status nests inside Atlas Garden as the care vocabulary for growths that are placed, rooted, tending, shading, grafted, pruned, composting, dormant, or invasive.

The current working statuses are:

```text
planted     placed as living structure, still finding its clean carries
rooted      dependable enough to support nearby growth, still alive and revisable
tending     needs return, checking, spacing, or clearer support
shading     obscuring another growth or being obscured by one
grafted     reattached to the support it actually traces
pruned      reduced so the order can breathe and re-enter
composting  released as doctrine while kept as learning
dormant     placed but not currently developing
invasive    over-carrying beyond support or crowding the root system
```

## Reads

Garden Status becomes recognisable where a term or branch is inside the Atlas and needs its care state named so the Atlas can tend uncertainty through order.

This changes the entry question from "is this final enough to be admitted?" to:

```text
Can this growth be placed?
What holds it?
What care state is it in?
What does it need next?
```

## Carries

