INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.participant','Participant','participant','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Participant.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/participant.html','# Participant

Participant names anyone or any system taking part in Reality Mechanics by using, questioning, testing, or contributing to the Atlas. Participation becomes practice where the participant repeats the work with enough attention for correction to remain available.

## Places

Participant places anyone or any system taking part in Reality Mechanics by using, questioning, testing, or contributing to the Atlas.

## Holds

Participant is held by [[Participation]] and [[Reality Mechanics]].

## Pairs

Participant pairs with [[Atlas Practice]]. Participant names the one who takes part; Atlas Practice names the discipline that keeps participation retraceable.

## Traces

- [[Participation]]
- [[Reality Mechanics]]

## Nests

Participant nests as the one taking part in Atlas Practice.

## Reads

Participant becomes recognisable where a person, AI, practice, or system engages the Atlas in a way that can affect reading, placement, correction, or contribution.

A participant is not included by claim alone and not excluded for being unfinished. Participation becomes readable where contribution can enter with enough boundary, trace, and correction to remain answerable.

Participation does not by itself confer grounding authority. A person, AI, or system may contribute to tracing and checking; an AI or automated system does not ground a note on its own. Grounding remains an accountable participant judgement rather than an output state inferred from fluent participation.

## Carries

- [[Practice]]','Participant Participant names anyone or any system taking part in Reality Mechanics by using, questioning, testing, or contributing to the Atlas. Participation becomes practice where the participant repeats the work with enough attention for correction to remain available. Places Participant places anyone or any system taking part in Reality Mechanics by using, questioning, testing, or contributing to the Atlas. Holds Participant is held by Participation and Reality Mechanics. Pairs Participant pairs with Atlas Practice. Participant names the one who takes part; Atlas Practice names the discipline that keeps participation retraceable. Traces Participation Reality Mechanics Nests Participant nests as the one taking part in Atlas Practice. Reads Participant becomes recognisable where a person, AI, practice, or system engages the Atlas in a way that can affect reading, placement, correction, or contribution. A participant is not included by claim alone and not excluded for being unfinished. Participation becomes readable where contribution can enter with enough boundary, trace, and correction to remain answerable. Participation does not by itself confer grounding authority. A person, AI, or system may contribute to tracing and checking; an AI or automated system does not ground a note on its own. Grounding remains an accountable participant judgement rather than an output state inferred from fluent participation. Carries Practice','Participant Participant names anyone or any system taking part in Reality Mechanics by using, questioning, testing, or contributing to the Atlas. Participation becomes practice where the…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["practice.atlas-practice","practice.practice","practice.reality-mechanics","second.participation"]','{"holds":["second.participation","practice.reality-mechanics"],"traces":["second.participation","practice.reality-mechanics"],"carries":["practice.practice"],"pairs":["practice.atlas-practice"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',209,'sha256:6870d3406a19853bfd89db23fc3486be9e2fcbaa94131752d69a6803fd5eecf8','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.posture-read','Posture Read','posture-read','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Posture Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/posture-read.html','# Posture Read

Posture Read names a versioned order experiment: a postulate can be read as a posture of relation.

A posture is not a proof and not a doctrine. It is how relation is held toward relation so that an order can become constructible. In this read, Euclid is useful as an exemplar because his postulates show relation entering a constructible order. Reality Mechanics does not copy geometry; it asks what kind of relational posture lets an order become traceable, comparable, correctable, and re-enterable.

Posture Read is planted rather than rooted. It gives the Atlas a tended place to grow, compare, test, fail, graft, or compost postulate experiments without mistaking the experiment for the root system.

The current experimental sequence is:

```text
Connection
Posture
Structure
Clear
Clean
```

This does not replace [[Hold]], [[Carry]], and [[Place]]. It tests whether those operations are better understood as what a posture of relation does when it begins to generate order:

```text
relation holds as connection
connection is oriented as posture
posture carries as structure
structure becomes clear where it can be followed
clear structure becomes clean where it carries without residue
```

## Places

Posture Read places a versioned order experiment that reads postulate as posture: an act of relation through which connection can become structure, clear, and clean.

## Holds

Posture Read is held by [[Posture]] and [[Atlas Practice]]. Posture must be available as the orientating condition, and Atlas Practice must hold the discipline that lets the experiment be traced, tested, revised, or rejected.

## Pairs

Carry-Trace Test stands beside Posture Read as its practice check. Posture Read proposes an order; [[Carry-Trace Test]] checks whether its carries return by trace.

## Traces

- [[Posture]]
- [[Atlas Practice]]
- [[Connection]]
- [[Structure]]
- [[Clear]]
- [[Clean]]
- [[Structural Disorder]]

## Nests

Posture Read nests inside Atlas Practice as a working order experiment, not as a replacement for the Atlas or a final doctrine.

It gives the Atlas somewhere to keep alternative or failed postures. A failed posture is not discarded as useless; it shows what the order cannot carry, where re-entry collapses, what becomes shaded, and which dependency cannot be made clean.

## Reads

Posture Read becomes recognisable where a postulate is treated as a posture of relation: not a belief to defend, but an orientation through which relation becomes constructible, readable, and retraceable.

In this read, disorder is not a positive thing beside order. Disorder is shaded order: order under loss, occlusion, interruption, residue, or unreadability. [[Structural Disorder]] is therefore not an alternate substance; it is where dependency order can no longer be cleanly retraced.

A posture can be located within a nested order by running carry and trace simultaneously. Carrying forward shows what the posture enables; tracing backward shows what holds it. Nesting ambiguity — where a posture''s position in the order is unclear — resolves where both directions can be followed through the same passage. A posture whose carry cannot be backtraced, or whose trace cannot be carried forward, has not yet found its nesting position. The practice of running both directions is not supplementary to the posture test; it is how a participant determines where in the order a posture actually sits.

The read remains working. It may clarify the Atlas, distort it, or fail. Its value is that the failure can be traced.

## Carries

