INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.pruning','Pruning','pruning','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Pruning.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/pruning.html','# Pruning

Pruning names the garden practice of removing drift, overgrowth, or misplaced carrying without treating branch correction as root replacement.

Pruning is not punishment and not rejection of growth. It is care applied where a growth has begun to shade, overload, distort, or detach from the order that lets it carry.

## Places

Pruning places the garden practice of removing drift, overgrowth, or misplaced carrying without treating branch correction as root replacement.

## Holds

Pruning is held by [[Garden Pass]], [[Root Resilience]], and [[Structural Disorder]]. A tending pass must locate the growth, roots must remain resilient enough to withstand branch correction, and structural disorder must name the dependency loss being pruned.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Pruning is a care action inside Garden Pass.

## Traces

- [[Garden Pass]]
- [[Root Resilience]]
- [[Structural Disorder]]

## Nests

Pruning nests inside Atlas Garden wherever branch growth obscures, distorts, overloads, or detaches from what holds it.

## Reads

Pruning becomes recognisable where correction removes drift or overgrowth while preserving the dependency order that lets the branch be re-entered or released.

The pruning question is:

```text
What growth is exceeding its support?
What root, trunk, or branch is it shading?
What can be removed without losing the living trace?
What must be released because it no longer answers to what holds it?
```

## Carries

No downstream carries are claimed yet.','Pruning Pruning names the garden practice of removing drift, overgrowth, or misplaced carrying without treating branch correction as root replacement. Pruning is not punishment and not rejection of growth. It is care applied where a growth has begun to shade, overload, distort, or detach from the order that lets it carry. Places Pruning places the garden practice of removing drift, overgrowth, or misplaced carrying without treating branch correction as root replacement. Holds Pruning is held by Garden Pass, Root Resilience, and Structural Disorder. A tending pass must locate the growth, roots must remain resilient enough to withstand branch correction, and structural disorder must name the dependency loss being pruned. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Pruning is a care action inside Garden Pass. Traces Garden Pass Root Resilience Structural Disorder Nests Pruning nests inside Atlas Garden wherever branch growth obscures, distorts, overloads, or detaches from what holds it. Reads Pruning becomes recognisable where correction removes drift or overgrowth while preserving the dependency order that lets the branch be re entered or released. The pruning question is: Carries No downstream carries are claimed yet.','Pruning Pruning names the garden practice of removing drift, overgrowth, or misplaced carrying without treating branch correction as root replacement. Pruning is not punishment and not rejection…','working','tending',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.structural-disorder","practice.garden-pass","practice.root-resilience"]','{"holds":["practice.garden-pass","practice.root-resilience","ground.structural-disorder"],"traces":["practice.garden-pass","practice.root-resilience","ground.structural-disorder"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',183,'sha256:5533a789aa93ab3a109701f2ea6b33fc01a011b65bcdc90fbbb8f8d33283482d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.reality-bearing-connection','Reality-Bearing Connection','reality-bearing-connection','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Reality-Bearing Connection.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/reality-bearing-connection.html','# Reality-Bearing Connection

Reality-Bearing Connection names a connection that can carry reality through trace, read, bearing, and retrace. It may link information, but it must also remain returnable to what supports it. This is the value held by the Atlas: not the mapped body as an object, but the connection that can still answer to reality.

A reality-bearing connection keeps relation readable, traceable, and answerable across fields without flattening the fields into each other.

Reality-bearing relation is coupled enough to participate, and nested enough to be ordered. Coupling gives connection; nesting gives dependency order. Connection without nesting becomes flat; nesting without coupling becomes detached. A reality-bearing connection requires both: connection enough to participate, and asymmetry enough to remain traceable.

## Places

Reality-Bearing Connection places a connection that can carry reality through trace, read, bearing, and retrace.

## Holds

Reality-Bearing Connection is held by [[Atlas]], [[Bearing]], and [[Retrace Read|Retrace]].

## Pairs

Reality-Bearing Connection is vertical. It names a connection that can carry reality through trace, read, bearing, and retrace, and carries this forward into [[Atlasing]]. Reality-Bearing Connection holds [[Atlas]], [[Bearing]], and [[Retrace Read]] — it is the upstream condition that makes Atlasing available. There is no lateral co-present condition that Reality-Bearing Connection requires and that requires it in return at this order.

## Traces

- [[Atlas]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Retrace Read|Retrace]]

## Nests

Reality-Bearing Connection nests where notes, terms, supports, reads, and retraces carry reality rather than mere information.

## Reads

Reality-Bearing Connection becomes recognisable where a link, placement, or relation is coupled enough to participate and nested enough to be ordered, so it can be followed back through what supports it and still carry the reality it claims to connect.

## Carries

- [[Atlasing]]
