planted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.read","first.trace","practice.atlas-practice","practice.check","practice.order-trace","practice.practice"]','{"holds":["first.read","first.trace","practice.practice","practice.order-trace","practice.check"],"traces":["first.read","first.trace","practice.practice","practice.order-trace","practice.check"],"carries":["practice.atlas-practice"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":3,"text":"Thinking And Reckoning","anchor":"thinking-and-reckoning"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',579,'sha256:b5025ffedfc7cab11314c27632fa68db20b38bab1baf73c8ac0fbaee88cbedb2','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.retrace-practice','Retrace Practice','retrace-practice','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Retrace Practice.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/retrace-practice.html','# Retrace Practice

Retrace Practice names the Atlas [[Practice]] of recovering the dependency path that produced the current read.

Reality Mechanics is the discipline through which retraceable dependency is mapped.

This folder contains the practices, discipline notes, memory notes, runtime notes, and drift checks that keep the Atlas retraceable.

Retrace can use storage or archives, but it is not defined by them. It is the practice of preserving access back through trace, dependency, bearing, relation, and ground.

## Places

Retrace Practice places the Atlas [[Practice]] of recovering the dependency path that produced the current read.

## Holds

Retrace Practice is held by [[Trace]], [[Ground]], [[Relation]], [[Reality Mechanics]], and [[Practice]].

## Pairs

Retrace Practice pairs with [[Order Trace]]. Order Trace follows the dependency movement forward; Retrace Practice recovers it backward. Each requires the other: the forward path is only nameable against the possibility of returning through it; the return is only possible where a forward path was laid.

## Traces

- [[Regenerate]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Ground]]
- [[Relation]]
- [[Reality Mechanics]]
- [[Practice]]
- [[Root Resilience]]
- [[Higher Order Crossing|Threshold (Higher → Atlas Practice)]]

## Nests

Retrace Practice nests within higher-order or practice conditions.

## Reads

Retrace Practice becomes recognisable where a note, branch, domain, or release can show how it became available and what dependency path carries it.

It is read where the Atlas can still recover the path, not only preserve information.

## Carries

- [[Tracing]]
- [[Retracing]]
