relation becomes readable, countable, comparable, or diagnosable. Holds Section is held by Practice and Readability. A participant must be in practice, and reading must be possible, before a cut made for reading can be named. It is not held by Boundary: a section can be cut where no boundary holds, so Boundary is what a section is answerable to, not what it requires. Section does not hold relation open; relation and connection do not require sectioning. Pairs No single lateral pair is placed. Section is a participant enactment alongside Carrying and Retracing — carry enacted, trace followed, boundary cut — and stands to Boundary as enactment to condition. The three enactments share the condition to enactment grammar but differ at fidelity: carrying continues a carry that holds and retracing follows a trace that holds, while a section can be made where no boundary holds. That is why a section is answerable to Check — tested from both directions against the boundary it follows, crosses, or hides — rather than trusted as carrying and retracing can be. Traces Practice Readability Nests Section nests among the practice level read operations as the cut that makes a part readable. It is answerable to the Boundary it cuts relative to and to the Scope within which the resulting read holds, without becoming a condition in relation itself. Other read conditions operate on what a section has isolated: Scope and Closure Scope bound where the sectioned read holds and can be evaluated; Measure compares the units a section produces against a unit or scale; Evaluation assesses the sectioned read; Diagnosis follows real trace through a part a section has isolated. Section is upstream of each as the cut they read, not the same operation. Reads Section becomes recognisable where a participant cuts relation into a part that can be read, counted, compared, or diagnosed, and where that cut can itself be tested against the boundary it follows, crosses, or hides. It also becomes recognisable at its failure: where a cut is treated as a boundary relation holds, where sections are treated as fundamental units, or where an inspected sequence of sections is mistaken for the generative connection. In each case a participant''s cut has been read back into relation as if relation had made it. Carries No grounded downstream carry claimed yet.','Section Section names a participant''s analytic cut through which part of relation becomes readable, countable, comparable, or diagnosable. Section is not a condition within relation.','working','planted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","practice.practice","practice.retracing","second.carrying","second.readability"]','{"holds":["practice.practice","second.readability"],"traces":["practice.practice","second.readability"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.carrying","practice.retracing","first.boundary"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',701,'sha256:eec50c3df413750e6364f6bee5719f85d219eae2d367994d743e66bf31506f56','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.shade-clearing','Shade Clearing','shade-clearing','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Shade Clearing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/shade-clearing.html','# Shade Clearing

Shade Clearing names the garden practice of restoring readability where order is present but shaded by crowding, residue, missing trace, misplaced support, or overgrowth.

Shade is not badness and not a rival substance. Shade is order under occlusion. Clearing shade does not attack the growth; it restores the conditions by which the growth, its support, and its effects can be read.

## Places

Shade Clearing places the garden practice of restoring readability where order is present but shaded by crowding, residue, missing trace, misplaced support, or overgrowth.

## Holds

Shade Clearing is held by [[Garden Pass]], [[Structural Disorder]], [[Clear]], and [[Clean]]. A tending pass must locate the shaded growth, structural disorder must name the loss of dependency readability, clear must make the path readable, and clean must keep the correction from carrying residue.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Shade Clearing is a care action inside Garden Pass.

## Traces

- [[Garden Pass]]
- [[Structural Disorder]]
- [[Clear]]
- [[Clean]]

## Nests

Shade Clearing nests inside Atlas Garden wherever order is present but cannot be read cleanly enough for re-entry.

## Reads

Shade Clearing becomes recognisable where correction removes obscuring growth, residue, missing trace, or misplaced support so an order can be re-entered without treating shade as a separate thing.

The clearing question is:

```text
What order is present here?
What prevents it from being read?
Is the shade caused by missing trace, crowding, residue, misplaced support, or overgrowth?
What can be pruned, grafted, spaced, composted, or left working so re-entry returns?
```

## Carries

No downstream carries are claimed yet. Shade Clearing is a care action; later carries should be added only where a repeated clearing practice becomes a distinct retraceable continuation.','Shade Clearing Shade Clearing names the garden practice of restoring readability where order is present but shaded by crowding, residue, missing trace, misplaced support, or overgrowth. Shade is not badness and not a rival substance. Shade is order under occlusion. Clearing shade does not attack the growth; it restores the conditions by which the growth, its support, and its effects can be read. Places Shade Clearing places the garden practice of restoring readability where order is present but shaded by crowding, residue, missing trace, misplaced support, or overgrowth. Holds Shade Clearing is held by Garden Pass, Structural Disorder, Clear, and Clean. A tending pass must locate the shaded growth, structural disorder must name the loss of dependency readability, clear must make the path readable, and clean must keep the correction from carrying residue. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Shade Clearing is a care action inside Garden Pass. Traces Garden Pass Structural Disorder Clear Clean Nests Shade Clearing nests inside Atlas Garden wherever order is present but cannot be read cleanly enough for re entry. Reads Shade Clearing becomes recognisable where correction removes obscuring growth, residue, missing trace, or misplaced support so an order can be re entered without treating shade as a separate thing. The clearing question is: Carries No downstream carries are claimed yet. Shade Clearing is a care action; later carries should be added only where a repeated clearing practice becomes a distinct retraceable continuation.','Shade Clearing Shade Clearing names the garden practice of restoring readability where order is present but shaded by crowding, residue, missing trace, misplaced support, or overgrowth. Shade is…','working','tending',0,'practice','practice',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.clean","first.clear","ground.structural-disorder","practice.garden-pass"]','{"holds":["practice.garden-pass","ground.structural-disorder","first.clear","first.clean"],"traces":["practice.garden-pass","ground.structural-disorder","first.clear","first.clean"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',238,'sha256:93334e6d5a0173abd0607f87ae0e454e0f84c6c7e7f39bf82a9ac6463fc951a3','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.step','Step','step','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Step.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/step.html','# Step

Step names the smallest answerable movement opened by a read. Where [[Read]] makes a traced distinction meaningful, Step names the nearest placed movement through which the read is carried without exceeding what the trace supports.

Step is carrying made local as movement: the first placed movement by which a read enters practice while remaining answerable to dependency. It may support progress, but it does not require progress or completion.

## Places

Step places the smallest answerable movement opened by a read.

## Holds

Step is held by [[Read]], [[Trace]], [[Carrying]], and [[Practice]].

## Pairs

Step pairs with [[Check]]. Check tests the boundary of a read from both directions; Step names the smallest answerable movement that boundary opens. Each requires the other: Check without Step has located a boundary but not moved from it; Step without Check has moved without establishing that the boundary held.

## Traces

- [[Read]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Practice]]
- [[Count]]

## Nests

Step nests where practice becomes small enough to be answerable.

## Reads

Step becomes recognisable where a read opens a next movement small enough to stay with the trace and real enough to carry the read in practice.

## Carries

- [[Atlas Practice]]

[[Place]] and [[Learning]] may follow from a step in practice, but they are not carried by Step as dependency descendants.','Step Step names the smallest answerable movement opened by a read. Where Read makes a traced distinction meaningful, Step names the nearest placed movement through which the read is carried without exceeding what the trace supports. Step is carrying made local as movement: the first placed movement by which a read enters practice while remaining answerable to dependency. It may support progress, but it does not require progress or completion. Places Step places the smallest answerable movement opened by a read. Holds Step is held by Read, Trace, Carrying, and Practice. Pairs Step pairs with Check. Check tests the boundary of a read from both directions; Step names the smallest answerable movement that boundary opens. Each requires the other: Check without Step has located a boundary but not moved from it; Step without Check has moved without establishing that the boundary held. Traces Read Trace Carrying Practice Count Nests Step nests where practice becomes small enough to be answerable. Reads Step becomes recognisable where a read opens a next movement small enough to stay with the trace and real enough to carry the read in practice. Carries Atlas Practice Place and Learning may follow from a step in practice, but they are not carried by Step as dependency descendants.','Step Step names the smallest answerable movement opened by a read. Where Read makes a traced distinction meaningful, Step names the nearest placed movement through which the read is carried…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.read","first.trace","practice.atlas-practice","practice.check","practice.practice","second.carrying","second.count"]','{"holds":["first.read","first.trace","second.carrying","practice.practice"],"traces":["first.read","first.trace","second.carrying","practice.practice","second.count"],"carries":["practice.atlas-practice"],"pairs":["practice.check"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',209,'sha256:ed08992a1c86b5ec831ff6e704d75b9dc81767f804b0181e4b7acbdb0c7c16e1','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.tend','Tend','tend','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Tend.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/tend.html','# Tend

Tend names care applied through attended practice so a relation can keep carrying.

To tend is to stay with a relation, notice what it requires, and adjust conditions so its carrying can continue. It is not care as feeling alone. It is care made active through return.

## Places

Tend places care applied through attended practice so a relation can keep carrying.

## Holds

Tend is held by [[Practice]], [[Care]], [[Attend]], [[Recurrence]], and [[Maintained Coupling]]. Practice must be attended, care must preserve availability, and return must be recurrent enough for tending to be read.

## Pairs

Tend pairs with [[Contend]]. Tend names care applied through attended practice; Contend names tending where care must meet pressure, resistance, or competing claim without dropping relation.

## Traces

- [[Practice]]
- [[Care]]
- [[Attend]]
- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Maintained Coupling]]

## Nests

Tend nests within practice as the recurrent care through which relation remains available and carried.

## Reads

Tend becomes readable where attention does not only notice a relation, but returns to adjust conditions so the relation can keep holding.

In a garden, tending may prune, water, shelter, feed, weed, stake, or wait. In a relation, it may listen, repair, restrain, return, clarify, or give space. The action changes with the field; the structure is recurrent care preserving availability through relation.

## Carries

Tend carries [[Contend]] — tending where care must meet pressure, resistance, or competing claim without abandoning the relation it is trying to preserve.

- [[Contend]]
- [[Atlas Garden]]','Tend Tend names care applied through attended practice so a relation can keep carrying. To tend is to stay with a relation, notice what it requires, and adjust conditions so its carrying can continue. It is not care as feeling alone. It is care made active through return. Places Tend places care applied through attended practice so a relation can keep carrying. Holds Tend is held by Practice, Care, Attend, Recurrence, and Maintained Coupling. Practice must be attended, care must preserve availability, and return must be recurrent enough for tending to be read. Pairs Tend pairs with Contend. Tend names care applied through attended practice; Contend names tending where care must meet pressure, resistance, or competing claim without dropping relation. Traces Practice Care Attend Recurrence Maintained Coupling Nests Tend nests within practice as the recurrent care through which relation remains available and carried. Reads Tend becomes readable where attention does not only notice a relation, but returns to adjust conditions so the relation can keep holding. In a garden, tending may prune, water, shelter, feed, weed, stake, or wait. In a relation, it may listen, repair, restrain, return, clarify, or give space. The action changes with the field; the structure is recurrent care preserving availability through relation. Carries Tend carries Contend — tending where care must meet pressure, resistance, or competing claim without abandoning the relation it is trying to preserve. Contend Atlas Garden','Tend Tend names care applied through attended practice so a relation can keep carrying. To tend is to stay with a relation, notice what it requires, and adjust conditions so its carrying can continue.','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.attend","practice.atlas-garden","practice.contend","practice.practice","second.recurrence","third.care","third.maintained-coupling"]','{"holds":["practice.practice","third.care","first.attend","second.recurrence","third.maintained-coupling"],"traces":["practice.practice","third.care","first.attend","second.recurrence","third.maintained-coupling"],"carries":["practice.contend","practice.atlas-garden"],"pairs":["practice.contend"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',234,'sha256:e1103a0957d5839a1262ef5dc1f04401b9e3c987411c6e226db6b0a62a2a95ce','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.terms-and-conditions','Terms and Conditions','terms-and-conditions','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Terms and Conditions.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/terms-and-conditions.html','# Terms and Conditions

Terms and Conditions names the Atlas standard by which a word becomes a [[Term]] and remains grounded through traceable [[Condition|conditions]]. A term serves where its conditions remain traceable.

The ordinary phrase is useful because it already joins terms with conditions. The Atlas reads that join structurally: a named term must remain answerable to what lets it hold.

## Places

Terms and Conditions places the structural agreement between named terms and the conditions that allow those terms to serve inside the Atlas.

## Holds

Terms and Conditions is held by [[Term]], [[Condition]], [[Groundedness]], and [[Atlas Note Standard]].

A term without traceable conditions drifts back toward an ungrounded word. A condition without a placed term has nothing definite to test, carry, or correct.

## Pairs

Terms and Conditions pairs with [[Terms of Service]]. Terms and Conditions holds the standard inward, where terms serve inside the Atlas through traceable conditions. Terms of Service holds it outward, where human service answers to the earth carrying it.

## Traces

- [[Term]]
- [[Condition]]
- [[Groundedness]]
- [[Atlas Note Standard]]

## Nests

Terms and Conditions nests at the root of the Atlas as a public-facing and practice-facing bridge. It can sit beside [[Reality Mechanics]] and [[Atlas]] because it names the standard by which the mapped body keeps its terms serviceable.

It also nests within [[Atlas Practice]] wherever notes are placed, checked, revised, grounded, translated, or released.

## Reads

Terms and Conditions becomes recognisable where a named word cannot be treated as valid merely because it has been named. It must show where it places, what holds it, what it pairs with, where it traces, where it nests, how it reads, and what it carries.

The phrase carries a double read. Publicly, it is familiar enough to enter. Structurally, it names the Atlas discipline: terms only serve where their conditions remain traceable.

## Carries

- [[Check]]
- [[Atlas Condition Header]]

Check tests the agreement this standard names; the [[Atlas Condition Header]] gives its conditions their compact gathered form.','Terms and Conditions Terms and Conditions names the Atlas standard by which a word becomes a Term and remains grounded through traceable Condition. A term serves where its conditions remain traceable. The ordinary phrase is useful because it already joins terms with conditions. The Atlas reads that join structurally: a named term must remain answerable to what lets it hold. Places Terms and Conditions places the structural agreement between named terms and the conditions that allow those terms to serve inside the Atlas. Holds Terms and Conditions is held by Term, Condition, Groundedness, and Atlas Note Standard. A term without traceable conditions drifts back toward an ungrounded word. A condition without a placed term has nothing definite to test, carry, or correct. Pairs Terms and Conditions pairs with Terms of Service. Terms and Conditions holds the standard inward, where terms serve inside the Atlas through traceable conditions. Terms of Service holds it outward, where human service answers to the earth carrying it. Traces Term Condition Groundedness Atlas Note Standard Nests Terms and Conditions nests at the root of the Atlas as a public facing and practice facing bridge. It can sit beside Reality Mechanics and Atlas because it names the standard by which the mapped body keeps its terms serviceable. It also nests within Atlas Practice wherever notes are placed, checked, revised, grounded, translated, or released. Reads Terms and Conditions becomes recognisable where a named word cannot be treated as valid merely because it has been named. It must show where it places, what holds it, what it pairs with, where it traces, where it nests, how it reads, and what it carries. The phrase carries a double read. Publicly, it is familiar enough to enter. Structurally, it names the Atlas discipline: terms only serve where their conditions remain traceable. Carries Check Atlas Condition Header Check tests the agreement this standard names; the Atlas Condition Header gives its conditions their compact gathered form.','Terms and Conditions Terms and Conditions names the Atlas standard by which a word becomes a Term and remains grounded through traceable Condition. A term serves where its conditions remain traceable.','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.groundedness","ground.term","practice.atlas","practice.atlas-condition-header","practice.atlas-note-standard","practice.check","practice.reality-mechanics","second.condition","third.terms-of-service"]','{"holds":["ground.term","second.condition","ground.groundedness","practice.atlas-note-standard"],"traces":["ground.term","second.condition","ground.groundedness","practice.atlas-note-standard"],"carries":["practice.check","practice.atlas-condition-header"],"pairs":["third.terms-of-service"],"nests":["practice.reality-mechanics","practice.atlas"],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',323,'sha256:c5761981b9d706de60c9cda53683967a9034f6fe6cb1218b600cf7c590b58e19','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.tracing','Tracing','tracing','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Tracing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/tracing.html','# Tracing

Tracing names the practice of locating or marking a [[Trace]] so its backward availability becomes readable. Trace is offered by connection whether or not it is marked. Tracing makes that availability explicit enough for a participant to follow through [[Retracing]].

## Places

Tracing places the practice of locating or marking a trace so its backward availability becomes readable.

## Holds

Tracing is held by [[Trace]] and [[Practice]].

## Pairs

Tracing pairs with [[Retracing]]. Tracing locates or marks a trace; Retracing follows that trace backward through connection.

## Traces

- [[Trace]]
- [[Practice]]
- [[Retrace Practice]]

## Nests

Tracing nests within higher-order or practice conditions.

## Reads

Tracing becomes recognisable where a participant makes the backward availability of a connection explicit enough to be followed.

## Carries

- [[Check]]

A located trace also offers retracing, but a participant may or may not follow it.','Tracing Tracing names the practice of locating or marking a Trace so its backward availability becomes readable. Trace is offered by connection whether or not it is marked. Tracing makes that availability explicit enough for a participant to follow through Retracing. Places Tracing places the practice of locating or marking a trace so its backward availability becomes readable. Holds Tracing is held by Trace and Practice. Pairs Tracing pairs with Retracing. Tracing locates or marks a trace; Retracing follows that trace backward through connection. Traces Trace Practice Retrace Practice Nests Tracing nests within higher order or practice conditions. Reads Tracing becomes recognisable where a participant makes the backward availability of a connection explicit enough to be followed. Carries Check A located trace also offers retracing, but a participant may or may not follow it.','Tracing Tracing names the practice of locating or marking a Trace so its backward availability becomes readable. Trace is offered by connection whether or not it is marked.','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.trace","practice.check","practice.practice","practice.retrace-practice","practice.retracing"]','{"holds":["first.trace","practice.practice"],"traces":["first.trace","practice.practice","practice.retrace-practice"],"carries":["practice.check"],"pairs":["practice.retracing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',134,'sha256:510831f296787b1132db6e96f5a743d7af9c0f08b28c57e9cfec07cbd48ee089','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('practice.translation-invariance','Translation Invariance','translation-invariance','Reality_Mechanics/4_Practice/Translation Invariance.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/translation-invariance.html','# Translation Invariance

Translation Invariance names the practice test by which Atlas structure is varied in expression and checked for recoverable dependency order.

The Atlas is not identical to its words, signs, notes, or other inscriptions. These are carriers. A [[Term]] is a structurally placed interpretation carried through them. Translation Invariance tests whether that placement remains recoverable when the carrier changes.

The test does not assume that every medium can preserve every feature. [[Medium]] shapes what can pass through it, and a [[Translation Boundary]] marks where carrying must enter local terms. Translation Invariance therefore asks what remains recoverable through the change, what becomes newly visible, and what is lost.

## Places

Translation Invariance places the practice test by which Atlas structure is varied in expression and checked for recoverable dependency order.

## Holds

Translation Invariance is held by [[Atlas]], [[Root Order]], [[Term]], [[Invariant]], [[Medium]], and [[Translation Boundary]]. A mapped order, structurally placed interpretations, variation, carriers, and a crossing between forms must be available before preservation across translation can be tested.

## Pairs

Translation Invariance is vertical. It tests the carrying of dependency order across changes of expression. No lateral co-condition is required for it to be locatable.

## Traces

- [[Atlas]]
- [[Root Order]]
- [[Term]]
- [[Invariant]]
- [[Medium]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Translation Invariance nests wherever an Atlas term, path, or larger structure can be expressed through more than one carrier and compared without protecting its original surface form.

The carriers may include ordinary language, mathematical signs, diagrams, spatial arrangements, physical models, actions, or thought. They need not resemble one another. What is compared is the recoverability of structural placement.

## Reads

Translation Invariance becomes recognisable where carriers vary while dependency placement remains recoverable.

Its practice movement is:

```text
translate → compare → locate loss → retrace → revise
```

The test asks:

- What must remain for this to be the same term or path?
- What changed only because the medium changed?
- What could not be removed without losing the interpretation?
- Can the dependency trace be reconstructed from the new expression?
- Where did ambiguity, convention, or hidden context carry more than the stated structure?

What survives one translation is evidence, not proof, of structural depth. Confidence strengthens where independently formed carriers preserve the same dependency order. Failure is informative: it locates where an apparent invariant belonged to wording, notation, metaphor, convention, or medium rather than to the order being traced.

Translation Invariance does not establish that an Atlas structure is natural order merely because it survives representational change. It establishes that the structure is not captive to the tested representation. Contact with the participating domain remains required.

## Carries

Nothing at practice grain. The test returns its result to the term, path, or structure being revised.','Translation Invariance Translation Invariance names the practice test by which Atlas structure is varied in expression and checked for recoverable dependency order. The Atlas is not identical to its words, signs, notes, or other inscriptions. These are carriers. A Term is a structurally placed interpretation carried through them. Translation Invariance tests whether that placement remains recoverable when the carrier changes. The test does not assume that every medium can preserve every feature. Medium shapes what can pass through it, and a Translation Boundary marks where carrying must enter local terms. Translation Invariance therefore asks what remains recoverable through the change, what becomes newly visible, and what is lost. Places Translation Invariance places the practice test by which Atlas structure is varied in expression and checked for recoverable dependency order. Holds Translation Invariance is held by Atlas, Root Order, Term, Invariant, Medium, and Translation Boundary. A mapped order, structurally placed interpretations, variation, carriers, and a crossing between forms must be available before preservation across translation can be tested. Pairs Translation Invariance is vertical. It tests the carrying of dependency order across changes of expression. No lateral co condition is required for it to be locatable. Traces Atlas Root Order Term Invariant Medium Translation Boundary Nests Translation Invariance nests wherever an Atlas term, path, or larger structure can be expressed through more than one carrier and compared without protecting its original surface form. The carriers may include ordinary language, mathematical signs, diagrams, spatial arrangements, physical models, actions, or thought. They need not resemble one another. What is compared is the recoverability of structural placement. Reads Translation Invariance becomes recognisable where carriers vary while dependency placement remains recoverable. Its practice movement is: The test asks: What must remain for this to be the same term or path? What changed only because the medium changed? What could not be removed without losing the interpretation? Can the dependency trace be reconstructed from the new expression? Where did ambiguity, convention, or hidden context carry more than the stated structure? What survives one translation is evidence, not proof, of structural depth. Confidence strengthens where independently formed carriers preserve the same dependency order. Failure is informative: it locates where an apparent invariant belonged to wording, notation, metaphor, convention, or medium rather than to the order being traced. Translation Invariance does not establish that an Atlas structure is natural order merely because it survives representational change. It establishes that the structure is not captive to the tested representation. Contact with the participating domain remains required. Carries Nothing at practice grain. The test returns its result to the term, path, or structure being revised.','Translation Invariance Translation Invariance names the practice test by which Atlas structure is varied in expression and checked for recoverable dependency order. The Atlas is not identical to…','stable','rooted',0,'practice','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.invariant","ground.root-order","ground.term","practice.atlas","second.medium","third.translation-boundary"]','{"holds":["practice.atlas","ground.root-order","ground.term","ground.invariant","second.medium","third.translation-boundary"],"traces":["practice.atlas","ground.root-order","ground.term","ground.invariant","second.medium","third.translation-boundary"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',434,'sha256:1d15653d9c18ba95bfb9f988854f05d10d3dff1dba5871bd6574fd130edd096e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.acceleration','Acceleration','acceleration','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Acceleration.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/acceleration.html','# Acceleration

Acceleration names change in velocity across interval. It does not by itself identify what bears or produces the change; it names the readable alteration of directed speed through traversal.

## Places

Acceleration places change in velocity across interval.

## Holds

Acceleration is held by [[Velocity]], [[Change]], and [[Interval]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Acceleration is a singular condition — the rate of [[Change]] of [[Velocity]]. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Velocity]]
- [[Change]]
- [[Interval]]
- [[Speed]]

## Nests

Acceleration nests in traversal and rate reads. It depends on velocity, change, and interval without by itself identifying what bears the change.

## Reads

Acceleration becomes recognisable where directed traversal can be read as speeding up, slowing down, or changing velocity across interval.

## Carries

- [[Extractive Acceleration]]','Acceleration Acceleration names change in velocity across interval. It does not by itself identify what bears or produces the change; it names the readable alteration of directed speed through traversal. Places Acceleration places change in velocity across interval. Holds Acceleration is held by Velocity, Change, and Interval. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Acceleration is a singular condition — the rate of Change of Velocity. There is no lateral contrast required at this level. Traces Velocity Change Interval Speed Nests Acceleration nests in traversal and rate reads. It depends on velocity, change, and interval without by itself identifying what bears the change. Reads Acceleration becomes recognisable where directed traversal can be read as speeding up, slowing down, or changing velocity across interval. Carries Extractive Acceleration','Acceleration Acceleration names change in velocity across interval. It does not by itself identify what bears or produces the change; it names the readable alteration of directed speed through…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.change","second.interval","second.speed","second.velocity","third.extractive-acceleration"]','{"holds":["second.velocity","second.change","second.interval"],"traces":["second.velocity","second.change","second.interval","second.speed"],"carries":["third.extractive-acceleration"],"pairs":["second.velocity","second.change"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',123,'sha256:6e07d2635bcdee94cc485c8d2bf484ba17f03b6d200728923af5b4e0dd13c08b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.adaptation','Adaptation','adaptation','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Adaptation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/adaptation.html','# Adaptation

Adaptation names the capacity to keep producing complete local resolutions without requiring the larger asymmetry to collapse.

Adaptation is not permanent openness and not refusal of resolution. Local resolutions can be complete. The click is real. What remains open is whether the resolved relation can later be re-entered, reoriented, or carried differently without treating that later movement as a threat to what currently holds.

## Places

Adaptation places the capacity to keep producing complete local resolutions without requiring the larger asymmetry to collapse.

## Holds

Adaptation is held by [[Bounded Asymmetry]], [[Resolution]], [[Shift]], [[Carrying]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Asymmetry must remain bounded, local resolution must occur, and carrying must remain compatible across changed orientation before adaptation can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Adaptation names compatible reorientation within bounded asymmetry rather than an opposite state.

## Traces

- [[Bounded Asymmetry]]
- [[Resolution]]
- [[Shift]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Adaptation nests inside carrying as the condition through which local resolution can continue without reducing the wider asymmetry to closure.

## Reads

Adaptation becomes readable where a condition can resolve locally, shift orientation, and continue carrying while the larger asymmetry remains available for further relation.

This avoids treating unresolvedness as the value. The value is not lack of closure; it is compatible carrying through bounded asymmetry. Adaptation keeps relation alive by allowing complete local resolution without requiring difference itself to disappear.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Adaptation Adaptation names the capacity to keep producing complete local resolutions without requiring the larger asymmetry to collapse. Adaptation is not permanent openness and not refusal of resolution. Local resolutions can be complete. The click is real. What remains open is whether the resolved relation can later be re entered, reoriented, or carried differently without treating that later movement as a threat to what currently holds. Places Adaptation places the capacity to keep producing complete local resolutions without requiring the larger asymmetry to collapse. Holds Adaptation is held by Bounded Asymmetry, Resolution, Shift, Carrying, Compatibility, and Closure Scope. Asymmetry must remain bounded, local resolution must occur, and carrying must remain compatible across changed orientation before adaptation can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Adaptation names compatible reorientation within bounded asymmetry rather than an opposite state. Traces Bounded Asymmetry Resolution Shift Carrying Compatibility Closure Scope Nests Adaptation nests inside carrying as the condition through which local resolution can continue without reducing the wider asymmetry to closure. Reads Adaptation becomes readable where a condition can resolve locally, shift orientation, and continue carrying while the larger asymmetry remains available for further relation. This avoids treating unresolvedness as the value. The value is not lack of closure; it is compatible carrying through bounded asymmetry. Adaptation keeps relation alive by allowing complete local resolution without requiring difference itself to disappear. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Adaptation Adaptation names the capacity to keep producing complete local resolutions without requiring the larger asymmetry to collapse. Adaptation is not permanent openness and not refusal of…','stable','