INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.apparent-bearing','Apparent Bearing','apparent-bearing','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Apparent Bearing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/apparent-bearing.html','# Apparent Bearing

Apparent bearing names bearing becoming presented. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, apparent bearing names the condition through which that holding becomes available to be noticed — bearing that presents itself as bearing.

## Places

Apparent Bearing places bearing becoming presented.

## Holds

Apparent Bearing is held by [[Bearing]] and [[Apparent]].

## Pairs

Apparent Bearing is vertical. It names the read of bearing becoming presented, and carries this forward into [[Observation]]. No lateral co-present condition is required for Apparent Bearing to be locatable — the presentation of bearing has no structural sibling at this order.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Apparent]]

## Nests

Apparent Bearing nests inside bearing reads as bearing presented enough to be noticed.

## Reads

Apparent bearing becomes recognisable where carrying can be noticed — where holding presents itself as holding rather than remaining invisible.

## Carries

- [[Observation]]','Apparent Bearing Apparent bearing names bearing becoming presented. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, apparent bearing names the condition through which that holding becomes available to be noticed — bearing that presents itself as bearing. Places Apparent Bearing places bearing becoming presented. Holds Apparent Bearing is held by Bearing and Apparent. Pairs Apparent Bearing is vertical. It names the read of bearing becoming presented, and carries this forward into Observation. No lateral co present condition is required for Apparent Bearing to be locatable — the presentation of bearing has no structural sibling at this order. Traces Bearing Apparent Nests Apparent Bearing nests inside bearing reads as bearing presented enough to be noticed. Reads Apparent bearing becomes recognisable where carrying can be noticed — where holding presents itself as holding rather than remaining invisible. Carries Observation','Apparent Bearing Apparent bearing names bearing becoming presented. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, apparent bearing names the condition through which that holding becomes…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.apparent","first.bearing","second.observation"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","first.apparent"],"traces":["first.bearing","first.apparent"],"carries":["second.observation"],"pairs":["second.observation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',138,'sha256:dbb263516d2681bc7b031cc7020c59ddf88b91709111e622b4a654f15c316cd4','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.apparent-source','Apparent Source','apparent-source','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Apparent Source.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/apparent-source.html','# Apparent Source

Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source where trace does not recover it as what actually bears the carrying.

A structure may be visible, proximal, authoritative, fluent, stable, or powerful enough to appear as source. Apparent Source does not mean the structure is unreal or carries nothing. It means the structure does not bear the carrying in the source-role attributed to it.

## Places

Apparent Source places a presented or attributed structure taken as source where trace does not recover it as what actually bears the carrying.

## Holds

Apparent Source is held by [[Apparent]], [[Trace]], [[Carrying]], and [[Structure]]. A structure must be presented, carrying must be active, and trace must be available to test whether the presented source actually bears it before apparent source can be named.

## Pairs

Apparent Source pairs with [[Bearing Source]]. Bearing Source names the structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition; Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source that trace does not recover as its bearer. Each requires the other to be locatable: actual source is tested against what only appears to bear, while apparent source can only be diagnosed where actual bearing remains recoverable.

## Traces

- [[Apparent]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Structure]]

## Nests

Apparent Source nests inside carrying where a visible, proximal, authoritative, or stable structure is taken as source while its bearing remains unsupported by trace.

## Reads

Apparent Source becomes recognisable where retrace passes through or beyond the structure treated as source and recovers the actual bearing elsewhere.

An author may be the apparent source of a claim whose bearing comes from a wider practice, world, or inherited relation. A model may be the apparent source of an answer whose bearing comes from training, tools, human labour, energy, and checked external conditions. Apparent Source does not erase the local carrier; it corrects the role assigned to it.

## Carries

- [[Source Drift]]','Apparent Source Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source where trace does not recover it as what actually bears the carrying. A structure may be visible, proximal, authoritative, fluent, stable, or powerful enough to appear as source. Apparent Source does not mean the structure is unreal or carries nothing. It means the structure does not bear the carrying in the source role attributed to it. Places Apparent Source places a presented or attributed structure taken as source where trace does not recover it as what actually bears the carrying. Holds Apparent Source is held by Apparent, Trace, Carrying, and Structure. A structure must be presented, carrying must be active, and trace must be available to test whether the presented source actually bears it before apparent source can be named. Pairs Apparent Source pairs with Bearing Source. Bearing Source names the structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition; Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source that trace does not recover as its bearer. Each requires the other to be locatable: actual source is tested against what only appears to bear, while apparent source can only be diagnosed where actual bearing remains recoverable. Traces Apparent Trace Carrying Structure Nests Apparent Source nests inside carrying where a visible, proximal, authoritative, or stable structure is taken as source while its bearing remains unsupported by trace. Reads Apparent Source becomes recognisable where retrace passes through or beyond the structure treated as source and recovers the actual bearing elsewhere. An author may be the apparent source of a claim whose bearing comes from a wider practice, world, or inherited relation. A model may be the apparent source of an answer whose bearing comes from training, tools, human labour, energy, and checked external conditions. Apparent Source does not erase the local carrier; it corrects the role assigned to it. Carries Source Drift','Apparent Source Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source where trace does not recover it as what actually bears the carrying. A structure may be visible, proximal,…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.apparent","first.trace","higher.source-drift","second.bearing-source","second.carrying","second.structure"]','{"holds":["first.apparent","first.trace","second.carrying","second.structure"],"traces":["first.apparent","first.trace","second.carrying","second.structure"],"carries":["higher.source-drift"],"pairs":["second.bearing-source"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',317,'sha256:e6797f2b7e62d526365fbf6be74576c6352a2a7f835720f9f86c6a68c15f0b10','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.balance','Balance','balance','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Balance.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/balance.html','# Balance

Balance names pressure regulated between retain and release so relation remains compatible.

Balance is not stillness, symmetry, equality, or equal amount. It may be dynamic, uneven, rhythmic, responsive, and continuously adjusting. A body balancing, a building carrying load, a relationship bearing strain, or a mind returning to ground all show balance where pressure remains regulated enough for relation to continue.

## Places

Balance places compatible regulation of pressure between retain and release.

## Holds

Balance is held by [[Pressure]], [[Retain]], [[Release]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Capacity]]. Pressure must be locally borne, retention and release must be available, and carrying must remain compatible before balance can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Balance names dynamic regulation rather than a static opposite.

## Traces

- [[Pressure]]
- [[Retain]]
- [[Release]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Capacity]]

## Nests

Balance nests inside carrying as the regulation through which pressure remains bearable enough for relation to continue.

## Reads

Balance becomes readable where pressure is regulated between retain and release so relation remains compatible.

Balance is the natural form of pressure where pressure remains answerable to relation. Too much retention can become overload, compression, rigidity, injury, or obsession. Too much release can become dissipation, loss of form, avoidance, collapse, or leakage.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Balance Balance names pressure regulated between retain and release so relation remains compatible. Balance is not stillness, symmetry, equality, or equal amount. It may be dynamic, uneven, rhythmic, responsive, and continuously adjusting. A body balancing, a building carrying load, a relationship bearing strain, or a mind returning to ground all show balance where pressure remains regulated enough for relation to continue. Places Balance places compatible regulation of pressure between retain and release. Holds Balance is held by Pressure, Retain, Release, Compatibility, and Capacity. Pressure must be locally borne, retention and release must be available, and carrying must remain compatible before balance can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Balance names dynamic regulation rather than a static opposite. Traces Pressure Retain Release Compatibility Capacity Nests Balance nests inside carrying as the regulation through which pressure remains bearable enough for relation to continue. Reads Balance becomes readable where pressure is regulated between retain and release so relation remains compatible. Balance is the natural form of pressure where pressure remains answerable to relation. Too much retention can become overload, compression, rigidity, injury, or obsession. Too much release can become dissipation, loss of form, avoidance, collapse, or leakage. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Balance Balance names pressure regulated between retain and release so relation remains compatible. Balance is not stillness, symmetry, equality, or equal amount.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.release","second.capacity","second.compatibility","second.pressure","second.retain"]','{"holds":["second.pressure","second.retain","first.release","second.compatibility","second.capacity"],"traces":["second.pressure","second.retain","first.release","second.compatibility","second.capacity"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',211,'sha256:b8ad5dff38425d1ed19083731fda6b3ed477882c732f1d72651e61a0a7298259','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.be','Be','be','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Be.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/be.html','# Be

Be names presence holding. Where presence names coupled relation locally available, be names that availability sustained: something continues to be present rather than only having been present. Permanence can be a later read, but be names presence held without requiring re-establishment.

## Places

Be places presence holding.

## Holds

Be is held by [[Presence]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Be is a singular condition — the minimal presence required for anything to be at all. There is no lateral contrast at the be level. The asymmetry is expressed in what be becomes: [[Being]], [[Exist]], and [[Become]].

## Traces

- [[Presence]]

## Nests

Be nests under presence as presence holding without requiring permanence.

## Reads

Be becomes recognisable where presence can be read as continuing rather than merely having appeared — where something is present now rather than only once.

## Carries

- [[Being]]
- [[Exist]]
- [[Become]]
- [[Real]]','Be Be names presence holding. Where presence names coupled relation locally available, be names that availability sustained: something continues to be present rather than only having been present. Permanence can be a later read, but be names presence held without requiring re establishment. Places Be places presence holding. Holds Be is held by Presence. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Be is a singular condition — the minimal presence required for anything to be at all. There is no lateral contrast at the be level. The asymmetry is expressed in what be becomes: Being, Exist, and Become. Traces Presence Nests Be nests under presence as presence holding without requiring permanence. Reads Be becomes recognisable where presence can be read as continuing rather than merely having appeared — where something is present now rather than only once. Carries Being Exist Become Real','Be Be names presence holding. Where presence names coupled relation locally available, be names that availability sustained: something continues to be present rather than only having been present.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.become","second.being","second.exist","second.presence","second.real"]','{"holds":["second.presence"],"traces":["second.presence"],"carries":["second.being","second.exist","second.become","second.real"],"pairs":["second.being","second.exist","second.become"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',139,'sha256:a17b6ee5259102da6166d23844019ddd20c69a11e496ccaa590304233c2a618f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.bearing-read','Bearing Read','bearing-read','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Bearing Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/bearing-read.html','# Bearing Read

Bearing read names the class of second-order produced reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways — as presented, visible, invisible, divisible, or indivisible. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, bearing reads name the different ways that holding condition can be taken up and read. A bearing read does not change the bearing; it names how the bearing becomes available to evaluation.

## Places

Bearing Read places the class of second-order produced reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways — as presented, visible, invisible, divisible, or indivisible.

## Holds

Bearing Read is held by [[Bearing]].

## Pairs

Bearing Read is a class note. It groups the second-order reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways. As a class, it is vertical — it organises its nested reads rather than pairing with a lateral co-present condition.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]

## Nests

Bearing Read nests as the class of second-order reads that make bearing available to evaluation in specific ways.

[[Apparent Bearing]]
[[Invisible Bearing]]
[[Divisible Bearing]]
[[Indivisible Bearing]]

## Reads

Bearing read becomes recognisable where a term names a specific way in which bearing is readable — not bearing itself but bearing as read through a particular condition.

## Carries','Bearing Read Bearing read names the class of second order produced reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways — as presented, visible, invisible, divisible, or indivisible. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, bearing reads name the different ways that holding condition can be taken up and read. A bearing read does not change the bearing; it names how the bearing becomes available to evaluation. Places Bearing Read places the class of second order produced reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways — as presented, visible, invisible, divisible, or indivisible. Holds Bearing Read is held by Bearing. Pairs Bearing Read is a class note. It groups the second order reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways. As a class, it is vertical — it organises its nested reads rather than pairing with a lateral co present condition. Traces Bearing Nests Bearing Read nests as the class of second order reads that make bearing available to evaluation in specific ways. Apparent Bearing Invisible Bearing Divisible Bearing Indivisible Bearing Reads Bearing read becomes recognisable where a term names a specific way in which bearing is readable — not bearing itself but bearing as read through a particular condition. Carries','Bearing Read Bearing read names the class of second order produced reads through which bearing becomes readable in specific ways — as presented, visible, invisible, divisible, or indivisible.…','stable','rooted',0,'second','class',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing"]','{"holds":["first.bearing"],"traces":["first.bearing"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',205,'sha256:6f6d69c9e7eb851f6fdd9f766b554736ccb1989766bb3ccf73b785b5c87aa04d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.bearing-relation','Bearing Relation','bearing-relation','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Bearing Relation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/bearing-relation.html','# Bearing Relation

Bearing Relation names coupled relation bearing on coupled relation. Where coupling names distinct resolved conditions held in relation and presence makes that coupling locally available, bearing relation names those coupled conditions beginning to bear on each other within a scope.

## Places

Bearing Relation places coupled relation bearing on coupled relation.

## Holds

Bearing Relation is held by [[Coupling]], [[Presence]], and [[Bearing]]. Coupled relation must be locally available and able to bear before active participation can begin.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Bearing Relation is a singular condition at its juncture — the named structural connection between coupled conditions. There is no lateral contrast required to locate bearing relation. The structural asymmetry is fully expressed by what bearing relation becomes: [[Participation]].

## Traces

- [[Coupling]]
- [[Presence]]
- [[Bearing]]

## Nests

Bearing Relation nests as a second-order bridge between coupling, presence, and participation. It is singular and structural, and should not be collapsed into the third-order branch family Bearing Relations.

## Reads

Bearing Relation becomes recognisable where coupled relation does not merely remain mutually available, but bears on what it is coupled with so that participation can become active.
## Carries

- [[Participation]]
- [[Relationship]]
- [[Trust]]','Bearing Relation Bearing Relation names coupled relation bearing on coupled relation. Where coupling names distinct resolved conditions held in relation and presence makes that coupling locally available, bearing relation names those coupled conditions beginning to bear on each other within a scope. Places Bearing Relation places coupled relation bearing on coupled relation. Holds Bearing Relation is held by Coupling, Presence, and Bearing. Coupled relation must be locally available and able to bear before active participation can begin. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Bearing Relation is a singular condition at its juncture — the named structural connection between coupled conditions. There is no lateral contrast required to locate bearing relation. The structural asymmetry is fully expressed by what bearing relation becomes: Participation. Traces Coupling Presence Bearing Nests Bearing Relation nests as a second order bridge between coupling, presence, and participation. It is singular and structural, and should not be collapsed into the third order branch family Bearing Relations. Reads Bearing Relation becomes recognisable where coupled relation does not merely remain mutually available, but bears on what it is coupled with so that participation can become active. Carries Participation Relationship Trust','Bearing Relation Bearing Relation names coupled relation bearing on coupled relation. Where coupling names distinct resolved conditions held in relation and presence makes that coupling locally…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.coupling","second.participation","second.presence","third.relationship","third.trust"]','{"holds":["second.coupling","second.presence","first.bearing"],"traces":["second.coupling","second.presence","first.bearing"],"carries":["second.participation","third.relationship","third.trust"],"pairs":["second.participation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',188,'sha256:93b8ab2283a26dc50fd9113ca9d85b936f517e435cb04aea88c56bb8cc43ee4f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.bearing-source','Bearing Source','bearing-source','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Bearing Source.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/bearing-source.html','# Bearing Source

Bearing Source names structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition.

It is not a separate source-object behind relation. In the Atlas sense, structure is ordered relation that bears. Bearing Source names the structural role from which a carried condition receives its actual bearing.

Origin, author, authority, or first cause can be relevant, but they are not automatically source. Source here means the bearing structure recovered by trace.

## Places

Bearing Source places the structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition.

## Holds

Bearing Source is held by [[Bearing]], [[Trace]], [[Carrying]], and [[Structure]]. Carrying must be present, bearing must be active, structure must be doing the holding, and a trace must be available before bearing source can be named.

## Pairs

Bearing Source pairs with [[Apparent Source]]. Bearing Source names the structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition; Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source that trace does not recover as its bearer. Each requires the other to be locatable: actual source is tested against what only appears to bear, while apparent source can only be diagnosed where actual bearing remains recoverable.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Structure]]
## Nests

Bearing Source nests inside carrying where trace can recover the structure from which a carried condition receives its bearing.

## Reads

Bearing Source becomes readable where a carried condition can be traced back to the structure that actually bears it. In knowledge this may be a read, word, claim, role, or responsibility; in other fields it may be material, capacity, consequence, memory, form, or use.

## Carries

- [[Sever]]
- [[Competence Boundary]]
- [[Reality Check]]
- [[Source Drift]]','Bearing Source Bearing Source names structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition. It is not a separate source object behind relation. In the Atlas sense, structure is ordered relation that bears. Bearing Source names the structural role from which a carried condition receives its actual bearing. Origin, author, authority, or first cause can be relevant, but they are not automatically source. Source here means the bearing structure recovered by trace. Places Bearing Source places the structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition. Holds Bearing Source is held by Bearing, Trace, Carrying, and Structure. Carrying must be present, bearing must be active, structure must be doing the holding, and a trace must be available before bearing source can be named. Pairs Bearing Source pairs with Apparent Source. Bearing Source names the structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition; Apparent Source names a presented or attributed structure taken as source that trace does not recover as its bearer. Each requires the other to be locatable: actual source is tested against what only appears to bear, while apparent source can only be diagnosed where actual bearing remains recoverable. Traces Bearing Trace Carrying Structure Nests Bearing Source nests inside carrying where trace can recover the structure from which a carried condition receives its bearing. Reads Bearing Source becomes readable where a carried condition can be traced back to the structure that actually bears it. In knowledge this may be a read, word, claim, role, or responsibility; in other fields it may be material, capacity, consequence, memory, form, or use. Carries Sever Competence Boundary Reality Check Source Drift','Bearing Source Bearing Source names structure recovered by trace as what actually bears a carried condition. It is not a separate source object behind relation.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.trace","higher.source-drift","second.apparent-source","second.carrying","second.sever","second.structure","third.competence-boundary","third.reality-check"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","first.trace","second.carrying","second.structure"],"traces":["first.bearing","first.trace","second.carrying","second.structure"],"carries":["second.sever","third.competence-boundary","third.reality-check","higher.source-drift"],"pairs":["second.apparent-source"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',275,'sha256:7f20c7eb042e9e9e0255aae2b13514b9a622cd96754af7d8f65d515fdb817fad','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.become','Become','become','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Become.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/become.html','# Become

Become names presence changing while remaining traceable. Where being names presence carried, become names that carrying moving through resolution: presence participates through change without losing the dependency path through which the change can be followed. Replacement can be one kind of becoming, but become names traceable change.

## Places

Become places presence changing while remaining traceable.

## Holds

Become is held by [[Being]] and [[Process]].

## Pairs

Become is vertical. It names presence changing while remaining traceable, and is carried by [[Being]] through [[Process]]. There is no lateral co-present condition that Become requires and that requires Become in return. Change of presence traces to sustained presence — it does not sit beside it.

## Traces

- [[Being]]
- [[Process]]
- [[Be]]

## Nests

Become nests where carried presence changes through a traceable process.

## Reads

Become becomes recognisable where presence can be read as changing through a traceable sequence — where what is present now is different from what was present before while remaining followable.

## Carries','Become Become names presence changing while remaining traceable. Where being names presence carried, become names that carrying moving through resolution: presence participates through change without losing the dependency path through which the change can be followed. Replacement can be one kind of becoming, but become names traceable change. Places Become places presence changing while remaining traceable. Holds Become is held by Being and Process. Pairs Become is vertical. It names presence changing while remaining traceable, and is carried by Being through Process. There is no lateral co present condition that Become requires and that requires Become in return. Change of presence traces to sustained presence — it does not sit beside it. Traces Being Process Be Nests Become nests where carried presence changes through a traceable process. Reads Become becomes recognisable where presence can be read as changing through a traceable sequence — where what is present now is different from what was present before while remaining followable. Carries','Become Become names presence changing while remaining traceable. Where being names presence carried, become names that carrying moving through resolution: presence participates through change…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.be","second.being","second.process"]','{"holds":["second.being","second.process"],"traces":["second.being","second.process","second.be"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.being","second.process"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',159,'sha256:ac512e1bda6d4f9aa9b70350e34a9259682cde208ddc02b677503f421034f730','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.being','Being','being','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Being.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/being.html','# Being

Being names presence carried. Where be names presence held, being names that holding sustained through carrying: presence continuing to participate rather than only holding in place. Substance or essence can be later reads of being, but here being names presence moving forward through carrying.

## Places

Being places presence carried.

## Holds

Being is held by [[Be]] and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Being is vertical. It names presence carried, and carries this forward into [[Become]] (presence changing while remaining traceable). There is no lateral co-present condition required for Being to be locatable — sustained presence has no structural sibling at this order.

## Traces

- [[Be]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Live]]

## Nests

Being nests where held presence is sustained through carrying.

## Reads

Being becomes recognisable where presence can be read as carried, so something is present and participating forward through what carries it.

## Carries

- [[Become]]','Being Being names presence carried. Where be names presence held, being names that holding sustained through carrying: presence continuing to participate rather than only holding in place. Substance or essence can be later reads of being, but here being names presence moving forward through carrying. Places Being places presence carried. Holds Being is held by Be and Carrying. Pairs Being is vertical. It names presence carried, and carries this forward into Become (presence changing while remaining traceable). There is no lateral co present condition required for Being to be locatable — sustained presence has no structural sibling at this order. Traces Be Carrying Live Nests Being nests where held presence is sustained through carrying. Reads Being becomes recognisable where presence can be read as carried, so something is present and participating forward through what carries it. Carries Become','Being Being names presence carried. Where be names presence held, being names that holding sustained through carrying: presence continuing to participate rather than only holding in place.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.be","second.become","second.carrying","second.live"]','{"holds":["second.be","second.carrying"],"traces":["second.be","second.carrying","second.live"],"carries":["second.become"],"pairs":["second.become"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',138,'sha256:391bfbb95732012792b6ded2659dc23f53222a75587d31c091118f01fdf6dfa7','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.boundary-loosening','Boundary Loosening','boundary-loosening','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Boundary Loosening.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/boundary-loosening.html','# Boundary Loosening

Boundary Loosening names a coupled boundary becoming less tightly held while the coupling has not yet fully broken. It can lead to decoupling, but it first names the readable weakening, widening, softening, or loss of tightness in the boundary that coupling has been holding.

## Places

Boundary Loosening places a coupled boundary becoming less tightly held while the coupling has not yet fully broken.

## Holds

Boundary Loosening is held by [[Coupled Boundary]] and [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Boundary Loosening is a singular condition — the reduction of coupled boundary compatibility. The asymmetry is expressed in what boundary loosening carries: [[Decoupling]].

## Traces

- [[Coupled Boundary]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Boundary Loosening nests between coupled boundary and decoupling. It names weakening before full break.

## Reads

Boundary Loosening becomes recognisable where a coupled boundary remains available but no longer holds the same tightness, constraint, or mutual fit it previously carried.

## Carries

- [[Decoupling]]','Boundary Loosening Boundary Loosening names a coupled boundary becoming less tightly held while the coupling has not yet fully broken. It can lead to decoupling, but it first names the readable weakening, widening, softening, or loss of tightness in the boundary that coupling has been holding. Places Boundary Loosening places a coupled boundary becoming less tightly held while the coupling has not yet fully broken. Holds Boundary Loosening is held by Coupled Boundary and Compatibility. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Boundary Loosening is a singular condition — the reduction of coupled boundary compatibility. The asymmetry is expressed in what boundary loosening carries: Decoupling. Traces Coupled Boundary Compatibility Nests Boundary Loosening nests between coupled boundary and decoupling. It names weakening before full break. Reads Boundary Loosening becomes recognisable where a coupled boundary remains available but no longer holds the same tightness, constraint, or mutual fit it previously carried. Carries Decoupling','Boundary Loosening Boundary Loosening names a coupled boundary becoming less tightly held while the coupling has not yet fully broken. It can lead to decoupling, but it first names the readable…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.compatibility","second.coupled-boundary","second.decoupling"]','{"holds":["second.coupled-boundary","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.coupled-boundary","second.compatibility"],"carries":["second.decoupling"],"pairs":["second.decoupling"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',148,'sha256:f5ae31118835096c30ac149688f26ca976e7913f07f00c7d9ff849b100992832','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.capacity','Capacity','capacity','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Capacity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/capacity.html','# Capacity

Capacity names supportable carrying within a current condition. Where compatibility names the condition under which carrying can proceed and threshold names a located condition under strain where change becomes readable, capacity names how much load can remain supportable before carrying must [[Shift|shift]], reduce, fail, or re-resolve. Container size can show capacity, but capacity first names carrying evaluated within scope, support, condition, and compatibility.

## Places

Capacity places supportable carrying within a current condition.

## Holds

Capacity is held by [[Compatibility]], [[Threshold]], and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Capacity pairs with [[Overload]]. Capacity names supportable carrying; Overload names load exceeding that supportable capacity.

## Traces

- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Threshold]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Load]]

## Nests

Capacity nests as a carrying condition and passage check. It names supportable carrying before overload, failure, shift, or re-resolution.

## Reads

Capacity becomes recognisable where a carrying condition can be read by what it can support within the current scope — where load remains possible up to the point at which compatibility begins to fail.

Capacity becomes especially visible through [[Pressure]]: load locally borne through relation tests how much carrying can remain compatible before reduction, release, transfer, overload, or re-resolution becomes necessary.

[[Energy]] names generated availability for carrying where that availability becomes readable as supportable capacity, pressure, flow, work, movement, transformation, maintenance, repair, or continuation.

## Carries

- [[Pressure]]
- [[Energy]]
- [[Overload]]
- [[Balance]]
- [[Resonance]]','Capacity Capacity names supportable carrying within a current condition. Where compatibility names the condition under which carrying can proceed and threshold names a located condition under strain where change becomes readable, capacity names how much load can remain supportable before carrying must Shift, reduce, fail, or re resolve. Container size can show capacity, but capacity first names carrying evaluated within scope, support, condition, and compatibility. Places Capacity places supportable carrying within a current condition. Holds Capacity is held by Compatibility, Threshold, and Carrying. Pairs Capacity pairs with Overload. Capacity names supportable carrying; Overload names load exceeding that supportable capacity. Traces Compatibility Threshold Carrying Load Nests Capacity nests as a carrying condition and passage check. It names supportable carrying before overload, failure, shift, or re resolution. Reads Capacity becomes recognisable where a carrying condition can be read by what it can support within the current scope — where load remains possible up to the point at which compatibility begins to fail. Capacity becomes especially visible through Pressure: load locally borne through relation tests how much carrying can remain compatible before reduction, release, transfer, overload, or re resolution becomes necessary. Energy names generated availability for carrying where that availability becomes readable as supportable capacity, pressure, flow, work, movement, transformation, maintenance, repair, or continuation. Carries Pressure Energy Overload Balance Resonance','Capacity Capacity names supportable carrying within a current condition. Where compatibility names the condition under which carrying can proceed and threshold names a located condition under…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.threshold","second.balance","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.energy","second.load","second.overload","second.pressure","second.resonance"]','{"holds":["second.compatibility","first.threshold","second.carrying"],"traces":["second.compatibility","first.threshold","second.carrying","second.load"],"carries":["second.pressure","second.energy","second.overload","second.balance","second.resonance"],"pairs":["second.overload"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',217,'sha256:6510877bd68bdbbf52dd17b9b0f0f3df743df2fec8a44c84df1b389f6f18bfaa','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.carried-condition','Carried Condition','carried-condition','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Carried Condition.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/carried-condition.html','# Carried Condition

Carried Condition names the carrying condition returned to when load has concentrated too tightly in the participant or carrier.

The root sentence is:

```text
You are carried.
```

This is not reassurance added to carrying. It names a mechanics of carrying: before a participant carries, carrying is already occurring. Ground, gravity, weight, breath, support, and interval can take part of the load before meaning, interpretation, or decision returns.

Where load exceeds solitary carrying, meaning can wait.

## Places

Carried Condition places the carrying condition returned to when load has concentrated too tightly in the participant or carrier.

## Holds

Carried Condition is held by [[Carrying]], [[Ground]], [[Gravity]], [[Load]], [[Capacity]], and [[Overload]].

Carrying names the movement being restored. Ground names what is acknowledged before the system derives its own terms. Gravity names the natural-world field bearing through which weight is carried toward ground. Load and Capacity name what is being borne and what can support it. Overload names the excess condition that makes return to prior carrying conditions necessary.

## Pairs

Carried Condition pairs with [[Overload]]. Overload names load exceeding supportable capacity; Carried Condition names return to prior carrying conditions before interpretation or further carrying.

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Ground]]
- [[Gravity]]
- [[Load]]
- [[Capacity]]
- [[Overload]]

## Nests

Carried Condition nests inside [[Carrying]] as a return condition: where the carrier stops treating itself as the only carrier and lets prior carrying conditions take load.

It is not only an emergency condition. It becomes readable in fatigue, burnout, illness, shock, collapse, grief, accident, disorder, recovery, and ordinary overload wherever self-carrying has narrowed too much.

## Reads

Carried Condition becomes recognisable where load, pressure, fatigue, shock, illness, burnout, collapse, or ordinary overload exceeds self-carrying and the first movement is return to carried condition.

The movement is:

```text
load concentrates
-> self-carrying narrows
-> return to carried condition
-> ground and gravity take load
-> breath gives interval
-> carrying becomes available again
```

In practice this can read as:

```text
You are carried.
Lower to ground if possible.
Let the ground hold weight.
Feel gravity and ground together.
Stay with one breath, then one more.
Meaning can wait.
```

This does not replace care, emergency support, medical care, or direct human response where those are needed. It places the mechanical first return: carrying conditions before interpretation.

## Carries

- [[Recovery]]
- [[Recarry]]
