- [[Step]]','Carrying Carrying is not yet Retracing. Carry is the forward passage made available where relation is held. Carrying is movement through that passage. What carries may be resolved, strained, changing, or still being formed; Resolution can shape carrying without being a universal prerequisite for it. Carrying does not create a separate relation from trace. The same connection that carries forward offers Trace backward. Retracing is a participant following that trace. Places Carrying places held forward availability being enacted. Holds Carrying is held by Hold and Carry. Forward passage must be held before it can be enacted. Pairs Carrying pairs with Retracing. Carrying is movement through the forward availability of a held connection; Retracing is movement through the backward availability of that same connection. Traces Hold Carry Connection First Order Crossing Nests Carrying nests as enacted forward movement through connection. Resolution, transfer, holding, participation, and other conditions may shape carrying without defining every instance of it. Reads Carrying becomes recognisable where held forward availability is being entered or continued, whether what passes is resolved, strained, changing, or still being formed. Carries Union Compatibility Flow Energy Carried Condition Resistance Load Capacity Traction Extend Growth Decay Adaptation Recarry Guard Intake Bearing Source Constraint Live Recursive Nested Coupling Engineered Coupling Improvisation Effect Consequence Return Face Timescale Coupling Participation Pace Echo Know Being Process Splinter Retain Apparent Source Dependency Extent Medium Member Structure Moving Sustaining Transforming Ship and Ark Terms of Service Extractive Acceleration Nested Carrying Step','Carrying Carrying is not yet Retracing. Carry is the forward passage made available where relation is held.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.carry","first.connection","first.first-order-crossing","first.h