h":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',370,'sha256:ae9e86bc4f82b6de84467f9bc939e0b8a52ea7eec590c92ae591dfe85914bf14','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.closure','Closure','closure','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/closure.html','# Closure

Closure names a read becoming bounded enough for evaluation. [[Boundary]] locates distinction, and [[Resolution]] determines bearing. Closure is the condition that lets a read be evaluated as holding within a scope. It does not require finality, completion, or an exhaustive read.

## Places

Closure places a read becoming bounded enough for evaluation.

## Holds

Closure is held by [[Boundary]] and [[Resolution]]. A read must be bounded and determined enough to be evaluated.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Closure is a singular condition — the bounding of resolution at a [[Scope]]. There is no lateral contrast at the closure level. The asymmetry is expressed in what closure becomes: [[Closure Scope]].

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]
- [[Resolution]]

## Nests

Closure nests as a second-order support root. It makes evaluation, traversal, scope, and local holding possible without requiring finality.

## Reads

Closure becomes recognisable where a read is bounded enough to be evaluated — where something can be assessed as holding or not holding within a delimited extent.
## Carries

- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Scope]]
- [[Decision]]','Closure Closure names a read becoming bounded enough for evaluation. Boundary locates distinction, and Resolution determines bearing. Closure is the condition that lets a read be evaluated as holding within a scope. It does not require finality, completion, or an exhaustive read. Places Closure places a read becoming bounded enough for evaluation. Holds Closure is held by Boundary and Resolution. A read must be bounded and determined enough to be evaluated. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Closure is a singular condition — the bounding of resolution at a Scope. There is no lateral contrast at the closure level. The asymmetry is expressed in what closure becomes: Closure Scope. Traces Boundary Resolution Nests Closure nests as a second order support root. It makes evaluation, traversal, scope, and local holding possible without requiring finality. Reads Closure becomes recognisable where a read is bounded enough to be evaluated — where something can be assessed as holding or not holding within a delimited extent. Carries Closure Scope Scope Decision','Closure Closure names a read becoming bounded enough for evaluation. Boundary locates distinction, and Resolution determines bearing.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.resolution","second.closure-scope","second.decision","second.scope"]','{"holds":["first.boundary","first.resolution"],"traces":["first.boundary","first.resolution"],"carries":["second.closure-scope","second.scope","second.decision"],"pairs":["second.closure-scope","second.scope"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',164,'sha256:e35c5d99a9a530289a02606f0381f2a2e19e1167ec6f357ba87a41a48bf17083','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.cognitive-participation','Cognitive Participation','cognitive-participation','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability Conditions/Cognitive Participation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/cognitive-participation.html','# Cognitive Participation

Cognitive Participation names relation participating in readability: the condition through which readable difference is received, distinguished, oriented, or responded to within a participating system.

This allows cognition to scale. A cell, body, animal, person, institution, ecology, tool-coupled system, or AI-coupled system may participate in readable difference without that participation being conscious in the higher-order sense.

## Places

Cognitive Participation places relation participating in readability — the condition through which readable difference is received, distinguished, oriented, or responded to within a participating system.

## Holds

Cognitive Participation is held by [[Readability]] and [[Participation]]. Difference must be available to be read, and relation must be actively taking part in a scope before cognition can be named structurally.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Cognitive Participation is a hinge between readability and participation.

## Traces

- [[Readability]]
- [[Participation]]

## Nests

Cognitive Participation nests between readability and recognition as the participating uptake of readable difference before that difference is identified as this.

## Reads

Cognitive Participation becomes readable where relation receives, distinguishes, or orients to readable difference without requiring consciousness, self-awareness, or human thought.

[[Readability]] makes difference available to be read; [[Participation]] makes relation actively take part in the scope where that readability matters. [[Recognition Read|Recognition]] follows where that uptake resolves as this. Field-level [[Cognition]] follows where cognitive participation becomes organised as thought, memory, self, modelling, or knowing.

## Carries

Cognitive Participation carries [[Recognition Read|Recognition]] and [[Cognition]]: the structural reads through which participated readability becomes identifiable, then organised inside the Cognition field.
- [[Recognition Read|Recognition]]
- [[Cognition]]
- [[Observation]]','Cognitive Participation Cognitive Participation names relation participating in readability: the condition through which readable difference is received, distinguished, oriented, or responded to within a participating system. This allows cognition to scale. A cell, body, animal, person, institution, ecology, tool coupled system, or AI coupled system may participate in readable difference without that participation being conscious in the higher order sense. Places Cognitive Participation places relation participating in readability — the condition through which readable difference is received, distinguished, oriented, or responded to within a participating system. Holds Cognitive Participation is held by Readability and Participation. Difference must be available to be read, and relation must be actively taking part in a scope before cognition can be named structurally. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Cognitive Participation is a hinge between readability and participation. Traces Readability Participation Nests Cognitive Participation nests between readability and recognition as the participating uptake of readable difference before that difference is identified as this. Reads Cognitive Participation becomes readable where relation receives, distinguishes, or orients to readable difference without requiring consciousness, self awareness, or human thought. Readability makes difference available to be read; Participation makes relation actively take part in the scope where that readability matters. Recognition Read follows where that uptake resolves as this. Field level Cognition follows where cognitive participation becomes organised as thought, memory, self, modelling, or knowing. Carries Cognitive Participation carries Recognition Read and Cognition: the structural reads through which participated readability becomes identifiable, then organised inside the Cognition field. Recognition Read Cognition Observation','Cognitive Participation Cognitive Participation names relation participating in readability: the condition through which readable difference is received, distinguished, oriented, or responded to…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.observation","second.participation","second.readability","second.recognition-read","third.cognition"]','{"holds":["second.readability","second.participation"],"traces":["second.readability","second.participation"],"carries":["second.recognition-read","third.cognition","second.observation"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',256,'sha256:d0457c858bf80558e28c103bc8fa0eec6a359f1c21e97878f8a00358aa368ca2','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.coherence','Coherence','coherence','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Coherence.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/coherence.html','# Coherence

Coherence names compatible patterns holding together. Where pattern names readable recurrence and compatibility names the condition through which carrying remains supportable, coherence names the condition through which multiple patterns hold together without losing their individual readability. Agreement, unity, or sameness may show coherence, but coherence names compatibility across a scope.

## Places

Coherence places compatible patterns holding together.

## Holds

Coherence is held by [[Pattern]] and [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Coherence pairs with [[Incoherence]]. Coherence names compatible patterns holding together; Incoherence names that compatibility no longer remaining readable.

## Traces

- [[Pattern]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Recurrence]]

## Nests

Coherence nests where multiple patterns hold together across a scope without losing individual readability.

## Reads

Coherence becomes recognisable where multiple patterns can be read as holding together — where what recurs across a scope remains compatible rather than collapsing into disorder.

## Carries

- [[Stability]]
- [[Incoherence]]
- [[Knowledge]]','Coherence Coherence names compatible patterns holding together. Where pattern names readable recurrence and compatibility names the condition through which carrying remains supportable, coherence names the condition through which multiple patterns hold together without losing their individual readability. Agreement, unity, or sameness may show coherence, but coherence names compatibility across a scope. Places Coherence places compatible patterns holding together. Holds Coherence is held by Pattern and Compatibility. Pairs Coherence pairs with Incoherence. Coherence names compatible patterns holding together; Incoherence names that compatibility no longer remaining readable. Traces Pattern Compatibility Recurrence Nests Coherence nests where multiple patterns hold together across a scope without losing individual readability. Reads Coherence becomes recognisable where multiple patterns can be read as holding together — where what recurs across a scope remains compatible rather than collapsing into disorder. Carries Stability Incoherence Knowledge','Coherence Coherence names compatible patterns holding together. Where pattern names readable recurrence and compatibility names the condition through which carrying remains supportable, coherence…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.compatibility","second.incoherence","second.pattern","second.recurrence","second.stability","third.knowledge"]','{"holds":["second.pattern","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.pattern","second.compatibility","second.recurrence"],"carries":["second.stability","second.incoherence","third.knowledge"],"pairs":["second.incoherence"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',135,'sha256:b2c2509763b5a87a516b27d8b71bfe8b4a8944d81e8e13b1179de51a24166ee6','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.collapse','Collapse','collapse','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Collapse.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/collapse.html','# Collapse

Collapse names a bounded carrying relation read as ceasing to hold at the current closure scope. Where disorder names stability no longer holding, collapse names the specific read where the bounded condition can no longer be followed — strain has exceeded what the read can trace as bearing. Collapse is scope-relative: it names where carrying crosses a [[Terminal]] the current scale cannot follow, read as an end. Over a wider closure scope, what reads as collapse may be carrying continuing past the available scale. Collapse does not name destruction, non-relation, or finality; it names loss of the readable bounded condition at this scope.

## Places

Collapse places a bounded carrying relation read as ceasing to hold at the current closure scope.

## Holds

Collapse is held by [[Dependency Disorder]] and [[Bearing]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Collapse is a singular condition — the failure of structural bearing under dependency disorder. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Dependency Disorder]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Overload]]
- [[Terminal]]
- [[Disorder]]

## Nests

Collapse nests where bounded carrying becomes unreadable at the current closure scope without claiming final non-relation.

## Reads

Collapse becomes recognisable where a previously bounded carrying condition can no longer be read as holding — where bearing has failed rather than merely strained.

## Carries','Collapse Collapse names a bounded carrying relation read as ceasing to hold at the current closure scope. Where disorder names stability no longer holding, collapse names the specific read where the bounded condition can no longer be followed — strain has exceeded what the read can trace as bearing. Collapse is scope relative: it names where carrying crosses a Terminal the current scale cannot follow, read as an end. Over a wider closure scope, what reads as collapse may be carrying continuing past the available scale. Collapse does not name destruction, non relation, or finality; it names loss of the readable bounded condition at this scope. Places Collapse places a bounded carrying relation read as ceasing to hold at the current closure scope. Holds Collapse is held by Dependency Disorder and Bearing. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Collapse is a singular condition — the failure of structural bearing under dependency disorder. There is no lateral contrast required at this level. Traces Dependency Disorder Bearing Overload Terminal Disorder Nests Collapse nests where bounded carrying becomes unreadable at the current closure scope without claiming final non relation. Reads Collapse becomes recognisable where a previously bounded carrying condition can no longer be read as holding — where bearing has failed rather than merely strained. Carries','Collapse Collapse names a bounded carrying relation read as ceasing to hold at the current closure scope. Where disorder names stability no longer holding, collapse names the specific read where…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.dependency-disorder","second.disorder","second.overload","second.terminal"]','{"holds":["second.dependency-disorder","first.bearing"],"traces":["second.dependency-disorder","first.bearing","second.overload","second.terminal","second.disorder"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',211,'sha256:7cfca5082ce63d671b53e58110cd3a06c4a982dc61d956d3fc006194bde52460','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.compatibility','Compatibility','compatibility','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Compatibility.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/compatibility.html','# Compatibility

Compatibility names the condition through which what is being carried can continue through the conditions it moves into. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, compatibility names the check that the continuation remains supportable — that what is carried and what it moves through can hold together without one destroying the other. Compatibility does not guarantee resolution; it names the condition under which carrying can proceed.

## Places

Compatibility places the condition through which what is being carried can continue through the conditions it moves into.

## Holds

Compatibility is held by [[Carrying]] and [[Coupling]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Compatibility is a singular condition — the mutual availability of carried conditions through coupling. The asymmetry is expressed in what compatibility carries: [[Stability]], [[Capacity]], and [[Know]].

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Coupling]]

## Nests

Compatibility nests as a passage condition for carrying. It regulates whether carrying can continue through encountered conditions.

## Reads

Compatibility becomes recognisable where carrying can be evaluated as supportable — where what is being carried and the conditions it moves through can be read as holding together at the current scope.
