INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.coupled-boundary','Coupled Boundary','coupled-boundary','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Coupled Boundary.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/coupled-boundary.html','# Coupled Boundary

Coupled Boundary names boundary held through coupling. Where boundary locates distinction and coupling holds resolved conditions in relation, coupled boundary names the condition through which distinct boundaries remain mutually available without collapsing into sameness or separating into unrelatedness.

## Places

Coupled Boundary places boundary held through coupling.

## Holds

Coupled Boundary is held by [[Boundary]] and [[Coupling]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Coupled Boundary is a singular condition — the boundary held through coupling. The asymmetry is expressed in what coupled boundary carries: [[Coupled Contact]], [[Boundary Loosening]], [[Sever]], and [[Decoupling]].

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]
- [[Coupling]]

## Nests

Coupled Boundary nests as the boundary form of coupling. It keeps boundaries mutually available without collapse or unrelated separation.

## Reads

Coupled Boundary becomes recognisable where a boundary is not merely located, but held in relation with another boundary so that each side remains distinct while participating in a shared coupling.

Coupled Boundary also carries [[Responsibility]]. A system may carry consequence without being the boundary that bears responsibility. Responsibility follows the trace to the coupled boundary where participation became actionable: attention, control, decision, evaluation, consent, or checking entered the relation strongly enough to affect what follows.

The vehicle carries impact; the driver-vehicle coupling is where accountable participation enters when the trace returns to attention, control, or checking. The carrier of consequence is not always the responsible unit. The responsible unit is the coupled boundary through which consequence became actionable.
## Carries

- [[Coupled Contact]]
- [[Boundary Loosening]]
- [[Sever]]
- [[Decoupling]]
- [[Relationship]]
- [[Trust]]
- [[Violation]]
- [[Responsibility]]','Coupled Boundary Coupled Boundary names boundary held through coupling. Where boundary locates distinction and coupling holds resolved conditions in relation, coupled boundary names the condition through which distinct boundaries remain mutually available without collapsing into sameness or separating into unrelatedness. Places Coupled Boundary places boundary held through coupling. Holds Coupled Boundary is held by Boundary and Coupling. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Coupled Boundary is a singular condition — the boundary held through coupling. The asymmetry is expressed in what coupled boundary carries: Coupled Contact, Boundary Loosening, Sever, and Decoupling. Traces Boundary Coupling Nests Coupled Boundary nests as the boundary form of coupling. It keeps boundaries mutually available without collapse or unrelated separation. Reads Coupled Boundary becomes recognisable where a boundary is not merely located, but held in relation with another boundary so that each side remains distinct while participating in a shared coupling. Coupled Boundary also carries Responsibility. A system may carry consequence without being the boundary that bears responsibility. Responsibility follows the trace to the coupled boundary where participation became actionable: attention, control, decision, evaluation, consent, or checking entered the relation strongly enough to affect what follows. The vehicle carries impact; the driver vehicle coupling is where accountable participation enters when the trace returns to attention, control, or checking. The carrier of consequence is not always the responsible unit. The responsible unit is the coupled boundary through which consequence became actionable. Carries Coupled Contact Boundary Loosening Sever Decoupling Relationship Trust Violation Responsibility','Coupled Boundary Coupled Boundary names boundary held through coupling. Where boundary locates distinction and coupling holds resolved conditions in relation, coupled boundary names the condition…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","second.boundary-loosening","second.coupled-contact","second.coupling","second.decoupling","second.responsibility","second.sever","third.relationship","third.trust","third.violation"]','{"holds":["first.boundary","second.coupling"],"traces":["first.boundary","second.coupling"],"carries":["second.coupled-contact","second.boundary-loosening","second.sever","second.decoupling","third.relationship","third.trust","third.violation","second.responsibility"],"pairs":["second.coupled-contact","second.boundary-loosening","second.sever","second.decoupling"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',243,'sha256:fe8fc6f310d4ffbda67a7bbe9510c04cd80ce4c067a6d685a75e1fb6bbcab602','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.coupled-contact','Coupled Contact','coupled-contact','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Coupled Contact.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/coupled-contact.html','# Coupled Contact

Coupled Contact names contact maintained strongly enough for carrying, resistance, pressure, grip, traction, or effect to pass between conditions.

A tyre touching the road is [[Contact]]. A tyre gripping the road so that braking and steering effects can pass through the tyre-road relation is Coupled Contact.

Coupled Contact keeps the simple word contact from carrying too much. Contact names meeting. Coupled Contact names meeting that carries effect.

## Places

Coupled Contact places contact maintained strongly enough for carrying, resistance, pressure, grip, traction, or effect to pass between conditions.

## Holds

Coupled Contact is held by [[Contact]], [[Coupling]], and [[Presence]]. Contact must be locally available and held in relation before it can carry effect.

## Pairs

Coupled Contact pairs with [[Interposed Carrier]]. Coupled Contact names contact carrying effect; Interposed Carrier names a condition entering between contact and coupling, changing or interrupting what can pass.

## Traces

- [[Contact]]
- [[Coupling]]
- [[Presence]]
- [[Coupled Boundary]]

## Nests

Coupled Contact nests at a contact condition that remains coupled enough for carrying, resistance, grip, traction, or effect to pass.

## Reads

Coupled Contact becomes recognisable where contact does more than meet: it carries effect, resistance, grip, pressure, heat, or directed carrying between conditions.

## Carries

- [[Effect]]
- [[Friction]]
- [[Grip]]
- [[Traction]]','Coupled Contact Coupled Contact names contact maintained strongly enough for carrying, resistance, pressure, grip, traction, or effect to pass between conditions. A tyre touching the road is Contact. A tyre gripping the road so that braking and steering effects can pass through the tyre road relation is Coupled Contact. Coupled Contact keeps the simple word contact from carrying too much. Contact names meeting. Coupled Contact names meeting that carries effect. Places Coupled Contact places contact maintained strongly enough for carrying, resistance, pressure, grip, traction, or effect to pass between conditions. Holds Coupled Contact is held by Contact, Coupling, and Presence. Contact must be locally available and held in relation before it can carry effect. Pairs Coupled Contact pairs with Interposed Carrier. Coupled Contact names contact carrying effect; Interposed Carrier names a condition entering between contact and coupling, changing or interrupting what can pass. Traces Contact Coupling Presence Coupled Boundary Nests Coupled Contact nests at a contact condition that remains coupled enough for carrying, resistance, grip, traction, or effect to pass. Reads Coupled Contact becomes recognisable where contact does more than meet: it carries effect, resistance, grip, pressure, heat, or directed carrying between conditions. Carries Effect Friction Grip Traction','Coupled Contact Coupled Contact names contact maintained strongly enough for carrying, resistance, pressure, grip, traction, or effect to pass between conditions. A tyre touching the road is Contact.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.contact","second.coupled-boundary","second.coupling","second.effect","second.friction","second.grip","second.interposed_carrier","second.presence","second.traction"]','{"holds":["first.contact","second.coupling","second.presence"],"traces":["first.contact","second.coupling","second.presence","second.coupled-boundary"],"carries":["second.effect","second.friction","second.grip","second.traction"],"pairs":["second.interposed_carrier"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',198,'sha256:4ca1d6cdd6d3db24cc7b188ebafe1d95406c87f6724d45ef78e02bac5c992ba6','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.coupling','Coupling','coupling','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/coupling.html','# Coupling

Coupling names connected relation: two or more resolved conditions held in relation to each other. Where [[Resolved Asymmetry]] names a single determined condition, coupling names the condition through which determined conditions become mutually available while remaining distinct. Coupling is the second-order precondition for presence, reality, and identity.

Coupled relation connects. Contact can meet without coupling; a link can point without bearing; a category can group without participation. Coupling holds distinct resolved conditions in mutual availability so that relation can become locally present, answerable, and able to participate.

## Places

Coupling places connected relation — distinct resolved conditions held in mutual availability without collapsing into sameness.

## Holds

Coupling is held by [[Resolved Asymmetry]] and [[Carrying]]. Distinct conditions must be determined and carried enough to become mutually available.

## Pairs

Coupling pairs with [[Decoupling]]: coupling holds distinct resolved conditions in mutual availability; decoupling names that mutual availability no longer holding.

## Traces

- [[Resolved Asymmetry]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Union]]

## Nests

Coupling nests as a second-order support root. It makes presence, compatibility, identity, coupled contact, pair, and bearing relation possible without collapsing coupled conditions into sameness.

## Reads

Coupling becomes recognisable where two distinct resolved conditions can be read as connected relation — held in relation to each other, mutually available, and still distinct.
