- [[Nested Coupling]]
- [[Engineered Coupling]]
- [[Effect]]
- [[Reality]]
- [[Resonance]]
- [[Exchanging]]','Coupling Coupling names connected relation: two or more resolved conditions held in relation to each other. Where Resolved Asymmetry names a single determined condition, coupling names the condition through which determined conditions become mutually available while remaining distinct. Coupling is the second order precondition for presence, reality, and identity. Coupled relation connects. Contact can meet without coupling; a link can point without bearing; a category can group without participation. Coupling holds distinct resolved conditions in mutual availability so that relation can become locally present, answerable, and able to participate. Places Coupling places connected relation — distinct resolved conditions held in mutual availability without collapsing into sameness. Holds Coupling is held by Resolved Asymmetry and Carrying. Distinct conditions must be determined and carried enough to become mutually available. Pairs Coupling pairs with Decoupling: coupling holds distinct resolved conditions in mutual availability; decoupling names that mutual availability no longer holding. Traces Resolved Asymmetry Carrying Union Nests Coupling nests as a second order support root. It makes presence, compatibility, identity, coupled contact, pair, and bearing relation possible without collapsing coupled conditions into sameness. Reads Coupling becomes recognisable where two distinct resolved conditions can be read as connected relation — held in relation to each other, mutually available, and still distinct. Carries Presence Identity Compatibility Pair Coupled Boundary Coupled Contact Bearing Relation Coupled Asymmetry Maintained Coupling Nested Coupling Engineered Coupling Effect Reality Resonance Exchanging','Coupling Coupling names connected relation: two or more resolved conditions held in relation to each other. Where Resolved Asymmetry names a single determined condition, coupling names the…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.resolved-asymmetry","second.bearing-relation","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.coupled-asymmetry","second.coupled-boundary","second.coupled-contact","second.decoupling","second.effect","second.identity","second.pair","second.presence","second.reality","second.resonance","second.union","third.engineered-coupling","third.exchanging","third.maintained-coupling","third.nested-coupling"]','{"holds":["first.resolved-asymmetry","second.carrying"],"traces":["first.resolved-asymmetry","second.carrying","second.union"],"carries":["second.presence","second.identity","second.compatibility","second.pair","second.coupled-boundary","second.coupled-contact","second.bearing-relation","second.coupled-asymmetry","third.maintained-coupling","third.nested-coupling","third.engineered-coupling","second.effect","second.reality","second.resonance","third.exchanging"],"pairs":["second.decoupling"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',230,'sha256:6e27d6bc4e542f20551b46d4917620f4c6b7ffab012951e69022b39241dd879e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.current','Current','current','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Current.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/current.html','# Current

Current names directed flow through a medium. Where flow names carrying continuing through a medium, current names that flow as oriented and locally readable.

## Places

Current places directed flow through a medium.

## Holds

Current is held by [[Flow]], [[Orientation]], and [[Medium]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Current is a singular condition — flow directed through [[Orientation]] and [[Medium]]. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Flow]]
- [[Orientation]]
- [[Medium]]

## Nests

Current nests inside flow as oriented carrying through a medium.

## Reads

Current becomes recognisable where flow can be read as moving in a direction through a medium.

## Carries','Current Current names directed flow through a medium. Where flow names carrying continuing through a medium, current names that flow as oriented and locally readable. Places Current places directed flow through a medium. Holds Current is held by Flow, Orientation, and Medium. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Current is a singular condition — flow directed through Orientation and Medium. There is no lateral contrast required at this level. Traces Flow Orientation Medium Nests Current nests inside flow as oriented carrying through a medium. Reads Current becomes recognisable where flow can be read as moving in a direction through a medium. Carries','Current Current names directed flow through a medium. Where flow names carrying continuing through a medium, current names that flow as oriented and locally readable.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.orientation","second.flow","second.medium"]','{"holds":["second.flow","first.orientation","second.medium"],"traces":["second.flow","first.orientation","second.medium"],"carries":[],"pairs":["first.orientation","second.medium"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',100,'sha256:32a2f32f2a2d8906df694c4390e60f1d4cee9aca5bd09becd8909c7ba0ecef9e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.cycle','Cycle','cycle','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Participation Conditions/Cycle.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/cycle.html','# Cycle

Cycle names a return bounded by a recognisable period. Repetition can show a cycle, but does not define one: the recurrence must remain traceable as a carried condition, and the return must be bounded as one complete passage through a period.

## Places

Cycle places a return bounded by a recognisable period.

## Holds

Cycle is held by [[Recurrence]], [[Return]], and [[Period]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. [[Recurrence]], [[Return]], and [[Period]] carry downward into Cycle as one bounded readable passage.

## Traces

- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Return]]
- [[Period]]

## Nests

Cycle nests where recurrence makes a carried condition readable again through a recognisable period.

## Reads

Cycle becomes recognisable where a return can be bounded as one complete recurrence through a period.

## Carries','Cycle Cycle names a return bounded by a recognisable period. Repetition can show a cycle, but does not define one: the recurrence must remain traceable as a carried condition, and the return must be bounded as one complete passage through a period. Places Cycle places a return bounded by a recognisable period. Holds Cycle is held by Recurrence, Return, and Period. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Recurrence, Return, and Period carry downward into Cycle as one bounded readable passage. Traces Recurrence Return Period Nests Cycle nests where recurrence makes a carried condition readable again through a recognisable period. Reads Cycle becomes recognisable where a return can be bounded as one complete recurrence through a period. Carries','Cycle Cycle names a return bounded by a recognisable period. Repetition can show a cycle, but does not define one: the recurrence must remain traceable as a carried condition, and the return must…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.period","second.recurrence","second.return"]','{"holds":["second.recurrence","second.return","second.period"],"traces":["second.recurrence","second.return","second.period"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.recurrence","second.return","second.period"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',117,'sha256:7e5a44703b9ceb8e9ca8e496f289f7ca736dc20fc419bb37c9444f20ec706c7a','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.decay','Decay','decay','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Decay.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/decay.html','# Decay

Decay names decrease in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Failure can follow decay, but decay first names change read as loss or reduction within a closure scope.

## Places

Decay places decrease in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal.

## Holds

Decay is held by [[Change]], [[Scale]], and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Decay pairs with [[Growth]]. Decay reads decrease across traversal; Growth reads increase across traversal.

## Traces

- [[Change]]
- [[Scale]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Growth]]

## Nests

Decay nests inside change and scale reads as decrease across traversal.

## Reads

Decay becomes recognisable where a condition can be followed as decreasing in extent, carrying, or available participation.

## Carries

- [[Wear]]','Decay Decay names decrease in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Failure can follow decay, but decay first names change read as loss or reduction within a closure scope. Places Decay places decrease in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Holds Decay is held by Change, Scale, and Carrying. Pairs Decay pairs with Growth. Decay reads decrease across traversal; Growth reads increase across traversal. Traces Change Scale Carrying Growth Nests Decay nests inside change and scale reads as decrease across traversal. Reads Decay becomes recognisable where a condition can be followed as decreasing in extent, carrying, or available participation. Carries Wear','Decay Decay names decrease in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Failure can follow decay, but decay first names change read as loss or reduction within a closure scope.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.change","second.growth","second.scale","second.wear"]','{"holds":["second.change","second.scale","second.carrying"],"traces":["second.change","second.scale","second.carrying","second.growth"],"carries":["second.wear"],"pairs":["second.growth"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',103,'sha256:97f119a72f20d38464d5e7915b4ca81f8eebffcfe52558390f78c4f131151a9b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.decision','Decision','decision','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Decision.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/decision.html','# Decision

Decision names a carried sequence resolved at a choice point. Where strategy names a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution, decision names the condition through which that orientation reaches a point of determination — where one path is taken over others within the current closure scope. Decision does not name finality or correctness; it names the readable condition through which a strategy reaches its closure point.

## Places

Decision places a carried sequence resolved at a choice point.

## Holds

Decision is held by [[Strategy]] and [[Closure]].

## Pairs

Decision pairs with [[Strategy]]. Strategy orients a carried sequence; Decision names its point of determination.

## Traces

- [[Strategy]]
- [[Closure]]

## Nests

Decision nests at a closure point in a carried strategy where continuation requires one path to be taken.

## Reads

Decision becomes recognisable where a carried, oriented sequence reaches a point where continuation requires selecting one available path — where strategy resolves into a taken direction.

## Carries

- [[Evaluation]]','Decision Decision names a carried sequence resolved at a choice point. Where strategy names a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution, decision names the condition through which that orientation reaches a point of determination — where one path is taken over others within the current closure scope. Decision does not name finality or correctness; it names the readable condition through which a strategy reaches its closure point. Places Decision places a carried sequence resolved at a choice point. Holds Decision is held by Strategy and Closure. Pairs Decision pairs with Strategy. Strategy orients a carried sequence; Decision names its point of determination. Traces Strategy Closure Nests Decision nests at a closure point in a carried strategy where continuation requires one path to be taken. Reads Decision becomes recognisable where a carried, oriented sequence reaches a point where continuation requires selecting one available path — where strategy resolves into a taken direction. Carries Evaluation','Decision Decision names a carried sequence resolved at a choice point. Where strategy names a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution, decision names the condition through which that…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure","second.evaluation","second.strategy"]','{"holds":["second.strategy","second.closure"],"traces":["second.strategy","second.closure"],"carries":["second.evaluation"],"pairs":["second.strategy"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',153,'sha256:e03b350c7c0b0a89d956e83505bf17ff81cd8c2e07dc55ab4cd64fee48046eef','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.decoupling','Decoupling','decoupling','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Decoupling.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/decoupling.html','# Decoupling

Decoupling names coupling no longer holding a coupled boundary as mutual availability. Distance or difference can follow decoupling, but decoupling names the condition where what had been coupled no longer remains coupled at the boundary through which it was held together.

## Places

Decoupling places coupling no longer holding a coupled boundary as mutual availability.

## Holds

Decoupling is held by [[Coupled Boundary]], [[Boundary Loosening]], and [[Release]].

## Pairs

Decoupling pairs with [[Coupling]]: decoupling names mutual availability no longer holding; coupling names distinct resolved conditions held in mutual availability. Each is only locatable against the other — decoupling is only readable where coupling was operative, and coupling is only readable where decoupling is possible.

## Traces

- [[Coupled Boundary]]
- [[Boundary Loosening]]
- [[Release]]
## Nests

Decoupling nests where coupled boundary resolves as separation, release, or loss of mutual availability.

## Reads

Decoupling becomes recognisable where a coupled boundary resolves as separation, release, or loss of mutual availability rather than continued contact, compatibility, or participation.

## Carries','Decoupling Decoupling names coupling no longer holding a coupled boundary as mutual availability. Distance or difference can follow decoupling, but decoupling names the condition where what had been coupled no longer remains coupled at the boundary through which it was held together. Places Decoupling places coupling no longer holding a coupled boundary as mutual availability. Holds Decoupling is held by Coupled Boundary, Boundary Loosening, and Release. Pairs Decoupling pairs with Coupling: decoupling names mutual availability no longer holding; coupling names distinct resolved conditions held in mutual availability. Each is only locatable against the other — decoupling is only readable where coupling was operative, and coupling is only readable where decoupling is possible. Traces Coupled Boundary Boundary Loosening Release Nests Decoupling nests where coupled boundary resolves as separation, release, or loss of mutual availability. Reads Decoupling becomes recognisable where a coupled boundary resolves as separation, release, or loss of mutual availability rather than continued contact, compatibility, or participation. Carries','Decoupling Decoupling names coupling no longer holding a coupled boundary as mutual availability. Distance or difference can follow decoupling, but decoupling names the condition where what had…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.release","second.boundary-loosening","second.coupled-boundary","second.coupling"]','{"holds":["second.coupled-boundary","second.boundary-loosening","first.release"],"traces":["second.coupled-boundary","second.boundary-loosening","first.release"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.coupling"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',158,'sha256:cd7a56cf89cfb46f0aa3491f6be006bff43c301a63af2af1ddcfe8eda0432c9c','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.delayed-availability','Delayed Availability','delayed-availability','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Delayed Availability.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/delayed-availability.html','# Delayed Availability

Delayed availability names uneven availability across traversal — the condition through which what should be available at one point in a sequence becomes available only later, or not at all within the current scope. Where dependency disorder names the loss of retraceability, delayed availability names a specific effect: participation continues but the conditions required for compatible carrying are not yet present at the point where they are needed.

## Places

Delayed Availability places uneven availability across traversal — the condition through which what should be available at one point in a sequence becomes available only later, or not at all within the current scope.

## Holds

Delayed Availability is held by [[Dependency Disorder]] and [[Availability]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Delayed Availability is a singular condition — availability held back through dependency disorder. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Dependency Disorder]]
- [[Availability]]

## Nests

Delayed Availability nests inside dependency disorder as support arriving late, or not at all, within the current scope.

## Reads

Delayed availability becomes recognisable where a required condition is absent at the point of participation — where carrying proceeds but the dependency that should support it has not yet become available.

## Carries

- [[Faith Read]]
- [[Second-Order Disorder Effects]]','Delayed Availability Delayed availability names uneven availability across traversal — the condition through which what should be available at one point in a sequence becomes available only later, or not at all within the current scope. Where dependency disorder names the loss of retraceability, delayed availability names a specific effect: participation continues but the conditions required for compatible carrying are not yet present at the point where they are needed. Places Delayed Availability places uneven availability across traversal — the condition through which what should be available at one point in a sequence becomes available only later, or not at all within the current scope. Holds Delayed Availability is held by Dependency Disorder and Availability. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Delayed Availability is a singular condition — availability held back through dependency disorder. There is no lateral contrast required at this level. Traces Dependency Disorder Availability Nests Delayed Availability nests inside dependency disorder as support arriving late, or not at all, within the current scope. Reads Delayed availability becomes recognisable where a required condition is absent at the point of participation — where carrying proceeds but the dependency that should support it has not yet become available. Carries Faith Read Second Order Disorder Effects','Delayed Availability Delayed availability names uneven availability across traversal — the condition through which what should be available at one point in a sequence becomes available only later,…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.availability","second.dependency-disorder","second.second-order-disorder-effects","third.faith-read"]','{"holds":["second.dependency-disorder","first.availability"],"traces":["second.dependency-disorder","first.availability"],"carries":["third.faith-read","second.second-order-disorder-effects"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',203,'sha256:7a8c98eae17196bce5e0912316a16765e72ce7bc183e383180d242e38ffd7c9b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.dependency-disorder','Dependency Disorder','dependency-disorder','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Dependency Disorder.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/dependency-disorder.html','# Dependency Disorder

Dependency disorder names disorder in which the dependency path itself becomes unreadable. Where disorder names stability no longer holding, dependency disorder names the specific condition where the dependency trace through which a read could be re-established is obscured, bypassed, displaced, reversed, or forced. Dependency disorder is not mere instability; it names the loss of retraceability.

## Places

Dependency Disorder places disorder in which the dependency path itself becomes unreadable.

## Holds

Dependency Disorder is held by [[Disorder]] and [[Dependency Order]].

## Pairs

Dependency Disorder pairs with [[Dependency]]. Dependency names required support; Dependency Disorder names the dependency path becoming unreadable.

## Traces

- [[Disorder]]
- [[Dependency Order]]
- [[Structural Disorder]]
- [[Dependency]]

## Nests

Dependency Disorder nests where the trace required to re-establish a read is obscured, bypassed, displaced, reversed, or forced.

## Reads

Dependency disorder becomes recognisable where a condition appears to proceed while the dependency required for its carrying has been bypassed, displaced, or forced — where the trace back to what must hold is no longer available.

## Carries

- [[Collapse]]
- [[Delayed Availability]]
