sts":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',171,'sha256:2cbfd6069b7e8107cf367616448796ad2b5815492137e760682906f9e2a4969b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.dependency','Dependency','dependency','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Dependency.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/dependency.html','# Dependency

Dependency names one condition requiring another to remain available. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, dependency names the structural condition through which one carried condition cannot hold without another also holding. Weakness or subordination can involve dependency, but dependency first names the readable requirement that carrying preserves.

## Places

Dependency places one condition requiring another to remain available.

## Holds

Dependency is held by [[Dependency Order]] and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Dependency pairs with [[Dependency Disorder]]. Dependency names required support; Dependency Disorder names disorder where required support is misread, missing, or displaced.

## Traces

- [[Dependency Order]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Dependency nests inside carrying where one condition requires another to remain available.

## Reads

Dependency becomes recognisable where a condition cannot remain available without another condition also holding — where carrying is conditional on what else must be carried.

## Carries

- [[Dependency Disorder]]','Dependency Dependency names one condition requiring another to remain available. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, dependency names the structural condition through which one carried condition cannot hold without another also holding. Weakness or subordination can involve dependency, but dependency first names the readable requirement that carrying preserves. Places Dependency places one condition requiring another to remain available. Holds Dependency is held by Dependency Order and Carrying. Pairs Dependency pairs with Dependency Disorder. Dependency names required support; Dependency Disorder names disorder where required support is misread, missing, or displaced. Traces Dependency Order Carrying Nests Dependency nests inside carrying where one condition requires another to remain available. Reads Dependency becomes recognisable where a condition cannot remain available without another condition also holding — where carrying is conditional on what else must be carried. Carries Dependency Disorder','Dependency Dependency names one condition requiring another to remain available. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, dependency names the structural…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.dependency-order","second.carrying","second.dependency-disorder"]','{"holds":["ground.dependency-order","second.carrying"],"traces":["ground.dependency-order","second.carrying"],"carries":["second.dependency-disorder"],"pairs":["second.dependency-disorder"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',139,'sha256:ea091422d71a54ae210041e87799d3b7454943ff5160c4876902a0867feec921','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.difference','Difference','difference','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Difference.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/difference.html','# Difference

Difference names distinguishable non-sameness. Where [[Distinction]] names bounded unevenness becoming distinguishable, Difference names the produced read of that distinction as this rather than that. Opposition or conflict can show difference, but difference is broader: two things can be read as not the same while remaining related.

## Places

Difference places distinguishable non-sameness.

## Holds

Difference is held by [[Distinction]] and [[Readability]].

## Pairs

Difference is vertical. It names distinguishable non-sameness, and carries this forward into [[Form]], [[Information]], and [[Change]]. Difference is held by [[Distinction]] and [[Readability]] — it is the produced read of distinction at second order, not a co-present lateral condition alongside another second-order term.

## Traces

- [[Distinction]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Difference nests as the produced read of asymmetry becoming readable as this rather than that.

## Reads

Difference becomes recognisable where relation can be read as this rather than that — where non-sameness is present and readable rather than merely implied.

## Carries

- [[Form]]
- [[Information]]
- [[Change]]
- [[Dimension]]','Difference Difference names distinguishable non sameness. Where Distinction names bounded unevenness becoming distinguishable, Difference names the produced read of that distinction as this rather than that. Opposition or conflict can show difference, but difference is broader: two things can be read as not the same while remaining related. Places Difference places distinguishable non sameness. Holds Difference is held by Distinction and Readability. Pairs Difference is vertical. It names distinguishable non sameness, and carries this forward into Form, Information, and Change. Difference is held by Distinction and Readability — it is the produced read of distinction at second order, not a co present lateral condition alongside another second order term. Traces Distinction Readability Nests Difference nests as the produced read of asymmetry becoming readable as this rather than that. Reads Difference becomes recognisable where relation can be read as this rather than that — where non sameness is present and readable rather than merely implied. Carries Form Information Change Dimension','Difference Difference names distinguishable non sameness. Where Distinction names bounded unevenness becoming distinguishable, Difference names the produced read of that distinction as this rather…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.distinction","second.change","second.dimension","second.form","second.information","second.readability"]','{"holds":["first.distinction","second.readability"],"traces":["first.distinction","second.readability"],"carries":["second.form","second.information","second.change","second.dimension"],"pairs":["second.form","second.information","second.change"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',159,'sha256:f78c7eebe62ec26de152de2412b4ba8ce7761d044c3373c0a7190787a5313299','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.digress','Digress','digress','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Digress.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/digress.html','# Digress

Digress names traversal departing from the current scope. Where proceed names continuation within scope, digress names departure: traversal moves outside the current scope while relation remains available. Error or failure can involve digression, but digress first names readable departure.

## Places

Digress places traversal departing from the current scope.

## Holds

Digress is held by [[Traversal]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. Digress may open a later [[Return]], but Return does not require departure.

## Traces

- [[Traversal]]
- [[Proceed]]

## Nests

Digress nests where traversal departs from current scope while relation remains available.

## Reads

Digress becomes recognisable where traversal can be read as departing from the current scope — where participation moves outside the bounded extent without losing relation.

## Carries','Digress Digress names traversal departing from the current scope. Where proceed names continuation within scope, digress names departure: traversal moves outside the current scope while relation remains available. Error or failure can involve digression, but digress first names readable departure. Places Digress places traversal departing from the current scope. Holds Digress is held by Traversal. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Digress may open a later Return, but Return does not require departure. Traces Traversal Proceed Nests Digress nests where traversal departs from current scope while relation remains available. Reads Digress becomes recognisable where traversal can be read as departing from the current scope — where participation moves outside the bounded extent without losing relation. Carries','Digress Digress names traversal departing from the current scope. Where proceed names continuation within scope, digress names departure: traversal moves outside the current scope while relation…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.proceed","second.return","second.traversal"]','{"holds":["second.traversal"],"traces":["second.traversal","second.proceed"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.return"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',116,'sha256:437484e5fbf20802c1fab0bcd3c26cdcfc2b18f59d2f31512ef46e27ef145e19','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.dimension','Dimension','dimension','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Dimension.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/dimension.html','# Dimension

Dimension names a readable axis of difference. Where difference names distinguishable non-sameness, dimension names that difference held as an axis: a direction along which distinctions can be read, compared, and ordered. Spatial axes are dimensions, but dimension is broader: any readable direction of difference within a closure scope.

## Places

Dimension places a readable axis of difference.

## Holds

Dimension is held by [[Difference]] and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Dimension is a singular condition — the axis of difference within a closure scope. The asymmetry is expressed in what dimension carries: [[Scale]].

## Traces

- [[Difference]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Dimension nests where difference becomes a readable axis for comparison and order.

## Reads

Dimension becomes recognisable where difference can be read as directional — where distinctions can be arranged along a readable axis rather than merely noted as non-same.

## Carries

- [[Scale]]','Dimension Dimension names a readable axis of difference. Where difference names distinguishable non sameness, dimension names that difference held as an axis: a direction along which distinctions can be read, compared, and ordered. Spatial axes are dimensions, but dimension is broader: any readable direction of difference within a closure scope. Places Dimension places a readable axis of difference. Holds Dimension is held by Difference and Closure Scope. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Dimension is a singular condition — the axis of difference within a closure scope. The asymmetry is expressed in what dimension carries: Scale. Traces Difference Closure Scope Nests Dimension nests where difference becomes a readable axis for comparison and order. Reads Dimension becomes recognisable where difference can be read as directional — where distinctions can be arranged along a readable axis rather than merely noted as non same. Carries Scale','Dimension Dimension names a readable axis of difference. Where difference names distinguishable non sameness, dimension names that difference held as an axis: a direction along which distinctions…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.difference","second.scale"]','{"holds":["second.difference","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.difference","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["second.scale"],"pairs":["second.scale"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',141,'sha256:a6382358b3c831f2a6121320fbf06ceb1f660b304a6ae332db634bfd4bf2158f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.disorder','Disorder','disorder','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Disorder.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/disorder.html','# Disorder

Disorder names stability no longer holding. Where stability names identity and coherence sustained across scope, disorder names the condition through which that holding becomes unreadable — strain exceeding bearing, patterns no longer compatible, identity no longer recognisable as the same. Disorder does not name chaos or non-relation; it names the readable loss of a previously held stability within the current scope.

Disorder is shaded order, not a positive thing beside order. It is order under loss, occlusion, interruption, residue, or unreadability at the current scope.

## Places

Disorder places stability no longer holding.

## Holds

Disorder is held by [[Stability]] and [[Strain]].

## Pairs

Disorder pairs with [[Stability]]. Stability names identity and coherence holding; Disorder names that holding becoming unreadable.

## Traces

- [[Stability]]
- [[Strain]]

## Nests

Disorder nests where identity, coherence, or compatibility no longer holds within the current scope.

## Reads

Disorder becomes recognisable where a previously stable condition can no longer be read as holding — where identity, coherence, or compatibility has broken down within the current scope.

## Carries

- [[Incoherence]]
- [[Dependency Disorder]]
- [[Collapse]]
- [[Second-Order Disorder Effects]]','Disorder Disorder names stability no longer holding. Where stability names identity and coherence sustained across scope, disorder names the condition through which that holding becomes unreadable — strain exceeding bearing, patterns no longer compatible, identity no longer recognisable as the same. Disorder does not name chaos or non relation; it names the readable loss of a previously held stability within the current scope. Disorder is shaded order, not a positive thing beside order. It is order under loss, occlusion, interruption, residue, or unreadability at the current scope. Places Disorder places stability no longer holding. Holds Disorder is held by Stability and Strain. Pairs Disorder pairs with Stability. Stability names identity and coherence holding; Disorder names that holding becoming unreadable. Traces Stability Strain Nests Disorder nests where identity, coherence, or compatibility no longer holds within the current scope. Reads Disorder becomes recognisable where a previously stable condition can no longer be read as holding — where identity, coherence, or compatibility has broken down within the current scope. Carries Incoherence Dependency Disorder Collapse Second Order Disorder Effects','Disorder Disorder names stability no longer holding. Where stability names identity and coherence sustained across scope, disorder names the condition through which that holding becomes unreadable…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.strain","second.collapse","second.dependency-disorder","second.incoherence","second.second-order-disorder-effects","second.stability"]','{"holds":["second.stability","first.strain"],"traces":["second.stability","first.strain"],"carries":["second.incoherence","second.dependency-disorder","second.collapse","second.second-order-disorder-effects"],"pairs":["second.stability"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',175,'sha256:96aa813cbc001ece532b5d2f48c195bdd65efc81bf04b0ba05ff91f6644914db','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.divisible-bearing','Divisible Bearing','divisible-bearing','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Divisible Bearing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/divisible-bearing.html','# Divisible Bearing

Divisible bearing names bearing that can be separated into distinguishable parts without losing the carrying condition. Where bearing names strain held, divisible bearing names that holding as readable across distinguishable divisions — carrying that continues through separable parts.

## Places

Divisible Bearing places bearing that can be separated into distinguishable parts without losing the carrying condition.

## Holds

Divisible Bearing is held by [[Bearing]] and [[Divisible]].

## Pairs

Divisible Bearing pairs with [[Indivisible Bearing]]. Divisible Bearing carries through separable parts; Indivisible Bearing must remain whole to carry.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Divisible]]

## Nests

Divisible Bearing nests where carrying remains readable across distinguishable parts.

## Reads

Divisible bearing becomes recognisable where carrying can be read through distinguishable divisions — where the holding condition persists across separable parts without losing participation.

## Carries

- [[Pattern]]','Divisible Bearing Divisible bearing names bearing that can be separated into distinguishable parts without losing the carrying condition. Where bearing names strain held, divisible bearing names that holding as readable across distinguishable divisions — carrying that continues through separable parts. Places Divisible Bearing places bearing that can be separated into distinguishable parts without losing the carrying condition. Holds Divisible Bearing is held by Bearing and Divisible. Pairs Divisible Bearing pairs with Indivisible Bearing. Divisible Bearing carries through separable parts; Indivisible Bearing must remain whole to carry. Traces Bearing Divisible Nests Divisible Bearing nests where carrying remains readable across distinguishable parts. Reads Divisible bearing becomes recognisable where carrying can be read through distinguishable divisions — where the holding condition persists across separable parts without losing participation. Carries Pattern','Divisible Bearing Divisible bearing names bearing that can be separated into distinguishable parts without losing the carrying condition. Where bearing names strain held, divisible bearing names…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.divisible","second.indivisible-bearing","second.pattern"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","first.divisible"],"traces":["first.bearing","first.divisible"],"carries":["second.pattern"],"pairs":["second.indivisible-bearing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',127,'sha256:9e5c691c66fb7222b951e5b9c8cbedd3b983f88038f3f5619353d2faeb746fa6','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.drag','Drag','drag','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Drag.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/drag.html','# Drag

Drag names slowing resistance carried through flow. Drag is not blockage; it is resistance carried with flow as a reducing condition.

## Places

Drag places slowing resistance carried through flow.

## Holds

Drag is held by [[Resistance]], [[Flow]], and [[Speed]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Drag is a singular condition — resistance applied through [[Flow]] against [[Speed]]. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Resistance]]
- [[Flow]]
- [[Speed]]
- [[Friction]]

## Nests

Drag nests inside resistance and flow as slowing resistance rather than blockage.

## Reads

Drag becomes recognisable where flow continues while being slowed by the condition it passes through.

## Carries','Drag Drag names slowing resistance carried through flow. Drag is not blockage; it is resistance carried with flow as a reducing condition. Places Drag places slowing resistance carried through flow. Holds Drag is held by Resistance, Flow, and Speed. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Drag is a singular condition — resistance applied through Flow against Speed. There is no lateral contrast required at this level. Traces Resistance Flow Speed Friction Nests Drag nests inside resistance and flow as slowing resistance rather than blockage. Reads Drag becomes recognisable where flow continues while being slowed by the condition it passes through. Carries','Drag Drag names slowing resistance carried through flow. Drag is not blockage; it is resistance carried with flow as a reducing condition.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.flow","second.friction","second.resistance","second.speed"]','{"holds":["second.resistance","second.flow","second.speed"],"traces":["second.resistance","second.flow","second.speed","second.friction"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.flow","second.speed"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',99,'sha256:3111e9675f88bf8e2a816e90e9e45eb0841234af43caaf5372abe7862d3d9733','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.echo','Echo','echo','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability Conditions/Echo.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/echo.html','# Echo

Echo names a returned trace whose source is not directly present.

Echo is not mere repetition. Repetition can occur again without carrying a prior relation. Echo returns something of a prior relation as readable trace. It may be sound reflected, a word-form resonating, a grief returning, a cultural pattern repeating, or an AI output carrying a pattern whose bearing structure is not present in the output itself.

## Places

Echo places a returned trace whose source is not directly present.

## Holds

Echo is held by [[Readability]], [[Trace]], [[Recurrence]], and [[Carrying]]. A trace must be readable, recurrence must return it, and carrying must preserve enough of it for the return to be read before echo can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Echo is distinguished from source, memory, and recurrence by naming returned trace rather than original presence, stored carrying, or occurrence again.

## Traces

- [[Readability]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Echo nests inside readability where a prior relation returns as readable trace without the source being directly present.

## Reads

Echo becomes readable where a sound, form, word, pattern, feeling, gesture, or relation returns as trace while what produced it is no longer directly present.

A language echo is not proof of origin. It is a prompt to retrace relation. The echo may preserve a real path, or it may be coincidence, resemblance, or drift. Its value is not that it proves source, but that it makes a possible relation available for careful retrace.

## Carries

Echo carries no further public branch at this scope.','Echo Echo names a returned trace whose source is not directly present. Echo is not mere repetition. Repetition can occur again without carrying a prior relation. Echo returns something of a prior relation as readable trace. It may be sound reflected, a word form resonating, a grief returning, a cultural pattern repeating, or an AI output carrying a pattern whose bearing structure is not present in the output itself. Places Echo places a returned trace whose source is not directly present. Holds Echo is held by Readability, Trace, Recurrence, and Carrying. A trace must be readable, recurrence must return it, and carrying must preserve enough of it for the return to be read before echo can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Echo is distinguished from source, memory, and recurrence by naming returned trace rather than original presence, stored carrying, or occurrence again. Traces Readability Trace Recurrence Carrying Nests Echo nests inside readability where a prior relation returns as readable trace without the source being directly present. Reads Echo becomes readable where a sound, form, word, pattern, feeling, gesture, or relation returns as trace while what produced it is no longer directly present. A language echo is not proof of origin. It is a prompt to retrace relation. The echo may preserve a real path, or it may be coincidence, resemblance, or drift. Its value is not that it proves source, but that it makes a possible relation available for careful retrace. Carries Echo carries no further public branch at this scope.','Echo Echo names a returned trace whose source is not directly present. Echo is not mere repetition.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.trace","second.carrying","second.readability","second.recurrence"]','{"holds":["second.readability","first.trace","second.recurrence","second.carrying"],"traces":["second.readability","first.trace","second.recurrence","second.carrying"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',258,'sha256:b36a56c370ab22906b16f9a12ceb769319731ea746971f44742f8a99590cc2b4','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.effect','Effect','effect','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Effect.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/effect.html','# Effect

Effect names change in one condition carried through coupling from another condition.

Change alone does not establish effect. Two conditions may change together without one change being carried through their relation. Effect becomes available where the change remains traceable through coupling: what one condition carries alters what the other can hold, do, present, or continue.

## Places

Effect places change in one condition carried through coupling from another condition.

## Holds

Effect is held by [[Coupling]], [[Carrying]], and [[Change]]. Conditions must be coupled, carrying must pass through the relation, and a readable change must occur before effect can be named.

## Pairs

Effect is vertical. It is the singular carried change from which participatory alteration can later be read as [[Influence]]. No lateral opposite is required: absence of effect may indicate no carrying, incompatible coupling, insufficient resolution, or a change outside the current scope.

## Traces

- [[Coupling]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Change]]
- [[Coupled Contact]]

## Nests

Effect nests inside coupling where carrying from one condition becomes readable as change in another, whether contact is direct or mediated.

## Reads

Effect becomes recognisable where a change can be traced through a coupled relation to carrying from another condition rather than only occurring alongside it.

Effect does not by itself name intention, benefit, harm, control, or responsibility. Those are later reads of what the carried change does within participation.

## Carries

- [[Influence]]
- [[Responsibility]]
- [[Consequence]]
- [[Read and Effect]]','Effect Effect names change in one condition carried through coupling from another condition. Change alone does not establish effect. Two conditions may change together without one change being carried through their relation. Effect becomes available where the change remains traceable through coupling: what one condition carries alters what the other can hold, do, present, or continue. Places Effect places change in one condition carried through coupling from another condition. Holds Effect is held by Coupling, Carrying, and Change. Conditions must be coupled, carrying must pass through the relation, and a readable change must occur before effect can be named. Pairs Effect is vertical. It is the singular carried change from which participatory alteration can later be read as Influence. No lateral opposite is required: absence of effect may indicate no carrying, incompatible coupling, insufficient resolution, or a change outside the current scope. Traces Coupling Carrying Change Coupled Contact Nests Effect nests inside coupling where carrying from one condition becomes readable as change in another, whether contact is direct or mediated. Reads Effect becomes recognisable where a change can be traced through a coupled relation to carrying from another condition rather than only occurring alongside it. Effect does not by itself name intention, benefit, harm, control, or responsibility. Those are later reads of what the carried change does within participation. Carries Influence Responsibility Consequence Read and Effect','Effect Effect names change in one condition carried through coupling from another condition. Change alone does not establish effect.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.change","second.consequence","second.coupled-contact","second.coupling","second.influence","second.read-and-effect","second.responsibility"]','{"holds":["second.coupling","second.carrying","second.change"],"traces":["second.coupling","second.carrying","second.change","second.coupled-contact"],"carries":["second.influence","second.responsibility","second.consequence","second.read-and-effect"],"pairs":["second.influence"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',226,'sha256:91e121cbf78fe6f09715471c23a4d6a6c482d25a572ce29b3d5652ce71460d9b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.energy','Energy','energy','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Energy.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/energy.html','# Energy

Energy names generated availability for carrying.

This does not replace physical, biological, or domain-specific definitions of energy. It places what energy does in the Atlas order: energy names availability generated within a condition that can carry work, movement, transformation, maintenance, attention, repair, or continuation.

The core read is:

```text
Energy is generated availability for carrying.
```

## Places

Energy places generated availability for carrying.

## Holds

Energy is held by [[Generic]], [[Carrying]], [[Capacity]], [[Pressure]], and [[Flow]].

Generic names the generative source condition. Carrying names held forward availability being enacted. Capacity names supportable carrying. Pressure names load becoming locally borne through relation. Flow names carrying continuing through a medium.

Energy becomes readable where generation makes carrying available as capacity, pressure, flow, work, movement, transformation, maintenance, attention, repair, or continuation.

## Pairs

No universal lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Energy names generated availability for carrying; its local oppositions appear as depletion, dissipation, overload, or incompatible release in particular domains.

## Traces

- [[Generic]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Capacity]]
- [[Pressure]]
- [[Flow]]

## Nests

Energy nests inside carrying as generated availability that can support work, movement, transformation, maintenance, attention, repair, or continuation.

It is not the source itself. It is the availability generated from a source or condition and made readable by what it can carry.

## Reads

Energy becomes recognisable where generation produces carrying availability.

The structural movement is:

```text
generation
-> available carrying
-> capacity, pressure, flow
-> work, movement, transformation, maintenance, repair, or continuation
```

Physical energy can be read where generated availability carries work, movement, heat, field relation, or transformation. Living energy can be read where metabolism converts intake, rest, strain, and repair into continued participation. Human energy can be read where received support, relation, nourishment, orientation, rest, or purpose becomes capacity to carry attention, care, work, speech, or action.

Energy becomes disorderly where availability continues without trace to what generated it, where it is extracted beyond compatible carrying, or where it is retained, released, or accelerated beyond the carrier''s resolution band.

## Carries

- [[Metabolism]]
- [[Recovery]]','Energy Energy names generated availability for carrying. This does not replace physical, biological, or domain specific definitions of energy. It places what energy does in the Atlas order: energy names availability generated within a condition that can carry work, movement, transformation, maintenance, attention, repair, or continuation. The core read is: Places Energy places generated availability for carrying. Holds Energy is held by Generic, Carrying, Capacity, Pressure, and Flow. Generic names the generative source condition. Carrying names held forward availability being enacted. Capacity names supportable carrying. Pressure names load becoming locally borne through relation. Flow names carrying continuing through a medium. Energy becomes readable where generation makes carrying available as capacity, pressure, flow, work, movement, transformation, maintenance, attention, repair, or continuation. Pairs No universal lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Energy names generated availability for carrying; its local oppositions appear as depletion, dissipation, overload, or incompatible release in particular domains. Traces Generic Carrying Capacity Pressure Flow Nests Energy nests inside carrying as generated availability that can support work, movement, transformation, maintenance, attention, repair, or continuation. It is not the source itself. It is the availability generated from a source or condition and made readable by what it can carry. Reads Energy becomes recognisable where generation produces carrying availability. The structural movement is: Physical energy can be read where generated availability carries work, movement, heat, field relation, or transformation. Living energy can be read where metabolism converts intake, rest, strain, and repair into continued participation. Human energy can be read where received support, relation, nourishment, orientation, rest, or purpose becomes capacity to carry attention, care, work, speech, or action. Energy becomes disorderly where availability continues without trace to what generated it, where it is extracted beyond compatible carrying, or where it is retained, released, or accelerated beyond the carrier''s resolution band. Carries Metabolism Recovery','Energy Energy names generated availability for carrying. This does not replace physical, biological, or domain specific definitions of energy.','working','planted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.generic","second.capacity","second.carrying","second.flow","second.pressure","third.metabolism","third.recovery"]','{"holds":["ground.generic","second.carrying","second.capacity","second.pressure","second.flow"],"traces":["ground.generic","second.carrying","second.capacity","second.pressure","second.flow"],"carries":["third.metabolism","third.recovery"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',304,'sha256:bf86b3b20b37233b65db8597545c0f05b0ffac3b6c43cfd78b343fc84b78e2b9','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.evaluation','Evaluation','evaluation','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Evaluation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/evaluation.html','# Evaluation

Evaluation names a read being assessed within a closure scope. Where readability names the condition that makes reading possible and closure scope names the bounded extent within which a read holds, evaluation names the act of taking a read up into assessment — checking whether it holds, comparing it against other reads, or determining its status within the current scope.

## Places

Evaluation places a read being assessed within a closure scope.

## Holds

Evaluation is held by [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Evaluation is vertical. It names a read being actively assessed within scope, and carries this forward into [[Observation]]. No lateral pair is required — assessment within scope has no structural sibling at this order.

## Traces

- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Decision]]

## Nests

Evaluation nests where a read is actively checked, compared, judged, or assessed within scope.

## Reads

Evaluation becomes recognisable where a read is being actively assessed rather than merely available — where something is being checked, compared, or judged within the current scope.

## Carries

- [[Observation]]
- [[Progress]]','Evaluation Evaluation names a read being assessed within a closure scope. Where readability names the condition that makes reading possible and closure scope names the bounded extent within which a read holds, evaluation names the act of taking a read up into assessment — checking whether it holds, comparing it against other reads, or determining its status within the current scope. Places Evaluation places a read being assessed within a closure scope. Holds Evaluation is held by Closure Scope. Pairs Evaluation is vertical. It names a read being actively assessed within scope, and carries this forward into Observation. No lateral pair is required — assessment within scope has no structural sibling at this order. Traces Closure Scope Decision Nests Evaluation nests where a read is actively checked, compared, judged, or assessed within scope. Reads Evaluation becomes recognisable where a read is being actively assessed rather than merely available — where something is being checked, compared, or judged within the current scope. Carries Observation Progress','Evaluation Evaluation names a read being assessed within a closure scope. Where readability names the condition that makes reading possible and closure scope names the bounded extent within which…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.decision","second.observation","second.progress"]','{"holds":["second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.closure-scope","second.decision"],"carries":["second.observation","second.progress"],"pairs":["second.observation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',164,'sha256:4987f11166a381ede18bf53a42b3f900e430b5960290f3b954b2a2c386c8c6fb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.exist','Exist','exist','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Exist.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/exist.html','# Exist

Exist names presence holding as real enough to be encountered or evaluated. Where real names presence holding as encounterable, exist names that condition sustained: what is real continues to be available for encounter, constraint, or evaluation within the current scope. Proof of existence can test this, but exist names continued real availability.

## Places

Exist places presence holding as real enough to be encountered or evaluated.

## Holds

Exist is held by [[Be]] and [[Real]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Exist is a singular condition — being in the real. The asymmetry is expressed in what exist carries: [[World]].

## Traces

- [[Be]]
- [[Real]]

## Nests

Exist nests where real availability continues as encounterable, constrainable, countable, or evaluable.

## Reads

Exist becomes recognisable where what holds as present can be encountered, constrained, affected, counted, or evaluated — where presence is real enough to participate in the conditions around it.

## Carries

- [[World]]','Exist Exist names presence holding as real enough to be encountered or evaluated. Where real names presence holding as encounterable, exist names that condition sustained: what is real continues to be available for encounter, constraint, or evaluation within the current scope. Proof of existence can test this, but exist names continued real availability. Places Exist places presence holding as real enough to be encountered or evaluated. Holds Exist is held by Be and Real. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Exist is a singular condition — being in the real. The asymmetry is expressed in what exist carries: World. Traces Be Real Nests Exist nests where real availability continues as encounterable, constrainable, countable, or evaluable. Reads Exist becomes recognisable where what holds as present can be encountered, constrained, affected, counted, or evaluated — where presence is real enough to participate in the conditions around it. Carries World','Exist Exist names presence holding as real enough to be encountered or evaluated. Where real names presence holding as encounterable, exist names that condition sustained: what is real continues…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.be","second.real","second.world"]','{"holds":["second.be","second.real"],"traces":["second.be","second.real"],"carries":["second.world"],"pairs":["second.world"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',145,'sha256:c1f487c59d7df76658ababee557bd467e13224eef0cfff4dc885795092d04597','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.extend','Extend','extend','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Extend.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/extend.html','# Extend

Extend names carrying outward beyond a current boundary while remaining answerable to the relation it carries from.

Expansion can increase scope, size, reach, or effect. Extend names the carrying movement by which a condition reaches beyond its current boundary without becoming detached from what bears it.

## Places

Extend places carrying outward beyond a current boundary while remaining answerable to the relation it carries from.

## Holds

Extend is held by [[Carrying]], [[Relation]], [[Boundary]], [[Trace]], and [[Compatibility]]. Carrying must continue beyond a current scope, cross or reach a boundary, remain traceable to the relation it carries from, and stay compatible before extension can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Extend is evaluated by whether outward carrying remains traceable to the relation it carries from.

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Relation]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Extend nests inside carrying where a resolved condition reaches beyond its current scope without losing answerability to what bears it.

## Reads

Extend becomes readable where carrying reaches outward from an existing hold, capacity, read, function, or relation and remains traceable enough to be evaluated.

A tool can extend capacity. Language can extend relation through symbol. A drawing can extend a building before the building exists. A model can extend cognition beyond native resolution. Each remains compatible where the extension stays answerable to the relation, trace, and scope it carries from.

Extension becomes unsafe where outward reach remains effective while trace to the structure that bears it is lost.

## Carries

Extend carries [[Extent]] — the reached range of outward carrying.

- [[Extent]]','Extend Extend names carrying outward beyond a current boundary while remaining answerable to the relation it carries from. Expansion can increase scope, size, reach, or effect. Extend names the carrying movement by which a condition reaches beyond its current boundary without becoming detached from what bears it. Places Extend places carrying outward beyond a current boundary while remaining answerable to the relation it carries from. Holds Extend is held by Carrying, Relation, Boundary, Trace, and Compatibility. Carrying must continue beyond a current scope, cross or reach a boundary, remain traceable to the relation it carries from, and stay compatible before extension can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Extend is evaluated by whether outward carrying remains traceable to the relation it carries from. Traces Carrying Relation Boundary Trace Compatibility Nests Extend nests inside carrying where a resolved condition reaches beyond its current scope without losing answerability to what bears it. Reads Extend becomes readable where carrying reaches outward from an existing hold, capacity, read, function, or relation and remains traceable enough to be evaluated. A tool can extend capacity. Language can extend relation through symbol. A drawing can extend a building before the building exists. A model can extend cognition beyond native resolution. Each remains compatible where the extension stays answerable to the relation, trace, and scope it carries from. Extension becomes unsafe where outward reach remains effective while trace to the structure that bears it is lost. Carries Extend carries Extent — the reached range of outward carrying. Extent','Extend Extend names carrying outward beyond a current boundary while remaining answerable to the relation it carries from. Expansion can increase scope, size, reach, or effect.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.relation","first.trace","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.extent"]','{"holds":["second.carrying","first.relation","first.boundary","first.trace","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.carrying","first.relation","first.boundary","first.trace","second.compatibility"],"carries":["second.extent"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',256,'sha256:58628450f5925f1876621696ffcc915d6f9f8e1c9cf74dbda3bd58f1121e88a0','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.extent','Extent','extent','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Extent.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/extent.html','# Extent

Extent names the reached range of carrying.

Where [[Extend]] names carrying outward beyond a current boundary, Extent names the range that carrying has reached. Extent does not mean universal completion. It asks how far carrying reaches before [[Scope]] bounds that reach for a read, test, or evaluation.

## Places

Extent places the reached range of carrying.

## Holds

Extent is held by [[Extend]], [[Carrying]], [[Boundary]], and [[Trace]]. Carrying must reach outward, the reach must be locatable, and trace must remain available before extent can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Extent is evaluated by whether the reached range remains traceable enough to be read and bounded enough by scope to be evaluated.

## Traces

- [[Extend]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Trace]]

## Nests

Extent nests inside carrying where extension has a reached range that can be located, tested, or answered for.

## Reads

Extent becomes readable where the reach of a condition, read, structure, claim, responsibility, or action can be located as far as it holds.

A claim has an extent. A repair has an extent. A tool has an extent. A structure has an extent. Asking for extent asks how far the carrying reaches without pretending that reach is total.

## Carries

Extent carries [[Scope]] — the boundary condition through which reached range becomes a readable range within which a read can hold.

- [[Scope]]
- [[Closure Scope]]','Extent Extent names the reached range of carrying. Where Extend names carrying outward beyond a current boundary, Extent names the range that carrying has reached. Extent does not mean universal completion. It asks how far carrying reaches before Scope bounds that reach for a read, test, or evaluation. Places Extent places the reached range of carrying. Holds Extent is held by Extend, Carrying, Boundary, and Trace. Carrying must reach outward, the reach must be locatable, and trace must remain available before extent can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Extent is evaluated by whether the reached range remains traceable enough to be read and bounded enough by scope to be evaluated. Traces Extend Carrying Boundary Trace Nests Extent nests inside carrying where extension has a reached range that can be located, tested, or answered for. Reads Extent becomes readable where the reach of a condition, read, structure, claim, responsibility, or action can be located as far as it holds. A claim has an extent. A repair has an extent. A tool has an extent. A structure has an extent. Asking for extent asks how far the carrying reaches without pretending that reach is total. Carries Extent carries Scope — the boundary condition through which reached range becomes a readable range within which a read can hold. Scope Closure Scope','Extent Extent names the reached range of carrying. Where Extend names carrying outward beyond a current boundary, Extent names the range that carrying has reached.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.trace","second.carrying","second.closure-scope","second.extend","second.scope"]','{"holds":["second.extend","second.carrying","first.boundary","first.trace"],"traces":["second.extend","second.carrying","first.boundary","first.trace"],"carries":["second.scope","second.closure-scope"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',225,'sha256:a04bed56297d3a9c68e278f85b9d17f18f5873259e0ad5a318f0c941bace1446','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.face','Face','face','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Face.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/face.html','# Face

Face names the boundary-surface condition through which carrying becomes answerable to read. It is continuity becoming locally answerable.

Face is also where carrying becomes answerable to response. Once carrying has a face, it can be met, trusted, misread, cared for, controlled, harmed, repaired, or recognised at a local boundary.

Face bridges truth and care. Truth requires carried reality to become answerable to read; care requires carried reality to become answerable to response. Face is the local exposure where both become possible.

Surface presents. Face answers. Surface is the presenting side of a condition; face is the return condition through which what is carried can become answerable to a reader.

## Places

Face places the boundary-surface condition through which carrying becomes answerable to read.

## Holds

Face is held by [[Boundary]], [[Surface]], [[Carrying]], [[Return]], and [[Readability]]. Boundary must locate distinction, surface must present, carrying must continue, and carried relation must become readable again before a face can answer back as read.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement. Face names a synthesis condition: carrying, boundary, surface, return, and readability held together as answerable presentation.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]
- [[Surface]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Return]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Face nests where carried trace reaches a boundary-surface through which inside and outside become mutually accountable. It can appear in physical, relational, cognitive, architectural, textual, cinematic, or technological reads.

## Reads

Face becomes readable where carrying can return through a located surface as read, or where non-return becomes readable as still-effective carrying.

A face can be fixed or dynamic. In a fountain, the face of the water is not separate from the flow; it is the local condition where continuous carrying becomes answerable to light, gravity, air, and the reader''s position.

In lithography, cinema, and videotape, the carried trace does not become image merely by existing. It becomes readable when the prepared face, reader, light, head, projection, or translation condition allows carrying to return as presentation.

Care, trust, repair, control, harm, and recognition all become possible where carrying has become locally answerable enough to be met.

In relation, a face is where what is carried can answer back. When carrying continues but cannot answer back through the current read condition, it may remain invisible, shaded, terminal, or hidden depending on the structure of non-return.

## Carries

Face carries no further public branch at this scope.','Face Face names the boundary surface condition through which carrying becomes answerable to read. It is continuity becoming locally answerable. Face is also where carrying becomes answerable to response. Once carrying has a face, it can be met, trusted, misread, cared for, controlled, harmed, repaired, or recognised at a local boundary. Face bridges truth and care. Truth requires carried reality to become answerable to read; care requires carried reality to become answerable to response. Face is the local exposure where both become possible. Surface presents. Face answers. Surface is the presenting side of a condition; face is the return condition through which what is carried can become answerable to a reader. Places Face places the boundary surface condition through which carrying becomes answerable to read. Holds Face is held by Boundary, Surface, Carrying, Return, and Readability. Boundary must locate distinction, surface must present, carrying must continue, and carried relation must become readable again before a face can answer back as read. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement. Face names a synthesis condition: carrying, boundary, surface, return, and readability held together as answerable presentation. Traces Boundary Surface Carrying Return Readability Nests Face nests where carried trace reaches a boundary surface through which inside and outside become mutually accountable. It can appear in physical, relational, cognitive, architectural, textual, cinematic, or technological reads. Reads Face becomes readable where carrying can return through a located surface as read, or where non return becomes readable as still effective carrying. A face can be fixed or dynamic. In a fountain, the face of the water is not separate from the flow; it is the local condition where continuous carrying becomes answerable to light, gravity, air, and the reader''s position. In lithography, cinema, and videotape, the carried trace does not become image merely by existing. It becomes readable when the prepared face, reader, light, head, projection, or translation condition allows carrying to return as presentation. Care, trust, repair, control, harm, and recognition all become possible where carrying has become locally answerable enough to be met. In relation, a face is where what is carried can answer back. When carrying continues but cannot answer back through the current read condition, it may remain invisible, shaded, terminal, or hidden depending on the structure of non return. Carries Face carries no further public branch at this scope.','Face Face names the boundary surface condition through which carrying becomes answerable to read. It is continuity becoming locally answerable.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","second.carrying","second.readability","second.return","second.surface"]','{"holds":["first.boundary","second.surface","second.carrying","second.return","second.readability"],"traces":["first.boundary","second.surface","second.carrying","second.return","second.readability"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',390,'sha256:c132c876077b8085e8ae3b364ec66f54a1785fb3c0da3fbdb0f8c41df1293186','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.flow','Flow','flow','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Flow.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/flow.html','# Flow

Flow names carrying continuing through a medium. Movement can show flow, but flow first names carrying that remains readable as passing through a through-condition without losing continuity.

## Places

Flow places carrying continuing through a medium.

## Holds

Flow is held by [[Carrying]], [[Medium]], and [[Process]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — into [[Throughput]], [[Current]], and [[Resistance]]

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Medium]]
- [[Process]]
- [[Change]]

## Nests

Flow nests inside carrying through a medium. It can open current, throughput, resistance, friction, drag, and heat.

## Reads

Flow becomes recognisable where a carried condition continues through a medium as an available process.

Where generated availability carries through a medium as work, movement, transformation, maintenance, or continuation, flow can make [[Energy]] readable.

## Carries

- [[Throughput]]
- [[Current]]
- [[Energy]]
- [[Resistance]]
- [[Friction]]
- [[Drag]]
- [[Heat]]','Flow Flow names carrying continuing through a medium. Movement can show flow, but flow first names carrying that remains readable as passing through a through condition without losing continuity. Places Flow places carrying continuing through a medium. Holds Flow is held by Carrying, Medium, and Process. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward — into Throughput, Current, and Resistance Traces Carrying Medium Process Change Nests Flow nests inside carrying through a medium. It can open current, throughput, resistance, friction, drag, and heat. Reads Flow becomes recognisable where a carried condition continues through a medium as an available process. Where generated availability carries through a medium as work, movement, transformation, maintenance, or continuation, flow can make Energy readable. Carries Throughput Current Energy Resistance Friction Drag Heat','Flow Flow names carrying continuing through a medium. Movement can show flow, but flow first names carrying that remains readable as passing through a through condition without losing continuity.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.change","second.current","second.drag","second.energy","second.friction","second.heat","second.medium","second.process","second.resistance","second.throughput"]','{"holds":["second.carrying","second.medium","second.process"],"traces":["second.carrying","second.medium","second.process","second.change"],"carries":["second.throughput","second.current","second.energy","second.resistance","second.friction","second.drag","second.heat"],"pairs":["second.throughput","second.current","second.resistance"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',122,'sha256:572aa22f407735b313c116190c99820d6e1755c3a1f9ab210b8868d0c136a227','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.form','Form','form','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Form.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/form.html','# Form

Form names readable arrangement. Where difference names distinguishable non-sameness, form names difference held as an arrangement — multiple distinctions readable together as one organised condition. Physical shape can be a form, but form is not limited to shape; it names any arrangement of differences that can be read as one thing.

## Places

Form places readable arrangement.

## Holds

Form is held by [[Difference]] and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Form pairs with [[Information]]: form names the shape of difference at a closure scope — how the difference is configured, what contour it takes; information names the content of that same difference — what that configuration carries and makes readable. Both hold [[Difference]] and [[Closure Scope]] and neither grounds the other. Each requires the other to be locatable: form without information is empty structure; information without form is unplaceable content.

## Traces

- [[Difference]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Form nests where differences are held as one readable arrangement rather than isolated non-sameness.

## Reads

Form becomes recognisable where difference is held as arrangement — where multiple distinctions can be read together rather than as isolated non-sameness.

## Carries

- [[Identity]]
- [[Pattern]]
- [[Kind]]
- [[Spell]]
- [[Glamour]]
- [[Surface]]
- [[Structural Gathering]]
- [[Structure]]
- [[Expressing]]
- [[Transforming]]','Form Form names readable arrangement. Where difference names distinguishable non sameness, form names difference held as an arrangement — multiple distinctions readable together as one organised condition. Physical shape can be a form, but form is not limited to shape; it names any arrangement of differences that can be read as one thing. Places Form places readable arrangement. Holds Form is held by Difference and Closure Scope. Pairs Form pairs with Information: form names the shape of difference at a closure scope — how the difference is configured, what contour it takes; information names the content of that same difference — what that configuration carries and makes readable. Both hold Difference and Closure Scope and neither grounds the other. Each requires the other to be locatable: form without information is empty structure; information without form is unplaceable content. Traces Difference Closure Scope Nests Form nests where differences are held as one readable arrangement rather than isolated non sameness. Reads Form becomes recognisable where difference is held as arrangement — where multiple distinctions can be read together rather than as isolated non sameness. Carries Identity Pattern Kind Spell Glamour Surface Structural Gathering Structure Expressing Transforming','Form Form names readable arrangement. Where difference names distinguishable non sameness, form names difference held as an arrangement — multiple distinctions readable together as one organised…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.difference","second.identity","second.information","second.kind","second.pattern","second.structural-gathering","second.structure","second.surface","third.expressing","third.glamour","third.spell","third.transforming"]','{"holds":["second.difference","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.difference","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["second.identity","second.pattern","second.kind","third.spell","third.glamour","second.surface","second.structural-gathering","second.structure","third.expressing","third.transforming"],"pairs":["second.information"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',194,'sha256:df57c0076fc8c665b7157cbd94ba8ea7de1ed40825b8b29494cc97741d7757ba','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.frequency','Frequency','frequency','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Frequency.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/frequency.html','# Frequency

Frequency names countable return as rate. Where recurrence names participation occurring again and Return names carried relation becoming readable again, frequency counts those readable returns within a measured interval.

## Places

Frequency places countable return as rate.

## Holds

Frequency is held by [[Recurrence]], [[Return]], and [[Rate]]. Recurrence must provide another occurrence, Return must make a carried condition readable enough to distinguish, and Rate must relate the count to an interval.

## Pairs

No universal lateral pair is required. [[Period]] is the reciprocal measure of Frequency where returns form a stable cycle. Irregular recurrence can still have a measured or averaged frequency without one fixed period.

## Traces

- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Return]]
- [[Rate]]

## Nests

Frequency nests inside recurrence and rate as counted returns within an interval.

## Reads

Frequency becomes recognisable where recurring participation has a return condition distinct enough to count per interval.

## Carries

- [[Hertz]]
- [[Resonance]]','Frequency Frequency names countable return as rate. Where recurrence names participation occurring again and Return names carried relation becoming readable again, frequency counts those readable returns within a measured interval. Places Frequency places countable return as rate. Holds Frequency is held by Recurrence, Return, and Rate. Recurrence must provide another occurrence, Return must make a carried condition readable enough to distinguish, and Rate must relate the count to an interval. Pairs No universal lateral pair is required. Period is the reciprocal measure of Frequency where returns form a stable cycle. Irregular recurrence can still have a measured or averaged frequency without one fixed period. Traces Recurrence Return Rate Nests Frequency nests inside recurrence and rate as counted returns within an interval. Reads Frequency becomes recognisable where recurring participation has a return condition distinct enough to count per interval. Carries Hertz Resonance','Frequency Frequency names countable return as rate. Where recurrence names participation occurring again and Return names carried relation becoming readable again, frequency counts those readable…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.hertz","second.period","second.rate","second.recurrence","second.resonance","second.return"]','{"holds":["second.recurrence","second.return","second.rate"],"traces":["second.recurrence","second.return","second.rate"],"carries":["second.hertz","second.resonance"],"pairs":["second.period"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',141,'sha256:0dd79c1e51642d157a7f31c3f8a16654e9b1ff9b57db05c159a12dfa8670604f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.friction','Friction','friction','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Friction.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/friction.html','# Friction

Friction names resistance at coupled contact during flow. Resistance becomes friction where contact is coupled enough to bear against carrying as it continues.

## Places

Friction places resistance at coupled contact during flow.

## Holds

Friction is held by [[Coupled Contact]], [[Resistance]], and [[Flow]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Friction is a singular condition — resistance generated through coupled contact and flow. The asymmetry is expressed in what friction carries: [[Grip]], [[Traction]], and [[Drag]].

## Traces

- [[Coupled Contact]]
- [[Contact]]
- [[Resistance]]
- [[Flow]]

## Nests

Friction nests at coupled contact during flow. It can slow, grip, wear, heat, or support carrying.

## Reads

Friction becomes recognisable where flow meets coupled contact and that contact resists, slows, grips, wears, or heats what is carried.

## Carries

- [[Grip]]
- [[Traction]]
- [[Drag]]
- [[Wear]]
- [[Heat]]','Friction Friction names resistance at coupled contact during flow. Resistance becomes friction where contact is coupled enough to bear against carrying as it continues. Places Friction places resistance at coupled contact during flow. Holds Friction is held by Coupled Contact, Resistance, and Flow. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Friction is a singular condition — resistance generated through coupled contact and flow. The asymmetry is expressed in what friction carries: Grip, Traction, and Drag. Traces Coupled Contact Contact Resistance Flow Nests Friction nests at coupled contact during flow. It can slow, grip, wear, heat, or support carrying. Reads Friction becomes recognisable where flow meets coupled contact and that contact resists, slows, grips, wears, or heats what is carried. Carries Grip Traction Drag Wear Heat','Friction Friction names resistance at coupled contact during flow. Resistance becomes friction where contact is coupled enough to bear against carrying as it continues.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.contact","second.coupled-contact","second.drag","second.flow","second.grip","second.heat","second.resistance","second.traction","second.wear"]','{"holds":["second.coupled-contact","second.resistance","second.flow"],"traces":["second.coupled-contact","first.contact","second.resistance","second.flow"],"carries":["second.grip","second.traction","second.drag","second.wear","second.heat"],"pairs":["second.grip","second.traction","second.drag"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',122,'sha256:60f6dcf78977972afb9b18a6cbf0a7ed1f283bd0e9349a1fc52c8bdf22e8c03d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.function','Function','function','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Function.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/function.html','# Function

Function names what a form makes available through compatible carrying. Where structure names form held as a carrying arrangement, function names the specific availability that arrangement produces: what can occur, be used, or participate through the structural arrangement. Purpose or intention can guide function, but function names the available participation a form makes possible through compatible carrying.

## Places

Function places what a form makes available through compatible carrying.

## Holds

Function is held by [[Structure]] and [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Function is vertical. It names what a form makes available through compatible carrying, and carries this forward into [[Strategy]]. Function holds [[Structure]] — it is downstream of structure, not co-present with it as a lateral pair.

## Traces

- [[Structure]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Function nests inside structure and compatibility as available participation made possible by form.

## Reads

Function becomes recognisable where a structural arrangement can be read as making something available — where what a form carries can be taken up and used within the current scope.

## Carries

- [[Strategy]]
- [[Transforming]]','Function Function names what a form makes available through compatible carrying. Where structure names form held as a carrying arrangement, function names the specific availability that arrangement produces: what can occur, be used, or participate through the structural arrangement. Purpose or intention can guide function, but function names the available participation a form makes possible through compatible carrying. Places Function places what a form makes available through compatible carrying. Holds Function is held by Structure and Compatibility. Pairs Function is vertical. It names what a form makes available through compatible carrying, and carries this forward into Strategy. Function holds Structure — it is downstream of structure, not co present with it as a lateral pair. Traces Structure Compatibility Nests Function nests inside structure and compatibility as available participation made possible by form. Reads Function becomes recognisable where a structural arrangement can be read as making something available — where what a form carries can be taken up and used within the current scope. Carries Strategy Transforming','Function Function names what a form makes available through compatible carrying. Where structure names form held as a carrying arrangement, function names the specific availability that…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.compatibility","second.strategy","second.structure","third.transforming"]','{"holds":["second.structure","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.structure","second.compatibility"],"carries":["second.strategy","third.transforming"],"pairs":["second.strategy"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',166,'sha256:ce0e546d17f14990404f30472e97ed82106cc052ee1e8ce87f2fb40c63d1b517','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.grip','Grip','grip','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Grip.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/grip.html','# Grip

Grip names useful friction at coupled contact. Where friction can slow or oppose movement, grip names the coupled contact condition through which resistance becomes support for carrying.

## Places

Grip places useful friction at coupled contact.

## Holds

Grip is held by [[Coupled Contact]], [[Friction]], and [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Grip is a singular condition — compatible coupled contact through friction. The asymmetry is expressed in what grip carries: [[Traction]].

## Traces

- [[Coupled Contact]]
- [[Contact]]
- [[Friction]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Resistance]]

## Nests

Grip nests inside friction as useful coupled contact resistance that supports carrying.

## Reads

Grip becomes recognisable where coupled contact resists enough to hold carrying without simply blocking it.

## Carries

- [[Traction]]','Grip Grip names useful friction at coupled contact. Where friction can slow or oppose movement, grip names the coupled contact condition through which resistance becomes support for carrying. Places Grip places useful friction at coupled contact. Holds Grip is held by Coupled Contact, Friction, and Compatibility. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Grip is a singular condition — compatible coupled contact through friction. The asymmetry is expressed in what grip carries: Traction. Traces Coupled Contact Contact Friction Compatibility Resistance Nests Grip nests inside friction as useful coupled contact resistance that supports carrying. Reads Grip becomes recognisable where coupled contact resists enough to hold carrying without simply blocking it. Carries Traction','Grip Grip names useful friction at coupled contact. Where friction can slow or oppose movement, grip names the coupled contact condition through which resistance becomes support for carrying.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.contact","second.compatibility","second.coupled-contact","second.friction","second.resistance","second.traction"]','{"holds":["second.coupled-contact","second.friction","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.coupled-contact","first.contact","second.friction","second.compatibility","second.resistance"],"carries":["second.traction"],"pairs":["second.traction"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',108,'sha256:5f8ffd7c45473f492431423edfae407bc5d969d09322f2beeec5f8a086432312','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.growth','Growth','growth','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Growth.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/growth.html','# Growth

Growth names increase in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Improvement can be one read of growth, but growth first names change read as increase within a closure scope.

Growth is not only faster output. Increase that depends on drawing down a hidden carrier may be read locally as growth while becoming extraction at a wider scope. Growth must remain answerable to what carries the increase.

## Places

Growth places increase in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal.

## Holds

Growth is held by [[Change]], [[Scale]], and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Growth pairs with [[Decay]]. Growth reads increase across traversal; Decay reads decrease across traversal.

## Traces

- [[Change]]
- [[Scale]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Growth nests inside change and scale reads as increase across traversal.

## Reads

Growth becomes recognisable where a condition can be followed as increasing in extent, carrying, or available participation.

## Carries

- [[Decay]]','Growth Growth names increase in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Improvement can be one read of growth, but growth first names change read as increase within a closure scope. Growth is not only faster output. Increase that depends on drawing down a hidden carrier may be read locally as growth while becoming extraction at a wider scope. Growth must remain answerable to what carries the increase. Places Growth places increase in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Holds Growth is held by Change, Scale, and Carrying. Pairs Growth pairs with Decay. Growth reads increase across traversal; Decay reads decrease across traversal. Traces Change Scale Carrying Nests Growth nests inside change and scale reads as increase across traversal. Reads Growth becomes recognisable where a condition can be followed as increasing in extent, carrying, or available participation. Carries Decay','Growth Growth names increase in carrying, scale, or available participation across traversal. Improvement can be one read of growth, but growth first names change read as increase within a closure…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.change","second.decay","second.scale"]','{"holds":["second.change","second.scale","second.carrying"],"traces":["second.change","second.scale","second.carrying"],"carries":["second.decay"],"pairs":["second.decay"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',140,'sha256:3057cf39bc98b2e000ced7f595a13756e03d655372ac43975f1dd6d3e197ebdc','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.guard','Guard','guard','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Guard.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/guard.html','# Guard

Guard names carrying organised around a boundary to preserve availability by regulating passage.

Guard is not inherently caring or controlling. It names the maintained boundary condition first. Later reads show what the guarding serves and what effects it produces.

## Places

Guard places carrying organised around a boundary to preserve availability by regulating passage.

## Holds

Guard is held by [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], [[Carrying]], [[Constraint]], and [[Compatibility]]. A boundary must locate what is at stake, carrying must maintain it, constraint must regulate passage, and the guarded availability must remain supportable before guard can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Guard names boundary-maintaining carrying. Whether that guarding later reads as care, control, safety, restriction, or harm depends on the relation and effects that follow.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Constraint]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Guard nests within carrying at a boundary, where passage is selectively constrained so that available bearing can remain.

## Reads

Guard becomes readable where a maintained boundary regulates what may enter, leave, or bear upon an available condition.

The threshold between compatible and incompatible guarding cannot be fixed by the word alone. It is read from effects: whether availability remains, whether participation can still affect the boundary, whether changed conditions can alter what is permitted, and whether protection preserves bearing or only confinement.

"Guard your heart" names this structure directly: maintain the boundary around what remains available to relation. A guard can preserve that availability, or make the boundary so complete that the guarded condition can no longer participate.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Guard Guard names carrying organised around a boundary to preserve availability by regulating passage. Guard is not inherently caring or controlling. It names the maintained boundary condition first. Later reads show what the guarding serves and what effects it produces. Places Guard places carrying organised around a boundary to preserve availability by regulating passage. Holds Guard is held by Boundary, Availability, Carrying, Constraint, and Compatibility. A boundary must locate what is at stake, carrying must maintain it, constraint must regulate passage, and the guarded availability must remain supportable before guard can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Guard names boundary maintaining carrying. Whether that guarding later reads as care, control, safety, restriction, or harm depends on the relation and effects that follow. Traces Boundary Availability Carrying Constraint Compatibility Nests Guard nests within carrying at a boundary, where passage is selectively constrained so that available bearing can remain. Reads Guard becomes readable where a maintained boundary regulates what may enter, leave, or bear upon an available condition. The threshold between compatible and incompatible guarding cannot be fixed by the word alone. It is read from effects: whether availability remains, whether participation can still affect the boundary, whether changed conditions can alter what is permitted, and whether protection preserves bearing or only confinement. "Guard your heart" names this structure directly: maintain the boundary around what remains available to relation. A guard can preserve that availability, or make the boundary so complete that the guarded condition can no longer participate. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Guard Guard names carrying organised around a boundary to preserve availability by regulating passage. Guard is not inherently caring or controlling.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.availability","first.boundary","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.constraint"]','{"holds":["first.boundary","first.availability","second.carrying","second.constraint","second.compatibility"],"traces":["first.boundary","first.availability","second.carrying","second.constraint","second.compatibility"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',264,'sha256:a1f101454d4cc1966021ee6e2db2b4a7644db38497424c6b3004bb81743dff0e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.heat','Heat','heat','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Heat.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/heat.html','# Heat

Heat names energetic consequence made readable through friction. In this atlas position, heat is not a full account of thermodynamics; it is the readable availability that appears where resistance in carrying becomes energetic change.

## Places

Heat places energetic consequence made readable through friction.

## Holds

Heat is held by [[Friction]], [[Change]], and [[Flow]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Heat is a singular condition — friction expressed through [[Change]] and [[Flow]]. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Friction]]
- [[Change]]
- [[Flow]]

## Nests

Heat nests inside frictional carrying as energetic consequence, not as a full account of thermodynamics.

## Reads

Heat becomes recognisable where friction changes carrying into energetic availability that can be felt, measured, or further carried.

