INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.identity','Identity','identity','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Identity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/identity.html','# Identity

Identity names sustained distinguishability. Where form names readable arrangement and recognition names a read becoming identifiable as this again, identity names the condition through which a formed distinction remains recognisable as itself across encounters — readable as the same condition held. Identity does not name essence or permanence; it names what holds as distinguishable across instances.

## Places

Identity places sustained distinguishability.

## Holds

Identity is held by [[Form]] and [[Recognition Read|Recognition]].

## Pairs

Identity is vertical. It names sustained distinguishability, and carries this forward into [[Stability]] and [[Self]]. Identity holds [[Form]] and [[Recognition Read]] — it is downstream in the dependency chain, not a lateral co-present condition alongside Difference or Form.

## Traces

- [[Form]]
- [[Recognition Read|Recognition]]
- [[Coupling]]
- [[Indivisible Bearing]]
- [[Kind]]

## Nests

Identity nests where form remains recognisable as itself across encounters without requiring essence or permanence.

## Reads

Identity becomes recognisable where a formed distinction can be read as this across encounters — where what holds as arranged continues to be identifiable as the same condition rather than a new one.

## Carries

- [[Stability]]
- [[Self]]','Identity Identity names sustained distinguishability. Where form names readable arrangement and recognition names a read becoming identifiable as this again, identity names the condition through which a formed distinction remains recognisable as itself across encounters — readable as the same condition held. Identity does not name essence or permanence; it names what holds as distinguishable across instances. Places Identity places sustained distinguishability. Holds Identity is held by Form and Recognition Read. Pairs Identity is vertical. It names sustained distinguishability, and carries this forward into Stability and Self. Identity holds Form and Recognition Read — it is downstream in the dependency chain, not a lateral co present condition alongside Difference or Form. Traces Form Recognition Read Coupling Indivisible Bearing Kind Nests Identity nests where form remains recognisable as itself across encounters without requiring essence or permanence. Reads Identity becomes recognisable where a formed distinction can be read as this across encounters — where what holds as arranged continues to be identifiable as the same condition rather than a new one. Carries Stability Self','Identity Identity names sustained distinguishability. Where form names readable arrangement and recognition names a read becoming identifiable as this again, identity names the condition through…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.coupling","second.form","second.indivisible-bearing","second.kind","second.recognition-read","second.stability","third.self"]','{"holds":["second.form","second.recognition-read"],"traces":["second.form","second.recognition-read","second.coupling","second.indivisible-bearing","second.kind"],"carries":["second.stability","third.self"],"pairs":["second.stability","third.self"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',172,'sha256:81242cc45cc9672aeb2aae8c4fbc506396a78d859d017d76c23f30431978bd9e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.incoherence','Incoherence','incoherence','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Incoherence.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/incoherence.html','# Incoherence

Incoherence names compatible pattern holding no longer remaining readable. Where coherence names multiple patterns holding together without losing their individual readability, incoherence names the condition where those patterns no longer hold together compatibly within the current scope. Incoherence is not chaos or contradiction in general; it names the loss of readable compatibility between patterns that were expected to carry together.

## Places

Incoherence places compatible pattern holding no longer remaining readable.

## Holds

Incoherence is held by [[Coherence]], [[Overload]], and [[Disorder]].

## Pairs

Incoherence pairs with [[Coherence]]. Coherence names compatible patterns holding together; Incoherence names loss of readable compatibility.

## Traces

- [[Coherence]]
- [[Overload]]
- [[Disorder]]

## Nests

Incoherence nests where patterns expected to carry together no longer remain compatibly readable.

## Reads

Incoherence becomes recognisable where multiple patterns can no longer be read as compatibly held together — where their carrying produces conflict, turbulence, shutdown, fragmentation, or disorder within the current scope.

## Carries

- [[Second-Order Disorder Effects]]','Incoherence Incoherence names compatible pattern holding no longer remaining readable. Where coherence names multiple patterns holding together without losing their individual readability, incoherence names the condition where those patterns no longer hold together compatibly within the current scope. Incoherence is not chaos or contradiction in general; it names the loss of readable compatibility between patterns that were expected to carry together. Places Incoherence places compatible pattern holding no longer remaining readable. Holds Incoherence is held by Coherence, Overload, and Disorder. Pairs Incoherence pairs with Coherence. Coherence names compatible patterns holding together; Incoherence names loss of readable compatibility. Traces Coherence Overload Disorder Nests Incoherence nests where patterns expected to carry together no longer remain compatibly readable. Reads Incoherence becomes recognisable where multiple patterns can no longer be read as compatibly held together — where their carrying produces conflict, turbulence, shutdown, fragmentation, or disorder within the current scope. Carries Second Order Disorder Effects','Incoherence Incoherence names compatible pattern holding no longer remaining readable. Where coherence names multiple patterns holding together without losing their individual readability,…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.coherence","second.disorder","second.overload","second.second-order-disorder-effects"]','{"holds":["second.coherence","second.overload","second.disorder"],"traces":["second.coherence","second.overload","second.disorder"],"carries":["second.second-order-disorder-effects"],"pairs":["second.coherence"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',151,'sha256:284b6c6c54d03c7cb74519f30c65eb322ba054e48eedc74d9bb5b161ba554131','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.indivisible-bearing','Indivisible Bearing','indivisible-bearing','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Indivisible Bearing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/indivisible-bearing.html','# Indivisible Bearing

Indivisible bearing names bearing that cannot be separated without changing the carrying condition. Where divisible bearing names holding across divisions, indivisible bearing names holding that must remain whole to continue carrying — the carrying condition changes if the bearing is divided.

## Places

Indivisible Bearing places bearing that cannot be separated without changing the carrying condition.

## Holds

Indivisible Bearing is held by [[Bearing]] and [[Indivisible]].

## Pairs

Indivisible Bearing pairs with [[Divisible Bearing]]. Indivisible Bearing must remain whole to carry; Divisible Bearing carries across distinguishable divisions.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Indivisible]]

## Nests

Indivisible Bearing nests where carrying must be read whole to remain the same carrying condition.

## Reads

Indivisible bearing becomes recognisable where carrying can only be read as whole — where separating the bearing condition would change what is being carried.

## Carries

- [[Identity]]','Indivisible Bearing Indivisible bearing names bearing that cannot be separated without changing the carrying condition. Where divisible bearing names holding across divisions, indivisible bearing names holding that must remain whole to continue carrying — the carrying condition changes if the bearing is divided. Places Indivisible Bearing places bearing that cannot be separated without changing the carrying condition. Holds Indivisible Bearing is held by Bearing and Indivisible. Pairs Indivisible Bearing pairs with Divisible Bearing. Indivisible Bearing must remain whole to carry; Divisible Bearing carries across distinguishable divisions. Traces Bearing Indivisible Nests Indivisible Bearing nests where carrying must be read whole to remain the same carrying condition. Reads Indivisible bearing becomes recognisable where carrying can only be read as whole — where separating the bearing condition would change what is being carried. Carries Identity','Indivisible Bearing Indivisible bearing names bearing that cannot be separated without changing the carrying condition. Where divisible bearing names holding across divisions, indivisible bearing…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.indivisible","second.divisible-bearing","second.identity"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","first.indivisible"],"traces":["first.bearing","first.indivisible"],"carries":["second.identity"],"pairs":["second.divisible-bearing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',132,'sha256:adce1f650fe6e4f131a8112ca16dd9975f14e228f2b8f5dd413fc2bce3c582be','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.influence','Influence','influence','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Participation Conditions/Influence.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/influence.html','# Influence

Influence names one participating condition altering how another condition is read, carried, or made available. Where [[Effect]] names change carried through coupling, Influence names that effect entering participation strongly enough to alter another condition''s readability or continuation. Influence is not control by itself.

## Places

Influence places one participating condition altering how another condition is read, carried, or made available.

## Holds

Influence is held by [[Participation]], [[Effect]], and [[Readability]].

## Pairs

Influence is vertical. It names one participating condition altering how another is read, carried, or made available, and carries this forward into [[Enchantment]], [[Binding]], and [[Wonder]]. Influence holds [[Participation]], [[Effect]], and [[Readability]] — there is no lateral co-present condition that Influence requires and that requires Influence in return at this order.

## Traces

- [[Participation]]
- [[Effect]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Influence nests where one participation changes the readability or continuation of another condition without becoming control by itself.

## Reads

Influence becomes recognisable where participation changes how another condition can be read, carried, constrained, opened, or continued.

## Carries

- [[Enchantment]]
- [[Binding]]
- [[Wonder]]','Influence Influence names one participating condition altering how another condition is read, carried, or made available. Where Effect names change carried through coupling, Influence names that effect entering participation strongly enough to alter another condition''s readability or continuation. Influence is not control by itself. Places Influence places one participating condition altering how another condition is read, carried, or made available. Holds Influence is held by Participation, Effect, and Readability. Pairs Influence is vertical. It names one participating condition altering how another is read, carried, or made available, and carries this forward into Enchantment, Binding, and Wonder. Influence holds Participation, Effect, and Readability — there is no lateral co present condition that Influence requires and that requires Influence in return at this order. Traces Participation Effect Readability Nests Influence nests where one participation changes the readability or continuation of another condition without becoming control by itself. Reads Influence becomes recognisable where participation changes how another condition can be read, carried, constrained, opened, or continued. Carries Enchantment Binding Wonder','Influence Influence names one participating condition altering how another condition is read, carried, or made available. Where Effect names change carried through coupling, Influence names that…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.effect","second.participation","second.readability","third.binding","third.enchantment","third.wonder"]','{"holds":["second.participation","second.effect","second.readability"],"traces":["second.participation","second.effect","second.readability"],"carries":["third.enchantment","third.binding","third.wonder"],"pairs":["third.enchantment","third.binding","third.wonder"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',167,'sha256:bae2ad8c4cabf710e28e2fc27406869eb5053c8e29e389f7949b6664b913a17f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.information','Information','information','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Information.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/information.html','# Information

Information names difference that makes a read available. Where difference names distinguishable non-sameness, information names the specific difference that changes what can be read — the difference that matters at the current scope. Data, content, or quantity can carry information, but information is the produced read through which a distinction becomes available to alter evaluation.

## Places

Information places difference that makes a read available.

## Holds

Information is held by [[Difference]] and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Information pairs with [[Form]]: information names the content of difference at a closure scope — what the difference carries and makes readable; form names the shape of that same difference — how it is configured and what contour it takes. Both hold [[Difference]] and [[Closure Scope]] and neither grounds the other. Each requires the other to be locatable: information without form is unplaceable; form without information is empty structure.

## Traces

- [[Difference]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Scale]]

## Nests

Information nests where difference changes what becomes available to evaluation.

## Reads

Information becomes recognisable where a difference can be read as changing what is available to evaluation — where not-same produces a readable alteration rather than mere distinction.

## Carries

- [[Know]]','Information Information names difference that makes a read available. Where difference names distinguishable non sameness, information names the specific difference that changes what can be read — the difference that matters at the current scope. Data, content, or quantity can carry information, but information is the produced read through which a distinction becomes available to alter evaluation. Places Information places difference that makes a read available. Holds Information is held by Difference and Closure Scope. Pairs Information pairs with Form: information names the content of difference at a closure scope — what the difference carries and makes readable; form names the shape of that same difference — how it is configured and what contour it takes. Both hold Difference and Closure Scope and neither grounds the other. Each requires the other to be locatable: information without form is unplaceable; form without information is empty structure. Traces Difference Closure Scope Scale Nests Information nests where difference changes what becomes available to evaluation. Reads Information becomes recognisable where a difference can be read as changing what is available to evaluation — where not same produces a readable alteration rather than mere distinction. Carries Know','Information Information names difference that makes a read available. Where difference names distinguishable non sameness, information names the specific difference that changes what can be read —…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.difference","second.form","second.know","second.scale"]','{"holds":["second.difference","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.difference","second.closure-scope","second.scale"],"carries":["second.know"],"pairs":["second.form"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',192,'sha256:bf2987e1b9f64cef5df63dc1669ec31723c661334e082f1b7f8e54088c56ebe0','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.intake','Intake','intake','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Intake.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/intake.html','# Intake

Intake names availability crossing inward through a boundary into carrying. Where in carries inward placement and carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, intake names the condition through which what was outside becomes available within a body, system, or scope. Intake does not determine whether what enters supports, disrupts, alters, or overloads carrying; it names the inward crossing that makes those later reads possible.

## Places

Intake places availability crossing inward through a boundary into carrying.

## Holds

Intake is held by [[In]], [[Availability]], and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Intake is vertical. It names inward crossing into carrying and carries this forward into [[Integration]] and [[Splinter]]. Integration names what becomes carried by the receiving order; Splinter names what remains unresolved within it.

## Traces

- [[In]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Intake nests at the boundary where outside availability crosses inward into carrying.

## Reads

Intake becomes recognisable where availability crosses inward through a boundary and enters carrying — where what was outside is no longer merely present at the boundary but has become available within the carrying condition.

## Carries

- [[Integration]]
- [[Splinter]]
- [[Space-Based Solar Power]]','Intake Intake names availability crossing inward through a boundary into carrying. Where in carries inward placement and carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, intake names the condition through which what was outside becomes available within a body, system, or scope. Intake does not determine whether what enters supports, disrupts, alters, or overloads carrying; it names the inward crossing that makes those later reads possible. Places Intake places availability crossing inward through a boundary into carrying. Holds Intake is held by In, Availability, and Carrying. Pairs Intake is vertical. It names inward crossing into carrying and carries this forward into Integration and Splinter. Integration names what becomes carried by the receiving order; Splinter names what remains unresolved within it. Traces In Availability Carrying Nests Intake nests at the boundary where outside availability crosses inward into carrying. Reads Intake becomes recognisable where availability crosses inward through a boundary and enters carrying — where what was outside is no longer merely present at the boundary but has become available within the carrying condition. Carries Integration Splinter Space Based Solar Power','Intake Intake names availability crossing inward through a boundary into carrying. Where in carries inward placement and carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted,…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.availability","first.in","second.carrying","second.integration","second.splinter","third.space-based-solar-power"]','{"holds":["first.in","first.availability","second.carrying"],"traces":["first.in","first.availability","second.carrying"],"carries":["second.integration","second.splinter","third.space-based-solar-power"],"pairs":["second.integration","second.splinter"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',180,'sha256:092d8f1905fec3f61a158f626810b3719d80b257153875247c9d97c1afed752d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.integration','Integration','integration','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Integration.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/integration.html','# Integration

Integration names intake resolved into compatible carrying without erasing the distinction of what entered.

[[Intake]] names availability crossing inward through a boundary. Integration names what happens where that intake becomes carried by the receiving order: it can participate in the condition, affect it, and be affected by it without remaining unresolved foreignness or being erased into sameness.

## Places

Integration places intake resolved into compatible carrying without erasing the distinction of what entered.

## Holds

Integration is held by [[Intake]], [[Resolution]], [[Regulation]], and [[Compatibility]]. What enters must be available within carrying, resolved enough to participate, maintainable within the receiving condition, and compatible with what carries it before integration can be named.

## Pairs

Integration pairs with [[Splinter]]. Integration names what has crossed inward and becomes carried by the receiving order; Splinter names what has crossed inward but remains unresolved within it. Each requires the other to be locatable: integration is readable against the possibility that intake remains foreign to the carrying order, while splinter is readable against the possibility that what entered could become compatibly carried.

## Traces

- [[Intake]]
- [[Resolution]]
- [[Regulation]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Integration nests inside carrying where what has entered becomes held by the receiving order without being erased or remaining unresolved foreignness.

## Reads

Integration becomes recognisable where what has entered can participate in the carrying condition, affect it, and be affected by it while remaining compatible with the order that now carries it.

Integration is not absorption into sameness. The entering distinction remains traceable even as it becomes part of wider carrying.

## Carries

- [[Nourishment]]','Integration Integration names intake resolved into compatible carrying without erasing the distinction of what entered. Intake names availability crossing inward through a boundary. Integration names what happens where that intake becomes carried by the receiving order: it can participate in the condition, affect it, and be affected by it without remaining unresolved foreignness or being erased into sameness. Places Integration places intake resolved into compatible carrying without erasing the distinction of what entered. Holds Integration is held by Intake, Resolution, Regulation, and Compatibility. What enters must be available within carrying, resolved enough to participate, maintainable within the receiving condition, and compatible with what carries it before integration can be named. Pairs Integration pairs with Splinter. Integration names what has crossed inward and becomes carried by the receiving order; Splinter names what has crossed inward but remains unresolved within it. Each requires the other to be locatable: integration is readable against the possibility that intake remains foreign to the carrying order, while splinter is readable against the possibility that what entered could become compatibly carried. Traces Intake Resolution Regulation Compatibility Nests Integration nests inside carrying where what has entered becomes held by the receiving order without being erased or remaining unresolved foreignness. Reads Integration becomes recognisable where what has entered can participate in the carrying condition, affect it, and be affected by it while remaining compatible with the order that now carries it. Integration is not absorption into sameness. The entering distinction remains traceable even as it becomes part of wider carrying. Carries Nourishment','Integration Integration names intake resolved into compatible carrying without erasing the distinction of what entered. Intake names availability crossing inward through a boundary.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.resolution","second.compatibility","second.intake","second.regulation","second.splinter","third.nourishment"]','{"holds":["second.intake","first.resolution","second.regulation","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.intake","first.resolution","second.regulation","second.compatibility"],"carries":["third.nourishment"],"pairs":["second.splinter"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',253,'sha256:381e200ce97469adb050325154d17c7f0c61809c44f908f0346b35e25f3fe1f5','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.interposed_carrier','Interposed Carrier','interposed-carrier','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Interposed Carrier.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/interposed-carrier.html','# Interposed Carrier

Interposed Carrier names the carrying medium that stands between two parties in contact, holding its own carrying condition between them. It does not merely block; it carries. It holds its own pressure or dynamic carrying between the parties, transforming what contact makes available.

[[Clearance]] names held separation before contact. Interposed Carrier names what holds between during contact: the medium that maintains dynamic separation within what appears as meeting.

The interposed carrier can prevent direct coupling: where a fluid layer interposes at full pressure, contact cannot become coupled contact — the medium carries before grip can form. It can also modify coupling: where a medium interposes within coupling, it changes how pressure, resistance, or traction carry between the parties.

## Places

Interposed Carrier places the carrying medium between two parties in contact — what holds its own pressure or dynamic carrying between them, modifying or preventing direct coupling.

## Holds

Interposed Carrier is held by [[Contact]] and [[Boundary]]. Contact must be present for something to interpose between the parties; boundary locates the medium''s own edges, distinguishing it from what it holds between.

## Pairs

Interposed Carrier pairs with [[Coupled Contact]]. Coupled Contact names contact that carries effect directly; Interposed Carrier names contact where a medium enters between and changes or interrupts what can pass.

## Traces

- [[Contact]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Tact]]

## Nests

Interposed Carrier nests between contact and coupling — where the meeting is not face-to-face but carried through a medium that holds its own pressure or dynamic carrying between the parties.

## Reads

Interposed Carrier becomes recognisable where contact is mediated by a dynamic condition. The water layer under a hydroplaning tyre, or the vapour film beneath a droplet on a hot surface, carries its own condition into the meeting.

## Carries

Interposed Carrier carries no further public branch at this scope.','Interposed Carrier Interposed Carrier names the carrying medium that stands between two parties in contact, holding its own carrying condition between them. It does not merely block; it carries. It holds its own pressure or dynamic carrying between the parties, transforming what contact makes available. Clearance names held separation before contact. Interposed Carrier names what holds between during contact: the medium that maintains dynamic separation within what appears as meeting. The interposed carrier can prevent direct coupling: where a fluid layer interposes at full pressure, contact cannot become coupled contact — the medium carries before grip can form. It can also modify coupling: where a medium interposes within coupling, it changes how pressure, resistance, or traction carry between the parties. Places Interposed Carrier places the carrying medium between two parties in contact — what holds its own pressure or dynamic carrying between them, modifying or preventing direct coupling. Holds Interposed Carrier is held by Contact and Boundary. Contact must be present for something to interpose between the parties; boundary locates the medium''s own edges, distinguishing it from what it holds between. Pairs Interposed Carrier pairs with Coupled Contact. Coupled Contact names contact that carries effect directly; Interposed Carrier names contact where a medium enters between and changes or interrupts what can pass. Traces Contact Boundary Tact Nests Interposed Carrier nests between contact and coupling — where the meeting is not face to face but carried through a medium that holds its own pressure or dynamic carrying between the parties. Reads Interposed Carrier becomes recognisable where contact is mediated by a dynamic condition. The water layer under a hydroplaning tyre, or the vapour film beneath a droplet on a hot surface, carries its own condition into the meeting. Carries Interposed Carrier carries no further public branch at this scope.','Interposed Carrier Interposed Carrier names the carrying medium that stands between two parties in contact, holding its own carrying condition between them. It does not merely block; it carries.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.contact","first.tact","second.coupled-contact"]','{"holds":["first.contact","first.boundary"],"traces":["first.contact","first.boundary","first.tact"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.coupled-contact"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',298,'sha256:2df16223e7092dc8a46a9dca1ad6635b89afaeb264fa38245469a2f2799da11b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.interval','Interval','interval','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Interval.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/interval.html','# Interval

Interval names a bounded separation within traversal. Where traversal names movement through a closure scope, interval names the readable between-condition that lets one occurrence, position, pause, or read be distinguished from another without losing the carried relation.

## Places

Interval places a bounded separation within traversal.

## Holds

Interval is held by [[Occur]], [[Traversal]], and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Interval is a singular condition — the traversal between occurrences. The asymmetry is expressed in what interval carries: [[Period]], [[Rate]], and [[Measure]].

## Traces

- [[Occur]]
- [[Traversal]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Time]]

## Nests

Interval nests inside traversal as bounded between-condition that can align, separate, pause, or return.

## Reads

Interval becomes recognisable where traversal can be read through a bounded between: before and after, here and there, one occurrence and another. An interval is not empty by default; it can carry relation by letting what surrounds it align, separate, pause, or return.

## Carries

- [[Period]]
- [[Rate]]
- [[Measure]]
- [[Rhythm]]
- [[Acceleration]]','Interval Interval names a bounded separation within traversal. Where traversal names movement through a closure scope, interval names the readable between condition that lets one occurrence, position, pause, or read be distinguished from another without losing the carried relation. Places Interval places a bounded separation within traversal. Holds Interval is held by Occur, Traversal, and Closure Scope. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Interval is a singular condition — the traversal between occurrences. The asymmetry is expressed in what interval carries: Period, Rate, and Measure. Traces Occur Traversal Closure Scope Time Nests Interval nests inside traversal as bounded between condition that can align, separate, pause, or return. Reads Interval becomes recognisable where traversal can be read through a bounded between: before and after, here and there, one occurrence and another. An interval is not empty by default; it can carry relation by letting what surrounds it align, separate, pause, or return. Carries Period Rate Measure Rhythm Acceleration','Interval Interval names a bounded separation within traversal. Where traversal names movement through a closure scope, interval names the readable between condition that lets one occurrence,…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.time","second.acceleration","second.closure-scope","second.measure","second.occur","second.period","second.rate","second.rhythm","second.traversal"]','{"holds":["second.occur","second.traversal","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.occur","second.traversal","second.closure-scope","first.time"],"carries":["second.period","second.rate","second.measure","second.rhythm","second.acceleration"],"pairs":["second.period","second.rate","second.measure"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',155,'sha256:72f4930846c3a2f2dcaeb5aa468f3d047105d3f980d706ceb1305398b5cfbfdc','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.invisible-bearing-read','Invisible Bearing Read','invisible-bearing-read','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Invisible Bearing Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/invisible-bearing-read.html','# Invisible Bearing Read

Invisible Bearing Read names bearing that carries participation without presenting as bearing. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, invisible bearing read names the condition through which that holding continues without being visible as holding. It is not hidden bearing — invisible bearing remains retraceable; what carries is not presented but can be recovered through retrace.

## Places

Invisible Bearing Read places bearing that carries participation without presenting as bearing.

## Holds

Invisible Bearing Read is held by [[Bearing]] and [[Invisible]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Invisible Bearing Read is a singular condition — a read of bearing through invisible conditions. The asymmetry is expressed in what it carries: [[Nesting Read]].

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Invisible]]

## Nests

Invisible Bearing Read nests where bearing remains retraceable without presenting as bearing.

## Reads

Invisible Bearing Read becomes recognisable where carrying can be traced despite not presenting as carrying — where something holds without showing that it holds.

## Carries

- [[Nesting Read]]','Invisible Bearing Read Invisible Bearing Read names bearing that carries participation without presenting as bearing. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, invisible bearing read names the condition through which that holding continues without being visible as holding. It is not hidden bearing — invisible bearing remains retraceable; what carries is not presented but can be recovered through retrace. Places Invisible Bearing Read places bearing that carries participation without presenting as bearing. Holds Invisible Bearing Read is held by Bearing and Invisible. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Invisible Bearing Read is a singular condition — a read of bearing through invisible conditions. The asymmetry is expressed in what it carries: Nesting Read. Traces Bearing Invisible Nests Invisible Bearing Read nests where bearing remains retraceable without presenting as bearing. Reads Invisible Bearing Read becomes recognisable where carrying can be traced despite not presenting as carrying — where something holds without showing that it holds. Carries Nesting Read','Invisible Bearing Read Invisible Bearing Read names bearing that carries participation without presenting as bearing. Where bearing names strain held as a readable condition, invisible bearing…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.invisible","second.nesting-read"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","first.invisible"],"traces":["first.bearing","first.invisible"],"carries":["second.nesting-read"],"pairs":["second.nesting-read"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',157,'sha256:66aef9b07de97d8b8a93c5c374219b07ff6b96f6d02ba59d51e71305d4d2567d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.kind','Kind','kind','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Kind.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/kind.html','# Kind

Kind names recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances. Where [[Form]] names readable arrangement and [[Pattern]] names readable recurrence, kind names the condition through which different instances can be read as belonging to the same relational sort without being collapsed into sameness.

Category can help read kind, but kind is more than a category. A category may sort from outside; kind remains answerable to the relation by which the instances belong together. Kind preserves enough recurrence for recognition while allowing each instance to remain locally distinct.

In ordinary language, kind also names a mode of care. Structurally, this preserves the sense that relation is met according to what it is: to be kind is to meet a condition without losing its kind.

## Places

Kind places recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances.

## Holds

Kind is held by [[Form]], [[Pattern]], and [[Recognition Read|Recognition]].

## Pairs

Kind pairs with [[Surface]]: kind names the recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances; surface names the presenting face through which a condition becomes available. Each requires the other — kind is only kind if it presents through surfaces; surface is only surface if something of a kind is presenting through it.

## Traces

- [[Generic]]
- [[Form]]
- [[Pattern]]
- [[Recognition Read|Recognition]]

## Nests

Kind nests where recurring form remains recognisable across distinct instances without collapsing them into sameness.

## Reads

Kind becomes recognisable where distinct instances can be read as the same relational sort while remaining different instances — where recurrence and form hold enough continuity for recognition without flattening local difference.

## Carries

- [[Identity]]
- [[Inheritance]]
- [[Care]]','Kind Kind names recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances. Where Form names readable arrangement and Pattern names readable recurrence, kind names the condition through which different instances can be read as belonging to the same relational sort without being collapsed into sameness. Category can help read kind, but kind is more than a category. A category may sort from outside; kind remains answerable to the relation by which the instances belong together. Kind preserves enough recurrence for recognition while allowing each instance to remain locally distinct. In ordinary language, kind also names a mode of care. Structurally, this preserves the sense that relation is met according to what it is: to be kind is to meet a condition without losing its kind. Places Kind places recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances. Holds Kind is held by Form, Pattern, and Recognition Read. Pairs Kind pairs with Surface: kind names the recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances; surface names the presenting face through which a condition becomes available. Each requires the other — kind is only kind if it presents through surfaces; surface is only surface if something of a kind is presenting through it. Traces Generic Form Pattern Recognition Read Nests Kind nests where recurring form remains recognisable across distinct instances without collapsing them into sameness. Reads Kind becomes recognisable where distinct instances can be read as the same relational sort while remaining different instances — where recurrence and form hold enough continuity for recognition without flattening local difference. Carries Identity Inheritance Care','Kind Kind names recurrent form recognisable across distinct instances. Where Form names readable arrangement and Pattern names readable recurrence, kind names the condition through which different…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.generic","second.form","second.identity","second.pattern","second.recognition-read","second.surface","third.care","third.inheritance"]','{"holds":["second.form","second.pattern","second.recognition-read"],"traces":["ground.generic","second.form","second.pattern","second.recognition-read"],"carries":["second.identity","third.inheritance","third.care"],"pairs":["second.surface"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',252,'sha256:4787792d921c7e0a7c554e7f98a20867c617ab2ba7f0c04bfdfa8741d128e1f3','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.know','Know','know','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability Conditions/Know.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/know.html','# Know

Know names a recognised read held as available. Where recognition names a read becoming identifiable as this again, know names the condition through which that recognised read is sustained: carried, usable, checkable, and revisable within the current scope. Certainty or truth can involve knowing, but know names a recognised read that continues to be available for use.

## Places

Know places a recognised read held as available.

## Holds

Know is held by [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Carrying]], and [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Know is vertical. It names a recognised read held as available, and carries this forward into [[Knowledge]] and [[Competence Boundary]]. Know holds [[Recognition Read]], [[Carrying]], and [[Compatibility]] — it is a downstream read of recognition and carrying, not a lateral co-present condition alongside another second-order term.

## Traces

- [[Recognition Read|Recognition]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Information]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Know nests where recognition remains carried, usable, checkable, and revisable within scope.

## Reads

Know becomes recognisable where a recognised read can be carried, used, checked, or revised — where what has been recognised continues to be available rather than having to be re-established.

## Carries

- [[Knowledge]]
- [[Competence Boundary]]
- [[Knowing]]','Know Know names a recognised read held as available. Where recognition names a read becoming identifiable as this again, know names the condition through which that recognised read is sustained: carried, usable, checkable, and revisable within the current scope. Certainty or truth can involve knowing, but know names a recognised read that continues to be available for use. Places Know places a recognised read held as available. Holds Know is held by Recognition Read, Carrying, and Compatibility. Pairs Know is vertical. It names a recognised read held as available, and carries this forward into Knowledge and Competence Boundary. Know holds Recognition Read, Carrying, and Compatibility — it is a downstream read of recognition and carrying, not a lateral co present condition alongside another second order term. Traces Recognition Read Carrying Compatibility Closure Scope Information Readability Nests Know nests where recognition remains carried, usable, checkable, and revisable within scope. Reads Know becomes recognisable where a recognised read can be carried, used, checked, or revised — where what has been recognised continues to be available rather than having to be re established. Carries Knowledge Competence Boundary Knowing','Know Know names a recognised read held as available. Where recognition names a read becoming identifiable as this again, know names the condition through which that recognised read is sustained:…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.closure-scope","second.compatibility","second.information","second.readability","second.recognition-read","third.competence-boundary","third.knowing","third.knowledge"]','{"holds":["second.recognition-read","second.carrying","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.recognition-read","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope","second.information","second.readability"],"carries":["third.knowledge","third.competence-boundary","third.knowing"],"pairs":["third.knowledge","third.competence-boundary"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',185,'sha256:63a6651a5e0e6271dff9d3063872d50715cf6533afa8e919869390469b4a4576','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.live','Live','live','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Live.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/live.html','# Live

Live names carrying continuing in participation. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, live names their combination held: carrying and participation are both continuing rather than remembered, predicted, or represented. A property can point to liveness, but live first names active continuing participation.

## Places

Live places carrying continuing in participation.

## Holds

Live is held by [[Carrying]] and [[Participation]].

## Pairs

Live is vertical. It names carrying continuing in participation, and carries this forward into [[Being]]. There is no lateral co-present condition that Live requires and that requires Live in return at this order.

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Participation]]

## Nests

Live nests where carrying and participation are both continuing in the current scope.

## Reads

Live becomes recognisable where participation is continuing rather than only having occurred — where carrying and participation are both present and active within the current scope.

## Carries

- [[Being]]','Live Live names carrying continuing in participation. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, live names their combination held: carrying and participation are both continuing rather than remembered, predicted, or represented. A property can point to liveness, but live first names active continuing participation. Places Live places carrying continuing in participation. Holds Live is held by Carrying and Participation. Pairs Live is vertical. It names carrying continuing in participation, and carries this forward into Being. There is no lateral co present condition that Live requires and that requires Live in return at this order. Traces Carrying Participation Nests Live nests where carrying and participation are both continuing in the current scope. Reads Live becomes recognisable where participation is continuing rather than only having occurred — where carrying and participation are both present and active within the current scope. Carries Being','Live Live names carrying continuing in participation. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.being","second.carrying","second.participation"]','{"holds":["second.carrying","second.participation"],"traces":["second.carrying","second.participation"],"carries":["second.being"],"pairs":["second.being"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',153,'sha256:d779aca911b40dff94506082334b33b5681ba50c0efdf2d654c6f2cf4b82ff86','1970-01-01','2026-06-25