INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.load','Load','load','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Load.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/load.html','# Load

Load names what bears on carrying. Where bearing names strain held as readable and carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, load names the carried demand, weight, or pressure that must remain supportable for carrying to continue. Load becomes [[Pressure]] where it becomes locally borne through relation. Load becomes burden where it strains carrying beyond supportable condition.

## Places

Load places what bears on carrying.

## Holds

Load is held by [[Bearing]] and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

Load is vertical. It names what bears on carrying, and carries this forward into [[Capacity]], [[Pressure]], and [[Overload]]. Load holds [[Bearing]] and [[Carrying]] — it is a downstream read of what bearing presses against carrying, not a lateral co-present condition alongside another second-order term.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Load nests inside carrying as what bears on continuation and tests capacity.

## Reads

Load becomes recognisable where carrying is not empty continuation but must support what bears on it — where continuation has weight, demand, or pressure that affects whether carrying can remain available.

## Carries

- [[Capacity]]
- [[Pressure]]
- [[Overload]]','Load Load names what bears on carrying. Where bearing names strain held as readable and carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, load names the carried demand, weight, or pressure that must remain supportable for carrying to continue. Load becomes Pressure where it becomes locally borne through relation. Load becomes burden where it strains carrying beyond supportable condition. Places Load places what bears on carrying. Holds Load is held by Bearing and Carrying. Pairs Load is vertical. It names what bears on carrying, and carries this forward into Capacity, Pressure, and Overload. Load holds Bearing and Carrying — it is a downstream read of what bearing presses against carrying, not a lateral co present condition alongside another second order term. Traces Bearing Carrying Nests Load nests inside carrying as what bears on continuation and tests capacity. Reads Load becomes recognisable where carrying is not empty continuation but must support what bears on it — where continuation has weight, demand, or pressure that affects whether carrying can remain available. Carries Capacity Pressure Overload','Load Load names what bears on carrying. Where bearing names strain held as readable and carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, load names the carried demand, weight,…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.capacity","second.carrying","second.overload","second.pressure"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","second.carrying"],"traces":["first.bearing","second.carrying"],"carries":["second.capacity","second.pressure","second.overload"],"pairs":["second.capacity","second.overload"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',174,'sha256:c460c314d70bf7e26c68ba9e4cce94626c816f22b8339e57b79debb9bf056c4f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.measure','Measure','measure','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Measure.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/measure.html','# Measure

Measure names a read compared against a bounded unit or scale. Truth can use measure, but measure first names the produced read through which extent, recurrence, interval, or change can be evaluated within a scope.

## Places

Measure places a read compared against a bounded unit or scale.

## Holds

Measure is held by [[Scale]] and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Measure is a singular condition — the reading of scale against a closure scope. The asymmetry is expressed in what measure carries: [[Unit]] and [[Rate]].

## Traces

- [[Scale]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Interval]]
- [[Number]]

## Nests

Measure nests where extent, recurrence, interval, or change can be evaluated against unit or scale.

## Reads

Measure becomes recognisable where a condition can be evaluated as more, less, equal, repeated, or extended against a readable unit or scale.

## Carries

- [[Unit]]
- [[Rate]]
- [[Speed]]','Measure Measure names a read compared against a bounded unit or scale. Truth can use measure, but measure first names the produced read through which extent, recurrence, interval, or change can be evaluated within a scope. Places Measure places a read compared against a bounded unit or scale. Holds Measure is held by Scale and Closure Scope. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Measure is a singular condition — the reading of scale against a closure scope. The asymmetry is expressed in what measure carries: Unit and Rate. Traces Scale Closure Scope Interval Number Nests Measure nests where extent, recurrence, interval, or change can be evaluated against unit or scale. Reads Measure becomes recognisable where a condition can be evaluated as more, less, equal, repeated, or extended against a readable unit or scale. Carries Unit Rate Speed','Measure Measure names a read compared against a bounded unit or scale. Truth can use measure, but measure first names the produced read through which extent, recurrence, interval, or change can be…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.interval","second.number","second.rate","second.scale","second.speed","second.unit"]','{"holds":["second.scale","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.scale","second.closure-scope","second.interval","second.number"],"carries":["second.unit","second.rate","second.speed"],"pairs":["second.unit","second.rate"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',135,'sha256:4c0d786d09c216add0bc578d31e2d3acd05beb5e42f53e48b8e9a2832e7faa63','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.medium','Medium','medium','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Medium.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/medium.html','# Medium

Medium names what carrying occurs through. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, medium names the condition that carrying moves through. Substance can be a medium, but medium first names the through-condition of carrying.

A medium allows some reads while thinning or blocking others. A phone call may allow voice, tone, and timing while not allowing enough behaviour read for some relational repair.

## Places

Medium places what carrying occurs through.

## Holds

Medium is held by [[Carrying]], [[Participation]], and [[Allow]].

## Pairs

Medium is vertical. It names what carrying occurs through, and carries this forward into [[Structure]], [[Flow]], and [[Current]]. Medium holds [[Carrying]], [[Participation]], and [[Allow]] — the passage condition of allowance makes medium available. There is no lateral co-present condition required for Medium to be locatable at this order.

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Allow]]

## Nests

Medium nests as the through-condition of carrying and participation. It shapes what can be allowed through.

## Reads

Medium becomes recognisable where carrying can be read as occurring through something — where participation passes through a condition rather than independently of it, and where that condition shapes what can be allowed through.

## Carries

- [[Structure]]
- [[Flow]]
- [[Current]]
- [[Teaching]]
- [[Communicating]]
- [[Expressing]]
- [[Translation Invariance]]','Medium Medium names what carrying occurs through. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, medium names the condition that carrying moves through. Substance can be a medium, but medium first names the through condition of carrying. A medium allows some reads while thinning or blocking others. A phone call may allow voice, tone, and timing while not allowing enough behaviour read for some relational repair. Places Medium places what carrying occurs through. Holds Medium is held by Carrying, Participation, and Allow. Pairs Medium is vertical. It names what carrying occurs through, and carries this forward into Structure, Flow, and Current. Medium holds Carrying, Participation, and Allow — the passage condition of allowance makes medium available. There is no lateral co present condition required for Medium to be locatable at this order. Traces Carrying Participation Allow Nests Medium nests as the through condition of carrying and participation. It shapes what can be allowed through. Reads Medium becomes recognisable where carrying can be read as occurring through something — where participation passes through a condition rather than independently of it, and where that condition shapes what can be allowed through. Carries Structure Flow Current Teaching Communicating Expressing Translation Invariance','Medium Medium names what carrying occurs through. Where carrying names held and placeable forward availability being enacted, medium names the condition that carrying moves through.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.allow","practice.translation-invariance","second.carrying","second.current","second.flow","second.participation","second.structure","third.communicating","third.expressing","third.teaching"]','{"holds":["second.carrying","second.participation","first.allow"],"traces":["second.carrying","second.participation","first.allow"],"carries":["second.structure","second.flow","second.current","third.teaching","third.communicating","third.expressing","practice.translation-invariance"],"pairs":["second.structure","second.flow","second.current"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',200,'sha256:e7e1a27bd5c723e810ae89f1414afe83929fd5bb8f29c8b92f2de8410f78ebfe','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.member','Member','member','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Member.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/member.html','# Member

Member names a scale-local participating part in a carried body.

A member is not an absolute identity. It is the placed participation a thing has where it belongs to a wider structure, field, body, system, or relation. A beam is a member at the frame scale. A person is a member at the family, team, community, or civic scale. At another scale, each is also made of smaller members and participates in larger ones.

Member preserves the thing-read without isolating it. A member carries itself, receives load or relation, and resolves what it carries into a wider body.

## Places

Member places a scale-local participating part in a carried body.

## Holds

Member is held by [[Thing]], [[Scale]], [[Structure]], [[Carrying]], and [[Participation]]. A thing must be readable at a scale, ordered enough to bear, and participating in a wider carried body before it can be read as a member.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Unit is a useful contrast: Unit names a bounded repeatable measure; Member names a scale-local participating part in a carried body.

A unit can be counted or compared without belonging to a body. A member is readable through belonging, bearing, and participation.

## Traces

- [[Thing]]
- [[Scale]]
- [[Structure]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Participation]]

## Nests

Member nests where a thing is made of smaller members, carries itself, receives load or relation, and resolves what it carries into a wider body.

At each scale, the member-read changes without breaking the relation. A structural member may be a beam in a frame, timber fibres in a beam, or a frame within a building. A human member may be a person in a family, organs in a body, cells in an organ, or a community within a wider field.

## Reads

Member becomes readable where a thing is located by its participation in a wider carried body rather than by isolated identity.

A [[Label]] may mark the current member-read for communication, coordination, or action. Beam, stud, rafter, post, citizen, patient, parent, worker, tool, and obstacle can each name a placed read. The member-read remains answerable to placement, scale, carrying, and participation.

This makes member a scale term as much as a belonging term. It names a recurring operation: carrying self-weight, receiving relation, and resolving what is carried into support, continuity, or participation.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Member Member names a scale local participating part in a carried body. A member is not an absolute identity. It is the placed participation a thing has where it belongs to a wider structure, field, body, system, or relation. A beam is a member at the frame scale. A person is a member at the family, team, community, or civic scale. At another scale, each is also made of smaller members and participates in larger ones. Member preserves the thing read without isolating it. A member carries itself, receives load or relation, and resolves what it carries into a wider body. Places Member places a scale local participating part in a carried body. Holds Member is held by Thing, Scale, Structure, Carrying, and Participation. A thing must be readable at a scale, ordered enough to bear, and participating in a wider carried body before it can be read as a member. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Unit is a useful contrast: Unit names a bounded repeatable measure; Member names a scale local participating part in a carried body. A unit can be counted or compared without belonging to a body. A member is readable through belonging, bearing, and participation. Traces Thing Scale Structure Carrying Participation Nests Member nests where a thing is made of smaller members, carries itself, receives load or relation, and resolves what it carries into a wider body. At each scale, the member read changes without breaking the relation. A structural member may be a beam in a frame, timber fibres in a beam, or a frame within a building. A human member may be a person in a family, organs in a body, cells in an organ, or a community within a wider field. Reads Member becomes readable where a thing is located by its participation in a wider carried body rather than by isolated identity. A Label may mark the current member read for communication, coordination, or action. Beam, stud, rafter, post, citizen, patient