INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.nested-relation','Nested Relation','nested-relation','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Nested Relation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/nested-relation.html','# Nested Relation

Nested relation names asymmetrical relation: relation participating within relation. Where within names relation held with inside placement and nesting names a prior organisation remaining available within a later one, nested relation names the specific condition through which one relation participates inside another while remaining retraceable as a distinct relation. Nested relation is not contained relation; it names relation that participates within relation while remaining itself.

Nested relation orders. It names the dependency asymmetry by which one relation is carried, bounded, conditioned, or read through a wider relation: inner/outer, carried/carrier, local/wider, prior/later, term/condition, read/read-condition. Without that asymmetry, relation becomes flat connection; without connection, nesting becomes detached hierarchy.

## Places

Nested Relation places asymmetrical relation — one relation participating within, and remaining ordered by, another relation.

## Holds

Nested Relation is held by [[Within]] and [[Nesting Read]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Nested Relation is a singular condition — a relation held within another relation. The asymmetry is expressed in what nested relation carries: [[Structural Gathering]].

## Traces

- [[Within]]
- [[Nesting Read]]

## Nests

Nested Relation nests where one relation participates within another while remaining retraceable as its own relation.

## Reads

Nested relation becomes recognisable where a relation can be read as participating within another relation — inner/outer, carried/carrier, local/wider, term/condition — while remaining followable as its own condition rather than dissolving into the outer one.

## Carries

- [[Structural Gathering]]
- [[Nested Coupling]]','Nested Relation Nested relation names asymmetrical relation: relation participating within relation. Where within names relation held with inside placement and nesting names a prior organisation remaining available within a later one, nested relation names the specific condition through which one relation participates inside another while remaining retraceable as a distinct relation. Nested relation is not contained relation; it names relation that participates within relation while remaining itself. Nested relation orders. It names the dependency asymmetry by which one relation is carried, bounded, conditioned, or read through a wider relation: inner/outer, carried/carrier, local/wider, prior/later, term/condition, read/read condition. Without that asymmetry, relation becomes flat connection; without connection, nesting becomes detached hierarchy. Places Nested Relation places asymmetrical relation — one relation participating within, and remaining ordered by, another relation. Holds Nested Relation is held by Within and Nesting Read. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Nested Relation is a singular condition — a relation held within another relation. The asymmetry is expressed in what nested relation carries: Structural Gathering. Traces Within Nesting Read Nests Nested Relation nests where one relation participates within another while remaining retraceable as its own relation. Reads Nested relation becomes recognisable where a relation can be read as participating within another relation — inner/outer, carried/carrier, local/wider, term/condition — while remaining followable as its own condition rather than dissolving into the outer one. Carries Structural Gathering Nested Coupling','Nested Relation Nested relation names asymmetrical relation: relation participating within relation. Where within names relation held with inside placement and nesting names a prior organisation…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.nesting-read","second.structural-gathering","second.within","third.nested-coupling"]','{"holds":["second.within","second.nesting-read"],"traces":["second.within","second.nesting-read"],"carries":["second.structural-gathering","third.nested-coupling"],"pairs":["second.structural-gathering"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',226,'sha256:662cf9b9e808fc33ca2df38f8b92989e917df49b54eccf9cc1109bb7362f6640','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.nesting-read','Nesting Read','nesting-read','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Nesting Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/nesting-read.html','# Nesting Read

Nesting Read names the produced read through which a prior organisation remains available within a later organisation. Where stability names identity and coherence holding across scope, nesting read names the condition through which a prior stable organisation is not replaced but carried within a later one — remaining available through retrace without requiring explicit acknowledgement.

## Places

Nesting Read places the produced read through which a prior organisation remains available within a later organisation.

## Holds

Nesting Read is held by [[Stability]] and [[Retrace Read|Retrace]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Nesting Read is a singular condition — a retrace read applied to stability within nesting. The asymmetry is expressed in what nesting read carries: [[Nested Carrying]] and [[Nested Relation]].

## Traces

- [[Stability]]
- [[Retrace Read|Retrace]]
- [[Invisible Bearing Read]]

## Nests

Nesting Read nests where prior organisation remains retraceable within a later organisation.

## Reads

Nesting Read becomes recognisable where a prior organisation can be traced within a later one — where what held before continues to hold as available within the current scope rather than having been replaced.

## Carries

- [[Nested Carrying]]
- [[Nested Relation]]','Nesting Read Nesting Read names the produced read through which a prior organisation remains available within a later organisation. Where stability names identity and coherence holding across scope, nesting read names the condition through which a prior stable organisation is not replaced but carried within a later one — remaining available through retrace without requiring explicit acknowledgement. Places Nesting Read places the produced read through which a prior organisation remains available within a later organisation. Holds Nesting Read is held by Stability and Retrace Read. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Nesting Read is a singular condition — a retrace read applied to stability within nesting. The asymmetry is expressed in what nesting read carries: Nested Carrying and Nested Relation. Traces Stability Retrace Read Invisible Bearing Read Nests Nesting Read nests where prior organisation remains retraceable within a later organisation. Reads Nesting Read becomes recognisable where a prior organisation can be traced within a later one — where what held before continues to hold as available within the current scope rather than having been replaced. Carries Nested Carrying Nested Relation','Nesting Read Nesting Read names the produced read through which a prior organisation remains available within a later organisation. Where stability names identity and coherence holding across…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["higher.nested-carrying","second.invisible-bearing-read","second.nested-relation","second.retrace-read","second.stability"]','{"holds":["second.stability","second.retrace-read"],"traces":["second.stability","second.retrace-read","second.invisible-bearing-read"],"carries":["higher.nested-carrying","second.nested-relation"],"pairs":["higher.nested-carrying","second.nested-relation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"t