INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.proceed','Proceed','proceed','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Proceed.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/proceed.html','# Proceed

Proceed names continuation without interruption. Where process names a carried sequence, proceed names that sequence continuing: moving forward through the current scope without departure or cessation. Progress or direction can be read later; proceed first names continuation as available.

## Places

Proceed places continuation without interruption.

## Holds

Proceed is held by [[Process]].

## Pairs

Proceed is vertical. It names continuation without interruption, and carries this forward into [[Progress]] and [[Digress]]. Proceed holds [[Process]] — it is a downstream read of process continuing, not a lateral co-present condition alongside another second-order term.

## Traces

- [[Process]]

## Nests

Proceed nests where a carried sequence continues through current scope without interruption.

## Reads

Proceed becomes recognisable where a carried sequence continues without interruption — where participation moves forward through the current scope.

## Carries

- [[Progress]]
- [[Digress]]
