Rate names relation read against interval. Where recurrence names participation occurring again and interval names bounded separation within traversal, rate names the produced read of how recurrence, change, or carrying relates to that interval.

## Places

Rate places relation read against interval.

## Holds

Rate is held by [[Recurrence]], [[Interval]], and [[Measure]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Rate is a singular condition — recurrence measured per interval. The asymmetry is expressed in what rate carries: [[Frequency]], [[Speed]], and [[Tempo]].

## Traces

- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Interval]]
- [[Measure]]

## Nests

Rate nests inside interval and measure as recurrence, change, or carrying read per interval.

## Reads

Rate becomes recognisable where recurrence, change, or carrying can be read as occurring per interval.

## Carries

- [[Frequency]]
- [[Speed]]
- [[Tempo]]
- [[Pace]]
- [[Timescale]]
- [[Throughput]]
- [[Resolution Rate]]','Rate Rate names relation read against interval. Where recurrence names participation occurring again and interval names bounded separation within traversal, rate names the produced read of how recurrence, change, or carrying relates to that interval. Places Rate places relation read against interval. Holds Rate is held by Recurrence, Interval, and Measure. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Rate is a singular condition — recurrence measured per interval. The asymmetry is expressed in what rate carries: Frequency, Speed, and Tempo. Traces Recurrence Interval Measure Nests Rate nests inside interval and measure as recurrence, change, or carrying read per interval. Reads Rate becomes recognisable where recurrence, change, or carrying can be read as occurring per interval. Carries Frequency Speed Tempo Pace Timescale Throughput Resolution Rate','Rate Rate names relation read against interval. Where recurrence names participation occurring again and interval names bounded separation within traversal, rate names the produced read of how…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.frequency","second.interval","second.measure","second.pace","second.recurrence","second.resolution-rate","second.speed","second.tempo","second.throughput","third.timescale"]','{"holds":["second.recurrence","second.interval","second.measure"],"traces":["second.recurrence","second.interval","second.measure"],"carries":["second.frequency","second.speed","second.tempo","second.pace","third.timescale","second.throughput","second.resolution-rate"],"pairs":["second.frequency","second.speed","second.tempo"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',121,'sha256:c04c90bc74cd78bd23f0bbb591a75626ab8c9354dbf4800ffdbf64d36ac1d5dd','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.read-and-effect','Read and Effect','read-and-effect','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Read and Effect.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/read-and-effect.html','# Read and Effect

Read and Effect names the distinction between how a condition becomes recognisable, what follows from a condition operating, and the traced account through which an effect becomes explainable.

A read names how a condition becomes recognisable; an effect names what follows from that condition; cause-read is the traced account through which an effect becomes explainable.

[[Read]] is not [[Effect]]. Read names recognisable presentation within a scope. Effect names a carried consequence: what follows when a condition operates through coupling, carrying, or contact. Cause is not the same as either read or effect, and it is not a first-order acting thing. Cause remains subordinate to [[Trace]]: it is a cause-read assigned after an effect is traced back through the carrying conditions that make it explainable.

The working order is:

Condition -> Read -> Effect -> Trace -> Cause-read.

This is a review order for avoiding false causality, not a claim that [[Trace]] begins only after [[Effect]]. Structurally, trace still makes read possible; after an effect is recognised, trace is followed again to form a cause-read.

A common error is treating a read as an acting force. This produces false causality, especially where the read is negative: shade, darkness, disorder, silence, absence, or other loss-reads can be mistaken for positive causes acting by themselves.

## Places

Read and Effect places the distinction between recognisability, consequence, trace, and cause-read.

## Holds

Read and Effect is held by [[Read]], [[Effect]], and [[Trace]]. A condition must be recognisable, its consequence distinguishable, and the path back through carrying conditions traceable before a cause-read can be assigned.

## Pairs

Read and Effect pairs with false causality: the error of treating a read as if it were an acting force.

## Traces

- [[Read]]
- [[Effect]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Read and Effect nests inside second-order distinction work, where recognisable presentation, carried consequence, trace, and cause-read must not collapse into one another.

## Reads

Read and Effect becomes recognisable where a recognisable condition, a following change, and the traced account through which that change becomes explainable are being confused or need to be kept separate.

## Structural Protection

This distinction protects against a common drift:

Read -> mistaken for thing -> mistaken for cause.

Shade may be treated as causing cooling. In the cleaner read, shade is the read, cooling may be the effect, and reduced light or heat input is the causal trace.

Darkness may be treated as acting. In the cleaner read, darkness is the read of absent light, not a force acting by itself.

Disorder may be treated as a force. In the cleaner read, disorder is the read of order no longer being held.

Silence may be treated as empty non-relation. In the cleaner read, silence is the read of absent or ceased sound or contact within a scope where that absence can become recognisable.

Entropy may be treated as disorder acting. In the cleaner read, entropy measures relaxation or dispersion of held order; the cause-read belongs to the traced carrying conditions through which that relaxation or dispersion occurs.

## Carries

No direct downstream carries are claimed yet.

Candidate review sites include [[Second-Order Disorder Effects]], [[Reality Check]], and [[Order Trace]], but they should not be treated as dependencies until they explicitly trace this distinction.','Read and Effect Read and Effect names the distinction between how a condition becomes recognisable, what follows from a condition operating, and the traced account through which an effect becomes explainable. A read names how a condition becomes recognisable; an effect names what follows from that condition; cause read is the traced account through which an effect becomes explainable. Read is not Effect. Read names recognisable presentation within a scope. Effect names a carried consequence: what follows when a condition operates through coupling, carrying, or contact. Cause is not the same as either read or effect, and it is not a first order acting thing. Cause remains subordinate to Trace: it is a cause read assigned after an effect is traced back through the carrying conditions that make it explainable. The working order is: Condition Read Effect Trace Cause read. This is a review order for avoiding false causality, not a claim that Trace begins only after Effect. Structurally, trace still makes read possible; after an effect is recognised, trace is followed again to form a cause read. A common error is treating a read as an acting force. This produces false causality, especially where the read is negative: shade, darkness, disorder, silence, absence, or other loss reads can be mistaken for positive causes acting by themselves. Places Read and Effect places the distinction between recognisability, consequence, trace, and cause read. Holds Read and Effect is held by Read, Effect, and Trace. A condition must be recognisable, its consequence distinguishable, and the path back through carrying conditions traceable before a cause read can be assigned. Pairs Read and Effect pairs with false causality: the error of treating a read as if it were an acting force. Traces Read Effect Trace Carrying Nests Read and Effect nests inside second order distinction work, where recognisable presentation, carried consequence, trace, and cause read must not collapse into one another. Reads Read and Effect becomes recognisable where a recognisable condition, a following change, and the traced account through which that change becomes explainable are being confused or need to be kept separate. Structural Protection This distinction protects against a common drift: Read mistaken for thing mistaken for cause. Shade may be treated as causing cooling. In the cleaner read, shade is the read, cooling may be the effect, and reduced light or heat input is the causal trace. Darkness may be treated as acting. In the cleaner read, darkness is the read of absent light, not a force acting by itself. Disorder may be treated as a force. In the cleaner read, disorder is the read of order no longer being held. Silence may be treated as empty non relation. In the cleaner read, silence is the read of absent or ceased sound or contact within a scope where that absence can become recognisable. Entropy may be treated as disorder acting. In the cleaner read, entropy measures relaxation or dispersion of held order; the cause read belongs to the traced carrying conditions through which that relaxation or dispersion occurs. Carries No direct downstream carries are claimed yet. Candidate review sites include Second Order Disorder Effects, Reality Check, and Order Trace, but they should not be treated as dependencies until they explicitly trace this distinction.','Read and Effect Read and Effect names the distinction between how a condition becomes recognisable, what follows from a condition operating, and the traced account through which an effect becomes…','working','planted',0,'second','distinction',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.read","first.trace","second.carrying","second.effect"]','{"holds":["first.read","second.effect","first.trace"],"traces":["first.read","second.effect","first.trace","second.carrying"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Structural Protection","anchor":"structural-protection"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',540,'sha256:240ee38fcaba165a67dbb0eae5f6118a65a6c419203bf7d82374acf331866f55','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.readability','Readability','readability','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/readability.html','# Readability

Readability names the condition through which a distinction becomes available to be read. [[Read]] names recognition of meaningful distinction at a point. Readability names the sustained condition that makes reading possible: distinction is present, traceable, attended, and held enough to enter evaluation. It is not the read itself; it is what makes reading available.

## Places

Readability places the sustained condition that makes reading possible.

## Holds

Readability is held by [[Read]] and [[Attend]]. Meaningful distinction must be read and attended enough to remain available for further reading.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — into [[Cognitive Participation]], [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Echo]], [[Visibility]], [[Know]], [[Influence]], [[Enchantment]], [[Wonder]], [[Pair]]. Readability is the sustained enabling condition for all reading; it is not one side of a lateral juncture. What reading opens up flows downward from it.

## Traces

- [[Read]]
- [[Attend]]
- [[Relation Read]]

## Nests

Readability nests as a second-order support root. It supports cognitive participation, recognition, visibility, knowing, influence, retrace, and later field reads.

## Reads

Readability becomes recognisable where a condition is present enough, attended enough, traceable enough, and held enough that a read can take place.

Readability is constrained by resolution band. A condition may be real and effective without being directly readable to a participant whose current band cannot receive, integrate, or carry it. What cannot be resolved directly may still become readable through translation, measurement, slowed sequence, repeated exposure, or changed carrying conditions.
## Carries

