as local pressure or forced into absence. Recarry begins where carrying continues after a path changes or narrows. Trace and Groundedness locate where the carrying came from; Release lets the local carrier stop holding the whole load alone; Compatibility lets grounding relations carry what remains differently. Recarry differs from Repair, Recovery, Retrace Read, and Regenerate. Repair restores compatible bearing. Recovery is embodied re bearing after fatigue or injury. Retrace follows the dependency path back. Regenerate recovers the generative trace. Recarry names the carrying itself being taken up again, differently. Carries Recarry carries Recovery as a body field expression: embodied carrying restored or resumed after fatigue or injury. Recovery','Recarry Recarry names carrying returned through contact and held again, differently. What is carried enters contact, meets another read, and comes back still held, but altered by trace.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.contact","first.release","first.trace","ground.groundedness","second.carrying","second.compatibility","third.recovery"]','{"holds":["second.carrying","first.trace","first.contact","ground.groundedness","first.release","second.compatibility"],"traces":["second.carrying","first.trace","first.contact","ground.groundedness","first.release","second.compatibility"],"carries":["third.recovery"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',405,'sha256:1ead810cf95d2629e82b694dca416ab5ff8874bb7d65989f8f7dea010c1e8a9a','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.recognition-read','Recognition Read','recognition-read','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability Conditions/Recognition Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/recognition-read.html','# Recognition Read

Recognition Read names a read becoming identifiable as this again. Where readability names the condition that makes reading possible, and [[Cognitive Participation]] names relation participating in readability, recognition read names the produced read through which something is identified as the same condition encountered before — this participant, this pattern, this state. Recognition read does not require perfect repetition; it names the condition through which a read can be held as identifiable across instances.

In cognitive fields, recognition is cognition becoming placed: what is received and distinguished is resolved as this within a boundary and closure scope. Recognition is therefore not the first availability of difference; it is a read becoming identifiable enough to be carried, checked, or returned to.

## Places

Recognition Read places a read becoming identifiable as this again.

## Holds

Recognition Read is held by [[Readability]] and [[Cognitive Participation]]. A read must be available and relation must participate in that readability before the read can become identifiable as this.

## Pairs

Recognition Read pairs with [[Retrace Read|Retrace]]. Recognition reads this again; Retrace follows back through what made the read available.

## Traces

- [[Readability]]
- [[Cognitive Participation]]
- [[Observation]]

## Nests

Recognition Read nests where a read can be held as this again across instances without requiring perfect repetition.

## Reads

Recognition Read becomes recognisable where a read can be held as this again — where what is present can be identified as the same condition that held before.
## Carries

- [[Know]]
- [[Pattern]]
- [[Identity]]
- [[Kind]]
- [[Parenting]]
