bservation","second.pattern","second.readability","second.retrace-read","third.knowing","third.parenting"]','{"holds":["second.readability","second.cognitive-participation"],"traces":["second.readability","second.cognitive-participation","second.observation"],"carries":["second.know","second.pattern","second.identity","second.kind","third.parenting","third.knowing"],"pairs":["second.retrace-read"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',242,'sha256:2958ee4602961d60e702e77b2700acf650d6363d3423d008d7a3f914a3808e54','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.recurrence','Recurrence','recurrence','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Participation Conditions/Recurrence.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/recurrence.html','# Recurrence

Recurrence names participation occurring again. Where [[Occur]] names presence taking place within scope and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, recurrence names another occurrence identifiable as the same participating condition across traversal. Recurrence does not by itself establish [[Return]]: the recurring condition must also remain carried and become readable again at a resolvable boundary.

## Places

Recurrence places participation occurring again.

## Holds

Recurrence is held by [[Occur]], [[Participation]], and [[Traversal]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Recurrence is a singular condition — participation occurring again across traversal. The lateral asymmetry appears in what recurrence carries: [[Coherence]] ↔ [[Incoherence]].

## Traces

- [[Occur]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Traversal]]

## Nests

Recurrence nests where participation occurs again and remains recognisable across instances.

## Reads

Recurrence becomes recognisable where participation can be read as occurring again — where what takes part now can be identified as the same condition that took part before.

