- [[Tend]]','Recurrence Recurrence names participation occurring again. Where Occur names presence taking place within scope and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, recurrence names another occurrence identifiable as the same participating condition across traversal. Recurrence does not by itself establish Return: the recurring condition must also remain carried and become readable again at a resolvable boundary. Places Recurrence places participation occurring again. Holds Recurrence is held by Occur, Participation, and Traversal. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Recurrence is a singular condition — participation occurring again across traversal. The lateral asymmetry appears in what recurrence carries: Coherence ↔ Incoherence. Traces Occur Participation Traversal Nests Recurrence nests where participation occurs again and remains recognisable across instances. Reads Recurrence becomes recognisable where participation can be read as occurring again — where what takes part now can be identified as the same condition that took part before. Carries Pattern Count Coherence Rate Frequency Period Cycle Wear Trust Recursive Rhythm Maintained Coupling Musical Rhythm Second Order Crossing Echo Unit Nesting Sustaining Practice Tend','Recurrence Recurrence names participation occurring again. Where Occur names presence taking place within scope and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, recurrence…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["practice.practice","practice.tend","second.coherence","second.count","second.cycle","second.echo","second.frequency","second.incoherence","second.occur","second.participation","second.pattern","second.period","second.rate","second.recursive","second.rhythm","second.second-order-crossing","second.traversal","second.unit","second.wear","third.maintained-coupling","third.musical-rhythm","third.nesting","third.sustaining","third.trust"]','{"holds":["second.occur","se