INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.resolution-rate','Resolution Rate','resolution-rate','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Resolution Rate.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/resolution-rate.html','# Resolution Rate

Resolution Rate names the rate at which a system can resolve meaningful distinction while maintaining retraceable order.

Resolution Rate is not simple speed. It is the speed at which relation can be read, resolved, and acted through without losing [[Coupling]], [[Clearance]], or trace. Speed measures movement. Resolution Rate measures resolved relation per available continuation.

A system may move quickly while resolving poorly. Another may move more slowly but resolve more meaningfully because more order is already nested and available.

The Atlas can use Resolution Rate on itself. A garden pass has improved resolution rate where new growth, shade, strain, or uncertainty becomes more placed, traceable, re-enterable, and available for correct continuation.

## Places

Resolution Rate places the rate at which meaningful distinction can be resolved while maintaining retraceable order.

## Holds

Resolution Rate is held by [[Rate]], [[Resolution]], [[Clearance]], [[Coupling]], [[Carrying]], and [[Nesting Read]]. Rate must be readable, distinction must resolve, relation must retain clearance and coupling, carrying must continue, and prior order must remain retraceable within the current read.

This uses [[Nesting Read]] rather than third-order [[Nesting]] as the direct hold. Resolution Rate may appear where nested prior organisation is available, but a second-order rate note should not depend upward on third-order nesting as its prerequisite.

## Pairs

Resolution Rate pairs with [[Speed]]. Speed measures traversal per interval; Resolution Rate measures resolved relation per available continuation.

## Traces

- [[Rate]]
- [[Resolution]]
- [[Clearance]]
- [[Coupling]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Nesting Read]]
- [[Retrace Read|Retrace]]

## Nests

Resolution Rate nests where resolving distinction, carrying, coupling, and nested prior order remain available quickly enough to support meaningful continuation.

## Reads

Resolution Rate becomes visible where different systems, practices, or the Atlas itself operate at different rates of meaningful update.

A fly can resolve nearby motion faster than a human reaction.

A skilled drummer can resolve rhythmic change faster than a beginner because the pattern has become nested through repetition.

A senior architect can resolve downstream consequences faster than a graduate because more dependency order is already carried.

AI can resolve linguistic pattern extremely quickly, but that does not mean it resolves lived reality at the same rate. In AI use, Resolution Rate must still be checked against [[AI Coupling]] and the traceability of what the fast linguistic read claims to carry.

In the garden read, Resolution Rate becomes visible where the Atlas converts growth into care without losing re-entry:

```text
new or strained material
-> placed growth
-> clearer holds
-> fewer false carries
-> named garden status
-> available next care action
```

More notes, faster edits, or fluent summaries do not by themselves indicate higher Resolution Rate. Higher Resolution Rate appears where the Atlas can absorb change and leave the next participant with a cleaner path back through what holds.

## Guard

Resolution Rate is not how fast something moves. It is how fast meaningful distinction can be resolved without losing trace.

Fast output, fast motion, or fast reaction may indicate high speed without high Resolution Rate.

Slow proceeding may still carry a high Resolution Rate where more order is already nested, available, and retraceable at the moment of action.

## Carries

- [[Garden Pass]]

Garden Pass can retrace Resolution Rate because a tending pass asks whether the pass increased the Atlas''s ability to resolve meaningful distinction while preserving trace, re-entry, and available continuation.

Possible future candidates include operating cadence, prediction, drift risk, and AI coupling, but those should become carries only where downstream notes can retrace this dependency.','Resolution Rate Resolution Rate names the rate at which a system can resolve meaningful distinction while maintaining retraceable order. Resolution Rate is not simple speed. It is the speed at which relation can be read, resolved, and acted through without losing Coupling, Clearance, or trace. Speed measures movement. Resolution Rate measures resolved relation per available continuation. A system may move quickly while resolving poorly. Another may move more slowly but resolve more meaningfully because more order is already nested and available. The Atlas can use Resolution Rate on itself. A garden pass has improved resolution rate where new growth, shade, strain, or uncertainty becomes more placed, traceable, re enterable, and available for correct continuation. Places Resolution Rate places the rate at which meaningful distinction can be resolved while maintaining retraceable order. Holds Resolution Rate is held by Rate, Resolution, Clearance, Coupling, Carrying, and Nesting Read. Rate must be readable, distinction must resolve, relation must retain clearance and coupling, carrying must continue, and prior order must remain retraceable within the current read. This uses Nesting Read rather than third order Nesting as the direct hold. Resolution Rate may appear where nested prior organisation is available, but a second order rate note should not depend upward on third order nesting as its prerequisite. Pairs Resolution Rate pairs with Speed. Speed measures traversal per interval; Resolution Rate measures resolved relation per available continuation. Traces Rate Resolution Clearance Coupling Carrying Nesting Read Retrace Read Nests Resolution Rate nests where resolving distinction, carrying, coupling, and nested prior order remain available quickly enough to support meaningful continuation. Reads Resolution Rate becomes visible where different systems, practices, or the Atlas itself operate at different rates of meaningful update. A fly can resolve nearby motion faster than a human reaction. A skilled drummer can resolve rhythmic change faster than a beginner because the pattern has become nested through repetition. A senior architect can resolve downstream consequences faster than a graduate because more dependency order is already carried. AI can resolve linguistic pattern extremely quickly, but that does not mean it resolves lived reality at the same rate. In AI use, Resolution Rate must still be checked against AI Coupling and the traceability of what the fast linguistic read claims to carry. In the garden read, Resolution Rate becomes visible where the Atlas converts growth into care without losing re entry: More notes, faster edits, or fluent summaries do not by themselves indicate higher Resolution Rate. Higher Resolution Rate appears where the Atlas can absorb change and leave the next participant with a cleaner path back through what holds. Guard Resolution Rate is not how fast something moves. It is how fast meaningful distinction can be resolved without losing trace. Fast output, fast motion, or fast reaction may indicate high speed without high Resolution Rate. Slow proceeding may still carry a high Resolution Rate where more order is already nested, available, and retraceable at the moment of action. Carries Garden Pass Garden Pass can retrace Resolution Rate because a tending pass asks whether the pass increased the Atlas''s ability to resolve meaningful distinction while preserving trace, re entry, and available continuation. Possible future candidates include operating cadence, prediction, drift risk, and AI coupling, but those should become carries only where downstream notes can retrace this dependency.','Resolution Rate Resolution Rate names the rate at which a system can resolve meaningful distinction while maintaining retraceable order. Resolution Rate is not simple speed.','working','planted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.clearance","first.resolution","practice.garden-pass","second.carrying","second.coupling","second.nesting-read","second.rate","second.retrace-read","second.speed"]','{"holds":["second.rate","first.resolution","first.clearance","second.coupling","second.carrying","second.nesting-read"],"traces":["second.rate","first.resolution","first.clearance","second.coupling","second.carrying","second.nesting-read","second.retrace-read"],"carries":["practice.garden-pass"],"pairs":["second.speed"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Guard","anchor":"guard"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',547,'sha256:5af839828e9e6b24b34775cd5d9bda6afa61b258fba50a835193e4345d535d4b','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.resonance','Resonance','resonance','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Resonance.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/resonance.html','# Resonance

Resonance names difference coupled through a shared carrying pattern.

Resonance is not sameness. It is not difference alone. It becomes readable where distinct conditions can carry a shared frequency, rhythm, pattern, or relation strongly enough that one moves, amplifies, returns, or becomes readable through the other.

## Places

Resonance places difference coupled through a shared carrying pattern.

## Holds

Resonance is held by [[Frequency]], [[Coupling]], [[Pattern]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Capacity]]. Recurrence must have readable rate or pattern, distinct conditions must couple, and the carrier must have compatible capacity before resonance can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Resonance is evaluated by whether shared carrying remains compatible or amplifies beyond capacity.

## Traces

- [[Frequency]]
- [[Coupling]]
- [[Pattern]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Capacity]]

## Nests

Resonance nests inside carrying where distinct conditions become mutually active through a shared frequency, rhythm, pattern, or carrying condition.

## Reads

Resonance becomes readable where one condition can carry, amplify, return, or be moved by another condition''s pattern without becoming identical to it.

A tuning fork resonates where another body can carry the same frequency. A bridge can fail where repeated forcing aligns with its carrying pattern and amplification exceeds capacity. A person can resonate with a word, image, grief, or idea where a returned pattern meets a carrying condition already present in them.

Resonance may support harmony, recognition, entrainment, amplification, or collapse. It remains compatible where the carrier can absorb, release, or resolve what is amplified. It becomes unsafe where shared pattern exceeds capacity and moves toward [[Overload]] or [[Collapse]].

## Carries

Resonance carries no further public branch at this scope.','Resonance Resonance names difference coupled through a shared carrying pattern. Resonance is not sameness. It is not difference alone. It becomes readable where distinct conditions can carry a shared frequency, rhythm, pattern, or relation strongly enough that one moves, amplifies, returns, or becomes readable through the other. Places Resonance places difference coupled through a shared carrying pattern. Holds Resonance is held by Frequency, Coupling, Pattern, Compatibility, and Capacity. Recurrence must have readable rate or pattern, distinct conditions must couple, and the carrier must have compatible capacity before resonance can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Resonance is evaluated by whether shared carrying remains compatible or amplifies beyond capacity. Traces Frequency Coupling Pattern Compatibility Capacity Nests Resonance nests inside carrying where distinct conditions become mutually active through a shared frequency, rhythm, pattern, or carrying condition. Reads Resonance becomes readable where one condition can carry, amplify, return, or be moved by another condition''s pattern without becoming identical to it. A tuning fork resonates where another body can carry the same frequency. A bridge can fail where repeated forcing aligns with its carrying pattern and amplification exceeds capacity. A person can resonate with a word, image, grief, or idea where a returned pattern meets a carrying condition already present in them. Resonance may support harmony, recognition, entrainment, amplification, or collapse. It remains compatible where the carrier can absorb, release, or resolve what is amplified. It becomes unsafe where shared pattern exceeds capacity and moves toward Overload or Collapse. Carries Resonance carries no further public branch at this scope.','Resonance Resonance names difference coupled through a shared carrying pattern. Resonance is not sameness.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.capacity","second.compatibility","second.coupling","second.frequency","second.pattern"]','{"holds":["second.frequency","second.coupling","second.pattern","second.compatibility","second.capacity"],"traces":["second.frequency","second.coupling","second.pattern","second.compatibility","second.capacity"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',261,'sha256:3482ab3e15813cb8cd376dc38732e6443872d382b82311df758f1932ef77608d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.responsibility','Responsibility','responsibility','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Coupling Conditions/Responsibility.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/responsibility.html','# Responsibility

Responsibility names participation made answerable for an effect where trace returns to the coupled boundary through which that effect became actionable.

Responsibility does not automatically belong to the object, system, or medium that carries a [[Consequence]]. The carrier of an effect and the participating boundary through which that effect became actionable may be different conditions.

## Places

Responsibility places participation made answerable for an effect where trace returns to the coupled boundary through which that effect became actionable.

## Holds

Responsibility is held by [[Participation]], [[Effect]], [[Trace]], and [[Coupled Boundary]]. An effect must be present, participation must have entered the relation, and trace must recover the boundary through which that participation affected what followed before responsibility can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Responsibility distinguishes the boundary through which an effect became actionable from the carrier through which its consequence later travelled.

## Traces

- [[Participation]]
- [[Effect]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Coupled Boundary]]

## Nests

Responsibility nests inside coupling where attention, control, decision, evaluation, consent, checking, or another participation condition enters strongly enough to affect what follows.

## Reads

Responsibility becomes recognisable where an effect can be followed back past its later carrier to the coupled boundary at which participation became able to alter the relation.

A vehicle may carry impact while responsibility traces to the driver–vehicle coupling through which attention, control, and checking entered. An AI output may carry consequence while responsibility traces through the human, institutional, interface, deployment, and checking boundaries that made the output actionable.

Responsibility does not by itself determine praise, blame, punishment, or repair. It first locates answerable participation in the dependency path.

At human scope, [[Borne and Carried]] gives one reason responsibility becomes readable without reducing it to imposed debt: received carrying can become answerable carrying.

## Carries

- [[Competence Boundary]]','Responsibility Responsibility names participation made answerable for an effect where trace returns to the coupled boundary through which that effect became actionable. Responsibility does not automatically belong to the object, system, or medium that carries a Consequence. The carrier of an effect and the participating boundary through which that effect became actionable may be different conditions. Places Responsibility places participation made answerable for an effect where trace returns to the coupled boundary through which that effect became actionable. Holds Responsibility is held by Participation, Effect, Trace, and Coupled Boundary. An effect must be present, participation must have entered the relation, and trace must recover the boundary through which that participation affected what followed before responsibility can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Responsibility distinguishes the boundary through which an effect became actionable from the carrier through which its consequence later travelled. Traces Participation Effect Trace Coupled Boundary Nests Responsibility nests inside coupling where attention, control, decision, evaluation, consent, checking, or another participation condition enters strongly enough to affect what follows. Reads Responsibility becomes recognisable where an effect can be followed back past its later carrier to the coupled boundary at which participation became able to alter the relation. A vehicle may carry impact while responsibility traces to the driver–vehicle coupling through which attention, control, and checking entered. An AI output may carry consequence while responsibility traces through the human, institutional, interface, deployment, and checking boundaries that made the output actionable. Responsibility does not by itself determine praise, blame, punishment, or repair. It first locates answerable participation in the dependency path. At human scope, Borne and Carried gives one reason responsibility becomes readable without reducing it to imposed debt: received carrying can become answerable carrying. Carries Competence Boundary','Responsibility Responsibility names participation made answerable for an effect where trace returns to the coupled boundary through which that effect became actionable. Responsibility does not…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.trace","second.coupled-boundary","second.effect","second.participation","third.competence-boundary"]','{"holds":["second.participation","second.effect","first.trace","second.coupled-boundary"],"traces":["second.participation","second.effect","first.trace","second.coupled-boundary"],"carries":["third.competence-boundary"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',293,'sha256:fa42f5cb77d4a0bc16aec53845736ebfcc20785fee8873a0b720e1d62581069c','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.retain','Retain','retain','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Retain.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/retain.html','# Retain

Retain names pressure kept within a carrying relation.

Retain is not the same as [[Hold]]. Hold is a first-order resolution mode: a resolved condition remains supportable as the same condition. Retain is second-order carrying regulation: pressure remains kept inside a carrying relation after it has become locally borne.

## Places

Retain places pressure kept within a carrying relation.

## Holds

Retain is held by [[Pressure]], [[Carrying]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Hold]]. Pressure must be locally borne, carrying must remain available, and holding must remain compatible before pressure can be read as retained.

## Pairs

Retain pairs with [[Release]]. Retain names pressure kept within a carrying relation; Release names strain leaving the bearing condition. Each is readable against the other.

## Traces

- [[Pressure]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Hold]]

## Nests

Retain nests inside carrying as ongoing keeping of pressure after it has become locally borne.

## Reads

Retain becomes readable where pressure remains kept in a carrying relation without immediately discharging, transferring, or collapsing.

Retained pressure can generate form, attention, memory, structure, discipline, growth, repair, or [[Energy]] where the carrying relation remains compatible. It becomes incompatible where pressure is kept beyond capacity, beyond resolution band, or beyond the relation able to receive and integrate it.

## Carries

- [[Energy]]
- [[Balance]]','Retain Retain names pressure kept within a carrying relation. Retain is not the same as Hold. Hold is a first order resolution mode: a resolved condition remains supportable as the same condition. Retain is second order carrying regulation: pressure remains kept inside a carrying relation after it has become locally borne. Places Retain places pressure kept within a carrying relation. Holds Retain is held by Pressure, Carrying, Compatibility, and Hold. Pressure must be locally borne, carrying must remain available, and holding must remain compatible before pressure can be read as retained. Pairs Retain pairs with Release. Retain names pressure kept within a carrying relation; Release names strain leaving the bearing condition. Each is readable against the other. Traces Pressure Carrying Compatibility Hold Nests Retain nests inside carrying as ongoing keeping of pressure after it has become locally borne. Reads Retain becomes readable where pressure remains kept in a carrying relation without immediately discharging, transferring, or collapsing. Retained pressure can generate form, attention, memory, structure, discipline, growth, repair, or Energy where the carrying relation remains compatible. It becomes incompatible where pressure is kept beyond capacity, beyond resolution band, or beyond the relation able to receive and integrate it. Carries Energy Balance','Retain Retain names pressure kept within a carrying relation. Retain is not the same as Hold.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.hold","first.release","second.balance","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.energy","second.pressure"]','{"holds":["second.pressure","second.carrying","second.compatibility","first.hold"],"traces":["second.pressure","second.carrying","second.compatibility","first.hold"],"carries":["second.energy","second.balance"],"pairs":["first.release"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',200,'sha256:b9c22d7703fe06250505119d5f3f5e72fe33565a03c9b3f1aec43c8ce6adebe8','1970-01-01','2026-06-27');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.retrace-read','Retrace Read','retrace-read','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability Conditions/Retrace Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/retrace-read.html','# Retrace Read

Retrace Read names a produced read through which a trace can recover the dependency path. Where trace names the direct path through which the apparent becomes followable, retrace read names the act of following that path back through its prior conditions — not repetition, not going backwards in time, but recovering what must have held for the current condition to be available. Retrace read is how a read returns to its ground at second order.

## Places

Retrace Read places a produced read through which a trace can recover the dependency path.

## Holds

Retrace Read is held by [[Read]], [[Trace]], and [[Return]]. A dependency path must be available, and its carried relation must become readable again as the path is followed.

## Pairs

Retrace Read pairs with [[Recognition Read]]: Recognition Read reads what the dependency pattern looks like from the reading position; Retrace Read traces back through the dependency path itself. Each requires the other to be locatable — recognition without retrace stays at the surface; retrace without recognition has no pattern to return to.

## Traces

- [[Read]]
- [[Trace]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Return]]
- [[Traversal]]

## Nests

Retrace Read nests where a read can return through its dependency path to recover what made it available.

## Reads

Retrace Read becomes recognisable where a dependency path can be followed back through prior conditions to recover what made the current read available — where "how did we get here" has a traceable answer.
## Carries

- [[Nesting Read]]
- [[Higher Recognition]]
- [[Reality-Bearing Connection]]
- [[Illusion]]
- [[Higher Order Crossing]]
- [[Root Resilience]]','Retrace Read Retrace Read names a produced read through which a trace can recover the dependency path. Where trace names the direct path through which the apparent becomes followable, retrace read names the act of following that path back through its prior conditions — not repetition, not going backwards in time, but recovering what must have held for the current condition to be available. Retrace read is how a read returns to its ground at second order. Places Retrace Read places a produced read through which a trace can recover the dependency path. Holds Retrace Read is held by Read, Trace, and Return. A dependency path must be available, and its carried relation must become readable again as the path is followed. Pairs Retrace Read pairs with Recognition Read: Recognition Read reads what the dependency pattern looks like from the reading position; Retrace Read traces back through the dependency path itself. Each requires the other to be locatable — recognition without retrace stays at the surface; retrace without recognition has no pattern to return to. Traces Read Trace Participation Return Traversal Nests Retrace Read nests where a read can return through its dependency path to recover what made it available. Reads Retrace Read becomes recognisable where a dependency path can be followed back through prior conditions to recover what made the current read available — where "how did we get here" has a traceable answer. Carries Nesting Read Higher Recognition Reality Bearing Connection Illusion Higher Order Crossing Root Resilience','Retrace Read Retrace Read names a produced read through which a trace can recover the dependency path. Where trace names the direct path through which the apparent becomes followable, retrace read…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.read","first.trace","higher.higher-order-crossing","higher.higher-recognition","practice.reality-bearing-connection","practice.root-resilience","second.nesting-read","second.participation","second.recognition-read","second.return","second.traversal","third.illusion"]','{"holds":["first.read","first.trace","second.return"],"traces":["first.read","first.trace","second.participation","second.return","second.traversal"],"carries":["second.nesting-read","higher.higher-recognition","practice.reality-bearing-connection","third.illusion","higher.higher-order-crossing","practice.root-resilience"],"pairs":["second.recognition-read"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',249,'sha256:dc02f47d4fe79552b36bd952b89b974cd0591e661afd1b1e0fab36fe5f332e36','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.return','Return','return','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Return.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/return.html','# Return

Return names carried relation becoming readable again at a resolvable boundary. It does not claim that continuity ceased while unread, that a departure was required, or that the returning event is identical to an earlier event.

Return is not repetition. Repetition is the apparent occurrence of the same event again. Return requires a carried relation to remain traceable across the difference between entries. A return is not going back. It is re-entering a carrying system with new relation available.

Coupling is a common form of the relation carried through Return, but it is not required in every instance. Return is also distinct from restoring a broken coupling. If coupling ceased, its restoration establishes coupling again; Return does not name that act. Return applies where carried relation becomes readable again, whether the carrying was continuously visible or only becomes visible at the returning boundary.

## Places

Return places carried relation becoming readable again at a resolvable boundary.

## Holds

Return is held by [[Boundary]], [[Carrying]], and [[Readability]]. Relation must continue, a boundary must locate a distinguishable entry, and that boundary must fall within a resolution band able to read it.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required. [[Digress]] can precede Return where traversal departs from a held scope, but departure is not required for every return.

## Traces

- [[Boundary]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Return nests where carried relation enters a boundary resolvable enough for its continuity to become readable again.

## Reads

Return becomes recognisable where continuity becomes readable again at a boundary — not as the same event repeated, but as carried relation recognised through a new entry.

An orbit carries coupling continuously; a year is readable at a selected return condition. A groove may continue through sound and bodily participation; a beat or bar marks a return condition within it. These are Atlas reads of continuity, not claims that physical continuity is made by observation.

## Carries

- [[Cycle]]
- [[Frequency]]
- [[Face]]
- [[Retrace Read|Retrace]]
- [[Grief]]
- [[Rhythm]]
- [[Musical Rhythm]]','Return Return names carried relation becoming readable again at a resolvable boundary. It does not claim that continuity ceased while unread, that a departure was required, or that the returning event is identical to an earlier event. Return is not repetition. Repetition is the apparent occurrence of the same event again. Return requires a carried relation to remain traceable across the difference between entries. A return is not going back. It is re entering a carrying system with new relation available. Coupling is a common form of the relation carried through Return, but it is not required in every instance. Return is also distinct from restoring a broken coupling. If coupling ceased, its restoration establishes coupling again; Return does not name that act. Return applies where carried relation becomes readable again, whether the carrying was continuously visible or only becomes visible at the returning boundary. Places Return places carried relation becoming readable again at a resolvable boundary. Holds Return is held by Boundary, Carrying, and Readability. Relation must continue, a boundary must locate a distinguishable entry, and that boundary must fall within a resolution band able to read it. Pairs No lateral pair is required. Digress can precede Return where traversal departs from a held scope, but departure is not required for every return. Traces Boundary Carrying Readability Nests Return nests where carried relation enters a boundary resolvable enough for its continuity to become readable again. Reads Return becomes recognisable where continuity becomes readable again at a boundary — not as the same event repeated, but as carried relation recognised through a new entry. An orbit carries coupling continuously; a year is readable at a selected return condition. A groove may continue through sound and bodily participation; a beat or bar marks a return condition within it. These are Atlas reads of continuity, not claims that physical continuity is made by observation. Carries Cycle Frequency Face Retrace Read Grief Rhythm Musical Rhythm','Return Return names carried relation becoming readable again at a resolvable boundary. It does not claim that continuity ceased while unread, that a departure was required, or that the returning…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","second.carrying","second.cycle","second.digress","second.face","second.frequency","second.readability","second.retrace-read","second.rhythm","third.grief","third.musical-rhythm"]','{"holds":["first.boundary","second.carrying","second.readability"],"traces":["first.boundary","second.carrying","second.readability"],"carries":["second.cycle","second.frequency","second.face","second.retrace-read","third.grief","second.rhythm","third.musical-rhythm"],"pairs":["second.digress"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',322,'sha256:842f0d58f925b550828aa3eed4d54f000553c9ad12257e1ced08e15dfe25c183','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.rhythm','Rhythm','rhythm','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Participation Conditions/Rhythm.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/rhythm.html','# Rhythm

Rhythm names patterned recurrence carried through interval. Where frequency names how often recurrence occurs and period names interval per recurrence, rhythm names recurrence becoming readable as a carried pattern.

## Places

Rhythm places patterned recurrence carried through interval.

## Holds

Rhythm is held by [[Pattern]], [[Recurrence]], [[Interval]], and [[Return]]. Recurrence must form a pattern through intervals, and carried relation must become readable again at boundaries within that pattern.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Rhythm is a singular condition — pattern through recurrence and interval. The asymmetry is expressed in what rhythm carries: [[Tempo]] and [[Melody]].

## Traces

- [[Pattern]]
- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Interval]]
- [[Cycle]]
- [[Frequency]]
- [[Medium]]
- [[Period]]
- [[Return]]

## Nests

Rhythm nests where recurrence is carried as a pattern through intervals.

## Reads

Rhythm becomes recognisable where recurrence is not merely counted but carried as a readable pattern through intervals.

## Carries

- [[Tempo]]
- [[Musical Rhythm]]','Rhythm Rhythm names patterned recurrence carried through interval. Where frequency names how often recurrence occurs and period names interval per recurrence, rhythm names recurrence becoming readable as a carried pattern. Places Rhythm places patterned recurrence carried through interval. Holds Rhythm is held by Pattern, Recurrence, Interval, and Return. Recurrence must form a pattern through intervals, and carried relation must become readable again at boundaries within that pattern. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Rhythm is a singular condition — pattern through recurrence and interval. The asymmetry is expressed in what rhythm carries: Tempo and Melody. Traces Pattern Recurrence Interval Cycle Frequency Medium Period Return Nests Rhythm nests where recurrence is carried as a pattern through intervals. Reads Rhythm becomes recognisable where recurrence is not merely counted but carried as a readable pattern through intervals. Carries Tempo Musical Rhythm','Rhythm Rhythm names patterned recurrence carried through interval. Where frequency names how often recurrence occurs and period names interval per recurrence, rhythm names recurrence becoming…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.cycle","second.frequency","second.interval","second.medium","second.pattern","second.period","second.recurrence","second.return","second.tempo","third.melody","third.musical-rhythm"]','{"holds":["second.pattern","second.recurrence","second.interval","second.return"],"traces":["second.pattern","second.recurrence","second.interval","second.cycle","second.frequency","second.medium","second.period","second.return"],"carries":["second.tempo","third.musical-rhythm"],"pairs":["second.tempo","third.melody"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',136,'sha256:92b881cd1607282fb86a6d700631ed4a43714aa00a647adc3fda220671a15029','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.scale','Scale','scale','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Scale.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/scale.html','# Scale

Scale names readable extent along a dimension. Where [[Dimension]] names a readable axis of difference, scale names how far along that axis a condition extends within the current scope.

Scale does not guarantee that order survives a change of scale. A scale transition remains traceable only where the operational order can be retraced across the transition. Where the apparent continuity of scale hides a substituted order, scale has become a site of drift rather than a preserved read.

Order may recur across scale, but each recurrence resolves through a different band. Recurrence allows translation across scale; resolution difference prevents collapse into sameness.

## Places

Scale places readable extent along a dimension.

## Holds

Scale is held by [[Dimension]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Scale is the magnitude of difference within a dimension. Its asymmetry is expressed in what it carries: [[Pattern]] and [[Measure]].

## Traces

- [[Dimension]]

## Nests

Scale nests where dimension has readable extent within closure scope.

## Reads

Scale becomes recognisable where a dimension can be read as having extent: more or less along a readable axis.

Scale also becomes recognisable where an order is tested across transition: the question is not only whether something is larger, smaller, faster, slower, nearer, or wider, but whether the same order can still be retraced after the change in extent.

A scale may exceed a participant''s resolution band without ceasing to be effective. At that point the scale must be translated, measured, sampled, inferred, or nested through another carrier before it becomes readable.

## Carries

- [[Pattern]]
- [[Information]]
- [[Measure]]
- [[Relative]]
- [[Growth]]
- [[Decay]]
- [[Thing]]
- [[Timescale]]
- [[Member]]
- [[Extractive Acceleration]]','Scale Scale names readable extent along a dimension. Where Dimension names a readable axis of difference, scale names how far along that axis a condition extends within the current scope. Scale does not guarantee that order survives a change of scale. A scale transition remains traceable only where the operational order can be retraced across the transition. Where the apparent continuity of scale hides a substituted order, scale has become a site of drift rather than a preserved read. Order may recur across scale, but each recurrence resolves through a different band. Recurrence allows translation across scale; resolution difference prevents collapse into sameness. Places Scale places readable extent along a dimension. Holds Scale is held by Dimension. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Scale is the magnitude of difference within a dimension. Its asymmetry is expressed in what it carries: Pattern and Measure. Traces Dimension Nests Scale nests where dimension has readable extent within closure scope. Reads Scale becomes recognisable where a dimension can be read as having extent: more or less along a readable axis. Scale also becomes recognisable where an order is tested across transition: the question is not only whether something is larger, smaller, faster, slower, nearer, or wider, but whether the same order can still be retraced after the change in extent. A scale may exceed a participant''s resolution band without ceasing to be effective. At that point the scale must be translated, measured, sampled, inferred, or nested through another carrier before it becomes readable. Carries Pattern Information Measure Relative Growth Decay Thing Timescale Member Extractive Acceleration','Scale Scale names readable extent along a dimension. Where Dimension names a readable axis of difference, scale names how far along that axis a condition extends within the current scope.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.decay","second.dimension","second.growth","second.information","second.measure","second.member","second.pattern","second.relative","second.thing","third.extractive-acceleration","third.timescale"]','{"holds":["second.dimension"],"traces":["second.dimension"],"carries":["second.pattern","second.information","second.measure","second.relative","second.growth","second.decay","second.thing","third.timescale","second.member","third.extractive-acceleration"],"pairs":["second.pattern","second.measure"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',259,'sha256:860bee827d790caace228e8b08bbdda0bbfbb820c622811eb2b21cfec3296a55','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.scope','Scope','scope','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Closure Conditions/Scope.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/scope.html','# Scope

Scope names the bounded extent within which a read can hold. Where [[Extent]] names the reached range of carrying, and closure names a read becoming sufficiently bounded for evaluation, scope names that extent as a readable condition: the range within which a read participates without extending beyond what holds at the current boundary. Scope is the extent of validity, not the read itself.

## Places

Scope places the bounded extent within which a read can hold.

## Holds

Scope is held by [[Closure]] and [[Extent]]. Closure must bound a read, and extent must locate the reached range, before scope can name where the read holds.

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Scope is a singular condition — the range held within a closure. The asymmetry is expressed in what scope carries: [[Closure Scope]].

## Traces

- [[Closure]]
- [[Extent]]

## Nests

Scope nests as the bounded extent within which carrying, reading, or evaluation can hold.

## Reads

Scope becomes recognisable where a condition is bounded enough to say where a read holds, fails, or changes — where something can be evaluated as within or beyond the current extent.
## Carries

- [[Closure Scope]]','Scope Scope names the bounded extent within which a read can hold. Where Extent names the reached range of carrying, and closure names a read becoming sufficiently bounded for evaluation, scope names that extent as a readable condition: the range within which a read participates without extending beyond what holds at the current boundary. Scope is the extent of validity, not the read itself. Places Scope places the bounded extent within which a read can hold. Holds Scope is held by Closure and Extent. Closure must bound a read, and extent must locate the reached range, before scope can name where the read holds. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Scope is a singular condition — the range held within a closure. The asymmetry is expressed in what scope carries: Closure Scope. Traces Closure Extent Nests Scope nests as the bounded extent within which carrying, reading, or evaluation can hold. Reads Scope becomes recognisable where a condition is bounded enough to say where a read holds, fails, or changes — where something can be evaluated as within or beyond the current extent. Carries Closure Scope','Scope Scope names the bounded extent within which a read can hold. Where Extent names the reached range of carrying, and closure names a read becoming sufficiently bounded for evaluation, scope…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.closure","second.closure-scope","second.extent"]','{"holds":["second.closure","second.extent"],"traces":["second.closure","second.extent"],"carries":["second.closure-scope"],"pairs":["second.closure-scope"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',183,'sha256:21e436087721dbf292df3b94b5d584fbc2a0c3f0eee9d23b31e52f84bc7eb01a','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.second-order-crossing','Threshold (Second → Third)','threshold-second-third','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Second Order Crossing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/threshold-second-third.html','# Threshold (Second → Third)

This threshold names the crossing from Second Order into Third Order.

## Places

Threshold (Second → Third) places the crossing where carrying through recurring participation begins to organise into a field.

## Holds

Threshold (Second → Third) is held by [[Second Order]], [[Participation]], and [[Recurrence]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — marks the transition into [[Field of Participation]] and [[Third Order]]

## Traces

- [[Second Order]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Recurrence]]

## Nests

Threshold (Second → Third) nests between orders. It marks a specific passage, not a general threshold.

## Reads

Threshold (Second → Third) becomes recognisable where carrying through participation recurs enough to organise into a field of participation.

**What Second Order makes available.**

Carrying enacts held and placeable forward availability. Participation names carrying actively taking part in a scope through presence and bearing relation.

**The crossing.**

Where participation recurs, it begins to organise into recognisable fields. The first third-order condition is Field of Participation — recurring organisation arising through participation.

## Carries

- [[Field of Participation]]
