irs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',163,'sha256:3ecf658d8d7006b9ff66b3d9f127243513031318dda22d1e92d6986ec33bf4cb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.second-order-disorder-effects','Second-Order Disorder Effects','second-order-disorder-effects','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Second-Order Disorder Effects.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/second-order-disorder-effects.html','# Second-Order Disorder Effects

Second-Order Disorder Effects names produced disorder in second-order reads where availability, recognition, carrying, or closure is treated as present before it can bear.

## Places

Second-Order Disorder Effects places produced disorder in second-order reads where availability, recognition, carrying, or closure is treated as present before it can bear.

## Holds

Second-Order Disorder Effects is held by [[Dependency Disorder]], [[Disorder]], [[Incoherence]], [[Delayed Availability]], and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Second-Order Disorder Effects is a singular condition — the consequences of disorder carried through incoherence. The asymmetry is expressed in what it carries: [[Hope]].

## Traces

- [[Dependency Disorder]]
- [[Disorder]]
- [[Incoherence]]
- [[Delayed Availability]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Second-Order Disorder Effects nests where availability, recognition, carrying, or closure is treated as present before it can bear.

## Reads

Second-Order Disorder Effects becomes recognisable where a produced read proceeds as though a condition is available, recognised, or stable while the dependency path cannot yet carry that claim.

## Carries

