INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.strategy','Strategy','strategy','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Strategy.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/strategy.html','# Strategy

Strategy names a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution. Where process names a carried sequence and structure names form held as a carrying arrangement, strategy names the condition through which a carried sequence is oriented toward a particular resolution within the current scope. Strategy does not name plan, intention, or outcome by itself; it names the orientation of a carried sequence toward a readable determination.

## Places

Strategy places a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution.

## Holds

Strategy is held by [[Structure]] and [[Process]].

## Pairs

Strategy pairs with [[Decision]]. Strategy orients a carried sequence toward resolution; Decision names the point where one path is taken.

## Traces

- [[Structure]]
- [[Process]]
- [[Function]]

## Nests

Strategy nests where a carried sequence is oriented toward a readable resolution.

## Reads

Strategy becomes recognisable where a carried sequence can be read as oriented — where participation is not merely proceeding but oriented toward a particular resolution.

## Carries

- [[Decision]]','Strategy Strategy names a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution. Where process names a carried sequence and structure names form held as a carrying arrangement, strategy names the condition through which a carried sequence is oriented toward a particular resolution within the current scope. Strategy does not name plan, intention, or outcome by itself; it names the orientation of a carried sequence toward a readable determination. Places Strategy places a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution. Holds Strategy is held by Structure and Process. Pairs Strategy pairs with Decision. Strategy orients a carried sequence toward resolution; Decision names the point where one path is taken. Traces Structure Process Function Nests Strategy nests where a carried sequence is oriented toward a readable resolution. Reads Strategy becomes recognisable where a carried sequence can be read as oriented — where participation is not merely proceeding but oriented toward a particular resolution. Carries Decision','Strategy Strategy names a carried sequence oriented toward a resolution. Where process names a carried sequence and structure names form held as a carrying arrangement, strategy names the…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.decision","second.function","second.process","second.structure"]','{"holds":["second.structure","second.process"],"traces":["second.structure","second.process","second.function"],"carries":["second.decision"],"pairs":["second.decision"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',150,'sha256:7017dc5b7e2f054dfd228d4475d06eabc562254f46767b33bcb451b98a7a7343','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.structural-gathering','Structural Gathering','structural-gathering','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Structural Gathering.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/structural-gathering.html','# Structural Gathering

Structural gathering names multiple participating relations held as one readable arrangement. Where nested relation names relation participating within relation, structural gathering names the condition through which multiple such relations can be read together — held as one arrangement rather than as separate nested conditions. Structural gathering does not name aggregation or collection; it names the readable condition of multiple relations holding together as an arrangement.

## Places

Structural Gathering places multiple participating relations held as one readable arrangement.

## Holds

Structural Gathering is held by [[Nested Relation]] and [[Form]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Structural Gathering is a singular condition — nested relation consolidated into form. The asymmetry is expressed in what structural gathering carries: [[Structure]] and [[Fabric]].

## Traces

- [[Nested Relation]]
- [[Form]]

## Nests

Structural Gathering nests where multiple nested relations can be read as one arrangement.

## Reads

Structural gathering becomes recognisable where multiple participating relations can be read together as one arrangement — where what is nested can be held as a readable whole rather than traced individually.

## Carries

- [[Structure]]
- [[Fabric]]','Structural Gathering Structural gathering names multiple participating relations held as one readable arrangement. Where nested relation names relation participating within relation, structural gathering names the condition through which multiple such relations can be read together — held as one arrangement rather than as separate nested conditions. Structural gathering does not name aggregation or collection; it names the readable condition of multiple relations holding together as an arrangement. Places Structural Gathering places multiple participating relations held as one readable arrangement. Holds Structural Gathering is held by Nested Relation and Form. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Structural Gathering is a singular condition — nested relation consolidated into form. The asymmetry is expressed in what structural gathering carries: Structure and Fabric. Traces Nested Relation Form Nests Structural Gathering nests where multiple nested relations can be read as one arrangement. Reads Structural gathering becomes recognisable where multiple participating relations can be read together as one arrangement — where what is nested can be held as a readable whole rather than traced individually. Carries Structure Fabric','Structural Gathering Structural gathering names multiple participating relations held as one readable arrangement. Where nested relation names relation participating within relation, structural…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["higher.fabric","second.form","second.nested-relation","second.structure"]','{"holds":["second.nested-relation","second.form"],"traces":["second.nested-relation","second.form"],"carries":["second.structure","higher.fabric"],"pairs":["second.structure","higher.fabric"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text