',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.invariant","second.carrying","second.coupling"]','{"holds":["second.carrying"],"traces":["second.carrying","ground.invariant"],"carries":["second.coupling"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',256,'sha256:5d4a61a0caf22ad5896e7c14ecd33004288de91f7a3fea7cab8680275ed364c7','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.unit','Unit','unit','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Produced Distinctions/Unit.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/unit.html','# Unit

Unit names a bounded repeatable measure. A unit is not the thing measured; it is the stable measure-condition through which comparison can remain readable across instances.

## Places

Unit places a bounded repeatable measure.

## Holds

Unit is held by [[Measure]] and [[Recurrence]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Unit is a singular condition — the standard of measure against recurrence. The asymmetry is expressed in what unit carries: [[Count]] and [[Hertz]].

## Traces

- [[Measure]]
- [[Recurrence]]

## Nests

Unit nests where measure remains repeatable across instances without changing the comparison condition.

## Reads

Unit becomes recognisable where a measure can be repeated across instances without changing the comparison condition.

## Carries

- [[Count]]
- [[Hertz]]','Unit Unit names a bounded repeatable measure. A unit is not the thing measured; it is the stable measure condition through which comparison can remain readable across instances. Places Unit places a bounded repeatable measure. Holds Unit is held by Measure and Recurrence. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Unit is a singular condition — the standard of measure against recurrence. The asymmetry is expressed in what unit carries: Count and Hertz. Traces Measure Recurrence Nests Unit nests where measure remains repeatable across instances without changing the comparison condition. Reads Unit becomes recognisable where a measure can be repeated across instances without changing the comparison condition. Carries Count Hertz','Unit Unit names a bounded repeatable measure. A unit is not the thing measured; it is the stable measure condition through which comparison can remain readable across instances.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.count","second.hertz","second.measure","second.recurrence"]','{"holds":["second.measure","second.recurrence"],"traces":["second.measure","second.recurrence"],"carries":["second.count","second.hertz"],"pairs":["second.count","second.hertz"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',107,'sha256:5ea0c43a600d279d0f2efb34df8d19acd551960688a4adfa01003a2fdac8a761','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.velocity','Velocity','velocity','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Velocity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/velocity.html','# Velocity

Velocity names speed with direction through traversal. Where speed names rate of traversal, velocity names that rate as oriented along a readable direction.

## Places

Velocity places speed with direction through traversal.

## Holds

Velocity is held by [[Speed]], [[Orientation]], and [[Traversal]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Velocity is a singular condition — speed with orientation. The asymmetry is expressed in what velocity carries: [[Acceleration]].

## Traces

- [[Speed]]
- [[Orientation]]
- [[Traversal]]

## Nests

Velocity nests inside traversal as speed with direction.

## Reads

Velocity becomes recognisable where traversal can be read as both how fast it proceeds and which way it bears.

## Carries

- [[Acceleration]]','Velocity Velocity names speed with direction through traversal. Where speed names rate of traversal, velocity names that rate as oriented along a readable direction. Places Velocity places speed with direction through traversal. Holds Velocity is held by Speed, Orientation, and Traversal. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Velocity is a singular condition — speed with orientation. The asymmetry is expressed in what velocity carries: Acceleration. Traces Speed Orientation Traversal Nests Velocity nests inside traversal as speed with direction. Reads Velocity becomes recognisable where traversal can be read as both how fast it proceeds and which way it bears. Carries Acceleration','Velocity Velocity names speed with direction through traversal. Where speed names rate of traversal, velocity names that rate as oriented along a readable direction.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.orientation","second.acceleration","second.speed","second.traversal"]','{"holds":["second.speed","first.orientation","second.traversal"],"traces":["second.speed","first.orientation","second.traversal"],"carries":["second.acceleration"],"pairs":["second.acceleration"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',98,'sha256:0cbe2a5fb23e973e2629377f0bca04af814764d1e1df615e46994cd8fcd1c801','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.visibility','Visibility','visibility','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Readability Conditions/Visibility.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/visibility.html','# Visibility

Visibility names the condition through which presented distinction becomes readable. Where visible carries the relational role of presented distinction, visibility names the produced read: what is presented can be taken up into evaluation. Presence may be visible, but visibility names presence held enough to be read within the current scope.

## Places

Visibility places the condition through which presented distinction becomes readable.

## Holds

Visibility is held by [[Visible]] and [[Readability]].

## Pairs

Visibility pairs with [[Observation]]. Visibility makes presentation readable; Observation takes that readability into evaluation.

## Traces

- [[Visible]]
- [[Readability]]
- [[Allow]]

## Nests

Visibility nests where presented distinction can be taken up into evaluation.

## Reads

Visibility becomes recognisable where presented distinction can be taken up into evaluation, so what is there can be read rather than only present.

## Carries

- [[Observation]]
- [[Glamour]]
- [[Illusion]]','Visibility Visibility names the condition through which presented distinction becomes readable. Where visible carries the relational role of presented distinction, visibility names the produced read: what is presented can be taken up into evaluation. Presence may be visible, but visibility names presence held enough to be read within the current scope. Places Visibility places the condition through which presented distinction becomes readable. Holds Visibility is held by Visible and Readability. Pairs Visibility pairs with Observation. Visibility makes presentation readable; Observation takes that readability into evaluation. Traces Visible Readability Allow Nests Visibility nests where presented distinction can be taken up into evaluation. Reads Visibility becomes recognisable where presented distinction can be taken up into evaluation, so what is there can be read rather than only present. Carries Observation Glamour Illusion','Visibility Visibility names the condition through which presented distinction becomes readable. Where visible carries the relational role of presented distinction, visibility names the produced…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.allow","first.visible","second.observation","second.readability","third.glamour","third.illusion"]','{"holds":["first.visible","second.readability"],"traces":["first.visible","second.readability","first.allow"],"carries":["second.observation","third.glamour","third.illusion"],"pairs":["second.observation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',129,'sha256:94bc20794b04459f54fe0a2c54f0ec678f12fd2ab202ca16025d2bd156e9b650','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.wear','Wear','wear','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Carrying Conditions/Wear.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/wear.html','# Wear

Wear names change left by recurring friction. Decay can involve wear, but wear first names reduction or alteration made readable where contact and resistance continue across recurrence.

## Places

Wear places change left by recurring friction.

## Holds

Wear is held by [[Friction]], [[Recurrence]], and [[Decay]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Wear is a singular condition — friction accumulated through [[Recurrence]] into [[Decay]]. There is no lateral contrast required at this level.

## Traces

- [[Friction]]
- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Decay]]

## Nests

Wear nests inside recurrence, friction, and decay as change left by repeated resistance.

## Reads

Wear becomes recognisable where repeated friction changes the condition that bears it.

## Carries','Wear Wear names change left by recurring friction. Decay can involve wear, but wear first names reduction or alteration made readable where contact and resistance continue across recurrence. Places Wear places change left by recurring friction. Holds Wear is held by Friction, Recurrence, and Decay. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Wear is a singular condition — friction accumulated through Recurrence into Decay. There is no lateral contrast required at this level. Traces Friction Recurrence Decay Nests Wear nests inside recurrence, friction, and decay as change left by repeated resistance. Reads Wear becomes recognisable where repeated friction changes the condition that bears it. Carries','Wear Wear names change left by recurring friction. Decay can involve wear, but wear first names reduction or alteration made readable where contact and resistance continue across recurrence.','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.decay","second.friction","second.recurrence"]','{"holds":["second.friction","second.recurrence","second.decay"],"traces":["second.friction","second.recurrence","second.decay"],"carries":[],"pairs":["second.recurrence","second.decay"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',102,'sha256:aab825e99c890be38a4ef374f8a6aa74e5003243a4e7928a7798c14670f168f0','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.within','Within','within','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/Within.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/within.html','# Within

Within names relation held inside a cleared boundary. Where in carries interior placement and clearance opens the relational space that allows alongside-ness, within names their compound: relation that is both inside and available within a bounded condition. Enclosure can show within, but within names interior placement under available clearance.

## Places

Within places relation held inside a cleared boundary.

## Holds

Within is held by [[In]], [[Clearance]], and [[Boundary]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward. Within is a singular condition — the condition of being inside a clearance and boundary. The asymmetry is expressed in what within carries: [[Nested Relation]].

## Traces

- [[In]]
- [[Clearance]]
- [[Boundary]]

## Nests

Within nests as the compound of interior placement and available clearance: relation held inside a bounded relational space.

## Reads

Within becomes recognisable where relation can be read as inside and alongside a bounded condition — where something participates from within rather than from outside or alongside only.

## Carries

- [[Nested Relation]]','Within Within names relation held inside a cleared boundary. Where in carries interior placement and clearance opens the relational space that allows alongside ness, within names their compound: relation that is both inside and available within a bounded condition. Enclosure can show within, but within names interior placement under available clearance. Places Within places relation held inside a cleared boundary. Holds Within is held by In, Clearance, and Boundary. Pairs Asymmetry carries downward. Within is a singular condition — the condition of being inside a clearance and boundary. The asymmetry is expressed in what within carries: Nested Relation. Traces In Clearance Boundary Nests Within nests as the compound of interior placement and available clearance: relation held inside a bounded relational space. Reads Within becomes recognisable where relation can be read as inside and alongside a bounded condition — where something participates from within rather than from outside or alongside only. Carries Nested Relation','Within Within names relation held inside a cleared boundary. Where in carries interior placement and clearance opens the relational space that allows alongside ness, within names their compound:…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","first.clearance","first.in","second.nested-relation"]','{"holds":["first.in","first.clearance","first.boundary"],"traces":["first.in","first.clearance","first.boundary"],"carries":["second.nested-relation"],"pairs":["second.nested-relation"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',153,'sha256:d87918ada772742c5dbe76e359ebef912543475785261020d7103d4158c64573','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('second.world','World','world','Reality_Mechanics/2_Second/Presence Conditions/World.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/world.html','# World

World names reality held as a participating scope. Where reality names coupled relation readable as real, world names that reality sustained as the scope within which participation occurs: the readable condition within which encounter, constraint, and relation continue to take place. Contents can show a world, but world names the participating scope itself.

## Places

World places reality held as a participating scope.

## Holds

World is held by [[Reality]] and [[Participation]].

## Pairs

World is vertical. It names reality held as a participating scope, and carries this forward into [[Knowledge]]. World holds [[Reality]] and [[Participation]] — it is downstream of reality becoming participatory, not a lateral co-present condition alongside another second-order term.

## Traces

- [[Reality]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Exist]]

## Nests

World nests where reality is held as the participating scope of encounter and continuation.

## Reads

World becomes recognisable where reality is read as the participating scope of encounter — where what is real is not just encounterable but forms the condition within which participation continues.

## Carries

- [[Knowledge]]','World World names reality held as a participating scope. Where reality names coupled relation readable as real, world names that reality sustained as the scope within which participation occurs: the readable condition within which encounter, constraint, and relation continue to take place. Contents can show a world, but world names the participating scope itself. Places World places reality held as a participating scope. Holds World is held by Reality and Participation. Pairs World is vertical. It names reality held as a participating scope, and carries this forward into Knowledge. World holds Reality and Participation — it is downstream of reality becoming participatory, not a lateral co present condition alongside another second order term. Traces Reality Participation Exist Nests World nests where reality is held as the participating scope of encounter and continuation. Reads World becomes recognisable where reality is read as the participating scope of encounter — where what is real is not just encounterable but forms the condition within which participation continues. Carries Knowledge','World World names reality held as a participating scope. Where reality names coupled relation readable as real, world names that reality sustained as the scope within which participation occurs:…','stable','rooted',0,'second','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["second.exist","second.participation","second.reality","third.knowledge"]','{"holds":["second.reality","second.participation"],"traces":["second.reality","second.participation","second.exist"],"carries":["third.knowledge"],"pairs":["third.knowledge"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',165,'sha256:88a2ae2a6dfcd07c97007627d6722db5c1ab70082f258cfb9e096024bab9fc5f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.accommodation','Accommodation','accommodation','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Accommodation.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/accommodation.html','# Accommodation

Accommodation is compatible bearing of variability through resolution.

## Places

Accommodation places compatible bearing of variability through resolution — the condition through which difference remains borne without requiring its elimination.

## Holds

Accommodation is held by [[Bounded Asymmetry]], [[Bearing]], and [[Resolution]]. Variability must be localised and held before it can be compatibly borne through resolution.

## Pairs

Accommodation pairs with [[Constrained Resolution]]. Accommodation names how bounded variability is borne through resolution; Constrained Resolution names the general condition of resolution within constraint that Accommodation embodies.

## Traces

- [[Bounded Asymmetry]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Resolution]]

- [[Constrained Resolution]]
## Nests

Accommodation nests within Relational Participation as a bearing-relations read on how variability remains compatibly borne through resolution.

## Reads

Accommodation becomes readable where variability remains compatibly borne through resolution.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bounded Asymmetry]] gives variability a readable condition and [[Bearing]] holds it.

Second: [[Compatibility]] and [[Resolution]] make the variability supportable within continued relation.

Third: [[Accommodation]] places that structural read inside bearing relations.

## Carries

