],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',166,'sha256:262a0862c9da9a9294cff5765504e0cc7b51386d882c8658c55d5970b27efcc2','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.ai-atlas-grounding','AI Atlas Grounding','ai-atlas-grounding','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/AI/AI Atlas Grounding.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/ai-atlas-grounding.html','# AI Atlas Grounding

AI Atlas Grounding names the use of current Atlas structure to preserve compatible proceeding and retraceable uptake during AI interaction.

## Places

AI Atlas Grounding places the grounding practice through which current Atlas structure is used to preserve compatible proceeding and retraceable uptake during AI interaction.

## Holds

AI Atlas Grounding is held by [[AI]], [[AI Coupling]], and [[Retrace Practice]] — it requires maintained coupling and a retrace-capable practice to preserve compatible proceeding.

## Pairs

AI Atlas Grounding pairs with [[AI Availability]]. AI Atlas Grounding names the practice that keeps AI coupling retraceable; AI Availability names what becomes usable within that coupling. Each is a distinct condition AI Coupling must maintain: retrace-ability and usability.

## Traces

- [[AI]]
- [[AI Coupling]]
- [[Retrace Practice]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

AI Atlas Grounding nests within the AI domain as the grounding practice that makes Atlas-assisted interaction retraceable rather than fluent substitution.

## Reads

AI Atlas Grounding becomes readable where AI coupling remains compatible with source dependency order at the relevant closure scope, so generated help can be used without replacing retrace.

## Carries

