s":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',192,'sha256:b9857e4e3cc894fa1b5ecf786ad7396fbcac4ab351a8794da89e05a171479a93','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.applied-read','Applied Read','applied-read','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Path Reads/Applied Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/applied-read.html','# Applied Read

Applied Read names local use of a path read in a specific case.

An applied read tests whether a field or domain translation still holds when it becomes local.

## Places

Applied Read places local use of a path read in a specific case.

It places the check point after a structural term has crossed a [[Translation Boundary]] and become terminal to field or domain language.

## Holds

Applied Read is held by [[Path Reads]] and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Path Reads]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Domain]]
- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Organised Domain]]
- [[Terminal]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Applied Read nests where a path read becomes usable in a bounded case without becoming the case itself.

It nests below branch translation: the local case tests whether the terminal domain expression still answers to the structural trace.

## Reads

Applied Read becomes recognisable where a path read can be tested within a specific local condition.

It becomes especially useful where a domain term can be traced back to the Atlas term it translates, then checked against the local case.
## Carries

- [[Diagnosis]]
- [[Control After Harm]]
- [[Control Drift]]
- [[Grief]]
- [[Harmonic Drift]]
- [[Improvisation]]
- [[Extractive Acceleration]]
- [[Space-Based Solar Power]]','Applied Read Applied Read names local use of a path read in a specific case. An applied read tests whether a field or domain translation still holds when it becomes local. Places Applied Read places local use of a path read in a specific case. It places the check point after a structural term has crossed a Translation Boundary and become terminal to field or domain language. Holds Applied Read is held by Path Reads and Closure Scope. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Path Reads Closure Scope Domain Field of Participation Organised Domain Terminal Translation Boundary Nests Applied Read nests where a path read becomes usable in a bounded case without becoming the case itself. It nests below branch translation: the local case tests whether the terminal domain expression still answers to the structural trace. Reads Applied Read becomes recognisable where a path read can be tested within a specific local condition. It becomes especially useful where a domain term can be traced back to the Atlas term it translates, then checked against the local case. Carries Diagnosis Control After Harm Control Drift Grief Harmonic Drift Improvisation Extractive Acceleration Space Based Solar Power','Applied Read Applied Read names local use of a path read in a specific case. An applied read tests whether a field or domain translation still holds when it becomes local.','stable','rooted',0,'third','class','path-reads','[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.terminal","third.control-after-harm","third.control-drift","third.diagnosis","third.domain","third.extractive-acceleration","third.field-of-participation","third.grief","third.harmonic-drift","third.improvisation","third.organised-domain","third.path-reads","third.space-based-solar-power","third.translation-boundary"]','{"holds":["third.path-reads","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.path-reads","second.closur