Architectural documentation names representational carrying for built resolution.

## Places

Architectural Documentation places representational carrying for built resolution.

## Holds

Architectural Documentation is held by [[Architecture]], [[Medium]].

## Pairs

Architectural Documentation pairs with [[Architectural Visibility]]. Architectural Documentation carries the structural condition through medium; Architectural Visibility names the readability condition that documentation must achieve.

## Traces

- [[Architecture]]
- [[Medium]]

## Nests

Architectural Documentation nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace.

## Reads

Architectural Documentation becomes readable where built conditions are carried through a medium so use, repair, construction, or evaluation can remain retraceable.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] and [[Bearing]] must hold enough for a built condition to be carried.

Second: [[Medium]] and [[Readability]] make that condition representable across readers and execution.

Third: [[Architectural Documentation]] places that carrying inside the [[Place Field]] as an architectural path read.

## Carries

