INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.bearing-relations','Bearing Relations','bearing-relations','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Bearing Relations.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/bearing-relations.html','# Bearing Relations

Bearing relations name the third-order relation family where [[Bearing Relation]] is read through downstream carrying relations.

## Places

Bearing Relations places the subdomain of relational-participation reads where coupling, bearing, and carrying become readable as held relational conditions.

## Holds

Bearing Relations is held by [[Relational Participation Field]], [[Bearing Relation]], and [[Coupling]]. Bearing must be traceable across coupling before relational conditions can be named as a subdomain.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Relational Participation Field]]
- [[Bearing Relation]]
- [[Coupling]]

## Nests

Bearing Relations nests within Relational Participation Field as the branch of notes where bearing becomes readable as carried relational condition.

## Reads

Bearing relations become readable where downstream terms evaluate how bearing relation is carried, constrained, repaired, maintained, or reciprocally held.

## Carries

Nothing at class grain. The nested reads — recorded under Nests — each trace their own structural ground.','Bearing Relations Bearing relations name the third order relation family where Bearing Relation is read through downstream carrying relations. Places Bearing Relations places the subdomain of relational participation reads where coupling, bearing, and carrying become readable as held relational conditions. Holds Bearing Relations is held by Relational Participation Field, Bearing Relation, and Coupling. Bearing must be traceable across coupling before relational conditions can be named as a subdomain. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Relational Participation Field Bearing Relation Coupling Nests Bearing Relations nests within Relational Participation Field as the branch of notes where bearing becomes readable as carried relational condition. Reads Bearing relations become readable where downstream terms evaluate how bearing relation is carried, constrained, repaired, maintained, or reciprocally held. Carries Nothing at class grain. The nested reads — recorded under Nests — each trace their own structural ground.','Bearing Relations Bearing relations name the third order relation family where Bearing Relation is read through downstream carrying relations. Places Bearing Relations places the subdomain of…','stable','rooted',0,'third','class','relational-participation','[]','[]','["second.bearing-relation","second.coupling","third.relational-participation-field"]','{"holds":["third.relational-participation-field","second.bearing-relation","second.coupling"],"traces":["third.relational-participation-field","second.bearing-relation","second.coupling"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',155,'sha256:eacaedf9b807a66bf5b9260929a5f37a032717c74ab0d08b373bbec73c5d6cb6','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.behaviour','Behaviour','behaviour','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Behaviour.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/behaviour.html','# Behaviour

Behaviour names carrying becoming action at a closure scope.

Feeling, emotion, and thought are reads. Behaviour is where a read begins to change what relation can carry.

## Places

Behaviour places carrying through relation at a closure scope — what is actually done through a control or participation condition, rather than what is intended.

## Holds

Behaviour is held by [[Carrying]], [[Control]], and [[Closure Scope]]. A carrying condition must be present and closure scope must bound the read before what is done becomes readable as behaviour.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Carrying]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Behaviour nests within Relational Participation as the closure-scope read of what carrying produces through control or participation.

## Reads

Behaviour becomes readable where carrying has entered action and can be evaluated by whether it preserves or damages compatible relation at the relevant closure scope.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Availability]] and [[Bearing]] make action carryable.

Second: [[Participation]], [[Compatibility]], [[Control]], and [[Closure Scope]] make action evaluable.

Third: [[Behaviour]] places carrying-into-action inside [[Relational Participation Field]] with bridge pressure from body, mind, and society.

Higher-Order Edge:

Behaviour remains third-order where action is readable at a closure scope.

It crosses into higher order where [[Consciousness]] makes behaviour available to the participant as its own action path and [[Self-Regulation]] changes future carrying.

Movement:

```text
read becomes action-pressure
-> action is selected, inhibited, or released
-> behaviour changes what relation can carry
-> compatibility is tested at closure scope
```

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Behaviour Behaviour names carrying becoming action at a closure scope. Feeling, emotion, and thought are reads. Behaviour is where a read begins to change what relation can carry. Places Behaviour places carrying through relation at a closure scope — what is actually done through a control or participation condition, rather than what is intended. Holds Behaviour is held by Carrying, Control, and Closure Scope. A carrying condition must be present and closure scope must bound the read before what is done becomes readable as behaviour. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Carrying Control Closure Scope Nests Behaviour nests within Relational Participation as the closure scope read of what carrying produces through control or participation. Reads Behaviour becomes readable where carrying has entered action and can be evaluated by whether it preserves or damages compatible relation at the relevant closure scope. The dependency movement is: First: Availability and Bearing make action carryable. Second: Participation, Compatibility, Control, and Closure Scope make action evaluable. Third: Behaviour places carrying into action inside Relational Participation Field with bridge pressure from body, mind, and society. Higher Order Edge: Behaviour remains third order where action is readable at a closure scope. It crosses into higher order where Consciousness makes behaviour available to the participant as its own action path and Self Regulation changes future carrying. Movement: Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Behaviour Behaviour names carrying becoming action at a closure scope. Feeling, emotion, and thought are reads.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.closure-scope","third.control"]','{"holds":["second.carrying","third.control","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["second.carrying","third.control","second.closure-scope"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',245,'sha256:274561be6594fdc430196b3b9f8e99a78a59f02b50bfa7988cb253cb1b363139','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.belong','Belong','belong','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Place Field/Belong.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/belong.html','# Belong

Belong names being placed within a field where participation fits and can remain compatibly carried.

This note places being inside the place/domain layer as fitted participation.

## Places

Belonging places the condition through which a participant is carried within a field where participation fits — the compatibility between what a participant carries and what the field can sustain.

## Holds

Belonging is held by [[Place Field]], [[Being]], [[Participation]], [[Compatibility]], [[World]], and [[Placed Participation]]. Participation must be present and compatibility must hold between the participant and the field before the carried fit can be named as belonging.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Place Field]]
- [[Being]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[World]]
- [[Placed Participation]]

## Nests

Belonging nests within the Place Field as the compatibility condition through which a participant is carried within a fitting field.

## Reads

Belong becomes readable where carried presence fits the field it participates in without bypassing boundary, compatibility, or dependency order.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] and [[Availability]] locate where participation can be carried.

Second: [[Being]], [[Participation]], [[Compatibility]], and [[World]] make fitted participation evaluable.

Third: [[Belong]] places that structural read inside the [[Place Field]].

Distinction:

Belong is not ownership.

Belonging is being carried in a field where participation fits.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Belong Belong names being placed within a field where participation fits and can remain compatibly carried. This note places being inside the place/domain layer as fitted participation. Places Belonging places the condition through which a participant is carried within a field where participation fits — the compatibility between what a participant carries and what the field can sustain. Holds Belonging is held by Place Field, Being, Participation, Compatibility, World, and Placed Participation. Participation must be present and compatibility must hold between the participant and the field before the carried fit can be named as belonging. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Place Field Being Participation Compatibility World Placed Participation Nests Belonging nests within the Place Field as the compatibility condition through which a participant is carried within a fitting field. Reads Belong becomes readable where carried presence fits the field it participates in without bypassing boundary, compatibility, or dependency order. The dependency movement is: First: Boundary and Availability locate where participation can be carried. Second: Being, Participation, Compatibility, and World make fitted participation evaluable. Third: Belong places that structural read inside the Place Field. Distinction: Belong is not ownership. Belonging is being carried in a field where participation fits. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Belong Belong names being placed within a field where participation fits and can remain compatibly carried. This note places being inside the place/domain layer as fitted participation.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','place','[]','[]','["second.being","second.compatibility","second.participation","second.world","third.place-field","third.placed-participation"]','{"holds":["third.place-field","second.being","second.participation","second.compatibility","second.world","third.placed-participation"],"traces":["third.place-field","second.being","second.participation","second.compatibility","second.world","third.placed-participation"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',225,'sha256:bd7889e07d29c8cdd6eb36d43ceb8a72e99ccf33922ee1e5754b600bfeb2d925','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.betrayal','Betrayal','betrayal','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Betrayal.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/betrayal.html','# Betrayal

Betrayal names trust damaged through violation of a relationship''s coupled boundary or bearing relation. It is harm to a relationship where trust had made continued bearing available.

## Places

Betrayal places harm to a relationship where trust had made continued bearing available — damage to a coupled boundary through violation of trusted bearing.

## Holds

Betrayal is held by [[Trust]], [[Violation]], and [[Relationship]]. Trust must have made continued bearing available and violation must have broken the coupled boundary before the damage can be read as betrayal.

## Pairs

Betrayal pairs with [[Trust]]. Trust names the read that a coupled boundary will hold through strain; Betrayal names when that boundary is broken against participation.

## Traces

- [[Trust]]
- [[Violation]]
- [[Relationship]]

- [[Decoupling]]
## Nests

Betrayal nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which trusted coupled bearing is violated.

## Reads

Betrayal becomes readable where a relationship''s trusted coupled boundary or bearing relation is violated, hidden, loosened, or made unretraceable in a way that damages continued participation.

## Carries

- [[Repair]]','Betrayal Betrayal names trust damaged through violation of a relationship''s coupled boundary or bearing relation. It is harm to a relationship where trust had made continued bearing available. Places Betrayal places harm to a relationship where trust had made continued bearing available — damage to a coupled boundary through violation of trusted bearing. Holds Betrayal is held by Trust, Violation, and Relationship. Trust must have made continued bearing available and violation must have broken the coupled boundary before the damage can be read as betrayal. Pairs Betrayal pairs with Trust. Trust names the read that a coupled boundary will hold through strain; Betrayal names when that boundary is broken against participation. Traces Trust Violation Relationship Decoupling Nests Betrayal nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which trusted coupled bearing is violated. Reads Betrayal becomes readable where a relationship''s trusted coupled boundary or bearing relation is violated, hidden, loosened, or made unretraceable in a way that damages continued participation. Carries Repair','Betrayal Betrayal names trust damaged through violation of a relationship''s coupled boundary or bearing relation. It is harm to a relationship where trust had made continued bearing available.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["second.decoupling","third.relationship","third.repair","third.trust","third.violation"]','{"holds":["third.trust","third.violation","third.relationship"],"traces":["third.trust","third.violation","third.relationship","second.decoupling"],"carries":["third.repair"],"pairs":["third.trust"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',161,'sha256:c74d2b19b5a158c52ee96ef5b74a8949870cd61476149809c44343dc6a9f6834','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.binding','Binding','binding','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Path Reads/Binding.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/binding.html','# Binding

Binding names constrained participation through carried influence. Binding is not constraint in general; it is influence holding participation within a narrowed course.

## Places

Binding places the constraining mode of enchantment — where influence narrows how participation can continue, exit, respond, or re-enter.

## Holds

Binding is held by [[Enchantment]], [[Constraint]], and [[Participation]]. Influence must alter readability, constraint must be operative, and participation must be present before narrowed course can be read as binding rather than as ordinary constraint.

## Pairs

Binding pairs with [[Wonder]]. Binding names enchantment constraining participation; Wonder names enchantment opening it.

## Traces

- [[Enchantment]]
- [[Constraint]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Influence]]

## Nests

Binding nests within the enchantment cluster as the constraining path read — the specific mode where enchantment holds participation within a narrowed course rather than expanding or misrepresenting it.

## Reads

Binding becomes recognisable where influence constrains how participation can continue, exit, respond, or re-enter. The path through influence and constraint must be entered for binding to become readable rather than being mistaken for constraint in general.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Binding Binding names constrained participation through carried influence. Binding is not constraint in general; it is influence holding participation within a narrowed course. Places Binding places the constraining mode of enchantment — where influence narrows how participation can continue, exit, respond, or re enter. Holds Binding is held by Enchantment, Constraint, and Participation. Influence must alter readability, constraint must be operative, and participation must be present before narrowed course can be read as binding rather than as ordinary constraint. Pairs Binding pairs with Wonder. Binding names enchantment constraining participation; Wonder names enchantment opening it. Traces Enchantment Constraint Participation Influence Nests Binding nests within the enchantment cluster as the constraining path read — the specific mode where enchantment holds participation within a narrowed course rather than expanding or misrepresenting it. Reads Binding becomes recognisable where influence constrains how participation can continue, exit, respond, or re enter. The path through influence and constraint must be entered for binding to become readable rather than being mistaken for constraint in general. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Binding Binding names constrained participation through carried influence. Binding is not constraint in general; it is influence holding participation within a narrowed course.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','path-reads','[]','[]','["second.constraint","second.influence","second.participation","third.enchantment","third.wonder"]','{"holds":["third.enchantment","second.constraint","second.participation"],"traces":["third.enchantment","second.constraint","second.participation","second.influence"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.wonder"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',178,'sha256:6922f8efd013becd11a7723501c8dc4682a1f1a17745f085077e3b3b2112e569','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.black-hole','Black Hole','black-hole','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Black Hole.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/black-hole.html','# Black Hole

Black Hole names a natural-world field condition where gravitational field bearing reaches a boundary at which clearance polarity inverts: the located (space) and continuation (time) arms of clearance exchange direction, so inward continuation becomes unavoidable and outward return becomes unavailable. It is a [[Terminal]] — a read-stop where outside readability ends while field bearing continues unread past the available scale. Read from our closure scope it appears as collapse; structurally the bounded condition holds, inverted, rather than failing. This note places the black hole as a third-order physical-field read without making it source structure.

## Places

Black Hole places the physical field condition at which traversal is no longer a compatible continuation — the closure scope where available carrying cannot escape the centring condition.

## Holds

Black Hole is held by [[Physical Field Conditions]], [[Field Availability Pattern]], [[Field Bearing]], [[Gravity]], [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], [[Terminal]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Traversal must cease to be a compatible continuation and a boundary must locate the closure before the terminal condition can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
- [[Field Availability Pattern]]
- [[Field Bearing]]
- [[Gravity]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Terminal]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Black Hole nests within Physical Field Conditions as the terminal field-bearing condition — the closure scope at which available carrying cannot proceed.

## Reads

Black Hole becomes readable where collapsed gravitational field bearing creates a boundary that changes what can return, escape, or remain available to outside evaluation.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], and [[Gravity]] locate what can return, escape, or remain readable.

Second: [[Field Bearing]], [[Collapse]], and [[Closure Scope]] make the loss of ordinary carrying evaluable.

Third: [[Black Hole]] places that structural read inside natural-world physical-field conditions.

Case Movement:

```text
gravitational collapse
-> located event boundary
-> field bearing alters escape and return
-> outside read becomes indirect
```

Related Applied Read:

[[Cosmic Polarity Read]] may use this note as one physical-field case in an applied comparison governed by [[Resolution Polarity]]. A black hole is adjacent to [[Invisible Bearing]] because gravitational bearing remains readable where ordinary light-return fails, but the structural pattern is not sourced from black holes.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Black Hole Black Hole names a natural world field condition where gravitational field bearing reaches a boundary at which clearance polarity inverts: the located (space) and continuation (time) arms of clearance exchange direction, so inward continuation becomes unavoidable and outward return becomes unavailable. It is a Terminal — a read stop where outside readability ends while field bearing continues unread past the available scale. Read from our closure scope it appears as collapse; structurally the bounded condition holds, inverted, rather than failing. This note places the black hole as a third order physical field read without making it source structure. Places Black Hole places the physical field condition at which traversal is no longer a compatible continuation — the closure scope where available carrying cannot escape the centring condition. Holds Black Hole is held by Physical Field Conditions, Field Availability Pattern, Field Bearing, Gravity, Boundary, Availability, Terminal, and Closure Scope. Traversal must cease to be a compatible continuation and a boundary must locate the closure before the terminal condition can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Physical Field Conditions Field Availability Pattern Field Bearing Gravity Boundary Availability Terminal Closure Scope Nests Black Hole nests within Physical Field Conditions as the terminal field bearing condition — the closure scope at which available carrying cannot proceed. Reads Black Hole becomes readable where collapsed gravitational field bearing creates a boundary that changes what can return, escape, or remain available to outside evaluation. The dependency movement is: First: Boundary, Availability, and Gravity locate what can return, escape, or remain readable. Second: Field Bearing, Collapse, and Closure Scope make the loss of ordinary carrying evaluable. Third: Black Hole places that structural read inside natural world physical field conditions. Case Movement: Related Applied Read: Cosmic Polarity Read may use this note as one physical field case in an applied comparison governed by Resolution Polarity. A black hole is adjacent to Invisible Bearing because gravitational bearing remains readable where ordinary light return fails, but the structural pattern is not sourced from black holes. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Black Hole Black Hole names a natural world field condition where gravitational field bearing reaches a boundary at which clearance polarity inverts: the located (space) and continuation (time)…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','natural-world','[]','[]','["first.availability","first.boundary","second.closure-scope","second.terminal","third.field-availability-pattern","third.field-bearing","third.gravity","third.physical-field-conditions"]','{"holds":["third.physical-field-conditions","third.field-availability-pattern","third.field-bearing","third.gravity","first.boundary","first.availability","second.terminal","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.physical-field-conditions","third.field-availability-pattern","third.field-bearing","third.gravity","first.boundary","first.availability","second.terminal","second.closure-scope"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',364,'sha256:c38b622af6175d0ff06d3dacca840cb4b684d12456e1292d6bf4538018406354','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.body-field','Body Field','body-field','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Body/Body Field.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/body-field.html','# Body Field

Body Field names the recurring field of participation through which bodily conditions — sensation, movement, injury, fatigue, recovery, feeling — become readable as organised experience.

## Places

Body Field places a recurring field of participation.

## Holds

Body Field is held by [[Field of Participation]], [[Organic Field]], [[Availability]], [[Strain]], [[Carrying]], and [[Compatibility]]. Field of Participation must structure a recurring scope and embodied structural conditions must be readable before the body field can be named. [[Body]] nests within this field; it does not hold the field that carries it.

## Pairs

Body Field pairs with [[Cognition Field]]. Body Field names the recurring field of embodied participation; Cognition Field names the recurring field of cognitive participation. Each bounds a scope the other depends on for full participation to hold.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Organic Field]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Strain]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Body Field nests as a public field container. Detailed branch notes remain compressed as working material.

[[Body]]
[[Emotion]]
[[Fatigue]]
[[Fatigue Boundary]]
[[Feeling]]
[[Injury]]
[[Metabolism]]
[[Recovery]]

## Reads

Body Field becomes recognisable where embodied sensation, limit, movement, injury, fatigue, feeling, or recovery organises participation as bodily experience.

At the [[Translation Boundary]], [[Bearing]], [[Strain]], [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], [[Resolution]], and [[Rhythm]] can become terminal to this field as local reads such as [[Body]], [[Feeling]], [[Emotion]], [[Fatigue]], [[Fatigue Boundary]], [[Injury]], and [[Recovery]].

## Carries

Body Field carries [[Body]] and [[Medicine]] — the field read of embodied participation and its applied branch. Nested reads are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.

- [[Body]]
