INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.branch','Branch','branch','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Branch.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/branch.html','# Branch

A Branch names a dependency path through participation. It is a traceable path through what a field or domain depends on, carries, and opens. Branches can occur within Organic Fields, within Organised Domains, or across the relation between them.

A branch often becomes visible at a [[Translation Boundary|translation joint]]: the point where a structural Atlas term becomes terminal to a field or domain.

## Places

Branch places a dependency path through participation: the joint where source terms, field terms, domain terms, and applied reads remain connected rather than collected.

## Holds

Branch is held by [[Field of Participation]], [[Domain]], and [[Dependency Order]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward into [[Path Reads]], [[Retrace Read]], [[Applied Read]], and [[Diagnosis]]. Branch names a dependency path through participation.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Domain]]
- [[Dependency Order]]
- [[Organised Domain]]
- [[Terminal]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Branch nests as a retraceable dependency path through fields, domains, or crossings.

It can nest structural-to-local translation, where an Atlas term enters a domain through a [[Translation Boundary]] and becomes carried by the domain''s own terms.

[[Path Reads]]
[[Applied Read]]
[[Diagnosis]]
[[Retrace Read|Retrace]]

## Reads

A Branch becomes recognisable where terms can be followed as a dependency path rather than as a loose collection. A branch remains readable only while its path can be retraced through the dependencies that carry it.

It is strongest where the reader can see what becomes terminal to the field or domain, what local term carries it, and what Atlas trace remains underneath.
## Carries

This note carries its organising role into the branches named in Nests and into branch-level field and domain terms.

- [[Faith Read]]
- [[Teaching]]
- [[Parenting]]
- [[Placement Mode]]
- [[Ship and Ark]]
