INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.cognition','Cognition','cognition','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Cognition/Cognition.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/cognition.html','# Cognition

Cognition names ordered participation in readability.

It is not the source of order. It is the condition through which a participant can receive, distinguish, retain, compare, orient, and respond to difference within a resolution band.

Recognition is one possible resolution of cognition: a read becomes placed as this. Cognition names the wider participatory condition through which such placing, retaining, comparing, remembering, modelling, and responding can occur.

## Places

Cognition places ordered participation in readability — the condition through which a participant can receive, distinguish, retain, compare, orient, and respond to difference within a resolution band.

## Holds

Cognition is held by [[Branch]], [[Cognition Field]], [[Cognitive Participation]], and [[Recurrence]]. Cognitive participation must be present and recurrence must make returnable comparison possible before cognition can be named as an organised field condition.

## Pairs

Cognition pairs with [[Body]]. Cognition names the cognitive structural condition within the participatory field; Body names the embodied structural condition. Each bounds a scope the other depends on.

## Traces

- [[Branch]]
- [[Cognition Field]]
- [[Cognitive Participation]]
- [[Recurrence]]

## Nests

Cognition nests within the Cognition Field branch as the field-level container for cognitive structural reads.

[[Thought]]
[[Memory]]
[[Self]]
[[Self-Bearing]]
[[Self-Control]]
[[Cognitive Carrying]]
[[Cognitive Metabolism]]
[[Answerable Mind]]
[[Cognitive Reads]]
[[Externalised Cognition]]

## Reads

Cognition becomes readable where a participant can receive, distinguish, retain, compare, orient, and respond to readable difference without making mind the source of order.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] and [[Availability]] make distinguishability present enough to be carried.

Second: [[Cognitive Participation]] and [[Recurrence]] make evaluated and returnable read possible.

Third: [[Cognition]] places that structural read within [[Cognition Field]] as participant-level ordered readability.

Recognition follows as a placed cognitive read where what is received and distinguished becomes identifiable as this. Knowing follows where that recognised read remains carried, usable, checkable, and revisable.

Higher-Order Edge:

Cognition remains third-order where it names mind-domain participation in thought, recognition, memory, modelling, or retained readability.

It crosses into higher order only where [[Consciousness]] makes the read available to the participant and [[Recursion]] changes how cognition is carried.

## Carries

Cognition carries [[Thought]], [[Memory]], [[Self]], [[Cognitive Carrying]], [[Cognitive Metabolism]], [[Answerable Mind]], [[Cognitive Reads]], and [[Externalised Cognition]] — the structural reads through which cognitive participation is evaluated at the relevant closure scope.

- [[Thought]]
- [[Memory]]
- [[Self]]
- [[Cognitive Carrying]]
- [[Cognitive Metabolism]]
- [[Answerable Mind]]
- [[Cognitive Reads]]
