INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.communicating','Communicating','communicating','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Placement Modes/Communicating.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/communicating.html','# Communicating

Communicating names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through readable transmission between positions. What a communication medium allows shapes which reads can be carried between those positions.

## Places

Communicating places the mode where participation is primarily carried through readable transmission between positions — where a read is carried across a medium between distinct participants.

## Holds

Communicating is held by [[Placement Mode]], [[Read]], [[Medium]], and [[Allow]]. A mode of participation must exist, readability must be transmissible, a medium must carry it, and allowance must be present before transmission can be placed as the primary mode.

## Pairs

Communicating pairs with [[Sensing]]. Sensing names detection of local difference; Communicating names readable transmission of that difference between positions.

## Traces

- [[Placement Mode]]
- [[Read]]
- [[Medium]]
- [[Allow]]

## Nests

Communicating nests within Placement Modes as the transmission mode — where the primary movement is carrying readability across speaker, medium, sign, or shared form.

## Reads

Communicating becomes recognisable where a note is primarily placed by carried readability across speaker, listener, sign, document, instruction, representation, or shared form.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Communicating Communicating names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through readable transmission between positions. What a communication medium allows shapes which reads can be carried between those positions. Places Communicating places the mode where participation is primarily carried through readable transmission between positions — where a read is carried across a medium between distinct participants. Holds Communicating is held by Placement Mode, Read, Medium, and Allow. A mode of participation must exist, readability must be transmissible, a medium must carry it, and allowance must be present before transmission can be placed as the primary mode. Pairs Communicating pairs with Sensing. Sensing names detection of local difference; Communicating names readable transmission of that difference between positions. Traces Placement Mode Read Medium Allow Nests Communicating nests within Placement Modes as the transmission mode — where the primary movement is carrying readability across speaker, medium, sign, or shared form. Reads Communicating becomes recognisable where a note is primarily placed by carried readability across speaker, listener, sign, document, instruction, representation, or shared form. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Communicating Communicating names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through readable transmission between positions. What a communication medium allows shapes which reads…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','placement-modes','[]','[]','["first.allow","first.read","second.medium","third.placement-mode","third.sensing"]','{"holds":["third.placement-mode","first.read","second.medium","first.allow"],"traces":["third.placement-mode","first.read","second.medium","first.allow"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.sensing"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',182,'sha256:96f05ee865a5ea9ebb787c617d68d7ae7a9f97347d32c3fa7d69d57703948a03','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.communion','Communion','communion','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Communion.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/communion.html','# Communion

Communion names the invariant condition of genuine collective participation: distinct participations genuinely together without collapsing into sameness.

[[Organic Field]] names participation organising itself through natural order. Communion is the prior condition organic field requires: the participation must be genuine before it can organise into a field.

[[Organised Domain]] names intentionally arranged participation. Communion is the prior condition organised arrangement requires: the participation must be genuine before arrangement can carry it rather than merely simulate it.

Communion is not aggregation. Aggregation places many together without genuine participation passing between them. Communion holds the gathering while genuine participation remains — many-while-genuinely-together is the structural signature of Communion.

Communion is hidden in functioning fields and domains because it is not the visible operation. It becomes clearest in absence: where form persists while genuine togetherness has gone, Communion was not present.

## Places

Communion places the invariant condition of genuine collective participation before the split into organic field and organised domain.

## Holds

Communion is held by [[Field of Participation]]. A field of participation must be established before distinct participations can be genuinely together.

## Pairs

Field of Participation carries downward — into Communion. Communion is an invariant carrier: it holds whether or not the split into organic or organised is visible.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Invariant]]

## Nests

Communion nests before the organic/organised split. It lets organic fields arise through genuine participation and organised domains carry genuine participation into arrangement rather than merely simulate it.

## Reads

Communion becomes recognisable where distinct participations are genuinely together: not merely co-present, coordinated, or aggregated, but held in a participation that something passes through.

It is also recognisable in absence, where members are present and procedures continue but nothing genuine passes between them.

## Carries

- [[Organic Field]]
- [[Organised Domain]]','Communion Communion names the invariant condition of genuine collective participation: distinct participations genuinely together without collapsing into sameness. Organic Field names participation organising itself through natural order. Communion is the prior condition organic field requires: the participation must be genuine before it can organise into a field. Organised Domain names intentionally arranged participation. Communion is the prior condition organised arrangement requires: the participation must be genuine before arrangement can carry it rather than merely simulate it. Communion is not aggregation. Aggregation places many together without genuine participation passing between them. Communion holds the gathering while genuine participation remains — many while genuinely together is the structural signature of Communion. Communion is hidden in functioning fields and domains because it is not the visible operation. It becomes clearest in absence: where form persists while genuine togetherness has gone, Communion was not present. Places Communion places the invariant condition of genuine collective participation before the split into organic field and organised domain. Holds Communion is held by Field of Participation. A field of participation must be established before distinct participations can be genuinely together. Pairs Field of Participation carries downward — into Communion. Communion is an invariant carrier: it holds whether or not the split into organic or organised is visible. Traces Field of Participation Invariant Nests Communion nests before the organic/organised split. It lets organic fields arise through genuine participation and organised domains carry genuine participation into arrangement rather than merely simulate it. Reads Communion becomes recognisable where distinct participations are genuinely together: not merely co present, coordinated, or aggregated, but held in a participation that something passes through. It is also recognisable in absence, where members are present and procedures continue but nothing genuine passes between them. Carries Organic Field Organised Domain','Communion Communion names the invariant condition of genuine collective participation: distinct participations genuinely together without collapsing into sameness. Organic Field names…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.invariant","third.field-of-participation","third.organic-field","third.organised-domain"]','{"holds":["third.field-of-participation"],"traces":["third.field-of-participation","ground.invariant"],"carries":["third.organic-field","third.organised-domain"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',292,'sha256:17a4e5b3b04f479b9aebd7216e0fc74992e16af68a130c2d0e425a82503dbc4f','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.competence-boundary','Competence Boundary','competence-boundary','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Knowledge/Competence Boundary.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/competence-boundary.html','# Competence Boundary

Competence Boundary names the boundary at which a participant''s knowledge, ability, responsibility, and action remain truthfully traceable to their bearing source. It is not a status boundary or a claim of worth; it is the readable edge where knowing, doing, and responsibility must remain compatible with what actually bears them.

## Places

Competence Boundary places the located limit at which a participant, practice, or domain can distinguish what it can compatibly carry from what it cannot — the closure scope of traceable carrying.

## Holds

Competence Boundary is held by [[Knowledge]], [[Boundary]], [[Compatibility]], [[Reality Check]], [[Bearing Source]], [[Know]], and [[Responsibility]]. Carrying must be traceable, responsibility must remain answerable to its bearing source, and compatibility must be evaluable before the limit of competent carrying can be named.

## Pairs

Competence Boundary pairs with [[Modelling]]. Competence Boundary names the located scope at which compatible carrying can no longer be reliably extended; Modelling names the representation through which compatible carrying is extended through medium. Each requires the other: modelling extends what competence boundary locates as the edge of compatible extension.

## Traces

- [[Knowledge]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Reality Check]]
- [[Bearing Source]]
- [[Know]]
- [[Responsibility]]

## Nests

Competence Boundary nests within the Knowledge Field as the closure-scope condition through which traceable carrying distinguishes what is within and beyond its compatible scope.

## Reads

Competence Boundary becomes readable where a participant, practice, or domain can distinguish what can be known, done, claimed, taught, delegated, or taken responsibility for without exceeding the bearing source that can actually carry and check it.

## Carries

- [[Restraint]]
