ot a…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','knowledge','[]','[]','["first.boundary","second.bearing-source","second.compatibility","second.know","second.responsibility","third.dominion","third.knowledge","third.modelling","third.reality-check","third.restraint"]','{"holds":["third.knowledge","first.boundary","second.compatibility","third.reality-check","second.bearing-source","second.know","second.responsibility"],"traces":["third.knowledge","first.boundary","second.compatibility","third.reality-check","second.bearing-source","second.know","second.responsibility"],"carries":["third.restraint","third.dominion"],"pairs":["third.modelling"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',252,'sha256:7f28e2708ef144d6e05e8a41551866e7218c0cc08de8705eeaf04544cf3de047','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.consent','Consent','consent','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Society/Consent.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/consent.html','# Consent

Consent names a society path read where participation becomes allowed by recognised boundary and communicated agreement.

## Places

Consent places the condition through which participation is made available within a recognised boundary — the structural node where recognition, participation, and compatibility hold as permission for carrying to proceed.

## Holds

Consent is held by [[Society Field]], [[Boundary]], [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Participation]], [[Compatibility]], [[Closure Scope]], and [[Society]]. A boundary must locate what is at stake, recognition must make it available, and compatibility must hold before permission for carrying can be named as consent.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Society Field]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Recognition Read|Recognition]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Society]]

## Nests

Consent nests within the Society Field as the structural condition through which participation is made available within a recognised boundary.

## Reads

Consent becomes readable where participation can proceed, pause, change, or stop through a recognised boundary at the relevant closure scope.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] and [[Bearing]] make participation limitable without collapse or force.

Second: [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Participation]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]] make consent evaluable.

Third: [[Consent]] places that structural read inside the [[Society Field]].

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Consent Consent names a society path read where participation becomes allowed by recognised boundary and communicated agreement. Places Consent places the condition through which participation is made available within a recognised boundary — the structural node where recognition, participation, and compatibility hold as permission for carrying to proceed. Holds Consent is held by Society Field, Boundary, Recognition Read, Participation, Compatibility, Closure Scope, and Society. A boundary must locate what is at stake, recognition must make it available, and compatibility must hold before permission for carrying can be named as consent. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Society Field Boundary Recognition Read Participation Compatibility Closure Scope Society Nests Consent nests within the Society Field as the structural condition through which participation is made available within a recognised boundary. Reads Consent becomes readable where participation can proceed, pause, change, or stop through a recognised boundary at the relevant closure scope. The dependency movement is: First: Boundary and Bearing make participation limitable without collapse or force. Second: Recognition Read, Participation, Compatibility, and Closure Scope make consent evaluable. Third: Consent places that structural read inside the Society Field. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Consent Consent names a society path read where participation becomes allowed by recognised boundary and communicated agreement. Places Consent places the condition through which participation is…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','society','[]','[]','["first.boundary","second.closure-scope","second.compatibility","second.participation","second.recognition-read","third.society","third.society-field"]','{"holds":["third.society-field","first.boundary","second.recognition-read","second.participation","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope","third.society"],"traces":["third.society-field","first.boundary","second.recognition-read","second.participation","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope","third.society"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',210,'sha256:4e02a8de63226148658964ffaa5c3e1c752a64a1eb6abf5815ed0a04a351b71e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.constrained-resolution','Constrained Resolution','constrained-resolution','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Constrained Resolution.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/constrained-resolution.html','# Constrained Resolution

Constrained resolution names compatible Resolution sustained under limiting Constraint conditions.

## Places

Constrained Resolution places resolution where what can be determined at scope is bounded by a prior constraint — bearing settling into a determined condition within limited options.

## Holds

Constrained Resolution is held by [[Constraint]] and [[Resolution]]. A constraint must bound what can hold before the determination can be read as constrained.

## Pairs

Constrained Resolution pairs with [[Accommodation]]. Constrained Resolution names the general condition of resolution within constraint; Accommodation names the specific bearing form of that resolution in relational participation.

## Traces

- [[Constraint]]
- [[Resolution]]

- [[Control]]
## Nests

Constrained Resolution nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which resolution holds within a bounded carrying scope.

## Reads

Constrained resolution becomes readable where limiting conditions remain present while compatible bearing still resolves.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Resolution]] determines what held relation becomes.

Second: [[Constraint]], [[Carrying]], and [[Compatibility]] make limited continuation evaluable.

Third: [[Constrained Resolution]] places that structural read inside bearing relations.

## Carries

Constrained Resolution carries [[Accommodation]] — the specific bearing form of resolution within bounded options.
