aces","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',176,'sha256:27b35a2f17c5c34029f79892794b20b9e56250dce59129e06e76d28cf47a0321','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.control-after-harm','Control After Harm','control-after-harm','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Applied Reads/Control After Harm.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/control-after-harm.html','# Control After Harm

Control After Harm reads a local case where control enters after damaged bearing and must be checked for protection, repair, or further harm.

## Places

Control After Harm places the applied read where control is exercised following harm — direction of availability in the context of incompatible carrying that preceded it.

## Holds

Control After Harm is held by [[Applied Read]], [[Harm]], [[Control]], [[Repair]], and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Control After Harm pairs with [[Control Drift]]. Control After Harm names the disorder where control is applied after harm without first restoring bearing; Control Drift names the disorder where control loses retrace to what it was constraining. Each is a distinct form of control losing its structural ground.

## Traces

- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Harm]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Repair]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Control After Harm nests within Relational Participation as an applied read of Control following harm, where direction of availability must be read against the incompatible carrying that preceded it.

## Reads

Control After Harm becomes readable where direction enters after harm and must preserve compatible re-bearing rather than force proceeding.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bearing]] and [[Resolution]] must be re-entered after harm.

Second: [[Compatibility]], [[Repair]], and [[Closure Scope]] make control evaluable as protection, repair support, or forced continuation.

Third: [[Control After Harm]] tests that condition inside the [[Relational Participation Field]] as an applied relation read.

Case Movement:

```text
harm damages bearing
-> control enters as protection
-> repair is required
-> control either supports re-bearing or forces continuation
```

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Control After Harm Control After Harm reads a local case where control enters after damaged bearing and must be checked for protection, repair, or further harm. Places Control After Harm places the applied read where control is exercised following harm — direction of availability in the context of incompatible carrying that preceded it. Holds Control After Harm is held by Applied Read, Harm, Control, Repair, and Closure Scope. Pairs Control After Harm pairs with Control Drift. Control After Harm names the disorder where control is applied after harm without first restoring bearing; Control Drift names the disorder where control loses retrace to what it was constraining. Each is a distinct form of control losing its structural ground. Traces Applied Read Harm Control Repair Closure Scope Nests Control After Harm nests within Relational Participation as an applied read of Control following harm, where direction of availability must be read against the incompatible carrying that preceded it. Reads Control After Harm becomes readable where direction enters after harm and must preserve compatible re bearing rather than force proceeding. The dependency movement is: First: Bearing and Resolution must be re entered after harm. Second: Compatibility, Repair, and Closure Scope make control evaluable as protection, repair support, or forced continuation. Third: Control After Harm tests that condition inside the Relational Participation Field as an applied relation read. Case Movement: Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Control After Harm Control After Harm reads a local case where control enters after damaged bearing and must be checked for protection, repair, or further harm. Places Control After Harm places…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","third.applied-read","third.control","third.control-drift","third.harm","third.repair"]','{"holds":["third.applied-read","third.harm","third.control","third.repair","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.applied-read","third.harm","third.control","third.repair","second.closure-scope"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.control-drift"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',236,'sha256:89faf21b94c68bfc0b9597477e0fa181a7431040a65b445123a959e1d19eddc7','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.control-drift','Control Drift','control-drift','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Applied Reads/Control Drift.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/control-drift.html','# Control Drift

Control Drift reads a local case where directed availability stops receiving the bearing condition it directs and begins forcing proceeding.

## Places

Control Drift places the applied read where control departs from compatible directed availability, becoming incompatible carrying beyond the closure scope of its relational grounding.

## Holds

Control Drift is held by [[Applied Read]], [[Control]], [[Dependency Disorder]], and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Control Drift pairs with [[Control After Harm]]. Control Drift names the disorder where control loses retrace to what it was constraining; Control After Harm names the disorder where control is applied after harm without first restoring bearing. Each is a distinct form of control losing its structural ground.

## Traces

- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Dependency Disorder]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Control Drift nests within Relational Participation as an applied read of Control, where direction of availability loses its compatible grounding.

## Reads

Control Drift becomes readable where direction continues after the bearing condition required for compatible proceeding has been displaced, forced, or made unable to correct the direction.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bearing]] and [[Availability]] must hold enough for direction to remain supportable.

Second: [[Dependency Disorder]] and [[Closure Scope]] make forced proceeding evaluable as drift.

Third: [[Control Drift]] tests that condition inside the [[Relational Participation Field]] as an applied relation read.

Case Movement:

```text
availability is directed
-> bearing weakens
-> direction continues
-> correction from the directed condition is not received
-> control becomes forced proceeding
```

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Control Drift Control Drift reads a local case where directed availability stops receiving the bearing condition it directs and begins forcing proceeding. Places Control Drift places the applied read where control departs from compatible directed availability, becoming incompatible carrying beyond the closure scope of its relational grounding. Holds Control Drift is held by Applied Read, Control, Dependency Disorder, and Closure Scope. Pairs Control Drift pairs with Control After Harm. Control Drift names the disorder where control loses retrace to what it was constraining; Control After Harm names the disorder where control is applied after harm without first restoring bearing. Each is a distinct form of control losing its structural ground. Traces Applied Read Control Dependency Disorder Closure Scope Nests Control Drift nests within Relational Participation as an applied read of Control, where direction of availability loses its compatible grounding. Reads Control Drift becomes readable where direction continues after the bearing condition required for compatible proceeding has been displaced, forced, or made unable to correct the direction. The dependency movement is: First: Bearing and Availability must hold enough for direction to remain supportable. Second: Dependency Disorder and Closure Scope make forced proceeding evaluable as drift. Third: Control Drift tests that condition inside the Relational Participation Field as an applied relation read. Case Movement: Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Control Drift Control Drift reads a local case where directed availability stops receiving the bearing condition it directs and begins forcing proceeding. Places Control Drift places the applied…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.dependency-disorder","third.applied-read","third.control","third.control-after-harm"]','{"holds":["third.applied-read","third.control","second.dependency-disorder","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.applied-read","third.control","second.dependency-disorder","second.closure-scope"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.control-after-harm"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',223,'sha256:2426fcbbdbb92487c6907981465ad60ba07156bccde802a0029d73b8c684a02a','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.control','Control','control','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Control.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/control.html','# Control

Control names bearing directing availability through relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction. The reciprocity is definitional: where the directed condition loses the ability to affect the direction, carrying becomes one-way and incompatible, and control passes into [[Harm]]. Control names directed availability that stays within compatible relation, not direction imposed by removing participation. Control remains reality-bearing where direction stays answerable to [[Care]] — the preserving bearing that keeps availability from being consumed by direction.

## Places

Control places bearing directing availability through relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction.

## Holds

Control is held by [[Bearing]], [[Availability]], and [[Constraint]]. Bearing must be present, availability must be at stake, and a constraining condition must be readable before direction within compatible relation can be named.

## Pairs

Control pairs with [[Care]]. Control names bearing that directs availability through constraint; Care names bearing that preserves availability through responsive relation. Control remains compatible where direction stays answerable to the availability care preserves.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Constraint]]

## Nests

Control nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which bearing directs available relation — the structural ground for all direction-bearing reads.

## Reads

Control becomes readable where bearing directs availability within relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction.

## Carries

Control carries [[Behaviour]], [[Constrained Resolution]], [[Control After Harm]], and [[Control Drift]] — what is done through a control condition, how resolution settles within bounded options, and the applied reads where control loses compatible grounding.
- [[Behaviour]]
- [[Constrained Resolution]]
- [[Control After Harm]]
- [[Control Drift]]
- [[Domination]]
- [[Dominion]]
- [[Restraint]]','Control Control names bearing directing availability through relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction. The reciprocity is definitional: where the directed condition loses the ability to affect the direction, carrying becomes one way and incompatible, and control passes into Harm. Control names directed availability that stays within compatible relation, not direction imposed by removing participation. Control remains reality bearing where direction stays answerable to Care — the preserving bearing that keeps availability from being consumed by direction. Places Control places bearing directing availability through relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction. Holds Control is held by Bearing, Availability, and Constraint. Bearing must be present, availability must be at stake, and a constraining condition must be readable before direction within compatible relation can be named. Pairs Control pairs with Care. Control names bearing that directs availability through constraint; Care names bearing that preserves availability through responsive relation. Control remains compatible where direction stays answerable to the availability care preserves. Traces Bearing Availability Constraint Nests Control nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which bearing directs available relation — the structural ground for all direction bearing reads. Reads Control becomes readable where bearing directs availability within relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction. Carries Control carries Behaviour, Constrained Resolution, Control After Harm, and Control Drift — what is done through a control condition, how resolution settles within bounded options, and the applied reads where control loses compatible grounding. Behaviour Constrained Resolution Control After Harm Control Drift Domination Dominion Restraint','Control Control names bearing directing availability through relation while the directed condition remains able to affect the direction. The reciprocity is definitional: where the directed…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["first.availability","first.bearing","second.constraint","third.behaviour","third.care","third.constrained-resolution","third.control-after-harm","third.control-drift","third.domination","third.dominion","third.restraint"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","first.availability","second.constraint"],"traces":["first.bearing","first.availability","second.constraint"],"carries":["third.behaviour","third.constrained-resolution","third.control-after-harm","third.control-drift","third.domination","third.dominion","third.restraint"],"pairs":["third.care"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',260,'sha256:405075c7fb2d5de40462cdbd1b6212f6364e886ae9a95a8b3846d0d9c8dd49cb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.cosmic-polarity-read','Cosmic Polarity Read','cosmic-polarity-read','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Applied Reads/Cosmic Polarity Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/cosmic-polarity-read.html','# Cosmic Polarity Read

Cosmic Polarity Read applies [[Resolution Polarity]] to natural-world physical-field reads, comparing [[Light]], [[Gravity]], [[Dark Matter]], [[Dark Energy]], and [[Black Hole]] as apparent clearance, constraint, invisible bearing, opening clearance, and collapse-boundary conditions.

This note holds the speculative cosmic application of [[Resolution Polarity]] without making cosmology source structure.

## Places

Cosmic Polarity Read places the applied comparison through which physical-field cases — gravity, dark matter, dark energy, light, and black holes — are read against Resolution Polarity.

## Holds

Cosmic Polarity Read is held by [[Natural World Field]], [[Physical Field Conditions]], [[Field Availability Pattern]], [[Field Bearing]], [[Resolution Polarity]], and [[Observation]]. Physical field conditions must hold and resolution polarity must be available as a structural lens before the applied comparison can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Natural World Field]]
- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
