## Nests

Cosmic Polarity Read nests within the Natural World Field as an applied structural comparison — a polarity read that holds physical-field cases against Resolution Polarity without claiming physical field conditions as structural source.

## Reads

Cosmic Polarity Read becomes available where physical-field notes are compared as a polarity set: light as apparent clearance, gravity as constrained clearance, dark matter as invisible bearing, dark energy as opening clearance, and black hole as boundary-limited non-return.

Comparison Cases:

- [[Light]] supplies apparent clearance.
- [[Gravity]] supplies constrained clearance.
- [[Dark Matter]] supplies the applied natural-world case of invisible bearing.
- [[Dark Energy]] supplies opening-clearance read.
- [[Black Hole]] supplies collapse-boundary read.
Derivation:

[[Resolution Polarity]] supplies the structural comparison pattern.

[[Visible]] supplies apparent presentation.

[[Field Bearing]] supplies field-level bearing on traversal, escape, attraction, closure, or measurable path.

[[Invisible Bearing]] supplies bearing that carries without presenting as bearing.

[[Light]] names apparent clearance.

[[Gravity]] names constrained clearance.

[[Dark Matter]] names a natural-world physical-field case of [[Invisible Bearing]].

[[Dark Energy]] names inferred opening of large-scale clearance beyond ordinary gravitational closure.

[[Black Hole]] names boundary-limited availability where gravitational collapse prevents ordinary light-return.

Cosmic Polarity Read names the natural-world application where these path reads are compared as a polarity set without promoting the comparison into first-order structure.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Clearance]], [[Visible]], [[Invisible]], [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], [[Bearing]], [[Resolution]], and [[Polarity]] make the physical-field comparison structurally possible.

Second: [[Field Bearing]], [[Visibility]], [[Invisible Bearing]], [[Resolution Polarity]], [[Readability]], [[Observation]], and [[Closure Scope]] make apparent clearance, constraint, invisible carrying, opening, closure, and read reversal evaluable.

Third: [[Cosmic Polarity Read]] applies the pattern inside [[Natural World Field]] without treating the application as source structure.
