INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.dark-energy','Dark Energy','dark-energy','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Dark Energy.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/dark-energy.html','# Dark Energy

Dark Energy names an inferred natural-world physical-field condition where large-scale located clearance continues to open beyond ordinary gravitational closure.

This note places dark energy as a third-order physical-field read without treating it as a substance or source structure.

## Places

Dark Energy places the physical field condition through which field availability is expanded against gravitational carrying — the structural read of field-bearing that opposes gravitational centring at scale.

## Holds

Dark Energy is held by [[Natural World Field]], [[Physical]], [[Physical Field Conditions]], [[Field Availability Pattern]], [[Field Bearing]], [[Gravity]], and [[Light]]. Physical field conditions must hold and field-bearing at scale must be readable before the expanding condition can be named.

## Pairs

Dark Energy pairs with [[Gravity]]. Dark Energy names the expanding condition that works against gravitational structuring at cosmic scale; Gravity names the attracting condition it opposes.

## Traces

- [[Natural World Field]]
- [[Physical]]
- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
- [[Field Availability Pattern]]
- [[Field Bearing]]
- [[Gravity]]
- [[Light]]

## Nests

Dark Energy nests within Physical Field Conditions as the expanding field-bearing condition — one physical-field case in the Cosmic Polarity Read.

## Reads

Dark Energy becomes readable where large-scale cosmic clearance continues to open in a way not resolved by visible matter, dark matter, or ordinary gravitational closure-bearing alone.

Derivation:

[[Physical Field Conditions]] supplies physical-field placement.

[[Field Availability Pattern]] supplies recurring physical-field availability pattern.

[[Field Bearing]] supplies the field-level bearing condition through which large-scale clearance becomes readable.

[[Gravity]] supplies the ordinary closure-bearing condition the expansion read is measured against.

[[Clearance]] supplies held separation.

[[Space]] supplies located clearance.

[[Light]] supplies apparent clearance.

Dark Energy names an inferred physical-field condition where large-scale located clearance continues to open beyond ordinary gravitational closure at cosmic closure scope.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Clearance]], [[Space]], [[Relation Read]], [[Availability]], and [[Gravity]] make large-scale separation and closure structurally readable.

Second: [[Field Bearing]], [[Light]], [[Visibility]], [[Readability]], and [[Closure Scope]] make cosmic expansion evaluable.

Third: [[Dark Energy]] places that expansion read inside [[Natural World Field]] and [[Physical Field Conditions]].

Related Applied Read:

[[Cosmic Polarity Read]] may use this note as one physical-field case governed by [[Resolution Polarity]].

## Carries

