INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.domain','Domain','domain','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domain.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/domain.html','# Domain

A Domain names an organised participation context. A domain organises one or more fields into a recognisable context, practice, discipline, institution, method, tool, technology, or applied arrangement. Domains remain valid where they preserve access back to the fields and traces they organise.

A domain also names where general Atlas terms meet a [[Translation Boundary]] and become terminal to local language. The domain does not replace the source structure; it translates that structure into terms the domain can use, test, teach, and repair.

Engineered can be artificial without being unreal. It names a mode of organisation where participation is intentionally, culturally, technically, institutionally, or methodically arranged.

A new domain is justified where participation is intentionally or culturally organised into a recognisable practice, context, tool, discipline, institution, or applied arrangement.

## Places

Domain places an organised participation context. It also places the terminal point where a structural term becomes readable through domain language while remaining retraceable to its Atlas dependency.

## Holds

Domain is held by [[Field of Participation]] and [[Organic and Organised Organisation]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Organic and Organised Organisation]]
- [[Place]]
- [[Society]]
- [[Terminal]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Domain nests where one or more fields are organised into a context, practice, discipline, tool, institution, or method.

It also nests local terms that are translations of structural Atlas terms at a [[Translation Boundary]].

## Reads

A Domain becomes recognisable where one or more fields are organised into a coherent participation context. A domain is readable where it can show what fields it organises, what branches it carries, and whether its organisation remains retraceable.

It becomes structurally useful where it can show what Atlas term becomes terminal to the domain, what local term carries it from there, and how the path can be retraced.

## Carries

- [[Branch]]
- [[Path Reads]]
- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Organised Domain]]
- [[Dominion]]
- [[Ship and Ark]]','Domain A Domain names an organised participation context. A domain organises one or more fields into a recognisable context, practice, discipline, institution, method, tool, technology, or applied arrangement. Domains remain valid where they preserve access back to the fields and traces they organise. A domain also names where general Atlas terms meet a Translation Boundary and become terminal to local language. The domain does not replace the source structure; it translates that structure into terms the domain can use, test, teach, and repair. Engineered can be artificial without being unreal. It names a mode of organisation where participation is intentionally, culturally, technically, institutionally, or methodically arranged. A new domain is justified where participation is intentionally or culturally organised into a recognisable practice, context, tool, discipline, institution, or applied arrangement. Places Domain places an organised participation context. It also places the terminal point where a structural term becomes readable through domain language while remaining retraceable to its Atlas dependency. Holds Domain is held by Field of Participation and Organic and Organised Organisation. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Field of Participation Organic and Organised Organisation Place Society Terminal Translation Boundary Nests Domain nests where one or more fields are organised into a context, practice, discipline, tool, institution, or method. It also nests local terms that are translations of structural Atlas terms at a Translation Boundary. Reads A Domain becomes recognisable where one or more fields are organised into a coherent participation context. A domain is readable where it can show what fields it organises, what branches it carries, and whether its organisation remains retraceable. It becomes structurally useful where it can show what Atlas term becomes terminal to the domain, what local term carries it from there, and how the path can be retraced. Carries Branch Path Reads Applied Read Organised Domain Dominion Ship and Ark','Domain A Domain names an organised participation context. A domain organises one or more fields into a recognisable context, practice, discipline, institution, method, tool, technology, or applied…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.place","second.terminal","third.applied-read","third.branch","third.dominion","third.field-of-participation","third.organic-and-organised-organisation","third.organised-domain","third.path-reads","third.ship-and-ark","third.society","third.translation-boundary"]','{"holds":["third.field-of-participation","third.organic-and-organised-organisation"],"traces":["third.field-of-participation","third.organic-and-organised-organisation","first.place","third.society","second.terminal","third.translation-boundary"],"carries":["third.branch","third.path-reads","third.applied-read","third.organised-domain","third.dominion","third.ship-and-ark"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',320,'sha256:d01b869ff80315e822dad25baab8881cff63b413c37e3ed3a5fa8c8c1bdd854c','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.domination','Domination','domination','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domination.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/domination.html','# Domination

Domination names dominion failed into control detached from care.

Domination is not authority as such. It is authority that no longer remains answerable to the domain it claims to govern. The domain, body, field, relation, or participant is treated as available for direction, extraction, or override while the carrying conditions that make it available are ignored or damaged.

## Places

Domination places dominion failed into control detached from care.

## Holds

Domination is held by [[Dominion]], [[Control]], [[Care]], [[Violation]], and [[Harm]]. Dominion must be the claimed authority, control must proceed, care must be absent or overridden, and incompatible carrying must damage available bearing before domination can be named.

## Pairs

Domination pairs with [[Dominion]]. Dominion names authority answerable to the domain it bears; Domination names that authority failed into control that overrides, consumes, or damages the domain.

## Traces

- [[Dominion]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Care]]
- [[Violation]]
- [[Harm]]

## Nests

Domination nests within domains where authority continues as control after it has stopped remaining answerable to the domain''s carrying conditions.

## Reads

Domination becomes readable where control treats a domain, body, field, relation, or participant as available for direction without remaining answerable to the care and boundaries that keep it carrying.

Domination often presents as order because direction still occurs. The disorder is structural: the authority continues while the carrying relation it depends on is consumed, silenced, extracted, or overridden.

## Carries

Domination carries no further public branch at this scope.','Domination Domination names dominion failed into control detached from care. Domination is not authority as such. It is authority that no longer remains answerable to the domain it claims to govern. The domain, body, field, relation, or participant is treated as available for direction, extraction, or override while the carrying conditions that make it available are ignored or damaged. Places Domination places dominion failed into control detached from care. Holds Domination is held by Dominion, Control, Care, Violation, and Harm. Dominion must be the claimed authority, control must proceed, care must be absent or overridden, and incompatible carrying must damage available bearing before domination can be named. Pairs Domination pairs with Dominion. Dominion names authority answerable to the domain it bears; Domination names that authority failed into control that overrides, consumes, or damages the domain. Traces Dominion Control Care Violation Harm Nests Domination nests within domains where authority continues as control after it has stopped remaining answerable to the domain''s carrying conditions. Reads Domination becomes readable where control treats a domain, body, field, relation, or participant as available for direction without remaining answerable to the care and boundaries that keep it carrying. Domination often presents as order because direction still occurs. The disorder is structural: the authority continues while the carrying relation it depends on is consumed, silenced, extracted, or overridden. Carries Domination carries no further public branch at this scope.','Domination Domination names dominion failed into control detached from care. Domination is not authority as such.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["third.care","third.control","third.dominion","third.harm","third.violation"]','{"holds":["third.dominion","third.control","third.care","third.violation","third.harm"],"traces":["third.dominion","third.control","third.care","third.violation","third.harm"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.dominion"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',231,'sha256:09b08370ab96c135db263496ac24a6c219f13603e32da4c67e0763ead838d369','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.dominion','Dominion','dominion','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Dominion.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/dominion.html','# Dominion

Dominion names bounded authority over a domain that remains answerable to the care, limits, and carrying conditions of that domain.

Dominion is not domination. Dominion is authority under obligation: the domain is not merely available to be used, extracted, or directed. It must remain cared for according to the conditions that let it continue carrying.

This is why dominion belongs after care rather than before it. Control has a place, but only where it serves the availability care preserves.

## Places

Dominion places bounded authority over a domain that remains answerable to the care, limits, and carrying conditions of that domain.

## Holds

Dominion is held by [[Domain]], [[Care]], [[Control]], [[Boundary]], and [[Competence Boundary]]. A domain must be present, control must remain bounded, care must preserve availability, and competence boundary must limit authority before dominion can be named.

## Pairs

Dominion pairs with [[Domination]]. Dominion names authority that remains answerable to the domain it bears; Domination names control detached from care and the carrying conditions of the domain.

## Traces

- [[Domain]]
- [[Care]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Competence Boundary]]

## Nests

Dominion nests within domains where authority directs participation while remaining answerable to what the domain requires in order to keep carrying.

## Reads

Dominion becomes readable where control is held inside care, boundary, and competence, so authority serves the carrying conditions of the domain rather than consuming them.

In a garden, dominion is not the power to make living systems obey any desired form. It is the bounded authority to tend, prune, restrain, support, harvest, and protect in ways that remain answerable to the living conditions of the garden. Care comes before control; control remains legitimate only where it serves care.

## Carries

Dominion carries [[Domination]] — the failure mode where authority detaches from care and begins consuming or overriding the domain it claims to govern.

- [[Domination]]','Dominion Dominion names bounded authority over a domain that remains answerable to the care, limits, and carrying conditions of that domain. Dominion is not domination. Dominion is authority under obligation: the domain is not merely available to be used, extracted, or directed. It must remain cared for according to the conditions that let it continue carrying. This is why dominion belongs after care rather than before it. Control has a place, but only where it serves the availability care preserves. Places Dominion places bounded authority over a domain that remains answerable to the care, limits, and carrying conditions of that domain. Holds Dominion is held by Domain, Care, Control, Boundary, and Competence Boundary. A domain must be present, control must remain bounded, care must preserve availability, and competence boundary must limit authority before dominion can be named. Pairs Dominion pairs with Domination. Dominion names authority that remains answerable to the domain it bears; Domination names control detached from care and the carrying conditions of the domain. Traces Domain Care Control Boundary Competence Boundary Nests Dominion nests within domains where authority directs participation while remaining answerable to what the domain requires in order to keep carrying. Reads Dominion becomes readable where control is held inside care, boundary, and competence, so authority serves the carrying conditions of the domain rather than consuming them. In a garden, dominion is not the power to make living systems obey any desired form. It is the bounded authority to tend, prune, restrain, support, harvest, and protect in ways that remain answerable to the living conditions of the garden. Care comes before control; control remains legitimate only where it serves care. Carries Dominion carries Domination — the failure mode where authority detaches from care and begins consuming or overriding the domain it claims to govern. Domination','Dominion Dominion names bounded authority over a domain that remains answerable to the care, limits, and carrying conditions of that domain. Dominion is not domination.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term',NULL,'[]','[]','["first.boundary","third.care","third.competence-boundary","third.control","third.domain","third.domination"]','{"holds":["third.domain","third.care","third.control","first.boundary","third.competence-boundary"],"traces":["third.domain","third.care","third.control","first.boundary","third.competence-boundary"],"carries":["third.domination"],"pairs":["third.domination"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',299,'sha256:43955815db1bbd9a1dc7f0ff3099273854a43deda5e60329b11c47c39876f116','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.earth-carrying','Earth Carrying','earth-carrying','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Earth Carrying.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/earth-carrying.html','# Earth Carrying

Earth Carrying names the carrying relation through which [[Earth]] holds human life, society, history, invention, and choice within material and ecological consequence. Earth is not only a setting around human systems; Earth Carrying names the condition by which those systems are carried too.

Earth Carrying includes protection. Earth carries by holding exposure within survivable limits: breathable atmosphere, gravity, temperature range, water cycles, food webs, shielding, and repair conditions. These are not scenery around participation; they are prior carrying conditions for participation.

## Places

Earth Carrying places the carrying relation through which [[Earth]] holds human life, society, history, invention, and choice within material and ecological consequence.

## Holds

Earth Carrying is held by [[Earth]], [[Carrying]], [[Dependency]], and [[Invisible]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Earth]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Dependency]]
- [[Invisible]]

## Nests

Earth Carrying nests where Earth is read as a carrier with supportable limits and obligations.

## Reads

Earth Carrying becomes recognisable where built, economic, digital, or institutional systems appear primary while the earthly relation carrying and protecting them remains backgrounded, taken as given, or no longer read.

Earth Carrying also becomes recognisable where long-order earthly carrying is converted into short-order resolution. [[Extractive Acceleration]] diagnoses that conversion when speed appears to belong to the fast system while the slower earthly carrier is drawn down or hidden.
## Carries

- [[Sustenance Field]]
- [[Terms of Service]]
- [[Extractive Acceleration]]
- [[Space-Based Solar Power]]','Earth Carrying Earth Carrying names the carrying relation through which Earth holds human life, society, history, invention, and choice within material and ecological consequence. Earth is not only a setting around human systems; Earth Carrying names the condition by which those systems are carried too. Earth Carrying includes protection. Earth carries by holding exposure within survivable limits: breathable atmosphere, gravity, temperature range, water cycles, food webs, shielding, and repair conditions. These are not scenery around participation; they are prior carrying conditions for participation. Places Earth Carrying places the carrying relation through which Earth holds human life, society, history, invention, and choice within material and ecological consequence. Holds Earth Carrying is held by Earth, Carrying, Dependency, and Invisible. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Earth Carrying Dependency Invisible Nests Earth Carrying nests where Earth is read as a carrier with supportable limits and obligations. Reads Earth Carrying becomes recognisable where built, economic, digital, or institutional systems appear primary while the earthly relation carrying and protecting them remains backgrounded, taken as given, or no longer read. Earth Carrying also becomes recognisable where long order earthly carrying is converted into short order resolution. Extractive Acceleration diagnoses that conversion when speed appears to belong to the fast system while the slower earthly carrier is drawn down or hidden. Carries Sustenance Field Terms of Service Extractive Acceleration Space Based Solar Power','Earth Carrying Earth Carrying names the carrying relation through which Earth holds human life, society, history, invention, and choice within material and ecological consequence. Earth is not…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','natural-world','[]','[]','["first.invisible","second.carrying","second.dependency","third.earth","third.extractive-acceleration","third.space-based-solar-power","third.sustenance-field","third.terms-of-service"]','{"holds":["third.earth","second.carrying","second.dependency","first.invisible"],"traces":["third.earth","second.carrying","second.dependency","first.invisible"],"carries":["third.sustenance-field","third.terms-of-service","third.extractive-acceleration","third.space-based-solar-power"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',241,'sha256:f61b17954b2f37c3897f4bc3c9bf0a16e01045f6ad50c906c9da8df56f847f50','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.earth','Earth','earth','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Earth.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/earth.html','# Earth

Earth names the natural world body within which human participation becomes materially, ecologically, atmospherically, historically, and protectively carried. Earth is not only a location or object; it is the local carrying body through which life, society, sustenance, invention, memory, and choice remain possible.

Earth is not the setting of human activity. Earth is the carrying boundary that keeps human activity possible. Its atmosphere, gravity, water, soil, weather, life systems, and shielding conditions hold exposure within survivable limits. Every built shelter is nested inside this prior shelter.

Historic names preserve inherited reads of Earth. Gaia reads Earth as living and generative carrier. Terra and Tellus read Earth as material ground, land-body, and mother-body. Geo preserves Earth as ground made readable through place, measure, form, and description. These names are not separate sources in the Atlas; they are language traces of how Earth has been faced and carried through human history.

## Places

Earth places the natural world body within which human participation becomes materially, ecologically, atmospherically, historically, and protectively carried.

## Holds

Earth is held by [[Natural World]], [[World]], and [[Carrying]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Natural World]]
- [[World]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Earth nests inside Natural World as the local world-body through which participation is carried.

## Reads

Earth becomes recognisable where human life is read as occurring within a material, ecological, and protective carrying body rather than above, outside, or merely upon a background setting.

Earth also becomes recognisable where its protection has been backgrounded because it is constant. The ordinary face of Earth is life continuing; the trace is the carrying that prevents exposure from becoming terminal.
## Carries

- [[Earth Carrying]]
- [[Sustenance Field]]','Earth Earth names the natural world body within which human participation becomes materially, ecologically, atmospherically, historically, and protectively carried. Earth is not only a location or object; it is the local carrying body through which life, society, sustenance, invention, memory, and choice remain possible. Earth is not the setting of human activity. Earth is the carrying boundary that keeps human activity possible. Its atmosphere, gravity, water, soil, weather, life systems, and shielding conditions hold exposure within survivable limits. Every built shelter is nested inside this prior shelter. Historic names preserve inherited reads of Earth. Gaia reads Earth as living and generative carrier. Terra and Tellus read Earth as material ground, land body, and mother body. Geo preserves Earth as ground made readable through place, measure, form, and description. These names are not separate sources in the Atlas; they are language traces of how Earth has been faced and carried through human history. Places Earth places the natural world body within which human participation becomes materially, ecologically, atmospherically, historically, and protectively carried. Holds Earth is held by Natural World, World, and Carrying. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Natural World World Carrying Nests Earth nests inside Natural World as the local world body through which participation is carried. Reads Earth becomes recognisable where human life is read as occurring within a material, ecological, and protective carrying body rather than above, outside, or merely upon a background setting. Earth also becomes recognisable where its protection has been backgrounded because it is constant. The ordinary face of Earth is life continuing; the trace is the carrying that prevents exposure from becoming terminal. Carries Earth Carrying Sustenance Field','Earth Earth name