INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.enchantment','Enchantment','enchantment','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Path Reads/Enchantment.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/enchantment.html','# Enchantment

Enchantment names altered readability carried through influence. It does not require a supernatural claim; it names the path read where influence changes how something appears, attracts, binds, or opens participation.

## Places

Enchantment places altered readability through influence — the condition where influence changes how something is read so that participation is drawn, constrained, heightened, or misread through that altered read.

## Holds

Enchantment is held by [[Influence]] and [[Readability]]. Influence must be present and readability must be alterable before enchantment can be read as distinct from ordinary influence or ordinary appearance.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Influence]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Enchantment nests within Path Reads as the root condition from which altered-readability reads — Spell, Glamour, Illusion, Binding, Wonder — are derived.

## Reads

Enchantment becomes recognisable where influence changes the readability of a condition so that participation is drawn, constrained, heightened, or misread through that altered read. The path through readability and influence must be entered for enchantment to become readable rather than treated as source power or mere feeling.

## Carries

- [[Spell]]
- [[Glamour]]
- [[Illusion]]
- [[Binding]]
- [[Wonder]]','Enchantment Enchantment names altered readability carried through influence. It does not require a supernatural claim; it names the path read where influence changes how something appears, attracts, binds, or opens participation. Places Enchantment places altered readability through influence — the condition where influence changes how something is read so that participation is drawn, constrained, heightened, or misread through that altered read. Holds Enchantment is held by Influence and Readability. Influence must be present and readability must be alterable before enchantment can be read as distinct from ordinary influence or ordinary appearance. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Influence Readability Nests Enchantment nests within Path Reads as the root condition from which altered readability reads — Spell, Glamour, Illusion, Binding, Wonder — are derived. Reads Enchantment becomes recognisable where influence changes the readability of a condition so that participation is drawn, constrained, heightened, or misread through that altered read. The path through readability and influence must be entered for enchantment to become readable rather than treated as source power or mere feeling. Carries Spell Glamour Illusion Binding Wonder','Enchantment Enchantment names altered readability carried through influence. It does not require a supernatural claim; it names the path read where influence changes how something appears,…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','path-reads','[]','[]','["second.influence","second.readability","third.binding","third.glamour","third.illusion","third.spell","third.wonder"]','{"holds":["second.influence","second.readability"],"traces":["second.influence","second.readability"],"carries":["third.spell","third.glamour","third.illusion","third.binding","third.wonder"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',192,'sha256:8dd7baa1e0a04d0c30b11ca351db9a76c7916ae1ed74b60f47d0134cf5326ed2','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.engineered-coupling','Engineered Coupling','engineered-coupling','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Engineered Coupling.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/engineered-coupling.html','# Engineered Coupling

Engineered coupling is compatible Coupling carried through imposed, constructed, corrected, intentionally arranged, or externally maintained carrying conditions.

## Places

Engineered Coupling places coupling that is deliberately constructed to hold distinct resolved conditions in compatible mutual availability — coupling shaped by constraint and carrying rather than emergent.

## Holds

Engineered Coupling is held by [[Coupling]], [[Carrying]], and [[Constraint]]. Coupling must hold, carrying must continue, and a constraining structure must shape the coupling before it can be read as engineered.

## Pairs

Engineered Coupling pairs with [[Nested Coupling]]: engineered coupling names coupling deliberately constructed to hold distinct resolved conditions in compatible mutual availability through constraint; nested coupling names coupling held within a larger coupling structure — mutual availability that is itself carried within a containing relation. Each requires the other to be locatable — engineered coupling is only readable against the possibility of coupling arising through nesting; nested coupling is only readable against the possibility of deliberately constructed coupling.

## Traces

- [[Coupling]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Constraint]]

## Nests

Engineered Coupling nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which coupling is deliberately structured — the structural ground for Technology Domain and AI domain reads.

## Reads

Engineered coupling becomes readable where constructed carrying preserves availability, bearing, resolution, and dependency order.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bearing]] and [[Resolution]] make coupling possible.

Second: [[Coupling]], [[Carrying]], [[Constraint]], and [[Compatibility]] make arranged continuation evaluable.

Third: [[Engineered Coupling]] places that structural read inside made or externally maintained relation.

## Carries

