INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.externalised-cognition','Externalised Cognition','externalised-cognition','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Cognition/Externalised Cognition.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/externalised-cognition.html','# Externalised Cognition

Externalised cognition names branch-level carrying where cognitive participation is distributed into external structure.

## Places

Externalised Cognition places the condition through which cognitive carrying is extended through a medium — thought, memory, or knowing carried beyond the participant''s body through tool, record, or system.

## Holds

Externalised Cognition is held by [[Cognition]] and [[Medium]]. Cognition must be present and a medium must be able to carry the cognitive condition before externalised extension can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Cognition]]
- [[Medium]]

## Nests

Externalised Cognition nests within the Cognition Field as the path read for cognitive carrying extended through medium — the structural ground for AI, documentation, and knowledge-system reads.

## Reads

Externalised Cognition becomes readable where cognitive participation is carried through an external medium or structure while remaining retraceable as cognition rather than becoming detached output.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] and [[Availability]] must hold enough for cognitive participation to be located outside the body-mind loop.

Second: [[Medium]] and [[Carrying]] make that participation evaluable as externally supported cognition.

Third: [[Externalised Cognition]] places that carrying inside the [[Cognition Field]] as a cognition path read.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Externalised Cognition Externalised cognition names branch level carrying where cognitive participation is distributed into external structure. Places Externalised Cognition places the condition through which cognitive carrying is extended through a medium — thought, memory, or knowing carried beyond the participant''s body through tool, record, or system. Holds Externalised Cognition is held by Cognition and Medium. Cognition must be present and a medium must be able to carry the cognitive condition before externalised extension can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Cognition Medium Nests Externalised Cognition nests within the Cognition Field as the path read for cognitive carrying extended through medium — the structural ground for AI, documentation, and knowledge system reads. Reads Externalised Cognition becomes readable where cognitive participation is carried through an external medium or structure while remaining retraceable as cognition rather than becoming detached output. The dependency movement is: First: Boundary and Availability must hold enough for cognitive participation to be located outside the body mind loop. Second: Medium and Carrying make that participation evaluable as externally supported cognition. Third: Externalised Cognition places that carrying inside the Cognition Field as a cognition path read. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Externalised Cognition Externalised cognition names branch level carrying where cognitive participation is distributed into external structure. Places Externalised Cognition places the condition…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','cognition','[]','[]','["second.medium","third.cognition"]','{"holds":["third.cognition","second.medium"],"traces":["third.cognition","second.medium"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}