INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.faith-boundary','Faith Boundary','faith-boundary','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Faith/Faith Boundary.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/faith-boundary.html','# Faith Boundary

Faith Boundary names a carried boundary around relation whose content is not yet structurally readable.

It is above the current read, not above [[Relation]].

## Places

Faith Boundary places the located limit at which relation is recognised but what it carries cannot yet be read — the boundary around unresolvable readability held by faith.

## Holds

Faith Boundary is held by [[Faith Read|Faith]], [[Relation]], [[Boundary]], [[Bearing]], [[Delayed Availability]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Faith must hold the condition and a boundary must locate the limit of current readability before the unresolvable edge can be named.

## Pairs

Faith Boundary pairs with [[Faith Read]]. Faith Boundary names the edge at which faith''s claim becomes untestable at scope; Faith Read names the carried commitment that meets that edge.

## Traces

- [[Faith Read|Faith]]
- [[Relation]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Delayed Availability]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Faith Boundary nests within the Faith Field as the closure-scope condition through which faith holds what cannot yet be read.

## Reads

Faith Boundary becomes readable where relation is recognised, what it is cannot yet be read, and a carried boundary allows bearing before resolution, recurrence, or higher-order return becomes available.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Relation]], [[Boundary]], and [[Bearing]] allow unreadable relation to be recognised and carried without defining its content.

Second: [[Delayed Availability]] and [[Closure Scope]] distinguish unavailable structure from present readability.

Third: [[Faith Boundary]] places this carried boundary inside [[Faith Field]] without making it primitive or source authority.

Movement:

```text
relation is recognised
-> what it is cannot yet be read
-> faith carries a boundary around unavailable relation
-> bearing continues before resolution
-> recurrence may later make a read available
-> the read may return as recognition, correction, release, or practice
```

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Faith Boundary Faith Boundary names a carried boundary around relation whose content is not yet structurally readable. It is above the current read, not above Relation. Places Faith Boundary places the located limit at which relation is recognised but what it carries cannot yet be read — the boundary around unresolvable readability held by faith. Holds Faith Boundary is held by Faith Read, Relation, Boundary, Bearing, Delayed Availability, and Closure Scope. Faith must hold the condition and a boundary must locate the limit of current readability before the unresolvable edge can be named. Pairs Faith Boundary pairs with Faith Read. Faith Boundary names the edge at which faith''s claim becomes untestable at scope; Faith Read names the carried commitment that meets that edge. Traces Faith Read Relation Boundary Bearing Delayed Availability Closure Scope Nests Faith Boundary nests within the Faith Field as the closure scope condition through which faith holds what cannot yet be read. Reads Faith Boundary becomes readable where relation is recognised, what it is cannot yet be read, and a carried boundary allows bearing before resolution, recurrence, or higher order return becomes available. The dependency movement is: First: Relation, Boundary, and Bearing allow unreadable relation to be recognised and carried without defining its content. Second: Delayed Availability and Closure Scope distinguish unavailable structure from present readability. Third: Faith Boundary places this carried boundary inside Faith Field without making it primitive or source authority. Movement: Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Faith Boundary Faith Boundary names a carried boundary around relation whose content is not yet structurally readable. It is above the current read, not above Relation.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','faith','[]','[]','["first.bearing","first.boundary","first.relation","se