INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.faith-field','Faith Field','faith-field','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Faith/Faith Field.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/faith-field.html','# Faith Field

Faith Field names the recurring field of participation through which carried commitment toward unavailable resolution, mystery, and sacred orientation become readable as organised experience.

## Places

Faith Field places a recurring field of participation.

## Holds

Faith Field is held by [[Field of Participation]], [[Organic Field]], [[Faith Read|Faith]], [[Bearing]], [[Delayed Availability]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Field of Participation must structure a recurring scope and bearing must hold what cannot yet be read before the faith field can be named.

## Pairs

Faith Field pairs with [[Knowledge Field]]. Faith Field names the field of carried commitment toward unavailable resolution; Knowledge Field names the field of carried knowing tested through recurrence and compatibility. Each requires the other to be distinguishable: faith holds what knowledge cannot yet reach; knowledge tests what faith carries.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Organic Field]]
- [[Faith Read|Faith]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Delayed Availability]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Faith Field nests as a public field container. Detailed branch notes remain compressed as working material.

[[Faith Boundary]]
[[Faith Read]]
[[Hope]]

## Reads

Faith Field becomes recognisable where unavailable resolution, mystery, sacred orientation, or carried commitment organises participation without becoming source authority.

At the [[Translation Boundary]], [[Availability]], [[Hidden Bearing]], [[Invisible Bearing]], [[Hope]], [[Higher Faith]], and [[Boundary]] can become terminal to this field as local reads such as [[Faith Read]], [[Faith Boundary]], and [[Hope]].

## Carries

Faith Field carries [[Hope]] — the structural read through which carried commitment is held at this field scope. Nested reads are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.
- [[Hope]]','Faith Field Faith Field names the recurring field of participation through which carried commitment toward unavailable resolution, mystery, and sacred orientation become readable as organised experience. Places Faith Field places a recurring field of participation. Holds Faith Field is held by Field of Participation, Organic Field, Faith Read, Bearing, Delayed Availability, and Closure Scope. Field of Participation must structure a recurring scope and bearing must hold what cannot yet be read before the faith field can be named. Pairs Faith Field pairs with Knowledge Field. Faith Field names the field of carried commitment toward unavailable resolution; Knowledge Field names the field of carried knowing tested through recurrence and compatibility. Each requires the other to be distinguishable: faith holds what knowledge cannot yet reach; knowledge tests what faith carries. Traces Field of Participation Organic Field Faith Read Bearing Delayed Availability Closure Scope Nests Faith Field nests as a public field container. Detailed branch notes remain compressed as working material. Faith Boundary Faith Read Hope Reads Faith Field becomes recognisable where unavailable resolution, mystery, sacred orientation, or carried commitment organises participation without becoming source authority. At the Translation Boundary, Availability, Hidden Bearing, Invisible Bearing, Hope, Higher Faith, and Boundary can become terminal to this field as local reads such as Faith Read, Faith Boundary, and Hope. Carries Faith Field carries Hope — the structural read through which carried commitment is held at this field scope. Nested reads are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground. Hope','Faith Field Faith Field names the recurring field of participation through which carried commitment toward unavailable resolution, mystery, and sacred orientation become readable as organised…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','faith','[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.closure-scope","second.delayed-availability","third.faith-read","third.field-of-participation","third.hope","third.knowledge-field","third.organic-field"]','{"holds":["third.field-of-participation","third.organic-field","third.faith-read","first.bearing","second.delayed-availability","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.field-of-participation","third.organic-field","third.faith-read","first.bearing","second.delayed-availability","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["third.hope"],"pairs":["third.knowledge-field"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',246,'sha256:168717b7ad22325702640cc5ad4d5ba04fc359a2627848b03f7c1c01d507025e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.faith-read','Faith Read','faith-read','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Faith/Faith Read.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/faith-read.html','# Faith Read

Faith Read names the field-level read of carried commitment toward higher order, unavailable resolution, or relation that exceeds the current boundary of structural readability.

Faith is above the current read, not above [[Relation]].

## Places

Faith Read places the third-order field condition through which carried commitment, mystery, ritual, and sacred orientation are held without requiring full readability at the current closure scope.

## Holds

Faith Read is held by [[Branch]], [[Readability]], [[Delayed Availability]], [[Bearing]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Bearing must hold what cannot yet be read, and delayed availability must be the structural condition before carried commitment can be named as faith.

## Pairs

Faith Read pairs with [[Faith Boundary]]. Faith Read names carried commitment through bearing that holds under delayed availability; Faith Boundary names the edge at which that commitment meets what cannot be resolved at scope.

## Traces

- [[Branch]]
- [[Readability]]
- [[Delayed Availability]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Faith Read nests within the Faith Field branch as the field-level condition for all faith, mystery, and sacred-orientation reads.

[[Faith Boundary]]
[[Hope]]

## Reads

Faith Read becomes readable where carried commitment remains oriented toward unavailable resolution without making what exceeds the current read into source authority.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] and [[Bearing]] hold relation where resolution is not fully available.

Second: [[Readability]] and [[Delayed Availability]] distinguish present read from unavailable resolution.

Third: [[Faith Read|Faith]] places carried commitment, mystery, ritual, sacred orientation, [[Faith Boundary]], and [[Hope]] inside [[Faith Field]] without making them source authority.

## Carries

- [[Faith Boundary]]
- [[Hope]]','Faith Read Faith Read names the field level read of carried commitment toward higher order, unavailable resolution, or relation that exceeds the current boundary of structural readability. Faith is above the current read, not above Relation. Places Faith Read places the third order field condition through which carried commitment, mystery, ritual, and sacred orientation are held without requiring full readability at the current closure scope. Holds Faith Read is held by Branch, Readability, Delayed Availability, Bearing, and Closure Scope. Bearing must hold what cannot yet be read, and delayed availability must be the structural condition before carried commitment can be named as faith. Pairs Faith Read pairs with Faith Boundary. Faith Read names carried commitment through bearing that holds under delayed availability; Faith Boundary names the edge at which that commitment meets what cannot be resolved at scope. Traces Branch Readability Delayed Availability Bearing Closure Scope Nests Faith Read nests within the Faith Field branch as the field level condition for all faith, mystery, and sacred orientation reads. Faith Boundary Hope Reads Faith Read becomes readable where carried commitment remains oriented toward unavailable resolution without making what exceeds the current read into source authority. The dependency movement is: First: Boundary and Bearing hold relation where resolution is not fully available. Second: Readability and Delayed Availability distinguish present read from unavailable resolution. Third: Faith Read places carried commitment, mystery, ritual, sacred orientation, Faith Boundary, and Hope inside Faith Field without making them source authority. Carries Faith Boundary Hope','Faith Read Faith Read names the field level read of carried commitment toward higher order, unavailable resolution, or relation that exceeds the current boundary of structural readability. Faith…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','faith','[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.closure-scope","second.delayed-availability","second.readability","third.branch","third.faith-boundary","third.hope"]','{"holds":["third.branch","second.readability","second.delayed-availability","first.bearing","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.branch","second.readability","second.delayed-availability","first.bearing","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["third.faith-boundary","third.hope"],"pairs":["third.faith-boundary"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',247,'sha256:4a364d250e21a38fa46c9db3f73cdc7a4651a6611dfe793acb73d9ad7b792aa0','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.fatigue-boundary','Fatigue Boundary','fatigue-boundary','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Body/Applied Reads/Fatigue Boundary.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/fatigue-boundary.html','# Fatigue Boundary

Fatigue Boundary reads a local body case where fatigue marks the limit of available effort and asks whether action should pause, reduce, continue, or receive support.

## Places

Fatigue Boundary places the applied read of the located limit on available carrying — the closure scope at which continued participation becomes incompatible with current capacity.

## Holds

Fatigue Boundary is held by [[Applied Read]], [[Fatigue]], [[Capacity]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Control]]. Fatigue must be readable and capacity must be locally evaluable before the limit on compatible carrying can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Fatigue Boundary names the applied read that locates the edge of compatible continuation under fatigue; no contrasting applied read exists in the Body field at this time.

## Traces

- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Fatigue]]
- [[Capacity]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Control]]

- [[Body]]
## Nests

Fatigue Boundary nests within the Body Field as an applied read of Fatigue at the boundary of compatible carrying.

## Reads

Fatigue Boundary becomes readable where reduced availability is sensed and the next action either respects, adjusts, supports, or overrides that limit.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], and [[Strain]] must hold enough for fatigue to become readable as a limit.

Second: [[Capacity]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]] make continued effort evaluable as supportable or incompatible.

Third: [[Fatigue Boundary]] tests that condition inside the [[Body Field]] as an applied body read.

Case Movement:

```text
fatigue becomes readable
-> boundary of available effort is located
-> capacity for continued action is checked
-> action adjusts, pauses, or receives support
-> or the read is overridden and strain becomes incompatible
```

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Fatigue Boundary Fatigue Boundary reads a local body case where fatigue marks the limit of available effort and asks whether action should pause, reduce, continue, or receive support. Places Fatigue Boundary places the applied read of the located limit on available carrying — the closure scope at which continued participation becomes incompatible with current capacity. Holds Fatigue Boundary is held by Applied Read, Fatigue, Capacity, Compatibility, and Control. Fatigue must be readable and capacity must be locally evaluable before the limit on compatible carrying can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Fatigue Boundary names the applied read that locates the edge of compatible continuation under fatigue; no contrasting applied read exists in the Body field at this time. Traces Applied Read Fatigue Capacity Compatibility Control Body Nests Fatigue Boundary nests within the Body Field as an applied read of Fatigue at the boundary of compatible carrying. Reads Fatigue Boundary becomes readable where reduced availability is sensed and the next action either respects, adjusts, supports, or overrides that limit. The dependency movement is: First: Boundary, Availability, and Strain must hold enough for fatigue to become readable as a limit. Second: Capacity, Compatibility, and Closure Scope make continued effort evaluable as supportable or incompatible. Third: Fatigue Boundary tests that condition inside the Body Field as an applied body read. Case Movement: Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Fatigue Boundary Fatigue Boundary reads a local body case where fatigue marks the limit of available effort and asks whether action should pause, reduce, continue, or receive support. Places…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','body','[]','[]','["second.capacity","second.compatibility","third.applied-read","third.body","third.control","third.fatigue"]','{"holds":["third.applied-read","third.fatigue","second.capacity","second.compatibility","third.control"],"traces":["third.applied-read","third.fatigue","second.capacity","second.compatibility","third.control","third.body"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',236,'sha256:011d139a77ce05401761cc820834aa580d719e87259cd2dd1e848a08e4e7e6bd','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.fatigue','Fatigue','fatigue','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Body/Fatigue.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/fatigue.html','# Fatigue

Fatigue names embodied reduction in available carrying where continued participation requires rest, pacing, support, release, or recovery.

## Places

Fatigue places embodied reduction in available carrying where continued participation requires rest, pacing, support, release, or recovery.

## Holds

Fatigue is held by [[Body]], [[Strain]], [[Load]], [[Capacity]], [[Availability]], [[Carrying]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Accumulated load must reduce available capacity before the limit on continued participation can be named as fatigue.

## Pairs

Fatigue pairs with [[Recovery]]. Fatigue names the reduction in available carrying through accumulated load; Recovery names the restoration of compatible carrying following fatigue or injury.

## Traces

- [[Body]]
- [[Strain]]
- [[Load]]
- [[Capacity]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Fatigue nests within the Body Field as the structural condition through which accumulated load reduces what can be carried — the ground for recovery, fatigue boundary, and capacity reads.

## Reads

Fatigue becomes readable where accumulated load reduces available capacity and changes what the body can carry without further incompatibility.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Strain]] reduces available bearing.

Second: [[Load]], [[Capacity]], [[Carrying]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]] make the limit on continued participation evaluable.

Third: [[Fatigue]] places that structural read inside the body branch.

## Carries

Fatigue carries [[Recovery]] and [[Fatigue Boundary]]. Recovery names the restoration of compatible carrying following fatigue; Fatigue Boundary names the located limit at which continued participation becomes incompatible with current capacity.

- [[Recovery]]
- [[Fatigue Boundary]]','Fatigue Fatigue names embodied reduction in available carrying where continued participation requires rest, pacing, support, release, or recovery. Places Fatigue places embodied reduction in available carrying where continued participation requires rest, pacing, support, release, or recovery. Holds Fatigue is held by Body, Strain, Load, Capacity, Availability, Carrying, Compatibility, and Closure Scope. Accumulated load must reduce available capacity before the limit on continued participation can be named as fatigue. Pairs Fatigue pairs with Recovery. Fatigue names the reduction in available carrying through accumulated load; Recovery names the restoration of compatible carrying following fatigue or injury. Traces Body Strain Load Capacity Availability Carrying Compatibility Closure Scope Nests Fatigue nests within the Body Field as the structural condition through which accumulated load reduces what can be carried — the ground for recovery, fatigue boundary, and capacity reads. Reads Fatigue becomes readable where accumulated load reduces available capacity and changes what the body can carry without further incompatibility. The dependency movement is: First: Strain reduces available bearing. Second: Load, Capacity, Carrying, Compatibility, and Closure Scope make the limit on continued participation evaluable. Third: Fatigue places that structural read inside the body branch. Carries Fatigue carries Recovery and Fatigue Boundary. Recovery names the restoration of compatible carrying following fatigue; Fatigue Boundary names the located limit at which continued participation becomes incompatible with current capacity. Recovery Fatigue Boundary','Fatigue Fatigue names embodied reduction in available carrying where continued participation requires rest, pacing, support, release, or recovery. Places Fatigue places embodied reduction in…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','body','[]','[]','["first.availability","first.strain","second.capacity","second.carrying","second.closure-scope","second.compatibility","second.load","third.body","third.fatigue-boundary","third.recovery"]','{"holds":["third.body","first.strain","second.load","second.capacity","first.availability","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.body","first.strain","second.load","second.capacity","first.availability","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["third.recovery","third.fatigue-boundary"],"pairs":["third.recovery"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',222,'sha256:7ce71979cc4905a1a965b7071d98a49b5f09ac3530f805ae2ff75324a6e0ab29','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.feeling','Feeling','feeling','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Body/Feeling.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/feeling.html','# Feeling

Feeling names embodied availability becoming readable to a participant.

A feeling is real as a read, but it does not decide cause, meaning, or action by itself. It shows that relation has become locally available.

## Places

Feeling places the condition through which the body makes change in availability detectable — the structural node where bodily sensing becomes a readable boundary condition.

## Holds

Feeling is held by [[Body]], [[Sensing]], [[Availability]], [[Boundary]], [[Strain]], and [[Readability]]. Bodily change must locate a detectable boundary before the availability of strain can be read as feeling.

## Pairs

Feeling pairs with [[Emotion]]. Feeling names available detection of bodily strain; Emotion names the condition where that detection gathers into pattern and presses bearing.

## Traces

- [[Body]]
- [[Sensing]]
- [[Availability]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Strain]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Feeling nests within the Body Field as the condition through which availability becomes detectable — the structural ground for emotion, sensation, and affect reads.

## Reads

Feeling becomes readable where embodied change is sensed as locally available to the participant before it has been fully patterned, named, expressed, or acted on.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Availability]], [[Boundary]], and [[Strain]] make embodied change present enough to be carried.

Second: [[Readability]] makes that embodied availability available to read.

Third: [[Feeling]] places sensed availability inside [[Body Field]] with bridge pressure from mind, relation, and expression.

Movement:

```text
body detects change
-> availability becomes felt
-> feeling can be borne
-> meaning and action remain to be checked
```

## Carries

Feeling carries [[Emotion]]. Where feeling gathers enough pattern and recognition, available detection becomes patterned pressure on bearing.

- [[Emotion]]','Feeling Feeling names embodied availability becoming readable to a participant. A feeling is real as a read, but it does not decide cause, meaning, or action by itself. It shows that relation has become locally available. Places Feeling places the condition through which the body makes change in availability detectable — the structural node where bodily sensing becomes a readable boundary condition. Holds Feeling is held by Body, Sensing, Availability, Boundary, Strain, and Readability. Bodily change must locate a detectable boundary before the availability of strain can be read as feeling. Pairs Feeling pairs with Emotion. Feeling names available detection of bodily strain; Emotion names the condition where that detection gathers into pattern and presses bearing. Traces Body Sensing Availability Boundary Strain Readability Nests Feeling nests within the Body Field as the condition through which availability becomes detectable — the structural ground for emotion, sensation, and affect reads. Reads Feeling becomes readable where embodied change is sensed as locally available to the participant before it has been fully patterned, named, expressed, or acted on. The dependency movement is: First: Availability, Boundary, and Strain make embodied change present enough to be carried. Second: Readability makes that embodied availability available to read. Third: Feeling places sensed availability inside Body Field with bridge pressure from mind, relation, and expression. Movement: Carries Feeling carries Emotion. Where feeling gathers enough pattern and recognition, available detection becomes patterned pressure on bearing. Emotion','Feeling Feeling names embodied availability becoming readable to a participant. A feeling is real as a read, but it does not decide cause, meaning, or action by itself.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','body','[]','[]','["first.availability","first.boundary","first.strain","second.readability","third.body","third.emotion","third.sensing"]','{"holds":["third.body","third.sensing","first.availability","first.boundary","first.strain","second.readability"],"traces":["third.body","third.sensing","first.availability","first.boundary","first.strain","second.readability"],"carries":["third.emotion"],"pairs":["third.emotion"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',236,'sha256:9e2655f40b90f2f390d3b8bba69e22021e7fb933fac0e8a7498b3a3eab6544bc','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.field-availability-pattern','Field Availability Pattern','field-availability-pattern','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Field Availability Pattern.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/field-availability-pattern.html','# Field Availability Pattern

Field Availability Pattern names recurring physical-field reads where availability changes through boundary, constraint, traversal, visibility, bearing, or scale.

Field Availability Pattern names that availability changes. [[Field Bearing]] names where changed field availability bears on traversal, escape, attraction, closure, visibility, or measurable path.

## Places

Field Availability Pattern places the structural pattern through which field-bearing conditions make availability readable — the recurrent structural shape of how fields present their carrying to readability.

## Holds

Field Availability Pattern is held by [[Physical Field Conditions]], [[Pattern]], [[Field Bearing]], [[Invisible Bearing]], and [[Natural World]]. Physical field conditions must hold, bearing must be present in the field, and pattern must gather before the structural shape of field availability can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
- [[Pattern]]
- [[Field Bearing]]
- [[Invisible Bearing]]
- [[Natural World]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Field Availability Pattern nests within Physical Field Conditions as the structural pattern condition that makes field-bearing availability readable.

## Reads

Field Availability Pattern becomes readable where a physical-field condition changes what can escape, couple, traverse, appear, bear, or be measured.

Derivation:

[[Relation Read]] names relation read as joined spread under a shared condition.

[[Availability]] names what becomes present enough to participate in evaluation.

[[Pattern]] names recurrence made readable through compatible closure.

Field Availability Pattern names recurring reads of availability changing within field conditions.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Relation Read]] and [[Availability]] make altered physical-field availability readable.

Second: [[Field Bearing]], [[Visibility]], [[Invisible Bearing]], and [[Closure Scope]] make the alteration locally evaluable.

Third: [[Field Availability Pattern]] places that structural read inside natural-world physical-field conditions.

Pattern Forms:

- Apparent clearance: [[Light]]
- Constrained clearance: [[Gravity]]
- Boundary-limited availability: [[Black Hole]]
- Arranged-boundary availability: [[Casimir Plates]]
- Low-interaction traversal: [[Neutrino]]
- Visibility-limited bearing / invisible bearing: [[Dark Matter]]
- Expansion-scale clearance: [[Dark Energy]]
- Indirect detection: currently visible through [[Neutrino]], [[Dark Matter]], and [[Dark Energy]]
- Scale-dependent visibility: currently visible across [[Light]], [[Gravity]], [[Black Hole]], [[Casimir Plates]], [[Neutrino]], [[Dark Matter]], and [[Dark Energy]]

Pattern Movement:

```text
field condition
-> availability changes
-> changed availability bears on boundary, constraint, traversal, coupling, visibility, measurement, or scale
-> read becomes apparent, indirect, measurable, limited, or scale-bound
```

Polarity Read:

[[Cosmic Polarity Read]] is an applied comparison, not a new field pattern.

It uses [[Resolution Polarity]] and [[Invisible Bearing]] to compare physical-field cases:

- [[Light]] as apparent clearance.
- [[Gravity]] as constrained clearance.
- [[Dark Matter]] as applied [[Invisible Bearing]].
- [[Dark Energy]] as expansion-scale clearance.
- [[Black Hole]] as boundary-limited non-return.

This comparison remains third-order and speculative. It does not claim that black holes create dark matter, dark energy, or universes.

## Carries

