INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.glamour','Glamour','glamour','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Path Reads/Glamour.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/glamour.html','# Glamour

Glamour names enchantment altering appearance or attraction. It is not beauty by itself; it is altered readability through which what is visible or presented draws participation beyond what direct support alone would carry.

## Places

Glamour places the specific enchantment of altered appearance — where visibility and form carry influence beyond what the underlying support would draw on its own.

## Holds

Glamour is held by [[Enchantment]], [[Visibility]], and [[Form]]. Influence must already alter readability, appearance must be visible, and form must carry before glamour can be read as distinct from beauty or ordinary attractiveness.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Enchantment]]
- [[Visibility]]
- [[Form]]

## Nests

Glamour nests within the enchantment cluster as the appearance-altering path read — the specific mode where enchantment works through visible form rather than through constraint or opening.

## Reads

Glamour becomes recognisable where appearance or presented form carries influence by changing how participation is drawn toward the read. The path through enchantment, visibility, and form must be entered for glamour to become readable rather than mistaken for beauty itself.

## Carries

