INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.governing','Governing','governing','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Placement Modes/Governing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/governing.html','# Governing

Governing names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through direction, constraint, rule, decision, or maintained order.

## Places

Governing places the mode where participation is primarily carried through direction, constraint, rule, or maintained order — where a scope is organised by decisions that limit or coordinate what can happen within it.

## Holds

Governing is held by [[Placement Mode]], [[Constraint]], [[Closure Scope]], and [[Resolution]]. A mode of participation must exist, constraint must be operable, a scope must be bounded, and resolution must be available before direction and order can be placed as the primary mode.

## Pairs

Governing pairs with [[Caring]]. Governing directs and constrains participation within a scope; Caring preserves and repairs the bearing that scope requires.

## Traces

- [[Placement Mode]]
- [[Constraint]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Resolution]]

## Nests

Governing nests within Placement Modes as the ordering mode — where the primary movement is directing, limiting, or coordinating participation rather than preserving, transmitting, or transforming it.

## Reads

Governing becomes recognisable where a note is primarily placed by directed carrying that limits, orders, decides, or coordinates participation within a scope.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Governing Governing names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through direction, constraint, rule, decision, or maintained order. Places Governing places the mode where participation is primarily carried through direction, constraint, rule, or maintained order — where a scope is organised by decisions that limit or coordinate what can happen within it. Holds Governing is held by Placement Mode, Constraint, Closure Scope, and Resolution. A mode of participation must exist, constraint must be operable, a scope must be bounded, and resolution must be available before direction and order can be placed as the primary mode. Pairs Governing pairs with Caring. Governing directs and constrains participation within a scope; Caring preserves and repairs the bearing that scope requires. Traces Placement Mode Constraint Closure Scope Resolution Nests Governing nests within Placement Modes as the ordering mode — where the primary movement is directing, limiting, or coordinating participation rather than preserving, transmitting, or transforming it. Reads Governing becomes recognisable where a note is primarily placed by directed carrying that limits, orders, decides, or coordinates participation within a scope. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Governing Governing names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through direction, constraint, rule, decision, or maintained order. Places Governing places the mode where…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','placement-modes','[]','[]','["first.resolution","second.closure-scope","second.constraint","third.caring","third.placement-mode"]','{"holds":["third.placement-mode","second.constraint","second.closure-scope","first.resolution"],"traces":["third.placement-mode","second.constraint","second.closure-scope","first.resolution"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.caring"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',187,'sha256:7a6a1c698c693d473b041fc426829a716b4829b27c26e7175475ab931f98e4fb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.gravity','Gravity','gravity','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Gravity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/gravity.html','# Gravity

Gravity names a natural-world physical-field read of field bearing where located clearance is constrained by mass-energy relation, altering availability of traversal, bearing, escape, and measurable path.

This note places gravity as a third-order physical-field read without making it source structure.

## Places

Gravity places the physical field condition through which mass-bearing relation makes availability structured toward a centre — the natural-world read of field bearing pulling available participation.

## Holds

Gravity is held by [[Natural World Field]], [[Physical]], [[Physical Field Conditions]], [[Field Bearing]], [[Field Availability Pattern]], and [[Natural World]]. Physical field conditions must hold and field bearing must structure availability before the centring condition can be named as gravity.

## Pairs

Gravity pairs with [[Dark Energy]]. Gravity names the centring and attracting field-bearing condition; Dark Energy names the expanding condition that works against gravitational structuring at cosmic scale.

## Traces

- [[Natural World Field]]
- [[Physical]]
- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
- [[Field Bearing]]
- [[Field Availability Pattern]]
- [[Natural World]]

## Nests

Gravity nests within Physical Field Conditions as the centring field-bearing condition — one physical-field case in the Cosmic Polarity Read.

## Reads

Gravity becomes readable where physical-field conditions bear on traversal so that orbit, return, escape, load, or measurement becomes altered at a closure scope.

Derivation:

[[Physical Field Conditions]] supplies physical-field placement.

[[Field Availability Pattern]] supplies the recurring physical-field availability pattern.

[[Clearance]] supplies held separation.

[[Space]] supplies located clearance.

Gravity names the physical-field read where located clearance is constrained and becomes measurable through altered traversal, bearing, escape, or path.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Clearance]], [[Space]], [[Relation Read]], [[Availability]], and [[Bearing]] make gravitational relation structurally readable.

Second: [[Readability]], [[Traversal]], [[Constraint]], and [[Closure Scope]] make altered path, load, orbit, and escape evaluable.

Third: [[Gravity]] places [[Field Bearing]] inside [[Natural World Field]] and [[Physical Field Conditions]] as a physical-field read.

Related Applied Read:

[[Cosmic Polarity Read]] may use this note as one physical-field case governed by [[Resolution Polarity]].

## Carries

Gravity carries [[Dark Energy]], [[Dark Matter]], and [[Black Hole]] — conditions that require gravitational field-bearing to hold before they can be named: the expanding opposition, the invisible bearing, and the terminal closure.

- [[Dark Energy]]
- [[Dark Matter]]
- [[Black Hole]]','Gravity Gravity names a natural world physical field read of field bearing where located clearance is constrained by mass energy relation, altering availability of traversal, bearing, escape, and measurable path. This note places gravity as a third order physical field read without making it source structure. Places Gravity places the physical field condition through which mass bearing relation makes availability structured toward a centre — the natural world read of field bearing pulling available participation. Holds Gravity is held by Natural World Field, Physical, Physical Field Conditions, Field Bearing, Field Availability Pattern, and Natural World. Physical field conditions must hold and field bearing must structure availability before the centring condition can be named as gravity. Pairs Gravity pairs with Dark Energy. Gravity names the centring and attracting field bearing condition; Dark Energy names the expanding condition that works against gravitational structuring at cosmic scale. Traces Natural World Field Physical Physical Field Conditions Field Bearing Field Availability Pattern Natural World Nests Gravity nests within Physical Field Conditions as the centring field bearing condition — one physical field case in the Cosmic Polarity Read. Reads Gravity becomes readable where physical field conditions bear on traversal so that orbit, return, escape, load, or measurement becomes altered at a closure scope. Derivation: Physical Field Conditions supplies physical field placement. Field Availability Pattern supplies the recurring physical field availability pattern. Clearance supplies held separation. Space supplies located clearance. Gravity names the physical field read where located clearance is constrained and becomes measurable through altered traversal, bearing, escape, or path. The dependency movement is: First: Clearance, Space, Relation Read, Availability, and Bearing make gravitational relation structurally readable. Second: R