INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.locating','Locating','locating','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Placement Modes/Locating.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/locating.html','# Locating

Locating names the placement mode where participation is primarily carried through position, boundary, place, or situated availability.

## Places

Locating places the mode where participation is primarily carried through position, boundary, or situated availability — where something is placed by where it is, where it can be entered, or what boundary situates it.

## Holds

Locating is held by [[Placement Mode]], [[Boundary]], [[Space]], and [[Closure Scope]]. A mode of participation must exist, space must be available, boundaries must situate position, and a scope must bound the location before situated placement can be placed as the primary mode.

## Pairs

Locating pairs with [[Moving]]. Locating names where something is; Moving names how it traverses from there.

## Traces

- [[Placement Mode]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Space]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Locating nests within Placement Modes as the positional mode — where the primary movement is situating participation within a bounded place rather than traversing, transforming, or transmitting it.

## Reads

Locating becomes recognisable where a note is primarily placed by where something is, where it can be entered, where it belongs, or what boundary situates it.

## Carries

