INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.maintained-coupling','Maintained Coupling','maintained-coupling','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Maintained Coupling.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/maintained-coupling.html','# Maintained Coupling

Maintained coupling is compatible Coupling sustained through corrective or supportive Bearing.

## Places

Maintained Coupling places the condition through which distinct coupled relation is held stable through recurrence — coupling that sustains across encounters and strain.

## Holds

Maintained Coupling is held by [[Coupling]], [[Bearing]], and [[Recurrence]]. Coupling must be present, bearing must hold it, and recurrence must establish the pattern before coupling can be read as maintained.

## Pairs

Maintained Coupling pairs with [[Maintained Coupling Failure]]. Maintained Coupling names the held condition; Maintained Coupling Failure names its loss at scope.

## Traces

- [[Coupling]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Recurrence]]

## Nests

Maintained Coupling nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which coupling is held as a recurring structural feature of relation.

## Reads

Maintained coupling becomes readable where compatible recurrence depends on corrective or supportive bearing.

## Carries

- [[Maintained Coupling Failure]]
- [[Tend]]

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bearing]] and [[Resolution]] make coupling possible.

Second: [[Coupling]], [[Carrying]], [[Recurrence]], and [[Compatibility]] make continuing coupling evaluable.

Third: [[Maintained Coupling]] places that structural read inside supportive or corrective bearing relations.','Maintained Coupling Maintained coupling is compatible Coupling sustained through corrective or supportive Bearing. Places Maintained Coupling places the condition through which distinct coupled relation is held stable through recurrence — coupling that sustains across encounters and strain. Holds Maintained Coupling is held by Coupling, Bearing, and Recurrence. Coupling must be present, bearing must hold it, and recurrence must establish the pattern before coupling can be read as maintained. Pairs Maintained Coupling pairs with Maintained Coupling Failure. Maintained Coupling names the held condition; Maintained Coupling Failure names its loss at scope. Traces Coupling Bearing Recurrence Nests Maintained Coupling nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which coupling is held as a recurring structural feature of relation. Reads Maintained coupling becomes readable where compatible recurrence depends on corrective or supportive bearing. Carries Maintained Coupling Failure Tend The dependency movement is: First: Bearing and Resolution make coupling possible. Second: Coupling, Carrying, Recurrence, and Compatibility make continuing coupling evaluable. Third: Maintained Coupling places that structural read inside supportive or corrective bearing relations.','Maintained Coupling Maintained coupling is compatible Coupling sustained through corrective or supportive Bearing. Places Maintained Coupling places the condition through which distinct coupled…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["first.bearing","practice.tend","second.coupling","second.recurrence","third.maintained-coupling-failure"]','{"holds":["second.coupling","first.bearing","second.recurrence"],"traces":["second.coupling","first.bearing","second.recurrence"],"carries":["third.maintained-coupling-failure","practice.tend"],"pairs":["third.maintained-coupling-failure"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',169,'sha256:0740c9bca17d7cd8ff90ce04d9070bde19aee6c5163b3660dd007043ce2a02f4','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.making-field','Making Field','making-field','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Making/Making Field.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/making-field.html','# Making Field

Making Field names the recurring field of participation through which producing, building, tool use, and bringing form into existence become readable as organised experience.

## Places

Making Field places a recurring field of participation.

## Holds

Making Field is held by [[Field of Participation]], [[Organic Field]], [[Making]], [[Participation]], [[Form]], and [[Carrying]]. Field of Participation must structure a recurring scope and relation must be carryable into form before the making field can be named.

## Pairs

Making Field pairs with [[Natural World Field]]. Making Field names the field of intentional form — relation carried into arrangement through action and craft; Natural World Field names the field of organic form — relation carried into arrangement through natural order without intentional design.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Organic Field]]
- [[Making]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Form]]
- [[Carrying]]

## Nests

Making Field nests as a public field container. Detailed branch notes remain compressed as working material.

[[Tool]]
[[Weapon]]
[[Hidden Carrying]]

## Reads

Making Field becomes recognisable where producing, building, tool use, craft, or formed arrangement organises participation through what is made available.

At the [[Translation Boundary]], [[Form]], [[Function]], [[Tool]], [[Medium]], [[Carrying]], [[Harm]], [[Control]], and [[Hidden Carrying]] can become terminal to this field as local reads such as [[Tool]], [[Weapon]], and [[Hidden Carrying]].

## Carries

Making Field carries [[Tool]], [[Weapon]], and [[Hidden Carrying]] — the structural reads through which augmenting tools, redirected capacity, and displaced dependencies are named at this field scope. Nested reads are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.

Making Field also carries [[Gardening]] as an applied domain read — the practice through which maintained coupling holds organic asymmetry within a compatible boundary.
- [[Tool]]
- [[Weapon]]
- [[Hidden Carrying]]
- [[Gardening]]','Making Field Making Field names the recurring field of participation through which producing, building, tool use, and bringing form into existence become readable as organised experience. Places Making Field places a recurring field of participation. Holds Making Field is held by Field of Participation, Organic Field, Making, Participation, Form, and Carrying. Field of Participation must structure a recurring scope and relation must be carryable into form before the making field can be named. Pairs Making Field pairs with Natural World Field. Making Field names the field of intentional form — relation carried into arrangement through action and craft; Natural World Field names the field of organic form — relation carried into arrangement through natural order without intentional design. Traces Field of Participation Organic Field Making Participation Form Carrying Nests Making Field nests as a public field container. Detailed branch notes remain compressed as working material. Tool Weapon Hidden Carrying Reads Making Field becomes recognisable where producing, building, tool use, craft, or formed arrangement organises participation through what is made available. At the Translation Boundary, Form, Function, Tool, Medium, Carrying, Harm, Control, and Hidden Carrying can become terminal to this field as local reads such as Tool, Weapon, and Hidden Carrying. Carries Making Field carries Tool, Weapon, and Hidden Carrying — the structural reads through which augmenting tools, redirected capacity, and displaced dependencies are named at this field scope. Nested reads are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground. Making Field also carries Gardening as an applied domain read — the practice through which maintained coupling holds organic asymmetry within a compatible boundary. Tool Weapon Hidden Carrying Gardening','Making Field Making Field names the recurring field of participation through which producing, building, tool use, and bringing form into existence become readable as organised experience. Places…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','making','[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.form","second.participation","third.field-of-participation","third.gardening","third.hidden-carrying","third.making","third.natural-world-field","third.organic-field","third.tool","third.weapon"]','{"holds":["third.field-of-participation","third.organic-field","third.making","second.participation","second.form","second.carrying"],"traces":["third.field-of-participation","third.organic-field","third.making","second.participation","second.form","second.carrying"],"carries":["third.tool","third.weapon","third.hidden-carrying","third.gardening"],"pairs":["third.natural-world-field"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',269,'sha256:bc2c5ef232aba6eecd821a58ccb6d6e311ee2f7ea3c0c3fd5b8c4944289e24cb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.making','Making','making','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Making/Making.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/making.html','# Making

Making names the organic field where participation brings form, tool, work, or arrangement into availability.

## Places

Making places the third-order field where relation is carried into form through action, material, tool, method, or craft — the structural field for production, fabrication, and intentional forming.

## Holds

Making is held by [[Participation]] and [[Field of Participation]]. Participation must structure a field before relation carried into form can be named as making.

## Pairs

Making pairs with [[Tool]]. Making names the act of carrying relation into form; Tool names the produced form that making carries into further participation as an augmenting condition.

## Traces

- [[Participation]]
- [[Field of Participation]]

## Nests

Making nests within the Making Field branch as the field-level container for production and fabrication reads.

[[Tool]]
[[Weapon]]
[[Hidden Carrying]]

## Reads

Making becomes recognisable where relation is carried into form through action, material, tool, method, or craft.

## Carries

Making carries [[Tool]], [[Weapon]], and [[Hidden Carrying]] — Tool names capacity extended through made form; Weapon names capacity redirected toward force, harm, or override; Hidden Carrying names the displaced dependencies that produced form may obscure.

- [[Tool]]
- [[Weapon]]
