INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.nourishment','Nourishment','nourishment','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Sustenance/Nourishment.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/nourishment.html','# Nourishment

Nourishment names a sustenance path read where living participation receives and carries availability enough to continue.

## Places

Nourishment places the condition through which intake of compatible material renews available carrying — the structural read of compatible intake sustaining the body''s or field''s continued carrying.

## Holds

Nourishment is held by [[Sustenance Field]], [[Live]], [[Integration]], [[Medium]], and [[Sustenance]]. Live conditions must be present, intake must become compatibly carried through a medium, and sustenance must require renewal before nourishment can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Nourishment names sustenance through compatible intake; its structural contrast — sustenance through non-intake routes such as rest or repair — is not yet a named vault term.

## Traces

- [[Sustenance Field]]
- [[Live]]
- [[Integration]]
- [[Medium]]
- [[Sustenance]]

## Nests

Nourishment nests within the Sustenance Field as the intake-renewal condition through which compatible carrying is sustained.

## Reads

Nourishment becomes readable where what is taken in preserves or restores compatible living carrying at a closure scope.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Availability]] and [[Bearing]] make continued participation carryable.

Second: [[Live]], [[Integration]], and [[Medium]] make nourishment evaluable.

Third: [[Nourishment]] places that structural read inside the [[Sustenance Field]].

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Nourishment Nourishment names a sustenance path read where living participation receives and carries availability enough to continue. Places Nourishment places the condition through which intake of compatible material renews available carrying — the structural read of compatible intake sustaining the body''s or field''s continued carrying. Holds Nourishment is held by Sustenance Field, Live, Integration, Medium, and Sustenance. Live conditions must be present, intake must become compatibly carried through a medium, and sustenance must require renewal before nourishment can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet. Nourishment names sustenance through compatible intake; its structural contrast — sustenance through non intake routes such as rest or repair — is not yet a named vault term. Traces Sustenance Field Live Integration Medium Sustenance Nests Nourishment nests within the Sustenance Field as the intake renewal condition through which compatible carrying is sustained. Reads Nourishment becomes readable where what is taken in preserves or restores compatible living carrying at a closure scope. The dependency movement is: First: Availability and Bearing make continued participation carryable. Second: Live, Integration, and Medium make nourishment evaluable. Third: Nourishment places that structural read inside the Sustenance Field. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Nourishment Nourishment names a sustenance path read where living participation receives and carries availability enough to continue. Places Nourishment places the condition through which intake…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','sustenance','[]','[]','["second.integration","second.live","second.medium","third.sustenance","third.sustenance-field"]','{"holds":["third.sustenance-field","second.live","second.integration","second.medium","third.sustenance"],"traces":["third.sustenance-f