INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.organic','Organic','organic','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Organic.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/organic.html','# Organic

Organic names Natural Order participating. Where Natural Order names the available order and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, organic names participation that arises through Natural Order rather than through intentional organisation: organisation grows from the available order without being imposed on it. Organic and engineered are not opposites; both participate within Natural Order. The distinction is whether organisation arises through relation or is intentionally arranged through participation.

## Places

Organic places Natural Order participating.

## Holds

Organic is held by [[Natural Order]] and [[Participation]].

## Pairs

Organic pairs with [[Natural Order]] and [[Organic Field]]. Organic names Natural Order participating; Organic Field names recurring organisation arising through that participation.

## Traces

- [[Natural Order]]
- [[Participation]]

## Nests

Organic nests wherever Natural Order participates through relation without requiring imposed arrangement.

## Reads

Organic becomes recognisable where participation organises through the available order without requiring intentional arrangement — where what forms does so through relation rather than through deliberate design.

## Carries

- [[Organic Field]]
- [[Organic and Organised Organisation]]','Organic Organic names Natural Order participating. Where Natural Order names the available order and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, organic names participation that arises through Natural Order rather than through intentional organisation: organisation grows from the available order without being imposed on it. Organic and engineered are not opposites; both participate within Natural Order. The distinction is whether organisation arises through relation or is intentionally arranged through participation. Places Organic places Natural Order participating. Holds Organic is held by Natural Order and Participation. Pairs Organic pairs with Natural Order and Organic Field. Organic names Natural Order participating; Organic Field names recurring organisation arising through that participation. Traces Natural Order Participation Nests Organic nests wherever Natural Order participates through relation without requiring imposed arrangement. Reads Organic becomes recognisable where participation organises through the available order without requiring intentional arrangement — where what forms does so through relation rather than through deliberate design. Carries Organic Field Organic and Organised Organisation','Organic Organic names Natural Order participating. Where Natural Order names the available order and participation names a carried, present relation actively taking part, organic names…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','organic','[]','[]','["ground.natural-order","second.participation","third.organic-and-organised-organisation","third.organic-field"]','{"holds":["ground.natural-order","second.participation"],"traces":["ground.natural-order","second.participation"],"carries":["third.organic-field","third.organic-and-organised-organisation"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',162,'sha256:4fada365e5fafcd4c651ab8d044cf865b741dde938f2a01226ee25ac84f49226','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.organised-domain','Organised Domain','organised-domain','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/Organised Domain.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/organised-domain.html','# Organised Domain

An Organised Domain names an intentionally arranged participation context. An Organised Domain is not the same as an Organic Field. It organises one or more fields into a recognisable practice, discipline, institution, method, model, framework, or applied arrangement. Organised domains can remain healthy where they preserve retraceability to the fields and relations they organise. They become structurally unsafe where their organisation carries participation while blocking retrace.

An Organised Domain is also where structural terms often become terminal to disciplined language. The domain term carries the branch forward only while the source relation remains retraceable.

## Places

Organised Domain places an intentionally arranged participation context where one or more fields become organised into practice, discipline, institution, method, model, framework, or applied arrangement.

It also places the point where a structural term becomes terminal to disciplined local language.

## Holds

Organised Domain is held by [[Domain]], [[Organic and Organised Organisation]], [[Field of Participation]], [[Society]].

## Pairs

Organised Domain pairs with [[Organic Field]]: organised domain names an intentionally arranged participation context where fields become organised into practice, discipline, institution, or method; organic field names a recurring field of participation that emerges through natural order. Each requires the other to be locatable — organised domain is only readable against the background of organic emergence; organic field is only readable against the possibility of organised arrangement.

## Traces

- [[Domain]]
- [[Organic and Organised Organisation]]
- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Communion]]
- [[Society]]
- [[Terminal]]

## Nests

Organised Domain nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace.

It can nest local domain terms as translations of structural Atlas terms.

## Reads

An Organised Domain becomes recognisable where participation is intentionally arranged, maintained, revised, inherited, taught, governed, or applied. It is read by asking what organic fields it organises and whether its carrying remains retraceable.

It is checked by asking what becomes terminal to this domain, what local language carries it, and whether that local language still permits retrace.

## Carries

- [[Branch]]
- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Higher Retrace|Retrace]]
- [[Hidden Bearing]]','Organised Domain An Organised Domain names an intentionally arranged participation context. An Organised Domain is not the same as an Organic Field. It organises one or more fields into a recognisable practice, discipline, institution, method, model, framework, or applied arrangement. Organised domains can remain healthy where they preserve retraceability to the fields and relations they organise. They become structurally unsafe where their organisation carries participation while blocking retrace. An Organised Domain is also where structural terms often become terminal to disciplined language. The domain term carries the branch forward only while the source relation remains retraceable. Places Organised Domain places an intentionally arranged participation context where one or more fields become organised into practice, discipline, institution, method, model, framework, or applied arrangement. It also places the point where a structural term becomes terminal to disciplined local language. Holds Organised Domain is held by Domain, Organic and Organised Organisation, Field of Participation, Society. Pairs Organised Domain pairs with Organic Field: organised domain names an intentionally arranged participation context where fields become organised into practice, discipline, institution, or method; organic field names a recurring field of participation that emerges through natural order. Each requires the other to be locatable — organised domain is only readable against the background of organic emergence; organic field is only readable against the possibility of organised arrangement. Traces Domain Organic and Organised Organisation Field of Participation Communion Society Terminal Nests Organised Domain nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace. It can nest local domain terms as translations of structural Atlas terms. Reads An Organised Domain becomes recognisable where participation is intentionally arranged, maintained, revised, inherited, taught, governed, or applied. It is read by asking what organic fields it organises and whether its carrying remains retraceable. It is checked by asking what becomes terminal to this domain, what local language carries it, and whether that local language still permits retrace. Carries Branch Applied Read Higher Retrace Hidden Bearing','Organised Domain An Organised Domain names an intentionally arranged participation context. An Organised Domain is not the same as an Organic Field.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','organised-domain','[]','[]','["higher.hidden-bearing","higher.higher-retrace","second.terminal","third.applied-read","third.branch","third.communion","third.domain","third.field-of-participation","third.organic-and-organised-organisation","third.organic-field","third.society"]','{"holds":["third.domain","third.organic-and-organised-organisation","third.field-of-participation","third.society"],"traces":["third.domain","third.organic-and-organised-organisation","third.field-of-participation","third.communion","third.society","second.terminal"],"carries":["third.branch","third.applied-read","higher.higher-retrace","higher.hidden-bearing"],"pairs":["third.organic-field"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',328,'sha256:12296530b3f4e40acd8b84f28605bcc03892c05fa8e7f97d191e72f76547d8f2','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.our-story-field','Our Story Field','our-story-field','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Our Story/Our Story Field.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/our-story-field.html','# Our Story Field

Our Story Field names the recurring field of participation through which shared inheritance, collective history, and intergenerational carrying become readable as organised experience.

## Places

Our Story Field places a recurring field of participation.

## Holds

Our Story Field is held by [[Field of Participation]], [[Organic Field]], and [[Our Story]]. [[Inheritance]] and [[Carrying Better]] nest as later reads; they do not hold the field that carries them.

## Pairs

Our Story Field pairs with [[Relational Participation Field]]. Our Story Field names the field of carried prior relation — what has been passed forward through history, memory, and inheritance; Relational Participation Field names the field of enacted present relation — how bearing, care, harm, and repair proceed between participants. History is enacted in the present; present participation accumulates into history.

## Traces

- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Organic Field]]
- [[Our Story]]

## Nests

Our Story Field nests as a public field container. Detailed branch notes remain compressed as working material.

[[Our Story]]
[[Inheritance]]
[[Carrying Better]]
[[Borne and Carried]]

## Reads

Our Story Field becomes recognisable where inheritance, memory, narrative, history, or intergenerational carrying organises participation as shared continuity.

At the [[Translation Boundary]], [[Memory]], [[Recurrence]], [[Carrying]], [[Inheritance]], [[Bearing Source|source]], and [[Return]] can become terminal to this field as local reads such as [[Our Story]], [[Inheritance]], [[Borne and Carried]], and [[Carrying Better]].

## Carries

Our Story Field carries [[Inheritance]], [[Borne and Carried]], and [[Carrying Better]] — the structural reads through which shared relational history is received, passed forward, and improved. Nested reads are recorded under Nests; each traces its own structural ground.
- [[Inheritance]]
- [[Carrying Better]]
