INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.physical-field-conditions','Physical Field Conditions','physical-field-conditions','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Physical Field Conditions.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/physical-field-conditions.html','# Physical Field Conditions

Physical Field Conditions names [[Physical]] natural-world reads where [[Relation Read]] conditions become readable through boundary, constraint, and measurable effect.

## Places

Physical Field Conditions places the branch container for natural-world physical reads — the structural node through which physical, field-bearing, and constraint conditions are held as a named branch.

## Holds

Physical Field Conditions is held by [[Branch]], [[Natural World Field]], [[Physical]], [[Condition]], [[Constraint]], and [[Field Bearing]]. Physical and field-bearing conditions must be nameable and constrainable before they can be held as a branch.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Branch]]
- [[Natural World Field]]
- [[Physical]]
- [[Condition]]
- [[Constraint]]
- [[Field Bearing]]

## Nests

Physical Field Conditions nests within the Natural World Field as the branch container for physical and field-bearing structural reads.

[[Physical]]
[[Field Bearing]]
[[Field Availability Pattern]]
[[Gravity]]
[[Light]]
[[Dark Matter]]
[[Dark Energy]]
[[Black Hole]]
[[Casimir Plates]]
[[Neutrino]]
[[Physical Space]]
[[Timescale]]
[[Cosmic Polarity Read]]

## Reads

Physical Field Conditions becomes readable where bounded field conditions alter availability enough to be sensed, measured, located, or modelled.

Derivation:

[[Physical]] names natural-world readability as material or field condition.

[[Relation Read]] names relation read as joined spread under a shared condition.

[[Condition]] names bounded availability under which a read can hold.

Physical Field Conditions names physical reads where field conditions alter availability enough to be sensed, measured, located, or modelled.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Relation Read]], [[Space]], and [[Boundary]] locate physical-field difference.

Second: [[Constraint]], [[Field Bearing]], and [[Readability]] make altered field availability evaluable.

Third: [[Physical Field Conditions]] places that structural read inside the natural-world domain.

Path Reads:

- [[Field Availability Pattern]]
- [[Physical Space]]
- [[Light]]
- [[Gravity]]
- [[Black Hole]]
- [[Casimir Plates]]
- [[Neutrino]]
- [[Dark Matter]]
- [[Dark Energy]]
- [[Cosmic Polarity Read]]

Shared Read:

Physical space, light, gravity, black holes, Casimir plates, neutrinos, dark matter, dark energy, and cosmic polarity test [[Field Availability Pattern]].

[[Field Bearing]] marks the point where altered field availability becomes bearing on traversal, escape, attraction, closure, visibility, or measurable path.

In physical space, located clearance becomes readable as measurable extent, distance, position, or traversable field relation.

In a black hole, gravitational collapse makes an event boundary decisive for escape and outside read.

In Casimir plates, arranged material boundaries alter available field modes enough for constrained field availability to bear on the plates as a measurable force.

In neutrinos, traversal remains broadly available while local visibility depends on rare coupling and indirect detection.

In light, clearance becomes readable as apparent traversal, separation, visibility, or field-event readability.

In gravity, located clearance becomes constrained so field bearing on traversal, fall, orbit, escape, and measurable path becomes physically readable.

In dark matter, [[Invisible Bearing]] becomes physically readable where gravitational [[Field Bearing]] remains readable while ordinary electromagnetic visibility remains unavailable.

In dark energy, large-scale cosmic clearance remains readable as expansion beyond ordinary gravitational closure, with [[Gravity]] supplying the ordinary closure-bearing condition read against.

Polarity Comparison:

[[Cosmic Polarity Read]] applies [[Resolution Polarity]] and [[Invisible Bearing]] to this physical-field branch.

It compares [[Light]], [[Gravity]], [[Dark Matter]], [[Dark Energy]], and [[Black Hole]] without treating any of them as source structure:

- [[Light]]: clearance appears.
- [[Gravity]]: clearance constrains.
- [[Dark Matter]]: [[Invisible Bearing]] becomes physically readable as bearing without ordinary appearance.
- [[Dark Energy]]: clearance opens beyond ordinary closure.
- [[Black Hole]]: clearance closes into boundary-limited non-return.
## Carries

Physical Field Conditions carries [[Gravity]], [[Field Availability Pattern]], [[Physical Space]], [[Timescale]], [[Light]], [[Neutrino]], and [[Casimir Plates]] — the specific physical field reads that become nameable once field-bearing conditions hold.

