pens beyond ordinary closure. Black Hole: clearance closes into boundary limited non return. Carries Physical Field Conditions carries Gravity, Field Availability Pattern, Physical Space, Timescale, Light, Neutrino, and Casimir Plates — the specific physical field reads that become nameable once field bearing conditions hold. Gravity Field Availability Pattern Physical Space Timescale Light Neutrino Casimir Plates','Physical Field Conditions Physical Field Conditions names Physical natural world reads where Relation Read conditions become readable through boundary, constraint, and measurable effect. Places…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','natural-world','[]','[]','["second.condition","second.constraint","third.branch","third.casimir-plates","third.field-availability-pattern","third.field-bearing","third.gravity","third.light","third.natural-world-field","third.neutrino","third.physical","third.physical-space","third.timescale"]','{"holds":["third.branch","third.natural-world-field","third.physical","second.condition","second.constraint","third.field-bearing"],"traces":["third.branch","third.natural-world-field","third.physical","second.condition","second.constraint","third.field-bearing"],"carries":["third.gravity","third.field-availability-pattern","third.physical-space","third.timescale","third.light","third.neutrino","third.casimir-plates"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',598,'sha256:c9f8db1b5554154cf6f164d259298543bc05d0f3550ac03ea86924a55293c1cb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.physical-space','Physical Space','physical-space','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Physical Space.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/physical-space.html','# Physical Space

Physical Space names [[Space]] read through [[Physical]] natural-world conditions as measurable extent, position, distance, field condition, or traversable physical relation.

Physical Space is downstream of [[Space]]. It is not the first-order source of spatial readability.

## Places

Physical Space places the structured extent within which physical field conditions become measurable — the dimensional and scaled ground for locating physical distinction.

## Holds

Physical Space is held by [[Natural World Field]], [[Physical]], [[Physical Field Conditions]], [[Dimension]], and [[Scale]]. Physical field conditions must hold and dimensional structure must be readable before measured extent can be named as physical space.

## Pairs

Physical Space pairs with [[Timescale]]. Physical Space names dimensional structure as a carrying parameter; Timescale names temporal extent as a carrying parameter. Each is one structural dimension of physical field conditions.

## Traces

- [[Natural World Field]]
- [[Physical]]
- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
- [[Dimension]]
- [[Scale]]
- [[Space]]

## Nests

Physical Space nests within Physical Field Conditions as the dimensional-structural condition through which physical field distinctions are located and measured.

## Reads

Physical Space becomes readable where located clearance appears as measurable or modelled physical extent, position, distance, or traversable field relation.

Derivation:

[[Physical]] names natural-world readability as material or field condition.

[[Space]] names located clearance.

Physical Space names located clearance read through natural-world material or field conditions.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Relation]], [[Clearance]], [[Space]], [[Relation Read]], and [[Boundary]] make located clearance readable.

Second: [[Dimension]], [[Scale]], and [[Readability]] make spatial relation evaluable by local resolution and mode of read.

Third: [[Physical Space]] places measurable spatial relation inside [[Natural World Field]] and [[Physical Field Conditions]].

## Carries

