{"holds":["second.participation","third.field-of-participation","first.space"],"traces":["second.participation","third.field-of-participation","first.space"],"carries":["third.belong"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',239,'sha256:4ccf665958d35e1433299dc17295932b2d97a6ec7d8807cf93ef9b00eb7410bb','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.placement-mode','Placement Mode','placement-mode','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Placement Mode.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/placement-mode.html','# Placement Mode

Placement Mode names the sorting of a third-order note by primary carrying mode.

Placement modes are not order roots. The third-order order root is [[Nesting]]. Placement modes describe how a third-order note is primarily carried inside the Atlas.

## Places

Placement Mode places the sorting of a third-order note by primary carrying mode.

## Holds

Placement Mode is held by [[Third Order]], [[Branch]], and [[Dependency Order]].

## Pairs

Placement Mode pairs with [[Diagnosis]]. Placement Mode sorts by carrying mode; Diagnosis tests how a path read applies in a bounded case.

## Traces

- [[Third Order]]
- [[Branch]]
- [[Dependency Order]]

## Nests

Placement Mode nests as a sorting read for third-order notes by primary carrying mode, not as an order root.

## Reads

Placement Mode becomes recognisable where a note can be located against a primary carrying mode and optional secondary crossings.
## Carries

- [[Knowing]]
- [[Caring]]
- [[Sustaining]]
- [[Locating]]
- [[Sensing]]
- [[Communicating]]
- [[Transforming]]
- [[Governing]]
- [[Moving]]
- [[Expressing]]
- [[Exchanging]]','Placement Mode Placement Mode names the sorting of a third order note by primary carrying mode. Placement modes are not order roots. The third order order root is Nesting. Placement modes describe how a third order note is primarily carried inside the Atlas. Places Placement Mode places the sorting of a third order note by primary carrying mode. Holds Placement Mode is held by Third Order, Branch, and Dependency Order. Pairs Placement Mode pairs with Diagnosis. Placement Mode sorts by carrying mode; Diagnosis tests how a path read applies in a bounded case. Traces Third Order Branch Dependency Order Nests Placement Mode nests as a sorting read for third order notes by primary carrying mode, not as an order root. Reads Placement Mode becomes recognisable where a note can be located against a primary carrying mode and optional secondary crossings. Carries Knowing Caring Sustaining Locating Sensing Communicating Transforming Governing Moving Expressing Exchanging','Placement Mode Placement Mode names the sorting of a third order note by primary carrying mode. Placement modes are not order roots.','stable','rooted',0,'third','class',NULL,'[]','[]','["ground.dependency-order","third.branch","third.caring","third.communicating","third.diagnosis","third.exchanging","third.expressing","third.governing","third.knowing","third.locating","third.moving","third.sensing","third.sustaining","third.third-order","third.transforming"]','{"holds":["third.third-order","third.branch","ground.dependency-order"],"traces":["third.third-order","third.branch","ground.dependency-order"],"carries":["third.knowing","third.caring","third.sustaining","third.locating","third.sensing","third.communicating","third.transforming","third.governing","third.moving","third.expressing","third.exchanging"],"pairs":["third.diagnosis"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',152,'sha256:b5238f514f004115f13ab166c471950c96f5159d3b99585fa071933f75104ea8','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.protective-control','Protective Control','protective-control','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/Parenting/Applied Reads/Protective Control.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/protective-control.html','# Protective Control

Protective Control reads a local parenting case where control enters to protect dependent availability after risk, harm, or insufficient bearing. It remains protective only where direction stays answerable to [[Care]] — the preserving bearing that makes the dependent availability worth protecting.

## Places

Protective Control places the local parenting case where control enters to protect dependent availability after risk, harm, or insufficient bearing.

## Holds

Protective Control is held by [[Applied Read]], [[Parenting]], [[Control After Harm]], [[Control]], [[Care]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]]. Protective direction must remain answerable to the availability care preserves before it can be read as compatible protection.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Parenting]]
- [[Control After Harm]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Care]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Protective Control nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace.

## Reads

Protective Control becomes readable where direction protects dependent availability while preserving the dependency path required for compatible repair and growth.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Availability]], [[Bearing]], and [[Resolution]] must hold enough for protective direction to remain supportable.

Second: [[Control]], [[Care]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]] make protection evaluable as repair-supporting or forced continuation.

Third: [[Protective Control]] tests that condition inside the [[Relational Participation Field]] as an applied parenting read.

Case Movement:

```text
risk or harm threatens bearing
-> parental control enters
-> protection must preserve compatibility
-> control either supports repair or becomes further harm
```

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Protective Control Protective Control reads a local parenting case where control enters to protect dependent availability after risk, harm, or insufficient bearing. It remains protective only where direction stays answerable to Care — the preserving bearing that makes the dependent availability worth protecting. Places Protective Control places the local parenting case where control enters to protect dependent availability after risk, harm, or insufficient bearing. Holds Protective Control is held by Applied Read, Parenting, Control After Harm, Control, Care, Compatibility, and Closure Scope. Protective direction must remain answerable to the availability care preserves before it can be read as compatible protection. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Applied Read Parenting Control After Harm Control Care Compatibility Closure Scope Nests Protective Control nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace. Reads Protective Control becomes readable where direction protects dependent availability while preserving the dependency path required for compatible repair and growth. The dependency movement is: First: Availability, Bearing, and Resolution must hold enough for protective direction to remain supportable. Second: Control, Care, Compatibility, and Closure Scope make protection evaluable as repair supporting or forced continuation. Third: Protective Control tests that condition inside the Relational Participation Field as an applied parenting read. Case Movement: Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Protective Control Protective Control reads a local parenting case where control enters to protect dependent availability after risk, harm, or insufficient bearing. It remains protective only…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','parenting','[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.compatibility","third.applied-read","third.care","third.control","third.control-after-harm","third.parenting"]','{"holds":["third.applied-read","third.parenting","third.control-after-harm","third.control","third.care","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.applied-read","third.parenting","third.control-after-harm","third.control","third.care","second.compatibility","second.closure-scope"],"carries":[],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',234,'sha256:cfadd78010f19950c6a7b7bebc9da1bc9d70ab92b4ef2b7ecbaf97fe77280349','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.reality-check','Reality Check','reality-check','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Knowledge/Reality Check.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/reality-check.html','# Reality Check

Reality check names branch-level evaluation of whether a read remains structurally compatible with its bearing source.

## Places

Reality Check places the evaluative read through which a claim, representation, or local model is checked for compatibility with what bears it — the closure-scope test of whether a read remains traceable.

## Holds

Reality Check is held by [[Reality]], [[Read]], [[Compatibility]], [[Closure Scope]], [[Bearing Source]], [[Dependency Disorder]], and [[Check]]. A claim must be present and compatibility must be evaluable at the relevant closure scope before the check can be performed.

## Pairs

Reality Check pairs with [[Knowledge]]: reality check names the evaluative read through which a claim is checked against what bears it; knowledge names the field where knowing is maintained, tested, and revised. Each requires the other — reality check has no field to apply within without knowledge; knowledge without reality check loses contact with what it claims to know.

## Traces

- [[Reality]]
- [[Read]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Bearing Source]]
- [[Dependency Disorder]]
- [[Check]]

- [[Knowledge]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]
## Nests

Reality Check nests within the Knowledge Field as the evaluative path read through which claims and models are tested against traceable bearing.

## Reads

Reality Check becomes readable where a representation, claim, or read is tested against what can still be borne, resolved, and carried by its bearing source at the relevant closure scope.

Reality Check also tests whether a read is calibrated to the order and scope of the question it is answering. A response may be locally valid inside one order while failing the question posed from another order. This is not simple relativism and not only overclaim; it is a compatibility failure between the resolution offered and the order in which the question requires answerability.

Reality Check also asks whether the boundary that turns read into action remains traceable. A read may appear correct as representation while failing as action if the accountable coupling is hidden, displaced, or treated as if consequence belonged only to the carrier.

Related Practice:

[[Check]] supplies the Atlas practice of locating a boundary by testing from both directions. Reality Check applies checking to whether a read remains compatible with its [[Bearing Source]] at the relevant [[Closure Scope]].

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bearing]] and [[Resolution]] must hold enough for a read to proceed.

Second: [[Read]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]] make the check evaluable.

Third: [[Reality Check]] applies that evaluation to claims, representations, and branch-local reads.

## Carries

- [[Competence Boundary]]','Reality Check Reality check names branch level evaluation of whether a read remains structurally compatible with its bearing source. Places Reality Check places the evaluative read through which a claim, representation, or local model is checked for compatibility with what bears it — the closure scope test of whether a read remains traceable. Holds Reality Check is held by Reality, Read, Compatibility, Closure Scope, Bearing Source, Dependency Disorder, and Check. A claim must be present and compatibility must be evaluable at the relevant closure scope before the check can be performed. Pairs Reality Check pairs with Knowledge: reality check names the evaluative read through which a claim is checked against what bears it; knowledge names the field where knowing is maintained, tested, and revised. Each requires the other — reality check has no field to apply within without knowledge; knowledge without reality check loses contact with what it claims to know. Traces Reality Read Compatibility Closure Scope Bearing Source Dependency Disorder Check Knowledge Translation Boundary Nests Reality Check nests within the Knowledge Field as the evaluative path read through which claims and models are tested against traceable bearing. Reads Reality Check becomes readable where a representation, claim, or read is tested against what can still be borne, resolved, and carried by its bearing source at the relevant closure scope. Reality Check also tests whether a read is calibrated to the order and scope of the question it is answering. A response may be locally valid inside one order while failing the question posed from another order. This is not simple relativism and not only overclaim; it is a compatibility failure between the resolution offered and the order in which the question requires answerability. Reality Check also asks whether the boundary that turns read into action remains traceable. A read may appear correct as representation while failing