INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.reciprocity','Reciprocity','reciprocity','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Reciprocity.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/reciprocity.html','# Reciprocity

Reciprocity names mutual participation within Bearing relation.

## Places

Reciprocity places bearing that moves compatibly across participation — the condition through which what is borne can be carried back, responded to, or returned within a participation scope.

## Holds

Reciprocity is held by [[Bearing]] and [[Participation]]. Bearing must be present and active participation must be in scope before bearing moving across participation can be read as reciprocal.

## Pairs

Reciprocity pairs with [[Reciprocity Breakdown]]. Reciprocity names compatible bearing across participation; Reciprocity Breakdown names its failure at closure scope.

## Traces

- [[Bearing]]
- [[Participation]]

## Nests

Reciprocity nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which bearing sustains compatible exchange across participation.

## Reads

Reciprocity becomes readable where participation is mutually carried through compatible bearing.

## Carries

Reciprocity carries [[Reciprocity Breakdown]] — the loss of compatible bearing across participation that reciprocity names as held.
- [[Reciprocity Breakdown]]
- [[Exchanging]]','Reciprocity Reciprocity names mutual participation within Bearing relation. Places Reciprocity places bearing that moves compatibly across participation — the condition through which what is borne can be carried back, responded to, or returned within a participation scope. Holds Reciprocity is held by Bearing and Participation. Bearing must be present and active participation must be in scope before bearing moving across participation can be read as reciprocal. Pairs Reciprocity pairs with Reciprocity Breakdown. Reciprocity names compatible bearing across participation; Reciprocity Breakdown names its failure at closure scope. Traces Bearing Participation Nests Reciprocity nests within Relational Participation as the condition through which bearing sustains compatible exchange across participation. Reads Reciprocity becomes readable where participation is mutually carried through compatible bearing. Carries Reciprocity carries Reciprocity Breakdown — the loss of compatible bearing across participation that reciprocity names as held. Reciprocity Breakdown Exchanging','Reciprocity Reciprocity names mutual participation within Bearing relation. Places Reciprocity places bearing that moves compatibly across participation — the condition through which what is borne…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.participation","third.exchanging","third.reciprocity-breakdown"]','{"holds":["first.bearing","second.participation"],"traces":["first.bearing","second.participation"],"carries":["third.reciprocity-breakdown","third.exchanging"],"pairs":["third.reciprocity-breakdown"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',139,'sha256:a8ddfaffb66571a85712f74858e50843844b0c86ad613b2a158cecfe471214d4','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.recovery','Recovery','recovery','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Body/Recovery.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/recovery.html','# Recovery

Recovery names embodied re-bearing where reduced or damaged availability becomes compatibly carried again.

## Places

Recovery places compatible re-bearing within the body following fatigue or injury — the restoration of carrying capacity through rest, repair, or sustained support.

## Holds

Recovery is held by [[Body]], [[Fatigue]], [[Injury]], [[Repair]], [[Recarry]], [[Carrying]], [[Energy]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Carried Condition]]. Prior carrying reduction or damage must be present before compatible re-bearing can be named as recovery.

## Pairs

Recovery pairs with [[Fatigue]]. Recovery names compatible re-bearing following reduction; Fatigue names the reduction. Both read the body''s capacity for continued participation.

## Traces

- [[Body]]
- [[Fatigue]]
- [[Injury]]
- [[Repair]]
- [[Recarry]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Energy]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Carried Condition]]

## Nests

Recovery nests within the Body Field as the condition through which compatible carrying is restored following fatigue or injury.

## Reads

Recovery becomes readable where embodied participation can return without repeating the incompatibility that reduced or damaged it.

The dependency movement is:

First: embodied [[Strain]] or damaged [[Boundary]] reduces available bearing.

Second: [[Repair]], [[Recarry]], [[Carrying]], and [[Compatibility]] make return supportable.

Third: [[Recovery]] places that structural read inside the body branch.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Recovery Recovery names embodied re bearing where reduced or damaged availability becomes compatibly carried again. Places Recovery places compatible re bearing within the body following fatigue or injury — the restoration of carrying capacity through rest, repair, or sustained support. Holds Recovery is held by Body, Fatigue, Injury, Repair, Recarry, Carrying, Energy, Compatibility, and Carried Condition. Prior carrying reduction or damage must be present before compatible re bearing can be named as recovery. Pairs Recovery pairs with Fatigue. Recovery names compatible re bearing following reduction; Fatigue names the reduction. Both read the body''s capacity for continued participation. Traces Body Fatigue Injury Repair Recarry Carrying Energy Compatibility Carried Condition Nests Recovery nests within the Body Field as the condition through which compatible carrying is restored following fatigue or injury. Reads Recovery becomes readable where embodied participation can return without repeating the incompatibility that reduced or damaged it. The dependency movement is: First: embodied Strain or damaged Boundary reduces available bearing. Second: Repair, Recarry, Carrying, and Compatibility make return supportable. Third: Recovery places that structural read inside the body branch. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Recovery Recovery names embodied re bearing where reduced or damaged availability becomes compatibly carried again. Places Recovery places compatible re bearing within the body following fatigue…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','body','[]','[]','["second.carried-condition","second.carrying","second.compatibility","second.energy","second.recarry","third.body","third.fatigue","third.injury","third.repair"]','{"holds":["third.body","third.fatigue","third.injury","third.repair","second.recarry","second.carrying","second.energy","second.compatibility","second.ca