INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.relationship','Relationship','relationship','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Relationship.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/relationship.html','# Relationship

Relationship names relation held as carried, coupled participation. It is relation given a shared boundary-form through which participants can bear on each other, maintain contact, repair, loosen, or decouple.

The "ship" read is structural rather than etymological: relationship is relation carried in a held form.

## Places

Relationship places the sustained, named form of coupled participation — the shared boundary through which bearing, repair, and ongoing relation take place.

## Holds

Relationship is held by [[Coupled Boundary]], [[Bearing Relation]], and [[Participation]]. Coupling must be bounded, bearing must be traceable across it, and participation must recur before relation can be held as a named shared form.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Coupled Boundary]]
- [[Bearing Relation]]
- [[Participation]]

## Nests

Relationship nests within Relational Participation as the named form of coupled participation. It is where the second-order structure of Coupled Boundary and Bearing Relation becomes a held, readable shared condition.

## Reads

Relationship becomes recognisable where relation is held through a coupled boundary and recurring participation so that what happens between participants can be carried, strained, protected, repaired, loosened, or lost as a shared condition.

## Carries

- [[Trust]]
- [[Betrayal]]','Relationship Relationship names relation held as carried, coupled participation. It is relation given a shared boundary form through which participants can bear on each other, maintain contact, repair, loosen, or decouple. The "ship" read is structural rather than etymological: relationship is relation carried in a held form. Places Relationship places the sustained, named form of coupled participation — the shared boundary through which bearing, repair, and ongoing relation take place. Holds Relationship is held by Coupled Boundary, Bearing Relation, and Participation. Coupling must be bounded, bearing must be traceable across it, and participation must recur before relation can be held as a named shared form. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Coupled Boundary Bearing Relation Participation Nests Relationship nests within Relational Participation as the named form of coupled participation. It is where the second order structure of Coupled Boundary and Bearing Relation becomes a held, readable shared condition. Reads Relationship becomes recognisable where relation is held through a coupled boundary and recurring participation so that what happens between participants can be carried, strained, protected, repaired, loosened, or lost as a shared condition. Carries Trust Betrayal','Relationship Relationship names relation held as carried, coupled participation. It is relation given a shared boundary form through which participants can bear on each other, maintain contact,…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','relational-participation','[]','[]','["second.bearing-relation","second.coupled-boundary","second.participation","third.betrayal","third.trust"]','{"holds":["second.coupled-boundary","second.bearing-relation","second.participation"],"traces":["second.coupled-boundary","second.bearing-relation","second.participation"],"carries":["third.trust","third.betrayal"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',200,'sha256:4a2470d2f150eb6c0fc68309bd6c2ccc024a3567303277c8285def7b7f803122','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.repair-mismatch','Repair Mismatch','repair-mismatch','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Bearing Relations/Applied Reads/Repair Mismatch.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/repair-mismatch.html','# Repair Mismatch

Repair Mismatch reads a local case where repair is attempted but does not re-enter the lost bearing into compatible carrying.

## Places

Repair Mismatch places the applied read where repair is attempted but addresses the wrong scope, condition, or bearing gap — restoration that misses where it needs to land.

## Holds

Repair Mismatch is held by [[Applied Read]], [[Repair]], [[Misrepair]], and [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Applied Read]]
- [[Repair]]
- [[Misrepair]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Repair Mismatch nests within Relational Participation as an applied read of Repair and Misrepair, where restoration of bearing misses the required scope.

## Reads

Repair Mismatch becomes readable where repair-like action preserves proceeding while failing to restore the bearing condition that was lost.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Bearing]] must be restored where relation has lost support.

Second: [[Compatibility]], [[Misrepair]], and [[Closure Scope]] make attempted repair evaluable as restored bearing or wrong-condition continuation.

Third: [[Repair Mismatch]] tests that condition inside the [[Relational Participation Field]] as an applied relation read.

Case Movement:

```text
bearing is lost
-> repair is attempted
-> proceeding continues
-> compatibility is not restored
```

