ird.cosmic-polarity-read"]','{"holds":["first.resolution","first.polarity","first.availability","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["first.resolution","first.polarity","first.availability","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["third.cosmic-polarity-read"],"pairs":["first.polarity"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',230,'sha256:ee72cbe7b02b7d8eeeb1e3932f85d16f5986feb89e76a5c5804303c2974f825e','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.restraint','Restraint','restraint','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Translation Boundaries/Restraint.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/restraint.html','# Restraint

Restraint names the translation boundary where constraint becomes terminal to participation from within. Carrying is intentionally held within a boundary, scope, or standard so it does not exceed what can bear, be checked, or be repaired. Restraint is not constraint in general; it is constraint taken up through participation and control.

## Places

Restraint places the boundary where constraint shifts from outside limit into inside participation.

## Holds

Restraint is held by [[Constraint]], [[Control]], [[Participation]], [[Closure Scope]], and [[Translation Boundary]]. A constraint must exist, control must be exercised, participation must take it up, and a scope or standard must bound it before intentional holding can be read as restraint rather than mere compliance or suppression.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Constraint]]
- [[Control]]
- [[Participation]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Competence Boundary]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Restraint nests within Translation Boundaries as a participation-and-control regime shift — where constraint is entered through participation rather than imposed from outside.

## Reads

Restraint becomes readable where participation controls action, language, movement, or relation within a constraint so carrying remains compatible with what can be borne, checked, trusted, or repaired.

## Carries

