INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.safety-boundary','Safety Boundary','safety-boundary','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Relational Participation/Safety/Safety Boundary.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/safety-boundary.html','# Safety Boundary

Safety boundary names a branch-level boundary condition that preserves compatible participation.

## Places

Safety Boundary places the located condition through which safe passage, harm-prevention, or compatible carrying is bounded — the structural edge that separates compatible from incompatible relation.

## Holds

Safety Boundary is held by [[Safety]], [[Boundary]], [[Compatibility]], and [[Closure Scope]]. A safety condition must be at stake, a boundary must locate the edge, and compatibility must govern what can cross before the condition can be read as a safety boundary.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Safety]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Compatibility]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Safety Boundary nests within Relational Participation as the closure-scope condition through which compatible and incompatible bearing are kept separable.

## Reads

Safety Boundary becomes readable where a located limit preserves compatible participation without turning protection into forced control.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]] locates the safety condition.

Second: [[Compatibility]] and [[Closure Scope]] make preserved participation evaluable.

Third: [[Safety Boundary]] places that structural read inside safety.

## Carries

