rd.branch","third.harm","third.relational-participation-field","third.safety-boundary"]','{"holds":["third.branch","third.relational-participation-field","first.availability","second.compatibility","second.collapse","first.boundary"],"traces":["third.branch","third.relational-participation-field","first.availability","second.compatibility","second.collapse","first.boundary"],"carries":["third.safety-boundary"],"pairs":["third.harm"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',213,'sha256:eda2ffeeb467780ae0772d7dd68fdce79935900675e6b459808c260c46f5ea26','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.scene','Scene','scene','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Translation Boundaries/Scene.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/scene.html','# Scene

Scene names a bounded field of presence where participation becomes terminal to what is happening here. A place, image, moment, or backdrop can help form a scene, but scene names participation gathered within a scope so that its conditions, relations, and movement become locally readable.

## Places

Scene places the translation boundary where occurrence, presence, and closure scope become terminal to a locally readable happening.

## Holds

Scene is held by [[Occur]], [[Presence]], [[Closure Scope]], [[Field of Participation]], and [[Translation Boundary]]. Something must be occurring, presence must be available, a scope must bound it, and a field of participation must hold it before the gathering can be read as a scene rather than as mere proximity or sequence.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Occur]]
- [[Presence]]
- [[Closure Scope]]
- [[Field of Participation]]
- [[Translation Boundary]]

## Nests

Scene nests within Translation Boundaries as a presence-and-scope terminal read — where happening, presence, and bounded scope converge into a locally readable situation.

## Reads

Scene becomes recognisable where participation is present within a bounded scope strongly enough to become terminal to a situated happening — where conditions, relations, and movement can be read as what is occurring here.

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Scene Scene names a bounded field of presence where participation becomes terminal to what is happening here. A place, image, moment, or backdrop can help form a scene, but scene names participation gathered within a scope so that its conditions, relations, and movement become locally readable. Places Scene places the translation boundary where occurrence, presence, and closure scope become terminal to a locally readable happening. Holds Scene is held by Occur, Presence, Closure Scope, Field of Participation, and Translation Boundary. Something must be occurring, presence must be available, a scope must bound it, and a field of participation must hold it before the gathering can be read as a scene rather than as mere proximity or sequence. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Occur Presence Closure Scope Field of Participation Translation Boundary Nests Scene nests within Translation Boundaries as a presence and scope terminal read — where happening, presence, and bounded scope converge into a locally readable situation. Reads Scene becomes recognisable where participation is present within a bounded scope strongly enough to become terminal to a situated happening — where conditions, relations, and movement can be read as what is occurring here. Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Scene Scene names a bounded field of presence where participation becomes terminal to what is happening here. A place, image, moment, or backdrop can help form a scene, but scene names…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','translation-boundaries','[]','[]','["second.closure-scope","second.occur","second.presence","third.field-of-participation","third.translation-boundary"]','{"holds":["second.occur","second.presence","second.closure-scope","third.field-of-participation","third.translation-boundary"],"traces":["second.