INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.sustenance','Sustenance','sustenance','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Sustenance/Sustenance.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/sustenance.html','# Sustenance

Sustenance names the organic field where participation is carried through nourishment, continuation, replenishment, and maintained availability.

## Places

Sustenance places the third-order field where participation depends on renewed availability that can continue to carry life, body, place, or practice — the structural field for nourishment, renewal, and continued carrying.

## Holds

Sustenance is held by [[Participation]] and [[Field of Participation]]. Participation must structure a field and renewed availability must be required before the sustaining condition can be named.

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Participation]]
- [[Field of Participation]]

## Nests

Sustenance nests within the Sustenance Field branch as the field-level container for nourishment and renewal reads.

[[Nourishment]]
[[Life]]
[[Care]]

## Reads

Sustenance becomes recognisable where participation depends on renewed availability that can continue to carry life, body, place, or practice.

## Carries

- [[Nourishment]]
- [[Life]]
- [[Care]]','Sustenance Sustenance names the organic field where participation is carried through nourishment, continuation, replenishment, and maintained availability. Places Sustenance places the third order field where participation depends on renewed availability that can continue to carry life, body, place, or practice — the structural field for nourishment, renewal, and continued carrying. Holds Sustenance is held by Participation and Field of Participation. Participation must structure a field and renewed availability must be required before the sustaining condition can be named. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Participation Field of Participation Nests Sustenance nests within the Sustenance Field branch as the field level container for nourishment and renewal reads. Nourishment Life Care Reads Sustenance becomes recognisable where participation depends on renewed availability that can continue to carry life, body, place, or practice. Carries Nourishment Life Care','Sustenance Sustenance names the organic field where participation is carried through nourishment, continuation, replenishment, and maintained availability. Places Sustenance places the third order…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','sustenance','[]','[]','["second.participation","third.care","third.field-of-participation","third.life","third.nourishment"]','{"holds":["second.participation","third.field-of-participation"],"traces":["second.participation","third.field-of-participation"],"carries":["third.nourishment","third.life","third.care"],"pairs":[],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',148,'sha256:92a63c4929a47bdf05f6daf8093bb6ddf0b0607c46eb3787dc29b874685f7394','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.teaching-boundary','Teaching Boundary','teaching-boundary','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/Teaching/Teaching Boundary.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/teaching-boundary.html','# Teaching Boundary

Teaching boundary names a branch-level boundary condition that preserves learning participation from overrun, collapse, or imposed order.

## Places

Teaching Boundary places a branch-level boundary condition that preserves learning participation from overrun, collapse, or imposed order.

## Holds

Teaching Boundary is held by [[Teaching]], [[Boundary]], [[Closure Scope]].

## Pairs

Teaching Boundary pairs with [[Learning Pace]]. Teaching Boundary names the edge at which bearing can no longer proceed compatibly with what the learner can carry; Learning Pace names the rate at which that bearing can be received.

## Traces

- [[Teaching]]
- [[Boundary]]
- [[Closure Scope]]

## Nests

Teaching Boundary nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace.

## Reads

Teaching Boundary becomes readable where the teaching condition stays within what the learner can compatibly bear and retrace, and where the learner''s failed uptake can correct the teaching condition.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Asymmetry]], [[Boundary]], and [[Bearing]] locate the teaching condition without collapsing guidance into control.

Second: [[Compatibility]] and [[Closure Scope]] make learning participation evaluable as supportable uptake or boundary repair.

Third: [[Teaching Boundary]] places that structural read inside teaching.

## Carries

- [[Pace Mismatch]]','Teaching Boundary Teaching boundary names a branch level boundary condition that preserves learning participation from overrun, collapse, or imposed order. Places Teaching Boundary places a branch level boundary condition that preserves learning participation from overrun, collapse, or imposed order. Holds Teaching Boundary is held by Teaching, Boundary, Closure Scope. Pairs Teaching Boundary pairs with Learning Pace. Teaching Boundary names the edge at which bearing can no longer proceed compatibly with what the learner can carry; Learning Pace names the rate at which that bearing can be received. Traces Teaching Boundary Closure Scope Nests Teaching Boundary nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace. Reads Teaching Boundary becomes readable where the teaching condition stays within what the learner can compatibly bear and retrace, and where the learner''s failed uptake can correct the teaching condition. The dependency movement is: First: Asymmetry, Boundary, and Bearing locate the teaching condition without collapsing guidance into control. Second: Compatibility and Closure Scope make learning participation evaluable as supportable uptake or boundary repair. Third: Teaching Boundary places that structural read inside teaching. Carries Pace Mismatch','Teaching Boundary Teaching boundary names a branch level boundary condition that preserves learning participation from overrun, collapse, or imposed order. Places Teaching Boundary places a branch…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','teaching','[]','[]','["first.boundary","second.closure-scope","third.learning-pace","third.pace-mismatch","third.teaching"]','{"holds":["third.teaching","first.boundary","second.closure-scope"],"traces":["third.teaching","first.boundary","second.closure-scope"],"carries":["third.pace-mismatch"],"pairs":["third.learning-pace"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',185,'sha256:27a44a2314807f1a2d16237191580481ce5d4c4f6436b6dfa9f060793c4bcbab','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.teaching','Teaching','teaching','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/Teaching/Teaching.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/teaching.html','# Teaching

Teaching names branch-level participation that preserves and develops available learning conditions through compatible uptake.

## Places

Teaching places branch-level participation that preserves and develops available learning conditions through compatible uptake.

## Holds

Teaching is held by [[Branch]], [[Knowledge Field]], [[Knowledge]], [[Bearing]], [[Medium]].

## Pairs

Teaching pairs with [[Learning]] and [[Parenting]]. Teaching carries bearing toward the learner through medium; Learning names what becomes available through that bearing. Parenting names care-bearing and developmental holding beside teaching''s knowledge-bearing.

## Traces

- [[Branch]]
- [[Knowledge Field]]
- [[Knowledge]]
- [[Bearing]]
- [[Medium]]

## Nests

Teaching nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace.

## Reads

Teaching becomes readable where instruction carries a learner into available uptake without imposing order faster than the learner can bear.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Asymmetry]], [[Availability]], and [[Bearing]] make a learning condition carryable without pretending teacher and learner bear the same read.

Second: [[Readability]], [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Know]], [[Medium]], and [[Compatibility]] make teaching evaluable as compatible uptake rather than mere instruction.

Third: [[Teaching]] places that structural read within knowledge participation.

Applied reads:

- [[Pace Mismatch]]
- [[Parenting]]

At the [[Translation Boundary]], [[Asymmetry]], [[Availability]], [[Bearing]], [[Medium]], [[Compatibility]], [[Pace]], and [[Recognition Read|Recognition]] become terminal to this domain as [[Learning]], [[Learning Pace]], [[Teaching Boundary]], and [[Pace Mismatch]].

## Carries

- [[Learning Pace]]
- [[Teaching Boundary]]
- [[Pace Mismatch]]
- [[Parenting]]','Teaching Teaching names branch level participation that preserves and develops available learning conditions through compatible uptake. Places Teaching places branch level participation that preserves and develops available learning conditions through compatible uptake. Holds Teaching is held by Branch, Knowledge Field, Knowledge, Bearing, Medium. Pairs Teaching pairs with Learning and Parenting. Teaching carries bearing toward the learner through medium; Learning names what becomes available through that bearing. Parenting names care bearing and developmental holding beside teaching''s knowledge bearing. Traces Branch Knowledge Field Knowledge Bearing Medium Nests Teaching nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace. Reads Teaching becomes readable where instruction carries a learner into available uptake without imposing order faster than the learner can bear. The dependency movement is: First: Asymmetry, Availability, and Bearing make a learning condition carryable without pretending teacher and learner bear the same read. Second: Readability, Recognition Read, Know, Medium, and Compatibility make teaching evaluable as compatible uptake rather than mere instruction. Third: Teaching places that structural read within knowledge participation. Applied reads: Pace Mismatch Parenting At the Translation Boundary, Asymmetry, Availability, Bearing, Medium, Compatibility, Pace, and Recognition Read become terminal to this domain as Learning, Learning Pace, Teaching Boundary, and Pace Mismatch. Carries Learning Pace Teaching Boundary Pace Mismatch Parenting','Teaching Teaching names branch level participation that preserves and develops available learning conditions through compatible uptake. Places Teaching places branch level participation that…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','teaching','[]','[]','["first.bearing","second.medium","third.branch","third.knowledge","third.knowledge-field","third.learning","third.learning-pace","third.pace-mismatch","third.parenting","third.teaching-boundary"]','{"holds":["third.branch","third.knowledge-field","third.knowledge","first.bearing","second.medium"],"traces":["third.branch","third.knowledge-field","third.knowledge","first.bearing","second.medium"],"carries":["third.learning-pace","third.teaching-boundary","third.pace-mismatch","third.parenting"],"pairs":["third.learning","third.parenting"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',212,'sha256:2433dde283f3adb1d55d35e83c169a45b8cd1c94aa963a1004dc21ba1f60a697','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.technology-domain','Technology Domain','technology-domain','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/Technology/Technology Domain.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/technology-domain.html','# Technology Domain

Technology Domain names the organised participation context through which produced arrangements extend, modify, automate, or support participation.

## Places

Technology Domain places the organised participation context through which produced arrangements extend, modify, automate, or support participation.

## Holds

Technology Domain is held by [[Domain]], [[Making Field]], [[Carrying]], [[Function]], [[Medium]].

## Pairs

No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read.

## Traces

- [[Domain]]
- [[Making Field]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Function]]
- [[Medium]]

## Nests

Technology Domain nests within [[Making Field]] as a branch index. It organises sub-domains — currently [[AI]] and [[Architecture]] — rather than carrying its own Applied Reads. New sub-domains (tools, infrastructure, automation) belong under Technology Domain where they carry a distinct branch of the same organised participation structure.

## Reads

Technology Domain becomes recognisable where participation is intentionally arranged through tools, systems, techniques, infrastructure, automation, or produced capabilities.

Technology Domain also becomes recognisable where produced arrangements accelerate resolution. That acceleration remains supportable only where the order carrying the speed remains retraceable; otherwise the domain can be read through [[Extractive Acceleration]].

Primary Mode:

[[Making]]

Secondary Modes:

[[Carrying]]
[[Function]]

Branches:

- tools
- systems
- infrastructure
- automation
- capability

At the [[Translation Boundary]], [[Making]], [[Tool]], [[Function]], [[Medium]], [[Carrying]], and [[Engineered Coupling]] become terminal to this domain as tools, systems, infrastructure, automation, capability, and [[AI]].

## Carries

- [[AI]]
- [[Architecture]]','Technology Domain Technology Domain names the organised participation context through which produced arrangements extend, modify, automate, or support participation. Places Technology Domain places the organised participation context through which produced arrangements extend, modify, automate, or support participation. Holds Technology Domain is held by Domain, Making Field, Carrying, Function, Medium. Pairs No lateral pair is required at this placement yet; this term currently reads as a branch or terminal read. Traces Domain Making Field Carrying Function Medium Nests Technology Domain nests within Making Field as a branch index. It organises sub domains — currently AI and Architecture — rather than carrying its own Applied Reads. New sub domains (tools, infrastructure, automation) belong under Technology Domain where they carry a distinct branch of the same organised participation structure. Reads Technology Domain becomes recognisable where participation is intentionally arranged through tools, systems, techniques, infrastructure, automation, or produced capabilities. Technology Domain also becomes recognisable where produced arrangements accelerate resolution. That acceleration remains supportable only where the order carrying the speed remains retraceable; otherwise the domain can be read through Extractive Acceleration. Primary Mode: Making Secondary Modes: Carrying Function Branches: tools systems infrastructure automation capability At the Translation Boundary, Making, Tool, Function, Medium, Carrying, and Engineered Coupling become terminal to this domain as tools, systems, infrastructure, automation, capability, and AI. Carries AI Architecture','Technology Domain Technology Domain names the organised participation context through which produced arrangements extend, modify, automate, or support participation. Places Technology Domain…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','technology','[]','[]','["second.carrying","second.function","second.medium","third.ai","third.architecture","third.domain","third.making-field"]','{"holds":["third.domain","third.making-field","second.carrying","second.function","second.medium"],"traces":["third.domain","third.making-field","second.carrying","second.function","second.medium"],"carries":["third.ai","third.architecture"],"pairs":[],"nests":["third.making-field"],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',218,'sha256:53ec201dff820fbf437ad6c8c5a3769ba13836ed0204dd60512b93f96c7ae85d','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.term-drift','Term Drift','term-drift','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Domains/Language/Applied Reads/Term Drift.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/term-drift.html','# Term Drift

Term drift occurs when a word recurs while its structural participation changes.

## Places

Term Drift places Term drift occurs when a word recurs while its structural participation changes.

## Holds

Term Drift is held by [[Language Domain]], [[Term]], [[Recurrence]], [[Difference]], [[Compatibility]].

## Pairs

Term Drift pairs with [[Inherited Term Drift]]. Term Drift names loss of dependency contact within a language context through recurrence; Inherited Term Drift names that loss carried across translation between contexts. Each is a distinct form of term drift.

## Traces

- [[Language Domain]]
- [[Term]]
- [[Recurrence]]
- [[Difference]]
- [[Compatibility]]

## Nests

Term Drift nests where this read holds at its field, domain, or practice scope without losing trace.

## Reads

Term Drift becomes readable where recurrence of a term no longer carries the same dependency position.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Difference]] changes participation.

Second: [[Recurrence]] and [[Compatibility]] make repeated term use evaluable.

Third: [[Term Drift]] places that structural read inside language.

Case Movement:

```text
term recurs
→ participation changes
→ dependency position shifts
→ apparent sameness becomes drift
```

## Carries

