INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.third-order-crossing','Threshold (Third → Higher)','threshold-third-higher','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Third Order Crossing.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/threshold-third-higher.html','# Threshold (Third → Higher)

This threshold names the crossing from Third Order into Higher Order.

## Places

Threshold (Third → Higher) places the crossing where organised and nested carrying enters its own carrying.

## Holds

Threshold (Third → Higher) is held by [[Third Order]], [[Nesting]], and [[Recursive]].

## Pairs

Asymmetry carries downward — marks the transition into [[Recursion]] and [[Higher Order]]

## Traces

- [[Third Order]]
- [[Nesting]]
- [[Recursive]]

## Nests

Threshold (Third → Higher) nests between Third Order and Higher Order.

## Reads

Threshold (Third → Higher) becomes recognisable where organised and nested carrying begins participating in the carrying that preserves, revises, or redirects it.

What Third Order makes available:

Participation organised into fields and domains. Branches as traceable dependency paths through participation. Recognition as the condition through which a read becomes identifiable as this again.

The crossing:

Where organised and nested carrying enters its own carrying, Recursion becomes available. Recursion is the first Higher Order condition.

## Carries

- [[Recursion]]
