INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.thought','Thought','thought','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Cognition/Thought.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/thought.html','# Thought

Thought names carried read inside cognition: readable relation modelled, named, interpreted, projected, questioned, or rehearsed.

A thought is a carried read or model. It is not automatically true, complete, or compatible.

Thought does not create order by itself. It becomes readable where relation has enough [[Clearance]] and [[Readability]] for a pattern to be taken up into cognitive form.

## Places

Thought places the condition through which readability is modelled or named — the carrying of a recognised pattern into a form that can guide attention or action.

## Holds

Thought is held by [[Cognition]], [[Read]], [[Readability]], [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Pattern]], and [[Medium]]. Readability must be present and pattern must be recognisable before the modelling or naming of that pattern can be carried as thought.

## Pairs

Thought pairs with [[Memory]]. Thought names the current cognitive carry; Memory names thought that recurs and remains retraceable.

## Traces

- [[Cognition]]
- [[Read]]
- [[Readability]]
- [[Recognition Read|Recognition]]
- [[Pattern]]
- [[Medium]]

## Nests

Thought nests within the Cognition Field as the condition through which readability is carried into nameable form — the structural ground for memory, self, and cognitive carrying reads.

## Reads

Thought becomes readable where relation is taken up into a cognitive model that can be held, revised, spoken, checked, or released.

This means thought is answerable to what made it readable. A thought may model order, but it does not become grounded until it can return to the relation, body, field, or source that carries it.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Availability]] and [[Boundary]] make something distinguishable enough to be taken up.

Second: [[Read]], [[Readability]], [[Recognition Read|Recognition]], [[Pattern]], and [[Medium]] make modelling, naming, interpretation, and projection evaluable.

Third: [[Thought]] places cognitive modelling inside [[Cognition Field]] with bridge pressure from language, expression, and relation.

Higher-Order Edge:

Thought remains third-order where it names a cognitive model, interpretation, projection, question, or rehearsal.

It crosses into higher order where [[Consciousness]] makes thought readable as thought and [[Self-Modelling]] or [[Self-Regulation]] changes how that thought is carried.

Movement:

```text
readability becomes available
-> cognition models or names it
-> thought can guide attention or action
-> truth and compatibility still need checking
```

## Carries

- [[Memory]]','Thought Thought names carried read inside cognition: readable relation modelled, named, interpreted, projected, questioned, or rehearsed. A thought is a carried read or model. It is not automatically true, complete, or compatible. Thought does not create order by itself. It becomes readable where relation has enough Clearance and Readability for a pattern to be taken up into cognitive form. Places Thought places the condition through which readability is modelled or named — the carrying of a recognised pattern into a form that can guide attention or action. Holds Thought is held by Cognition, Read, Readability, Recognition Read, Pattern, and Medium. Readability must be present and pattern must be recognisable before the modelling or naming of that pattern can be carried as thought. Pairs Thought pairs with Memory. Thought names the current cognitive carry; Memory names thought that recurs and remains retraceable. Traces Cognition Read Readability Recognition Read Pattern Medium Nests Thought nests within the Cognition Field as the condition through which readability is carried into nameable form — the structural ground for memory, self, and cognitive carrying reads. Reads Thought becomes readable where relation is taken up into a cognitive model that can be held, revised, spoken, checked, or released. This means thought is answerable to what made it readable. A thought may model order, but it does not become grounded until it can return to the relation, body, field, or source that carries it. The dependency movement is: First: Availability and Boundary make something distinguishable enough to be taken up. Second: Read, Readability, Recognition Read, Pattern, and Medium make modelling, naming, interpretation, and projection evaluable. Third: Thought places cognitive modelling inside Cognition Field with bridge pressure from language, expression, and relation. Higher Order Edge: Thought remains third order where it names a cognitive model, interpretation, projection, question, or rehearsal. It crosses into higher order where Consciousness makes thought readable as thought and Self Modelling or Self Regulation changes how that thought is carried. Movement: Carries Memory','Thought Thought names carried read inside cognition: readable relation modelled, named, interpreted, projected, questioned, or rehearsed. A thought is a carried read or model.','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','cognition','[]','[]','["first.read","second.medium","second.pattern","second.readability","second.recognition-read","third.cognition","third.memory"]','{"holds":["third.cognition","first.read","second.readability","second.recognition-read","second.pattern","second.medium"],"traces":["third.cognition","first.read","second.readability","second.recognition-read","second.pattern","second.medium"],"carries":["third.memory"],"pairs":["third.memory"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',327,'sha256:e0b1ee766bde2f3852fa8d3556e3eac55b287317e06ac67ad03a54ba00ff2410','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.timescale','Timescale','timescale','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Natural World/Timescale.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/timescale.html','# Timescale

Timescale names scale where held clearance becomes readable under particular carrying conditions.

Different organisms, bodies, cells, and ecosystems are different local readings of held clearance, not different kinds of time. Each has a native resolution capacity: a rate and scale at which order can be distinguished, integrated, carried, and responded to.

Resolution is band-limited. A participant does not resolve all order; it resolves a band of order — the range of scale, rate, intensity, difference, and interval it can receive, integrate, and carry.

## Places

Timescale places the condition through which carrying is evaluable across different orders of temporal extent and resolution capacity — the structural read of how carrying, life, and natural conditions become readable at different scales.

## Holds

Timescale is held by [[Time]], [[Readability]], [[Scale]], [[Rate]], [[Carrying]], [[Body]], [[Life Field]], and [[Natural World Field]]. Time must remain available as interval and continuation, while carrying, scale, rate, and resolution capacity make that continuation locally readable.

## Pairs

Timescale pairs with [[Physical Space]]. Timescale names temporal extent as a carrying parameter; Physical Space names dimensional structure as a carrying parameter. Each is one structural dimension of physical field conditions.

## Traces

- [[Scale]]
- [[Rate]]
- [[Carrying]]
- [[Body]]
- [[Life Field]]
- [[Natural World Field]]
- [[Time]]

- [[Physical Field Conditions]]
- [[Readability]]
## Nests

Timescale nests within the Natural World Field as the scale-structural condition through which carrying becomes readable across different temporal extents.

## Reads

Timescale becomes readable where held clearance is resolved locally enough for a participant, organism, cell, or ecosystem to carry relation at its own scale, rate, and native resolution band.

A being''s apparent time is shaped by what it can resolve. Slow and fast are not only external measures; they are also local readings of how much order can be distinguished, integrated, and carried per interval. Learning, fatigue, injury, attention, and practice can therefore change the felt scale of time by changing how sequence is resolved.

What falls outside a participant''s resolution band may still be real, effective, and traceable. It is not directly readable until it is slowed, amplified, translated, measured, inferred, or otherwise brought into a compatible carrying range.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Clearance]] and [[Time]] hold relation apart enough to remain readable.

Second: [[Scale]], [[Readability]], [[Rate]], and [[Carrying]] make local resolution evaluable under a carrying condition.

Third: [[Timescale]] places local readings of held clearance inside natural-world, body, and life participation.

Examples:

- insects
- birds
- fish
- humans
- trees
- cells
- ecosystems

## Carries

This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Timescale Timescale names scale where held clearance becomes readable under particular carrying conditions. Different organisms, bodies, cells, and ecosystems are different local readings of held clearance, not different kinds of time. Each has a native resolution capacity: a rate and scale at which order can be distinguished, integrated, carried, and responded to. Resolution is band limited. A participant does not resolve all order; it resolves a band of order — the range of scale, rate, intensity, difference, and interval it can receive, integrate, and carry. Places Timescale places the condition through which carrying is evaluable across different orders of temporal extent and resolution capacity — the structural read of how carrying, life, and natural conditions become readable at different scales. Holds Timescale is held by Time, Readability, Scale, Rate, Carrying, Body, Life Field, and Natural World Field. Time must remain available as interval and continuation, while carrying, scale, rate, and resolution capacity make that continuation locally readable. Pairs Timescale pairs with Physical Space. Timescale names temporal extent as a carrying parameter; Physical Space names dimensional structure as a carrying parameter. Each is one structural dimension of physical field conditions. Traces Scale Rate Carrying Body Life Field Natural World Field Time Physical Field Conditions Readability Nests Timescale nests within the Natural World Field as the scale structural condition through which carrying becomes readable across different temporal extents. Reads Timescale becomes readable where held clearance is resolved locally enough for a participant, organism, cell, or ecosystem to carry relation at its own scale, rate, and native resolution band. A being''s apparent time is shaped by what it can resolve. Slow and fast are not only external measures; they are also local readings of how much order can be distinguished, integrated, and carried per interval. Learning, fatigue, injury, attention, and practice can therefore change the felt scale of time by changing how sequence is resolved. What falls outside a participant''s resolution band may still be real, effective, and traceable. It is not directly readable until it is slowed, amplified, translated, measured, inferred, or otherwise brought into a compatible carrying range. The dependency movement is: First: Clearance and Time hold relation apart enough to remain readable. Second: Scale, Readability, Rate, and Carrying make local resolution evaluable under a carrying condition. Third: Timescale places local readings of held clearance inside natural world, body, and life participation. Examples: insects birds fish humans trees cells ecosystems Carries This note carries no further public branch at this scope.','Timescale Timescale names scale where held clearance becomes readable under particular carrying conditions. Different organisms, bodies, cells, and ecosystems are different local readings of held…','stable','rooted',0,'third','term','natural-world','[]','[]','["first.time","second.carrying","second.rate","second.readability","second.scale","third.body","third.life-field","third.natural-world-field","third.physical-field-conditions","third.physical-space"]','{"holds":["first.time","second.readability","second.scale","second.rate","second.carrying","third.body","third.life-field","third.natural-world-field"],"traces":["second.scale","second.rate","second.carrying","third.body","third.life-field","third.natural-world-field","first.time","third.physical-field-conditions","second.readability"],"carries":[],"pairs":["third.physical-space"],"nests":[],"reads":[]}','[{"depth":2,"text":"Places","anchor":"places"},{"depth":2,"text":"Holds","anchor":"holds"},{"depth":2,"text":"Pairs","anchor":"pairs"},{"depth":2,"text":"Traces","anchor":"traces"},{"depth":2,"text":"Nests","anchor":"nests"},{"depth":2,"text":"Reads","anchor":"reads"},{"depth":2,"text":"Carries","anchor":"carries"}]',410,'sha256:725909388f2b14a0c0457802671a4fc1975683cb2fe8b86a97d31b584621409c','1970-01-01','2026-06-25');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO entries (id,title,slug,source_path,public_url,content,plain_text,excerpt,status,garden_status,grounded,entry_order,entry_type,branch,aliases,tags,related,structure,headings,word_count,content_hash,created,updated) VALUES ('third.tool','Tool','tool','Reality_Mechanics/3_Third/Fields/Making/Tool.md','https://atlas.realitymechanics.nz/tool.html','# Tool

Tool names a making path read where form is made available to extend function through compatible use.

## Places

Tool places the condition through which a made form extends a participant''s carrying by translating relation into a usable resolution band — the structural node where form, function, medium, and readability combine to augment what relation can carry.

## Holds

Tool is held by [[Making Field]], [[Form]], [[Function]], [[Medium]], [[Making]], [[Extend]], and [[Readability]]. Form must be carried through making, extension must remain answerable to source, function must be readable through a medium, and the translated condition must enter a usable resolution band before the augmenting condition can be named as a tool.

## Pairs

Tool pairs with [[Hidden Carrying]]. Tool names the produced form that makes carrying available and visible; Hidden Carrying names the condition where produced form displaces and obscures the carrying it depends on.

## Traces

- [[Making Field]]
- [[Form]]
- [[Function]]
- [[Medium]]
- [[Making]]
- [[Extend]]
- [[Readability]]

## Nests

Tool nests within the Making Field as the condition through which made form extends carrying — the structural ground for technology, medium, and instrument reads.

## Reads

Tool becomes readable where a made form allows participation that would otherwise be unavailable, harder to carry, or less compatible by extending carrying into a form the participant can receive, integrate, and carry.

A tool does not remove the participant''s resolution band. It changes what reaches it. A microscope translates small-scale structure into optical read. A thermometer translates thermal condition into visible measure. A clock translates ordered recurrence into countable sequence. In each case, the tool extends read by carrying an order outside native resolution into a compatible form.

This makes tool-use answerable to its translation path. A tool can extend read, but it can also fabricate readability where the surface remains usable while the dependency path is hidden, broken, or displaced.

Tool and [[Weapon]] are distinguished by use-path rather than object-kind. Tool extends capacity within answerable purpose. Weapon redirects capacity toward force, harm, threat, disabling, coercion, or override.

The dependency movement is:

First: [[Boundary]], [[Availability]], and [[Bearing]] make formed use carryable.

Second: [[Form]], [[Function]], [[Medium]], [[Extend]], [[Readability]], [[Carrying]], and [[Compatibility]] make tool-use evaluable as compatible participation rather than mere access.

Third: [[Tool]] places that structural read inside the [[Making Field]].

## Carries

